rk under pressure\nHigh attention to details and accuracy\nExperience with AWS managed services and architecture – an advantage\nExperience with SCRUM/Agile methodologies – an advantage','2020-07-21',62),(59,'Malware campaigns hunter & researcher','SentinelOne is shaping the future of endpoint security through its unified, converged platform that automatically prevents, detects, and responds to threats in real-time. Our unique approach is based on deep inspection of all system processes combined with innovative machine learning to quickly isolate malicious behaviors, protecting devices against advanced, targeted threats in real time.\n\nWhat are we looking for?\nWe are looking for talented, customer facing security researchers, people that are hungry for knowledge, curious, explorers, observents, and ready “to catch them all”. If you love computers but hate malwares, familiar with attack techniques and want to expose the next APT - we’re looking for you.\n\nWhy us?\nBecause you will meet extraordinary challenges facing the newest malwares and tech obstacles and overcoming them. You will work with the very BEST in the industry in a flexible and independent environment.\nYou will be the first to hunt & uncover the greatest malware campaigns out there!\n\nWhat will you do?\nYou will be responsible for hunting and reversing the newest malwares and exploits out there. You will be designing methods to detect a wide range of malware types and campaigns. You will escort clients’ team and investigate advanced clients’ environment in search of the next unique campaigns and exploits out there.\n\nYou will be developing and using internal research tools, intelligence infrastructures, and investigate the spread and the new techniques you’ll find.\n\nYou will also be encouraged to write white papers, blogs and articles of your findings.\n\nWhat experience or knowledge should you bring?\nFamiliarity with the malware world (how malware operate, infamous families, evasion and exploi