quirements:\nM.Sc Or Ph.D Involving machine learning related research\nProven experience with machine learning frameworks and methodologies\nProven experience in one of the following: robotic learning, active learning, reinforcement learning, recommendation system or speech/NLP analysis\nHigh research capabilities including: designing experiments, finding, adjusting applying ideas from the literature and constructing innovative models and algorithms\nSelf-starter, auto-didactic and innovative\n\nAdvantage:\nDeveloper who loves to code in different environments and languages including Java, Python, R, Matlab, Scala and others\n\nIn a nutshell:\nWe are looking for a Machine Learning Researcher who is interested in continuing to develop new machine learning algorithms while also having a direct and immense, real-world impact.','2020-07-11',124),(83,'Data Scientist','Seebo is looking for a data scientist with a passion for data, hands-on capabilities, and strong analytical skills to join our data science team, taking an active part in the development of a wide spectrum of machine learning algorithms related to a range of business use cases. The ideal candidate is a highly motivated data enthusiast, a quick and passionate learner, with a vast understanding of data science pipeline components, such as data pre-processing, feature engineering, machine learning, and statistical algorithms. The candidate should be able to take an idea end-to-end from an early stage of research, through prototyping and up to production-level code.\n\nWhat you\'ll do::\nAnalyze large amounts of time-series data to discover trends and patterns.\nPropose solutions and strategies to meet business challenges.\nResearch and develop statistical learning models and predictive models appropriate for different use cases.\n\nWe\'d love to hear from you if you have::\nHands-on experience in using statistical modeling and machine learning techniques to build predictive models, with at 2+ years of industry