tist','jb-19 מספר משרה\n: עם ניסיון ב Data Scientist דרוש איש/ת פיתוח\nEvaluating state of art statistical modeling and machine Learning.\nBig data analysis, Modeling and Reporting.\nJob Requirements:Requirements:\nA minimum first degree in computer science/ applied math/ statistics.\nStrong algorithm development skills.\nProven experience with machine learning algorithms – both supervised and unsupervised.\nProven experience with optimization algorithms.\n5+ years of relevant experience with one of the following: Python, R, Matlab. Strong communication skills, creative, results driven, quick learner.\nExperience with big data, distributed processing, NoSQL databases – a significant advantage.\n\nהשם שלך\n\nמספר המשרה(חובה)\n\nהעלאת קו\"ח\n\nשתף את המשרה ותן לחברים שלך לעזור','2020-07-11',149),(97,'Data Scientist','Job Description:\nFor a hi-tech company developing products in the field of internet campaigns, with offices in the center\n\nTo research, select and tune machine learning models and algorithms to solve real world business problems using our data consisting of internal and 3rd party user interaction tracking (Big Data), publisher data (Google, Facebook, Bing, etc.) and other industry data, including:\n\nCreating and improving algorithm components, specifically the algorithm code itself; Working with a team of data scientists who collaborate to mine insights and find opportunities in interesting data from a variety of fields and geographies; Working with our algorithm development team to integrate these algorithms with the production data sources and the application ecosystem\n\nOur company research creates algorithms that bring real value to the world\'s top advertisers. Its role consists of identifying and defining functionality from conception to delivery, by fully understanding customer requirements, data, \"connecting the dots,\" creating an algorithm, and delivering a working algorithm to production.\n\nAdditional Positions:\nAlgorithm developer\n\nCategory:\nSoftware\n\nJob Qualifications:\nMsc or PhD in Computer Science, Mathematics, Statistics, Physics or related fields.\n\nExtensive experience with data mining / machine learning / optimization.\n\nExperience in one or more of the following areas is an advantage:\nMarketing (Search Engine/Display/Social) auctioning and bidding algorithms - big advantage!\nDeep learning.\nScalable Classification and Clustering techniques.\nStatistical modeling / information gains.\nJava / Scala\nBig data technologies - Hadoop, MapReduce, Hive, Spark.\nPython / R data science / analysis libraries.\n\nCompany Occupation:\nHigh Tech\n\nCompany Size:\nLarge (150+)','2020-07-05',150),(98,'Data Scientist','Kenshoo is uniquely positioned as the global leader in digital marketing software solutions, we offer algorithms that bring real value to the worlds top advertisers. Role consists of identifying and defining functionality from conception to delivery, by fully understanding customer requirements, data, \'connecting the dots\', creating an algorithm, and delivering a working algorithm to production.\nRole Description\nAs a Data Scientist on the core data science group, you will be a valuable member of an innovative data science group working on various problems to help and learn from each other to mine insights, find opportunities and \'connect the dots\'.\nData scientists work with business unit product and dev to build and maintain business value by defining, exploring and developing products combining Data Science and Machine Learning at the edge of technology. The data scientists code goes all the way into production with all the responsibility and satisfaction!\n\n\nRequirements:\nBsc or Msc in Computer Science, Mathematics, Statistics, Physics, Industrial Engineering or related fields.\n2+ years of experience with Deep Learning, using Tensorflow/Keras/pyTorch\nExcellent command of Python\nTeam-player, proactive, go-getter, self-sustained\nMarketing (Search/Display/Social) auc