sion of democratizing creativity with award-winning apps.\n\nJOB DESCRIPTION\nDESCRIPTION\n\nWe\'re looking for a Data Scientist to join our fast-growing team. The ideal candidate will be intricately involved in running analytical experiments in a methodological manner, and will regularly evaluate alternate models via theoretical approaches. This is a great opportunity to become a part of an innovative team that develops methodology and analysis tools that have a great impact on our products and clients.\n\nResponsibilities\nResearch and develop Machine Learning (ML) and statistical learning models for data analysis\nCollaborate with BI and marketing analyst teams\nKeep up-to-date with the latest technological trends\nCommunicate results and ideas to key decision makers\nImplement new statistical or other mathematical methodologies as needed for specific model or analysis\nRequirements\nMaster\'s Degree in Computer Science, Statistics, Applied Math or related field – mandatory. Ph.D. - advantage.\n2+ years practical experience with R/Python/Matlab - mandatory\nExtensive background in ML, Deep Networks, statistical analysis and data mining - mandatory\nGreat communication skills - mandatory\nData-oriented personality and creative thinking - mandatory\nExperience with SQL – advantage.','2020-07-23',167),(112,'Data Scientist לחברת Security','מיקום: ת\"א והמרכז\n\nתיאור המשרה:\nחברה מובילת שוק בתחום אבטחת המידע מגייסת Data Scientist.\nטכנולוגיית החברה מגנה על ישומיי אינטרנט ומידע רגיש הנמצא על שרתי בסיסי נתונים, שרתי אפליקציה ושרתי Web Services.\nלחברה מאות לקוחות בארץ ובעולם כולו, ממגזרים מגוונים.\nהחברה דוגלת בשמירה על איזון בית-עבודה.\nממוקמים בתל אביב בקרבת קו רכבת.\nשלח/י קו\"ח!\n\nדרישות המשרה:\nשנתיים ניסיון כ-Data Scientist\nתואר שני\nפיתוח ב-Python\nניסיון ב-ML/ AI/ NEURAL\nמס\' משרה: 120166','2020-07-23',76),(113,'Data Scientist','Back\nData Science\nData Scientist\nTel Aviv\n\nGenerate insights and impact from data.\n\nOfakim develops and utilizes the most powerful business management tools for a volatile exchange rate environment. We handle billions of dollars on monthly basis for thousands of businesses around the world.\n\nWith all this data, we’re looking for talented data scientists to help us better understand our users and build better products. If you are data curious, excited about deriving insights from data, and motivated by having the impact on the business, we want to hear from you.\n\nYou will:\nWork closely with product and business teams to identify important questions and answer them with data.\nApply statistical and econometric models on large datasets to measure results and outcomes and to predict future performance of users or products.\nDesign, analyze, and interpret the results of experiments.\nDrive the collection of new data and the refinement of existing data sources.\nBe part of an exceptionally strong team dedicated to turning data into knowledge.\n\nYou’d ideally have:\n2+ years experience working with and analyzing large datasets to solve problems.\nM.Sc/ Ph.D. in a highly quantitative field such as Mathematics /Statistics or Engineering.\nHighly skilled at writing SQL to query relational databases.\nStrong Python or R programming skills.\nStrong knowledge of statistics and experimental design.\nStrong communication and presentation skills.\nExcellent English verbal and written communication skills.\n\nYou should include these in your application:\nA resume and LinkedIn profile.\nDescription of the most interesting data analysis you’ve done, key findings and its impact.','2020-07-11',169),(114,'Sr. Staff Data Scientist','ServiceNow is seeking a talented Data Scientist to play a key role in the success of ServiceNow Event Management and Operational Intelligence products. Both are data-intensive products with many opportunities to implement Data Science and Machine Learning. The position includes research in wide variety of topics, implementing solutions, and following results in the field.\n\nEvent Management is one of the lead products in the ITOM business unit, the fastest growing business in ServiceNow. More on Event Management and Operational Intelligence can be found in the SN website:\nEvent Management: https://www.servicenow.com/products/event-management.html\nOperational Intelligence: https://www.servicenow.com/products/operational-intelligence.html\nWhat you get to do in this role:\nEnhance modeling for existing product capabilities such as noise reduction, anomaly detection, root cause analysis, and take them to the next level.\nDevelop algorithms for new product features.\nWork closely with team and architects to take algorithms from concept through production and deployment\nExperience in data analysis and data visualization tools\nCollaborate with industry leading machine learning technologists in the ServiceNow platform team\nIn order to be successful in this role, we need someone who has:\nD./M.Sc. in math, physics, engineering, computer science or an equivalent science degree\n4+ years of experience in data scientist / algorithm development positions\nProficiency in Anomaly detection, Machine Learning, Neural networks, NLP, Statistical Models. Must have exceptional skills in at least one of them\nExperience in leading a complex data science problem from ideation to production (or complex and vast academic works)\nStrong interpersonal skills and ability to successfully collaborate with talented and opinionated peers (Product, Dev, Quality, etc.) as part of the Nutrino’s team leaders’ group\nAbout the company:\n\nServiceNow is changing the way people work. With a service-orientation toward the activities, tasks and processes that make up day-to-day work life, we help the modern enterprise operate faster and be more scalable than ever before.\n\nWe’re disruptive. We work hard but try not to take ourselves too seriously. We are highly adaptable and constantly evolving. We are passionate about our product, and we live for our customers. We have high expectations and a career at ServiceNow means challenging yourself to always be better.\n\nWe provide competitive compensation, generous benefits and a professional atmosphere. This is a very collaborative and inclusive work environment where individuals strong on aptitude and attitude will have an opportunity to grow their professional careers through working with some of the most advanced technology and talented developers in the business.','2020-07-14',170),(115,'Senior Risk Data Scientist','A top-notch data-driven company. We’re growing so fast (180M users) that we’re collecting more data than we can monetize. Our Data Science group consists of ~50 people, of which there are 20+ data scientists, and others (engineering, curation and labeling) that help us make our projects successful and impactful for Wix. We apply SOTA Machine Learning techniques to Wix’s data to improve the product, internal processes and personalization for users, which in turn improves our profitability. And that’s where you come in.\n\nWe’re looking for a talented data genius to work in our amazing company. It\'s well known that we have a unique atmosphere at Wix and people really like to work here, probably because the company\'s culture is employee-first (after the user of course) :)\n\nYou are:\n\n\nKind of a unicorn, that is, an End-to-End Data Scientist. For us, this means you’re a data guy (or gal) with data x-ray eyes. A researcher at heart, you love the fraud & compliance domain, and have at least 5 years’ financial industry experience in a risk-related discipline. You also have extensive knowledge of the eCommerce fraud field and cyber-crime ecosystem.\n\nYou\'re proficient in SQL and have experience in slice and dice big data. You’re a scientist who can speak and sketch about conditional probabilities, entropies & embeddings as if it was your mother tongue. Although you can\'t think in more than 3 dimensions, we expect you to know the math of high dimensions, where our data resides.\n\nA Machine Learning practitioner, your arsenal is full of sharp ML tools. You deeply understand classical ML & DL algs for the whole spectrum of problems and domains: Computer Vision, NLP, Recommendation Systems, Supervised & Unsupervised Learning. You\'ll need them all! A business mind who can speak the business language, you know how to work across all levels and areas of the company with various stakeholders. You’re an impressive communicator at all levels. You’re proficient / fluent with Python machine learning tools and SQL, and you’re a programmer who’s experienced in coding your algorithms into production (pref in Python).\n\nIt goes without saying that you’re an awesome human being, the kind of person we want to hang out with in the pub at night (and we do).\n\nAs a Data Scientist, you will:\nBuild data driven tools to automate optimize velocity and scale risk decision points include, fraud detection and payment behavior.\nAggregate known risk (connecting the dots), be forward looking and externally aware, challenge known risks, illuminate unknown risks and ensure you actively handle and reduce legacy risk while improving business & fraud KPIs.\nFind the needle in our Big Data haystack! We seriously have tons of it - we know this is the kind of hype you’ll hear from a lot of companies, but we’ve got the data to back it up. We collect endless amounts of data every second... waiting for you to crunch them into actionable insights.\nGet to work on extremely diverse problems and domains.\nCreate an impact by applying Machine Learning techniques and models to Wix’s enormous piles of data.\nDirectly influence the way Wix does business by leading research projects and eventually implement them in production within the Wix ecosystem.\nWork collaboratively with other team members.\nStrive to learn new stuff and lead us to continue being a state-of-the-art group.\nTake the time needed to grow professionally. Once in a while you\'ll step out of your box and work on other different problems - whatever you choose!\n\nResponsibilities\nResponsibilities\nRequirements / Minimum requirements\nRequirements','2020-07-14',91),(116,'Data Scientist, Product','Facebook\'s mission is to give people the power to build community and bring the world closer together. Through our family of apps and services, we\'re building a different kind of company that connects billions of people around the world, gives them ways to share what matters most to them, and helps bring people closer together. Whether we\'re creating new products or helping a small business expand its reach, people at Facebook are builders at heart. Our global teams are constantly iterating, solving problems, and working together to empower people around the world to build community and connect in meaningful ways. Together, we can help people build stronger communities - we\'re just getting started.Build meaningful products with talented, supportive colleagues in a rewarding, diverse environment!\n\nThe job is to be the \"data eyes and ears\" guiding the product team. We\'re building innovative, exciting products used by many millions of people around the world. The data scientist finds what\'s working, what can be improved, what\'s missing. While not a management role, the data scientist drives strategy and roadmap of a large number of engineers and designers.\nSuited for people with experience studying data to guide product development. The key attributes needed are: mastery of SQL, strong quantitative logic, core statistical knowledge, instinctive product sense and focus on real-world impact.\n\nResponsibilities:\n\nApply your expertise in quantitative analysis and the presentation of data to see beyond the numbers and understand how our users interact with our growth products.\nWork as a key member of the product team to solve problems and identify trends and opportunities.\nInform, influence, support, and execute our product decisions and product launches.\nSet KPIs and goals, design and evaluate experiments, monitor key product metrics, understand root causes of changes in metrics.\nExploratory analysis to discover new opportunities: understanding ecosystems, user behaviors, and long-term trends\nidentifying levers to help move key metrics.\nMininum Qualifications:\n\n3+ years experience doing quantitative analysis, preferably for a web or mobile company\nFluency in SQL\nCore statistical knowledge\nProven experience leading data-driven projects from definition to execution: defining metrics, experiment design, communicating actionable insights.\nAble to mentor and guide junior data scientists\nExperience leading analytics teams - advantage\nPython, R or any other scripting language advantage\nPreferred Qualifications:','2020-07-20',127),(117,'Senior Data Scientist','About Verbit.ai\nVerbits smart transcription and captioning solution harnesses the power of artificial and human intelligence to provide over 99% accuracy, industry-leading turnaround time, and on-demand CART services. Our adaptive AI technology is customized for the higher education and legal industries. The company has more than 100 employees in Tel Aviv, Kiev and NY and has secured $65M of financing to date.\nJob Description\nAt Verbit, we combine the complementary powers of AI and HI (Human Intelligence) to form an efficient and precise transcription pipeline. This combined system relies on smart algorithms and deep insights into the power and limits of AI, how AI and HI interact, and human behavior dynamics.\nAs a Senior Data Scientist on our team, you\'ll take a leading role in expanding our understanding of these complex systems, design and run experiments followed by analyzing their results, and determine policies to be deployed in the field to further improve how we operate.\n\n\nRequirements:\n· B.Sc. in Data-related field\n· Advanced degree in fields related to Data Science - advantage\n· 3-5 years work experience in data science (statistics, machine learning)\n· 2+ years of coding experience with Python or similar language.\n· Experience in practical Statistics and/or Machine Learning, working with statistical packages (primarily sklearn and related packages in Python) and extracting insights from data.\n· Experience with creating complex data sets (SQL), data modeling, reporting and experiment design.\n· Deep interest and aptitude in data, metrics, analysis and trends.\n· Experience with NLP, speech analysis, linguistics and related fields.','2020-07-28',181),(118,'Data Scientist לחברת הייטק בתחום הAd-Tech ברמת החייל','מיקום: ת\"א והמרכז\n\nתיאור המשרה:\nהזדמנות מעולה לפניך!\nחברת הייטק מובילה בעולם ה-ad-tech מגייסת Data Scientist עם נסיון פרקטי בDeep Learning לתפקיד הכולל מחקר, פיתוח ומימוש אלגוריתמים מסוג Data Mining, Machine Learning, Deep Learning ואופטימיזציה. עבודה עם Scala, Java, Python וBig Data.\nמזמינים אותך להשתלב בחברה רווחית, עם תנאים מעולים, תוך שמירה על איזון בית עבודה!\n\nדרישות המשרה:\nנסיון עם Deep Learning\nנסיון עם Machine Learning\nהבנה מעמיקה בData\nנסיון בPython\nמס\' משרה: 121805','2020-07-14',76),(119,'Quantitative Data Scientist','לחברה בתחום ה- Algo Trading דרוש/ה Data Scientist . החברה מפתחת מערכת מבוססת אלגוריתמים של Machine learning ו Data mining למסחר אוטומטי בבורסה. לחברה אין לקוחות, היא סוחרת אך ורק בהון העצמי שלה ואת הרווחים היפים שעושה, מחלקת בין העובדים שלה. התפקיד כולל מחקר ופיתוח אלגוריתמים בתחום של Data Mining ו- Machine Learning וכן מימוש שלהם באמצעות C++ ו Python .\n\nמיקום: לוד - לפחות תואר ראשון בהצטיינות (ממוצע 90 ומעלה) מאוניברסיטה מובילה בתחומים רלוונטיים כגון מדעי המחשב, מתמטיקה, פיזיקה - ניסיון בביצוע מחקרים וכן במימוש אלגוריתמים באמצעות Python או C++ .','2020-07-27',183),(120,'Machine Learning Engineer','The Company\n\n\nWith more than a billion active listings, tens of millions of daily transactions, conducted by tens of millions of sellers / hundreds of millions of buyers, across more than 30 countries, and 22 different currencies, comprised of a product catalog staggering in diversity - eBay is a marketplace like no other that has ever existed If youre interested in joining a purpose driven community that is dedicated to creating an ambitious and inclusive workplace, join eBay a company you can be proud to be a part of.\n\nThe Role\n\n\nIn this role you will be a part of eBays global Buyer Experience research team. You will Combine strong software engineering principles with machine learning to build scalable learning workflows. Our team explores and provides solutions for extremely complex problems presented to hundreds of millions of users every day, by conducting research in the fields of Recommendation Systems, Machine Learning, NLP and Information Retrieval. We work closely with the product teams in order to bring state of the art technology to production. The main goal of the team is to bring personalized machine learning models to all eBay experiences, fitting the best experience to each of the hundreds millions of buyers. As a machine learning engineer you will be responsible for building the data collection pipelines, building the learning, testing and inference infrastructure and bringing the machine learning models to production.\n\nPrimary Job Responsibilities\n\n\nPlay a key role in leading the design and implementation of key systems of one of the world\'s largest internet and eCommerce companies - meeting the most challenging requirements around scalability, availability and big data processing.\n\nResponsibilities will include:\nDesign and implement the testing framework and CI/CD process for the system\nTake ownership and help drive the team and group efforts\nWorking with scientists and other engineers to investigate design approaches, prototype new technology, and evaluate technical feasibility\nWorking in an agile environment, constantly strive to increase the teams productivity and velocity\nRequired Skills\nDeep hand-on knowledge of Java application development, testing and frameworks\nSignificant e