ate, win, and grow with us in Or Yehuda, Israel.\n\nAs a member of the Central Data & Analytics team you will work on advanced Machine Learning (ML) and Data Mining projects within the Cyber Fraud and Risk Management (CFRM) line of business, with focus on building innovative solutions to solve various business problems.\n\nHow you\'ll contribute:\nWork with R&D and delivery teams to integrate Machine Learning directly into an existing, market-leading CFRM engine\nResearch and identify optimal new Machine Learning solutions to complex business problems such as fraud and anomaly detection and intelligent reduction of false positives\nAssist business groups within and beyond Bottomline implementing the CFRM solutions in performing exploratory data analysis related to their use cases\nAssist the business in evaluating scenarios and plan scope, feasibility, and approaches of potential Machine Learning solutions for each scenario\nProvide best practices and technical support for implementation, focused on stated business outcomes\nCollaborate closely on a cross-functional team and mentor, support the team of data scientists and analysts\nWhat will make you successful:\n3 years working with Java, Python, Scala\nBachelor\'s degree in Mathematics, Statistics, or Computer Science\nExperience in financial services, risk management or security solutions\nUnderstanding of the full software development life-cycle\nAbility to present suggested approaches and results focused on business value\nExperience in optimizing space/time trade-offs for computationally expensive processes\nExperience in Big Data technologies (Hadoop, Spark), large relational and NoSQL databases\nExtensive knowledge in data processing, Machine Learning, and data analysis frameworks such as scikit-learn, NumPy, Pandas, TensorFlow, NLTK\nFamiliar with Agile software development process as well as Dual Track Agile an advantage','2020-07-24',187),(122,'Data Scientist להקמת התחום בחברת סטארטאפ ברמת גן (קו רכבת) - 