itect','Responsibilities\nArchitect of multiple groups of R&D engineers including remote groups\nDesign and escort the development work on the product roadmap\nDrive for continuous improvement including adoption of new technologies while exploring the market needs\nResponsible for the domain technology, technical governance and improving the technical skills of the team\nInspire the team for innovation\nRequirements\nProven experience as a software architect - advantage\n5 years of experience in software development and coding. JAVA – MUST, C#, .NET – Advantage\nExperience working with offshore groups - advantage\nExcellent knowledge of software and application design and architecture\nUnderstanding of software quality assurance principles\nA technical mindset with great attention to detail\nHigh quality organizational and leadership skills\nOutstanding communication and presentation abilities\nBSc in computer science, engineering or relevant field (removed MSc/MA)','2020-07-28',62),(142,'Software Engineering innovation team','The Innovation Team\n\nOur Innovation team is an elite, agile team focusing on developing solutions that advance the firm\'s digital and innovation efforts. Uniquely, the team is mobilizing a blend of software development, engineering, data science, product, commercial and strategy skillsets to engage in a series of fast-paced, short-term projects.\n\nOur goals are to accelerate delivery through rapid development cycles, to build and test solutions for the firm\'s technical platforms in a fail fast approach - therefore advancing or learning from disruptive solution ideas early.\n\nAre we right for you?\n\nThe Innovation Lab\'s Software Developer will collaboratively take part of the full development lifecycle of analysis, design, implementation, testing and deployment. This will include:\nDeveloping jointly with domain experts and third parties\nBuilding prototypes of disruptive products in a fast-paced environment\nDesigning scalable technolo