ience optimizing for speed and scalability\nA user-centric mentality for building products\nStrong Linux background\n\n\nPreferred skills\nJavascript / Node / React\nDocker\nExperience in developing highly robust, safety-centered applications in the fields such as automotive, medical, military, aerospace etc.\nBackground in networking and real-time communication\nKnowledge of video encoding techniques\nComputer Vision','2020-07-28',252),(165,'Software Engineer','Yandex’s mission is to revolutionize the way people and goods are moving around. With its best in class self-driving cars technology, Yandex lets people move from point A to B safely, conveniently, and most efficiently. Our fully autonomous vehicles are built upon the blend of specialized hardware, sensors, and state-of-the-art technologies like computer vision, advanced deep learning, sensor fusion, and human behavior prediction. All these were developed in-house by our top-notch R&D teams comprised of people who face toughest technological challenges every day. If you are as enthusiastic about self-driving cars as we are and like working in an extremely agile, challenging, and rewarding environment, we shall talk.\n\nRequired experience:\nB.Sc. in Computer Science from a leading university;\nfluent in C++ and Python;\nBig Data industrial experience (MapReduce);\nhands-on machine learning experience;\nexcellent writing and communication skills in English.\n\nOptional:\nM.Sc. or Ph.D. in CS/EE/Math or related;\nadvanced machine learning or deep learning skills;\nindustrial experience in machine learning productization;\nexpertise in cloud technologies.\nResponsibilites\nAs a software engineer, you will be responsible for the design and implementation of data- and compute-intensive pipelines for machine learning tasks. You will invent and experiment daily building upon Yandex’s cloud and big data technologies as well as industry-leading tools and frameworks. You will collaborate with the international team of