pated in complex sales processes\nYour degree is in science/engineering.\nPersonal qualities:\nGoal-oriented, with a can-do attitude.\nStrong customer service ethic.\nTeam player who is also confident working alone.\nAble to plan workload, and navigate multiple, conflicting demands on their time.\nAble to see both the ‘big picture’ and to drill down to very low levels of detail, and articulate these as appropriate.\nPresentable and articulate.\nAutodidactic.\nLocation:\nThe position is based in the Azrieli Centre, Tel Aviv, Israel.\n\nSome travel, primarily to London and New York, may be required.\n\n]]>','2020-07-13',217),(203,'Full Stack Game Developer- Junior','A mobile games startup, creating the next big games on the market is looking for a talented, motivated Game Developer with a burning desire to develop great things!\nThe job is located in Tel-Aviv.\n\nThis position will be a strong contributor in designing, developing and maturing our Digital Games Platforms. This developer will be responsible for taking designs, strategies and concepts and turning them into functional interactive experience for our games and platform. This position will work closely with a cross functional internal and external team of designers, network operations, production and marketing.\nResponsibilities:\nDevelop responsive experiences for 2 screens - mobile and tablet\nClient and Server side programming\nEffectively present creative ideas and designs to cross functional teams\nRequirements:\n0-2 years of experience with Javascript, PHP\nWorking- Advanced knowledge of JavaScript libraries, such as jQuery, Node JS\nStrong understanding of responsive design\nExperience developing rapid prototypes of potential new features and interfaces\nExperience with integrating the front-end with server side technologies\nUser centered focus development mind set and discipline','2020-07-29',293),(205,'Frontend Team Lead','Cloudinary is the leading provider of media management solutions, powering the trusted, award-winning visual experiences for many of your favorite brands. Cloudinary is the de facto media platform standard for developers and non-technical brand managers looking to upload, store, transform, manage, and deliver images and videos online. With more than 30 billion assets under our management and 6,500 customers worldwide, were always looking for exceptional people to help us reach for the cloud.\nWe are looking for a people first, ego last, highly motivated Front-end Team lead to help us lead one of Cloudinarys strong FED teams with emphasis on our UI Widgets. To create, maintain and enhance end-to-end features, processes and practices within the R&D department. If you are passionate about people, coding & technology and also love tackling amazing challenges - we want to hear from you!\nAs a Team lead you and the team will be the owners of the developed features:\nWork with the product and UX team together with the backend and QA teams on the fine details of the functional requirements.\nTechnical design & architecture\nImplementation with attention to code quality & best practices\nTeams project management - Provide progress reports to sync stakeholders across the company\nLeading and Building a remote team of experienced developers.\nTake an active part in the implementation (hands-on) of the various features.\nRequirements:\n5+ years of experience in Front-end or Full stack development using modern frameworks (React/Angular/Vue)\n3+ years of experience in leading teams\nDeep knowledge of HTML, CSS and JavaScript\nAbility to design and develop complex components, dealing with advanced architectural issues\nExcellent communication skills and ability to drive requirements\nAbility to lead tasks independently\nA \"can-do\" attitude\nAdvantage: Project management experience.\n\n\ncustom_url:\nFE_TL','2020-07-29',295),(207,'Account Manager','Our sales team is growing rapidly and we are looking for an experienced Account Manager to join our team and focus on our Strategic / Tier 1 advertisers.\nThis person will be responsible for managing a large, dynamic book of business and developing strong relationships with our customers.\nWe are looking for someone who is passionate about media and advertisments world, has strong client-facing experience, and is ready to hit the ground running at an exciting, growing company.\n\nResponsibilities:\nManage client relationships during all post sale activities\nScedule meeting, analyse result, solve problem, seek for opportunities and upsell\nProblem solving and data driven to convey optimal account positioning to meet client KPI\'s\nReport on strategic insights, recommendations and new product capabilities to each client on a regular basis with a goal to upsell and seek new revenue opportunities\nConduct in-person quarterly business reviews with key accounts\nAnalyze book of business and identify opportunities for growth and improvement\nMonitor and identify trends in network data\nUpsell to hit quarterly revenue goals\nRequirements:\nMinimum 1 - 3 years of online advertising experience\nProven results in a customer-facing role; ability to build strong relationships\nStrong analytical skills and and the ability to learn quickly\nExcellent time management and prioritization skills\nOutstanding communication skills\nA true passion for online content and in-depth knowledge of web marketing\nThe will and ability to work in a fast-paced, ever-evolving environment and learn, learn, learn!\nPreference for candidates with a media agency or publisher background or both would be a plus\nMail your CV to jobs@FORTVISION.com','2020-07-29',297),(210,'Tier 1 Security Analyst','Dell Technologies Services is a diverse organization that provides best in class service to customers across Europe, the Middle East & Africa. We partner with companies in every industry and our organization is reflective of the diverse nature of the markets we serve. We believe that diversity in the workplace cultivates inclusion, inspires different perspectives and creates a positive culture.\n\nOur 10,000+ team of experts combine a deep understanding of technology and digital transformation, enabling businesses to efficiently unlock the full potential of their enterprise IT infrastructure. Our services portfolio scales from planning, design, deployment, implementation and configuration through to consulting services, complex integrations and expansion. Our organizational goal is to help our customers accelerate their business transformation by delivering an unmatched service led by a diverse team of world-class talent.\n\nThe Analyst works on information security problems that are diverse and highly complex. Selects methods and techniques for identifying and advocating effective security solutions both internally and externally. Develops approaches to address critical information security issues and manages crisis/incident response. Provides daily maintenance to and oversees operations of multiple customers’ firewall and network security infrastructure. Primarily works on firework product, IDS/IPS product, content filtering, vulnerability assessment tools in order to design, confirm, determine and/or troubleshoot network and system security issues.\n\nPlease note that this will initially be a 12 month contract with possibility of extension, operating on part-time hours (typically 20-25 hours per week). Shift work (including some weekend work) may also be required.\n\nKey Responsibilities\nFirst responder to incoming requests on cyber security incidents.\nPerform initial investigations, triage, enrich data, categorize and prioritize security incidents.\nDocument and monitor the status and progress of requests and the incident response.\nWork in a team environment reporting to managers in Ministry of Public Security, Security Operations Center (SOC).\nEssential Requirements\n1st degree student in Computer Science or Engineering or Sciences with at least 1.5 years left until completing university.\nBasic knowledge of fundamental cyber security and IT networking concepts – advantage\nGood verbal and written communications and interpersonal skills\nHigh motivation and ability to invest in continuous learning on cybersecurity topics\nDesirable Requirements\nSecurity Operations Center (SOC) experience and/or operating a Security Information & Event Management (SIEM) is an advantage\nCyber security experience from the military is an advantage\nKnowledge on telecom is advantage\nClosing Date: 29th May 2020\n\nBenefits\n\nOur people are the most critical component of our long-term success and their health and wellbeing are our priority. You will enjoy a comprehensive, locally competitive benefits package.\n\nDell is an equal opportunity employer. All qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to race, colour, religion, sex (including pregnancy), sexual orientation, gender identity and/or expression, national origin, protected veteran status, disability, genetics, or citizenship status (when otherwise legally authorized to work) and will not be discriminated against on the basis of such characteristics or any other status protected by the laws or regulations in the locations where we operate. Dell encourages applicants of all ages.','2020-07-03',102),(211,'Research Intern (AI)','Facebook\'s mission is to give people the power to build community and bring the world closer together. Through our family of apps and services, we\'re building a different kind of company that connects billions of people around the world, gives them ways to share what matters most to them, and helps bring people closer together. Whether we\'re creating new products or helping a small business expand its reach, people at Facebook are builders at heart. Our global teams are constantly iterating, solving problems, and working together to empower people around the world to build community and connect in meaningful ways. Together, we can help people build stronger communities - we\'re just getting started.Facebook is seeking Research Interns to join Facebook AI Research (FAIR). We are committed to advancing the field of artificial intelligence by making fundamental advances in scientific methods and technologies to help interact with and understand our world. We are seeking individuals passionate in areas such as deep learning, computer vision, audio and speech processing, natural language processing, machine learning, reinforcement learning, computational statistics, and applied mathematics.Our interns have an opportunity to make core algorithmic advances and apply their ideas at an unprecedented scale. Many of our interns publish at top tier conferences such as NIPS, ICML, ICLR, CVPR, ICCV, ECCV, ACL, NAACL, and EMNLP. This internship has a minimum 12-week duration beginning in January. Internships will be awarded on a rolling basis and candidates are encouraged to apply early.Applicants are expected to be pursuing a PhD in one of the areas listed above; outstanding Masters students may also be considered, as will B.S. candidates intending to enroll in a graduate program at the conclusion of the internship. To learn more about our research, visit: https://research.fb.com/category/facebook-ai-research-fair\n\nResponsibilities:\n\nPerform research to advance the science and technology of intelligent systems.\nPerform research that improves understanding and representation of the semantics of data (images, video, text, audio, and other modalities).\nDevise data-driven models of human behaviour.\nInfluence progress of relevant research communities by producing publications.\nCollaborate and increase productivity on existing research projects.\nMininum Qualifications:\n\nCurrently has, or is in the process of obtaining, a(n) Masters / PhD degree.\nPublications or experience in fields related to in machine learning, AI, computer vision, natural language processing, computational neuroscience, optimisation, computer science, statistics, applied mathematics, or data science.\nExperience solving analytical problems using quantitative approaches.\nAbility to manipulate and analyse large scale, high-dimensionality data from varying sources\nExperience in utilising theoretical and empirical research to solve problems.\nAbility to communicate research for public audiences of peers\nKnowledge in a programming language.\nMust obtain work authorization in country of employment at the time of hire, and maintain ongoing work authorization during employment.\nPreferred Qualifications:\n\nIntent to return to degree-program after the completion of the internship / co-op.\nPursuing a Ph.D. degree in Computer Science or related field.\nFirst-author publications at peer-reviewed AI conferences (e.g. NIPS, ICML, ICLR, CVPR, ICCV, ECCV, ACL, NAACL, and EMNLP).\nExperience building systems based on machine learning and/or deep learning methods.\nResearch and software engineer experience demonstrated via an internship, work experience, or coding competitions.\nKnowledge in Python, Lua, C++, C, C# and/or Java.','2020-07-17',127),(214,'Account Executive','Who are we?\nBrowsi applies AI and real-time page data to automatically optimize ad placements for ad viewability, scale & satisfied users.\nThe company was established in 2016.\nLocated in Ramat Gan.\n\nWhat are we looking for?\nWe are looking for a passionate, hardworking, can do approach person.\n\nAs an Account Executive, you will:\n· Achieving and exceeding individual sales goals as well as consistently meeting monthly/quarterly performance benchmarks\n· Becoming expertly knowledgeable about Browsi’s company offering and promoting it to relevant B2B clients\n· Building and developing a global sales pipeline across a portfolio of direct clients and agencies in the digital media industry\n· Effectively searching for new sales prospects by being fully immersed in the industry, identifying new market trends, networking and attending various trade shows and industry events\n· Managing the entire sales cycle from inception to deal close; including prospecting, pitching, negotiating and contract signing.\n· Providing timely feedback to management regarding performance, forecast and pipeline while documenting all sales activity in SalesForce CRM\n· Working closely with internal teams to maximize sales opportunities, advocate for clients, renew business and share knowledge across the organization\n\n\n\nRequirements\n2+ years of experience in Sales for the Digital Marketing industry\n· B.A./B.Sc Higher Education Degree\n· Strong selling capabilities and proven track record in successful sales activities\n· Proactive; curious; quick learner; able to work independently\n· Winner: Ambitious, tenacious; persistent, goal-oriented\n· Excellent Oral and Written Communication and Persuasion Skills\n· Team player with a positive, professional attitude\n· English at mother tongue level, other languages an advantage\n· Strong computer and internet skills\n· Ability to thrive in a dynamic, high activity, high transaction environment','2020-07-08',306),(215,'Submit Your Resume','Founded in 2017, Phantom Auto is the only company capable of remotely driving vehicles from hundreds of miles away. Our teleoperation safety solution is the missing piece in making autonomous vehicles a reality.\nWe are an energetic and passionate team on a mission to build the future of driving.\n\nAt Phantom, every day is a unique adventure as we work with the world\'s leading autonomous vehicle companies. Because we collaborate with companies throughout the world, we have the opportunity to develop on many unique vehicles.\n\nAs an early team member, you will be instrumental in defining the foundations of our product and culture.\nIf you are determined to take on the world\'s most complex challenges and help build an industry-defining company, this is the opportunity for you.\n\nWe are growing quickly and we\'re always interested in hearing from great people who want to join our team.\nTell us about you and what you\'re interested in, and we will be in touch if and when we think there may be a fit.','2020-07-07',252),(216,'Document Control Associate','We are seeking career minded, experienced and motivated individuals for a full-time position working with stakeholders across all departments and offices to support and maintain client-facing documents.\n\nPrimary responsibilities include (not limited to):\nCreate, maintain and manage forms, email templates, and trading agreements for all supported processes and languages for retail and institutional clients\nEnsure a consistent message across forms and email templates through approval protocol working directly with various departments\nStreamline existing forms and email templates\nEnsure all departmental processes and procedures are documented and updated\nParticipate in project-based work as an internal stakeholder\nLiaise with internal departments within the company including developers and other analysts/project managers\nOther job related tasks and projects as assigned\nQualifications:\nMust be eligible to work in Israel\nEnglish - Mother Tongue level (written and verbal)\nAble to work independently with minimal supervision\nHigh level of attention to detail\nOrganized and with good time management skills\nStrong research skills\nProficiency in MS Office\nAdded Benefits:\nExperience in email template and document management in SalesForce\nExperience with document creation, editing and publishing in Adobe Acrobat Reader & Pro X/XI and Adobe Sign forms\nExperience using FTP programs for managing and publishing content online\nLocation: Har Hotzvim, Jerusalem\nHours: Full time, 42.5 hours per week.\nMonday - Thursday: 8:00am - 5pm & Friday: 7:00am - 1:30pm (winter), 8:00am - 2:30pm (summer), with flexibility to occasionally work US hours.\n\nPrior to submitting your resume, the firm requests that you do the following:\nReview the firm\'s website thoroughly: www.fxcm.com/uk\nIf you have additional questions, contact a Recruiter at HR-Israel@fxcm.com\nopens an email client application\n\nEqual Opportunity Employer','2020-07-24',308),(218,'2020 Machine Learning Internship - Lab','Amazon Lab126 is an inventive research and development company that designs and engineers high-profile consumer electronics. Lab126 began in 2004 as a subsidiary of Amazon.com, Inc., originally creating the best-selling Kindle family of products. Since then, we have produced groundbreaking devices like Fire tablets, Fire TV, and Amazon Echo.\nWhat will you help us create?\n\nThe Role:\nYou will be part of a world-class Computer Vision team tasked with solving huge business problems through innovative technology and focus on product industrialization.\nWell need to tackle problems that span a variety of domains: computer vision, image recognition, machine learning, real-time and distributed systems. Everyone on the team needs to be entrepreneurial, wear many hats and work in a highly collaborative environment thats more startup than big company.\n\nThis is a part-time student position for six months.\nMajor responsibilities:\n- Research, design, implement and evaluate novel computer vision algorithms\n- Work on large-scale datasets, focusing on creating scalable and accurate computer vision systems in versatile application fields\n- Collaborate closely with team members on developing systems from prototyping to production level\n- Collaborate with teams spread all over the world\n- Work closely with software engineering teams to drive scalable, real-time implementations\n- Track general business activity and provide clear, compelling management reports on a regular basis\n\n\nBasic Qualifications\n\n· M.Sc. student in Computer Vision, Machine Learning, or related field\n· Experience in understanding and ability to implement algorithms in computer vision using both toolkits and self developed code\n· Experience in Java, C++, or other programming language, as well as with Python or similar scripting language\n\nPreferred Qualifications\n\n· Experience working with large datasets and Deep Learning algorithms\n· Excellent written and verbal communication skills, ability to communicate effectively to both technical and nontechnical audiences','2020-07-18',115),(219,'Customer Success Manager','JOB DESCRIPTION\n\nJob Requirements\n\nWe’re looking for a Customer Success Manager to join our team. In this role, you will work with our phenomenal clients and join in the disruptive technology and thought leadership in the Global Talent Experience Management. You will manage a process across all teams including procedures, internal service level agreements and productivity and quality metrics. You will collaborate and build relationships among Success, Sales and Support to deliver exceptional service. You will partner with Account Management to manage an integrated, complementary account management strategy focused on phenomenal customer satisfaction. You will partner with all customers to drive business value and lead the support function to establish expectations that provide timely, professional and accurate reactive support to all customers.\n\nAbout Company\n\nPhenom People is the leader in Talent Experience Management (TXM). We’re a fast-growing startup on a mission to help a billion people find the right job. As a category creator, our goal is to educate talent leaders on the benefits of TXM and how it helps solve the pain points for candidates, recruiters, employees, and management.\n\nWe’re also an awesome place to work: Among many other honors, we have been awarded Philadelphia’s Top Work Places for 2019 by Philly Mag, #1 Best Company Outlook in PA in 2019 by Comparably, and #5 in Inc. 5000\'s Best Workplaces in the Greater Philadelphia Area in 2018.\n\nPhenom People delivers the Phenom Talent Experience Management (TXM) platform to transform the talent journey from interested candidates to thriving employees to enthusiastic brand advocates, while helping HR break the stereotype of being a cost center instead of a revenue generator.\n\nRedefining the entire talent experience through a single platform approach, Phenom’s TXM platform provides companies with a unified solution which delivers a Career Site, CRM, CMS, Chatbot, SMS, Internal Mobility & Referrals, University Recruiting, Talent Analytics, and AI. Our platform is built on artificial intelligence (AI), which drives personalization, automation, and accuracy for candidates, recruiters, employees, and management.\n\nWe believe people should be happy and inspired by their jobs—just as we are. That simple belief fuels our collective desire to fundamentally transform the talent journey, and achieve our mission to help a billion people find the right job.\n\nDisclaimer\n\nWe are proud to be an equal opportunity workplace and is an affirmative action employer. We are committed to equal employment opportunity regardless of race, color, ancestry, religion, sex, national origin, sexual orientation, age, citizenship, marital status, disability, gender identity or Veteran status. We also consider qualified applicants regardless of criminal histories, consistent with legal requirements.\n\nWork Experience\n\nTo be successful in this role, you will need the following:\n\nA minimum of 5-7 years related experience\n\nExperience working in talent acquisition/recruitment or at a TA industry vendor\n\nStrong understanding of data and the ability to teach analytics to customers\n\nTraining experience (preferred)\n\nProven success in leading high-performance teams, achieving results through others, and being a strong team player\n\nPreviously successful in team building, scaling, management, coaching and mentorship\n\nAbility to organize and manage multiple, and at times competing priorities\n\nExperience using technology, metrics and reporting to manage a customer support function.\n\nExcellent product and process knowledge\n\nLanguages:\n\nFluent in Dutch & English\n\nFluency in French or German highly preferred\n\nBenefits\n\nWhat\'s in it for you?\n\nThe Europe team is growing so you will have a direct influence on the benefits that we are shaping. For now we do offer:\n\nCompetitive salary\n\nUnlimited holidays\n\nFreedom to do your job either from the office or at home\n\nWork directly with executive team while being part of a start-up in a scale up','2020-07-18',314),(220,'SDK Developer','We are looking for Mobile SDK Developer\nWe develop smart video discovery platform. Our mission is the bring users personalized content experience leveraging the power of data.\nOur products decipher what are the most engaging and pleasing videos.\nWe are well funded, led by top notch entrepreneurs, growing rapidly. We were acquired recently by a large conglomerate\nWe are looking for Mobile SDK Developer\nRequirements:\n\n3 years of experience developing for IOS or Android (preferably both)\nJS+HTML5\nBSc. Computer Science / Mathematics – Great advantage','2020-07-14',76),(221,'Primary Care Sales Representative, CVRM','At AstraZeneca we turn ideas into life changing medicines. Working here means being entrepreneurial, thinking big and working together to make the impossible a reality. Were focused on the potential of science to address the unmet needs of patients around the world. We commit to those areas where we think we can really change the course of medicine and bring big new ideas to life. As Diabetes Sales Representative Hod Hasharon, Israel, youll play a pivotal role in channeling our scientific capabilities to make a positive impact on changing patients lives.\n\nMain Duties and Responsibilities:\n\nYou will develop superior product and disease state knowledge and effectively educate and engage healthcare professionals in dialogue about clinical evidence, approved indications, and product efficacy/safety profiles to support on-label prescribing for appropriate patients. You will demonstrate a deep, clear and thorough understanding of the Diabetes disease state, Diabetes products and relevant competitor products, including their mechanisms of action, indications, efficacy, and safety. You will function independently with a high degree of sales proficiency to drive sales performance and ensure sales forecasts and assigned budgets meet or exceed therapeutic and territory expectations. You will successfully complete training requirements, including product examinations\n\nBy developing and maintain in-depth knowledge of market, demographic, and managed care information relative to your assigned sales territory. You will be able to work with your District Sales Manager to develop a local strategy and business plan to generate recognizable increases of sales in your territory. You will capitalize on formulary approvals and other opportunities through effective implementation of the Strategic Targeting Plans by using a wide variety of promotional, personnel resources and analytical tools to maximize effectiveness in assigned sales territory, based on local assessment of customer needs. You will provide special education to healthcare providers through appropriate programs that fall within AstraZenecas ethical guidelines. Work with other Diabetes Sales Representative around common objectives to coordinate selling efforts.\n\nEssential Requirements\n\nExperience of at least 1 year as a Medical Sales Representative\n\nBachelors degree in Biology/Life science\n\nBe results and sales oriented with demonstrated time management skills\n\nFluent in English\n\nA valid drivers license and safe driving record\n\nDesired Requirements\n\nExperience calling on the Diabetes and/or Specialty and/or Endocrinology customer\n\nKnowledge of the medical, healthcare or pharmacy industry\n\nDemonstrated effective leadership, organizational and communication skills\n\nDemonstrated judgment and decision-making capability\n\nAbility to learn, analyze, understand and convey complex