havior patterns by using sophisticated in-house built monitoring systems\nContact end users and report to internal and external providers while maintaining operational SLAs\nHave you done this kind of stuff?\n1-2 years experience in the world of online payments\nMother Tongue level English - writing, reading and speaking\nAbility to cope with changing requirements and different regulations per area/financial flow\nHands-on and team player\nStrong analytical and critical thinking skills\nAbility to make timely decisions, at times despite ambiguous processes or guidelines\nFlexible hours (working across the globe)\nDegree in Business Management, Economics or a related field (not a must)\n\n\nThe following would be considered a plus for candidates:\nExperience in the world of online payments\\ risk\\ compliance\nAdditional languages: Chinese\n**This is a full time hourly based salary position**\n\nA few words about us\n\nPayoneer is a leading payment platform and one of the world\'s fastest growing fintech companies, ranking high on Inc. 5000, Deloitte Fast 500, and the CNBC Disruptor List. We empower entrepreneurs and businesses anywhere in the world – from Cairo to California, Buenos Aires to Bangalore and Tel Aviv to Tokyo – to go beyond and grow successful, sustainable businesses. With millions of customers in over 200 countries worldwide and trusted by clients like Amazon, Airbnb and Google, Payoneer truly connects anyone, anywhere, with opportunities to trade globally.','2020-07-08',321),(224,'General NI Potential Candidate','Haven\'t found the job your looking for?\nWere always looking for more talent!\nSubmit your resume here','2020-07-26',160),(226,'Commission Analyst','Commission Analyst\n\nSummary\n\nVaronis Systems is the leader in unstructured and semi-structured data governance software, which is any human generated data that is within a company’s environment. Our goal is to protect companies most sensitive information from insider threats and cyberattacks. We do this by allowing organizations to analyze, secure, manage, and migrate their volumes of unstructured data.\n\nKey Responsibilities\nPreparing the commission plans to each of the Company’s Sales Team\nAnalyzing the cost of commission per Sales group, and ensuring no deviations from the budgeted target\nCommunicating and addressing any questions and quarries Sales team have in relation to their compensation\nReviewing the commission expense per team, per territory and ensuring no unusual events took place\nIn charge of updating the plans in the Company’s billing system so all information is accurate and up to date\nDesired Skills & Experience\nBachelor’s degree.\nWilling to work hard under pressure in a global dynamic environment\nOutstanding oral and written communication skills is a must\nSuperior planning, organization, and problem-solving skills\nHighly responsible, very detailed oriented and organized (Attention to details, follow-up, and time management skills)\nExcellent relationship building and people skills\nFluent in English (writing and speaking) and in Hebrew\nTeam player, can-do attitude, flexible, self-motivated\nMotivated, eager to learn','2020-07-16',324),(227,'Account Manager - Publishers','Woobi is searching for a talented, passionate for games, sales oriented Publisher Account Manager to join our team!\n\nIn this role, you will be the day to day contact with our publishers, and the voice and face of our business. Publisher Account Manager is responsible for growing each account, running trend and analytical reports, managing all post-sales communication with the publisher, from onboarding and testing, regular check-ins and relationship development, to monthly reporting.\n\nResponsibilities\n\nWorking with the publisher development team to onboard new publishers.\nWork with the ad operations team for campaign alignment.\nManage direct publisher accounts, monitor daily, and actively look for opportunities to grow supply by partnering with the sales team.\nTroubleshooting issues that arise with publisher integrations.\nBuild a long lasting relationship with each publisher.\nOnboard, train, and make recommendations to publishers integrating Woobi\'s monetization platform\nAssist with the integration of all new SDK publishers and ensure their needs are answered quickly and accurately by facilitating solutions across multiple departments\nHave regular meetings and calls with key publishers to ensure elite level service and to anticipate any development changes or needs\n\nRequirements:\nEnglish at mother tongue level – a must. Additional language is an advantage\nKnowledge / Experience in the online advertising industry – a must\n1-2 years experience as a Publisher AM – an advantage\nPrevious programmatic RTB experience - High Advantage\nSales experience - an advantage\nAnalytical skill and attention to detail – a must\nAbility to provide a high quality of customer service to Publishers.\nProficiency in MS-Office applications (Word, Excel)\nStrong written and oral communication skills\nBasic technical abilities, comfortable with learning new platforms, quick learner\nFunction well in a fast pacing environment, able to work under pressure\nEnthusiastic, highly motivated individual with a serious work ethic\nProactive; able to work independently; tenacious; goal-oriented; team player\nMultitasking skills, ability to see a project through until the end\nVery well organized\nBachelor\'s degree - an advantage','2020-07-11',325),(228,'Didn\'t find a position that suits you? Send us your Resume!','In case you haven\'t found any other relevant openings that suits your skills, please attach your CV here.','2020-07-21',17),(229,'Product Analyst','A profitable startup with over 25000 paying customers worldwide developing a platform for project management is looking for a Product Analyst to ensure data and insights are actionable to drive decisions across the business and communicate data-driven insights and recommend