e years focused on Node.js development.\nYour work history demonstrates successful experience with web client technologies such as React, Angular, VueJS.\nExperience with developing and monitoring micro-service architecture.\nYou welcome complex problems and work until you can find a workable solution.\nYou work cross-functionally and hold yourself accountable.\nYou can work with remote team members.\nNice to have, but certainly not necessary:\nAmazon Web Services experience: specifically VPC, EC2, EBS, S3, Redshift, and RDS\nExperience with Jenkins.\nExperience in building enterprise tools.\nExperience working for a consumer Internet company.\nAbout us: We are headquartered in San Francisco, with R&D in Tel Aviv, and are backed by Sequoia, GreatPoint Ventures, Optum Ventures, and large BCBS payers. Our customers include health plans and physician-led healthcare systems.\n\nBy inputting your information and clicking \"Submit Application\", you acknowledge that you have read and agree to Vim\'s Candidate Privacy Notice.','2020-07-27',105),(247,'Senior Security Researcher','SentinelOne is shaping the future of endpoint security through its unified, converged platform that automatically prevents, detects, and responds to threats in real-time. Our unique approach is based on deep inspection of all system processes combined with innovative machine learning to quickly isolate malicious behaviors, protecting devices against advanced, targeted threats in real time.\n\nWhat are we looking for?\n\nWe are looking for talented security researchers, people who look at the world differently, who explore, \"hunt\", live to beat the system and challenge it. People who are in a pursuit to outsmart the malware and overcome it.\n\nWhy us?\n\nBecause you will meet extraordinary challenges facing the newest malwares and tech obstacles and overcoming them.\nYou will work with the very BEST in the industry in a flexible and independent environment.\nYou will influence the design of a disruptive product that will shape the security industry of tomorrow.\n\nWhat will you do?\n\nYou will be responsible for strategic long term research, that would involve deep researching of OS internals including Windows and Linux, research for new vulnerabilities and novel threats.\nYou will be developing and using internal research tools, evaluating new advanced technologies and discovering new ways to detect/prevent attacks.\nYou will also be encouraged to write white papers, blogs and articles.\n\nWhat experience or knowledge should you bring?\nDeep understanding of Windows Internals knowledge - understanding how core system components (Process and Threads, Virtual Memory and more) work behind the scenes.\nExperience in malware analysis (statically and dynamically) and reverse engineering (x86/x64).\nExperienced with analysis tools, such as: IDA, WinDBG, SysInternals and more.\nExperienced with Python, C and C++ programming.\nExperienced with vulnerability research and/or vulnerability exploitation - advantage.\nUnderstanding of existing AVs internals - advantage.\n#LI-AR1','2020-07-19',78),(248,'Big Data Tech Lead','Big Data Tech Lead- IL\n\nWe\'re looking for an experienced Big Data Tech Lead, with a HO attitude to build our next generation scalable big data processing and analytics systems in the cloud. We work with various Big Data technologies such as Spark, Kafka, Druid and ElasticSearch (and more), and were looking for you...\n\nExperience and Skills:\n2+ years experience in technical Leadership for Enterprise products- mainly in a startup environment.\nEnthusiastic about performant web scale & complex systems and flows\nMeticulous about scalability and security\nExperienced in planning and building scalable real-time data systems\nHO Experienced in Java- mandatory.\nWell founded in data-structures and analytical problem solving\nTeam player and ability to mentor\nA fast learner with a \"Can DO!\" attitude\nEven Better:\nExperience in building microservice based architecture\nExpertise with Amazon Web Services ecosystem\nExperience in Complex processing workloads with SPARK.\nExperience with ElasticSearch or other search engine technologies\nHO Experienced in Kotlin/Scala or similar\nFamiliarity with building microservices using Akka, Vert.x or similar\nB.Sc. or M.Sc. in Computer Science / Engineering / Bioinformatics, or equivalent\nKnowledge with DynamoDB, Cassandra, MongoDB or other NoSQL databases\nSelf-taught from Coursera, Khan Academy, edX or others\nWhy Totango?\nTotango is a fast growing start-up building an ambitious cloud application. Youll have the opportunity to learn cutting edge technologies and make an impact.\nTotango leads the exciting new field of Customer Success. We help businesses pro-actively support their existing clients and reduce churn.\nWe\'re based in Tel-Aviv near Azrieli and HaShalom train station. It\'s a vibrant and fun place surrounded by public transport and great restaurants.\nYou\'ll enjoy the company of super bright people that are exciting to work with.\nPowered by JazzHR','2020-07-26',13),(249,'Executive Assistant','Executive Assistant\nJerusalem Venture Partners has created and invested in over 140 companies in Israel, the US, and Europe. JVPs investment strategy is spearheaded by deep expertise in identifying opportunities from inception and growing them into global industry leaders.\nWe are looking for a candidate who wants to be part of a dynamic and global business environment, a person with a getting things done and proactive attitude.\nYour role will be to keep your finger on the pulse of the business, compose executive communications emails, be part of the presentation preparation, support day-to-day business, and liaise with international business.\n\n\nRequirements:\nRequirements:\nBA degree\nAt least 3+ years experience as an Executive Assistant.\nNative English & Hebrew speaker.\nYou must have a forte in English creative writing\nSelf-sufficient, organized and be able to work with minimal supervision.\nProfessional, efficient, self-motivated and organized.\nWorking days - Sunday to Friday\n\n\nCompany:\nJVP\n\nRegion:\nIsrael','2020-07-28',347),(250,'Operational Assistant - NYU Tel Aviv (Part Time/Fixed Term)','About NYU Tel Aviv\nNYU Tel Aviv, an affiliate of New York University, aims to create a study abroad program of exceptional quality for its students, offering undergraduate students the opportunity to spend one semester or more living in Tel Aviv while studying for NYU accredited courses. The NYU Tel Aviv student body includes a diverse group students from all three degree-granting campuses (NYU New York, NYU Abu Dhabi and NYU Shanghai).\nThis is a part-time/fixed term role providing operational support to the site’s academic and student-life departments (classes, trips, events, delegation visits, etc.). Administrative support and coordination with internal and external stakeholders, suppliers and service providers. Procurement, invoices, payment processing.\n\nBA degree is required (students pursuing a BA can also apply)\nExperience in administrative management – Advantage.\nFluency in both English and Hebrew are required; knowledge of Arabic is an advantage.\nExcellent skills in Microsoft Excel.\nFamiliarity with Israeli and American cultures.\n\nThe University is an equal opportunity employer committed to equity, diversity and social inclusion.','2020-07-30',348),(251,'Copywriter and Storyteller','Description\n\nOverwolf is seeking a talented copywriter to join our pack - a wordsmith with passion for content writing and storytelling.\n\nOverwolf is a platform for developers who want to integrate with PC games. Thousands of developers use Overwolf to build mods and apps for leading PC games such as League of Legends, Fortnite, CS: GO, Hearthstone and many more.\n\nThis is a great opportunity to join a professional and fun marketing team at Overwolf and work in the dynamic esports and gaming ecosystem.\nResponsibilities\nWrite copy and micro-copy for a variety of products, including Overwolf’s home page, app interface, landing pages, video scripts, technical API documentation, blog posts and social media posts\nCraft stories and press releases that follow the brand’s tone of voice, working with our PR agencies in Israel and LA\nHelp other departments in the company to sharpen their copy so it’s clear and consistent\nCreate buzzworthy / viral content based on brand needs and partner opportunities\nDevelop and maintain a clear and consistent brand message in all copy\nRequirements\nNative English speaker\nMust be a PC gamer, bonus points if you play League of Legends\n2+ years of experience writing marketing/advertising copy and micro-copy\nExperience in a fast-growing startup - an advantage\nExperience in the video game industry - a strong advantage\nBachelor’s Degree (B.A./B.S.) in advertising, marketing, creative writing, communications, or a related field\nExcellent and communication skills (verbal and written)\nStrong interpersonal skills and a can-do approach\nJob Types: Full-time, Part-time, Contract\n\nExperience:\nCopywriting: 1 year (Preferred)\nLanguage:\nNative English (Required)','2020-07-26',349),(252,'Web Search Evaluator','Appen Web Search Evaluators perform basic online tasks to evaluate the quality and relevance of internet-based search results, advertisements and/or web page content. This position helps to ensure that people around the world are presented the most effective and relevant data possible when searching for information on the internet. In other words, your input counts in creating a better user experience for people looking for data online around the globe.\n\nThe Web Search Evaluator position is a part-time, work-from-home opportunity where all you need is a computer, sound card with speakers, high-speed internet connection and experience searching for information on the internet to get the job done.\n\nThese are entry-level positions that will allow the Web Search Evaluator to learn new technologies and receive income while helping improve the quality and relevancy of search returns!\n\nDon’t miss this opportunity to be part of Appen’s rapidly growing global Web Search Evaluation services providing critical data for the world’s top internet search engine companies!\n\nWork Schedule:\n\n· The Web Search Evaluator positions are flexible, part-time and up to 4 hours a day - 5 days a week!\n\nRequirements:\n\n· Must be currently residing in and able to perform work tasks in Israel\n\n· Proficient in written English and Hebrew language skills\n\n· Access to a computer that is less than 3 years old with a sound card and speakers\n\n· High-speed internet connection with experience using the internet and performing searches\n\n· Ability to read and write in English to understand and perform work tasks to customer specifications\n\nCharacteristics for Success:\n\n· Ability and desire to work from home doing internet-based work\n\n· Basic level of computer operational knowledge\n\n· Ability and willingness to comprehend and follow instructions independently\n\n· Experience as a freelancer or other work-from-home opportunities\n\n· Experience using the internet and performing searches\n\nCompensation:\n\n· Dependent upon project\n\nAppen Rewards and Recognition:\n\nFlexJobs – Recognized by FlexJobs as a Top 100 Company to Watch for Remote Jobs in 2014, 2015, 2016, 2017 including the #1 Ranking in 2017!\n\nDeloitte Technology Fast 50 – Three-time winner in the Deloitte Technology Fast 50 Australia Awards from 2012 through 2014.\n\nMomentum Mid-Market Awards – Finalist in the BRW Momentum Awards for Best Mid-Market Business $50-$100MM Category. In addition, Appen was a finalist in the 2014 Australian Growth Technology Company Awards.\n\nAustralian Export Rewards – Inaugural winner in 2008 of the Prime Minister’s Exporter of the Year Award and Australian Export Category winner, Information and Communication Technology Award.\n\nAppen’s clients are the top technology companies in the world. We are a global technology and language consulting firm, operating in 180 languages and we staff projects ranging in size from under one hundred to thousands of remote workers around the globe. Appen’s work provides the critical data our clients need to improve the technology experience in many platforms for all users.\n\nNote: Appen is actively hiring for many clients. We have other opportunities which may be contractor or employee status, or have different schedules and requirements. Our team will evaluate your application and review all positions that might be a quality fit based on your skills and experience. To see all our work opportunities, please visit join.appen.com.','2020-07-27',23),(253,'Product Manager - Detection','SentinelOne is a pioneer in delivering autonomous security for the endpoint, data center, and cloud environments to help organizations secure their assets with speed and simplicity. SentinelOne unifies prevention, detection, response, remediation, and forensics in a single platform powered by artificial intelligence. With SentinelOne, organizations can detect malicious behavior across multiple vectors, rapidly eliminate threats with the fully-automated integrated response and adapt their defenses against the most advanced cyberattacks.\n\nWhat are we looking for?\n\nWe are looking for a Product Manager, to drive all of our detection engines to new heights, initiate and drive the development of new detection engines and maintain our product position as the leading endpoint security platform in the market. This person must have hands-on experience in the area of security research and in leading visionary products, managing research teams, and experience in transforming advanced research capabilities into a leading product.\n\nWhy us?\n\nBecause you will work in a dynamic, exciting industry (Cyber Security) and will influence the way it shapes tomorrow. You will work tightly with the best endpoint security researchers and responsible for the most advanced endpoint protection product in the world. You will be part of a rapidly growing startup on an amazing journey of success, you will work with great people in an open, fun environment, and you will be part of an organization that truly values its people.\n\nWhat will you do?\nBe a part of a talented team that drives the product.\nUnderstand the market, competition, and customer needs in-depth.\nBe able to discuss the product detection solution with both very technical (like pen-testers) and less-technical personas, customers and prospects.\nGuide new detection capabilities from concept phase to launch by working closely with customers, sales engineers, R&D, and Research teams.\nDefine product phases to allow gradual release at SentinelOne intensive delivery pace.\nBuild and maintain our product detection roadmap and own the process of forming it into a plan for execution.\nEnsure our product detection capabilities are built to meet the most advanced attack simulation frameworks and top market 3rd party certification tests.\nMake data-driven decisions to prioritize the various detection efforts in the organization.\nDefine KPIs for Detection engines and push to have our R&D meet or beat them.\nHelp incubate new research initiatives from early exploration phases into a winning product capability.\nWhat experience or knowledge should you bring?\nYou have 2+ years of experience in product management and in shipping successful Security (especially endpoints) products at scale.\nYou have 4+ years of experience in hands-on security research, preferably in the area of endpoint security.\nYou move fast with a growth mindset. Ready to work hard and under pressure but you don\'t compromise on work ethics\nYou treasure collaboration and brainstorming, improve your team members and you see the product success as your own success.\nYou are technical enough to support yourself and the team around you and at the same time- enthusiastic to do and learn anything.\nKnowledgeable about next-generation endpoint protection, cyber-security technologies (traditional antivirus, network security, firewalls, vulnerability assessment, incident response, forensics)\nKnowledge around common attack flows and the malware world.\nGood understanding of kernel internals, at least in one of Linux, Windows, or macOS operating systems.\nStrong written, verbal, editing and presentation skills.\nHighly collaborative with a deep sense of ownership and accountability.\n#LI-AR1','2020-07-22',78),(254,'Internship Opportunities for Students','Data Scientists and AI reserachers at Microsoft help to improve the quality of experiences on our devices and services. We are looking for highly motivated and passionate Data Scientists to design and apply rigorous scientific methodology and algorithms to data to improve Microsoft’s devices, operating systems, and services. As a Data Scientist, you will provide unique insight into business and customer scenarios that cut across organizational boundaries and lead the growth of a data-driven culture within Microsoft.\n\nAs an AI expert, you will help push the state-of-the-art in computer vision, speech recognition and speech enhancement, using Microsoft\'s extensive domain- specific knowledge, data, and compute resources.\n\nWe are looking for people who wish to work on a meaningful and impactful project and make a difference while using their creativity to solve scientific problems. Are you willing to learn from others and open to new ideas? Do you want to support others to succeed and operate in a highly collaborative and global environment? Do you like working with real data and solving real world problems? If this sounds like you, Microsoft would like to invite you to come join us as you are, where you can find more than just a job.\n\nResponsibilities\n\n\nAs a Data Scientist or an AI reseracher intern , you will help formulate approaches to solve problems using various algorithms and data sources. You will incorporate an understanding of product functionality and customer perspective to provide context for those problems. You will use data exploration techniques to discover new questions or opportunities within your problem area and propose applicability and limitations of the data. Successful Data Scientists will interpret the results of their analysis, validate their approach, and learn to monitor, analyze, and iterate to continuously improve.\n\nYou will engage with peer stakeholders to produce clear, compelling, actionable insights that influence product and service improvements that will impact millions of customers. As a Data Scientist, you will also engage in the peer review process and act on feedback while learning innovative methods, algorithms, and tools to increase the impact and applicability of your results.\n\nQualifications\nDue to nature of the Intern Program we are currently prioritizing applications from students with final graduation date of summer 2022 and beyond\nCurrently pursuing MSc or PhD in Computer Science, Mathematics, Statistics, Applied Sciences like Physics or other quant-focused field.\nProficiency using one or more programming or scripting language to work with data such as: Python, C++, Perl, or C#.\nExperience and or project course work performing data analysis and applying statistics working with tools such as: R, MATLAB, AMPL, or SAS.\nExperience or course work applying ML to a type of data, including the application of ML algorithms on large scale data sets, and understanding of various ML algorithms and evaluations techniques.\nExperience with ML platforms such as TensorFlow, Pytorch, etc’.\nPassion to learn from your peers, manager, and other stakeholders in the Data Science and AI domain.\nAbility to interact with peers and stakeholders to drive product and business impact.\nStrong interpersonal and communications skills.\nMicrosoft is an equal opportunity employer. All qu