ith key customer contacts to ensure high levels of satisfaction and lay the foundations for continued growth and partnership\n\n\nApply Now!','2020-07-06',358),(261,'Big Data Team Lead','Big Data Team Lead- IL\n\nWe\'re looking for an experienced Big Data Team Lead, with a HO attitude to build our next generation scalable big data processing and analytics systems in the cloud. We work with cutting edge Big Data technologies such as Spark and ElasticSearch to stay ahead, and were looking for you...\n\nExperience and Skills:\n2+ years experience in technical management/ team Leadership for Enterprise products- mainly in a startup environment.\nEnthusiastic about performant web scale & complex systems and flows\nMeticulous about scalability and security\nExperienced in planning and building scalable real-time data systems\nHO Experienced in Java- mandatory.\nWell founded in data-structures and analytical problem solving\nA fast learner with a \"Can DO!\" attitude\nEven Better:\nExperience in building microservice based architecture\nExpertise with Amazon Web Services ecosystem\nExperience in Complex processing workloads with SPARK.\nExperience with ElasticSearch or other search engine technologies\nHO Experienced in Kotlin/Scala or similar\nFamiliarity with building microservices using Akka, Vert.x or similar\nB.Sc. or M.Sc. in Computer Science / Engineering / Bioinformatics, or equivalent\nKnowledge with DynamoDB, Cassandra, MongoDB or other NoSQL databases\nSelf-taught from Coursera, Khan Academy, edX or others\nWhy Totango?\nTotango is a fast growing start-up building an ambitious cloud application. Youll have the opportunity to learn cutting edge technologies and make an impact.\nTotango leads the exciting new field of Customer Success. We help businesses pro-actively support their existing clients and reduce churn.\nWe\'re based in Tel-Aviv near Azrieli and HaShalom train station. It\'s a vibrant and fun place surrounded by public transport and great restaurants.\nYou\'ll enjoy the company of super bright people that are exciting to work with.\nPowered by JazzHR','2020-07-07',13),(262,'Senior DevOps Engineer','Cloudinary is the leading provider of media management solutions, powering the trusted, award-winning visual experiences for many of your favorite brands. Cloudinary is the de facto media platform standard for developers and non-technical brand managers looking to upload, store, transform, manage, and deliver images and videos online. With more than 30 billion assets under our management and 6,500 customers worldwide, were always looking for exceptional people to help us reach for the cloud\nJoin our R&D team as a Senior DevOps Engineer. Define and create operations tools and processes for a massively scalable system, backing 10,000s of the worlds busiest websites and apps, which will hopefully grow to become the media backbone for the whole Internet.\nWe offer a fun and supportive environment in which you will constantly learn and evolve, and where your ideas will be embraced and pursued.\nResponsibilities\nManage live production environments. Handle ongoing monitoring and troubleshoot failures.\nProvide architectural solutions for complex data and processing requirements involving large-scale systems and rapid growth.\nManage live environment from server infrastructure all the way to applicative image management layers.\nImplement system monitoring procedures.\nDesign & implement our systems network topology.\nDesign, implement & develop various solutions according to R&D/Production needs\nWork closely with R&D teams to enable delivering features to production\nBe part of a 24/7 production support on-call rotation\nRequirements\nExperience with production systems.\nExperience working with dozens of servers online.\nExperience working with a 24/7/365 high-traffic web service.\nMust have experience with: Linux, AWS, MySQL, NoSQL, Elasticsearch, Web development: Ruby-on-Rails/Node.js, Shell scripting, Networking, Firewalls, Monitoring systems, System security.\nIt would be awesome if you have experience with: CDN/Jenkins/Terraform/Chef/Ansible/Saltstack/Python, Continuous Deployment/Integration tools.\nAWS Certifications - An advantage.\n\n\ncustom_url:\nDevOps_Engineer','2020-07-27',295),(263,'Testing Services Project Manager','Job Description:\n\nApplause empowers leading brands to deliver flawless digital experiences for their customers on any device, in every location. The company’s testing, feedback and research solutions enable businesses to delight customers, drive topline revenue and innovate faster.\n\nApplause ensures digital quality for websites, mobile apps and IoT products in a way no other approach can – via its technology platform and managed global community of over 500,000 on-demand digital experience experts. Only real people on real devices in real locations can provide real issues and feedback that brands need to deliver great digital customer experiences.\n\nFor our Israel operations, we are searching for a Testing Services Project Manager who will enjoy working hands-on in a fast-paced, start-up environment.\n\nYour responsibilities:\n\nDesign and manage the customers’ test requests to ensure valuable and precise test execution with our global community of testers.\n\nLead a team of Test Engineers within our community to develop, design and execute the appropriate testing solutions for our customers\' needs.\n\nDrive an effective use of testing resources and activities budget to increase financial efficiencies.\n\nMain point of interaction and/or escalation for all testing related items.\n\nMaintain an active communication with the internal account owners to ensure the customers satisfaction.\n\nSkills & Requirements:\n\nYou hold a degree, preferably in Engineering, Business, or a related field.\n\nAt least two years of experience as a Project Manager, Test Engineer or Test Manager for mobile applications, web products or a SaaS solution.\n\nGood technical and business understanding and a strong interest in the “app and digital world”.\n\nExcellent problem-solving skills, customer orientation, organizational and time-management skills.\n\nProven ability to manage multiple projects simultaneously while maintaining attention to details, timelines and budget.\n\nAbove-average commitment, quick learner and ability to work independently in a dynamic environment.\n\nExcellent written and verbal communication skills in English and Hebrew are a must.\n\nInterested? Apply right now!','2020-07-24',361),(264,'Fraud Analyst','Description\n\n\nTaboola is the world\'s leading content discovery platform, serving 360B recommendations to over 1B unique visitors each month on the web\'s most innovative publisher sites, including NBC, USA Today, The Weather Channel, Tribune and Fox Sports.\n\nTaboola is looking for a top notch Fraud Analyst whose main goal is to investigate low post click trends and improve conversions across our portfolio of brands. In addition, the Fraud analyst will be collaborating with a wide range of teams and stakeholders, and be exposed to various facets of our business, He will define and track fraud metrics, help improve the work process, and prevent fraud. The successful candidate should have a strong analytic background, technically skilled and have business understanding of the online industry.\n\nResponsibilities\nDevelop and automate reports, iteratively build and prototype dashboards to provide insights at scale, solving for analytical needs.\nLearn, maintain and improve our fraud detection process in Taboola\nIdentify and investigate publishers with low conversions and suggest optimization activities to improve their performances\nAnalyze data trends and translate them into actionable business insights\nManage fraud cases while acting as the main point of contact with AM\'s across the company\nDevelop a strong working relationship with AM\'s across the company to offer new optimization opportunities\nWork