tunity to join an incredible team and experience success with one of Israel\'s fastest growing startups.\n\n\nOur Team:\nThe Marketing team is the growth engine of monday.com! With every kind of marketer using every possible offline and online channel, the sky\'s our limit. We are bold, unconventional and on a mission to reach as many potential customers that we can\nAs the user acquisition team, we focus on the no-touch funnel, conquering all things online in our quest to target and reach more people. Were big spenders, with just the right mix of analytical and creative thinking.','2020-07-30',367),(270,'Junior Test and Product Engineer','Challenging job in an innovative environment. A group that will ramp you to the highest standards, with career path and skills that are always desired in the industry. Covering test development of SoC devices from the test concept & methodology phase through the ramp-up of the test solution, both hardware and software, all the way to volume production. Creating test programs and special tests for debug , characterization, and optimization towards mass production. Identifying bugs and design marginalities, leading characterization & debug efforts , production optimization and follow up . Close cooperation with design (e.g. DFT) , hardware and software teams\n\n\nBasic Qualifications\n\n· Bachelor\'s/Master\'s degree in Electrical Engineering\n· Work effectively in a start-up culture\n· A team player, with the ability to work in a rapidly evolving environment\n· Scripting skills\n\nPreferred Qualifications\n\n· Knowledge of SoC testing during both the development and volume production stages, including product ramp-up\n· Experience with Automated Test Equipment (ATE), preferably on Teradyne UltraFlex and Advantest 93k\n· Experience with C or C++ programing\n· Understanding of DFT and DFM methods\n· Familiar with chip design processes\n· Familiar with debug techniques\n· Familiar with data mining and analyses techniques','2020-07-23',115),(272,'Backend Developer- Cloud Team','SentinelOne was founded in 2013 by an elite group of cyber-security and defense experts. In our R&D offices in TLV, we develop a next-gen endpoint and server protection SW product that uses several layers of protection, including behavioral analysis (with ML on the collected data), anti-exploitation, traps and more in order to stop zero-day attacks that other vendors simply cant. It also provides unparalleled threat visibility at a minimum system impact.\n\nWhat are we looking for?\n\nWe are looking for a strong backend technical engineer to take part in building our next generation management console platform as a service.\n\nWhat will you do?\n\nYou will take part in the architecture, design and implementation of a multi-disciplinary cloud native software platform that will serve thousands of users and hundreds millions of events as part of SentinelOne\'s management console region services.\n\nWhat experience or knowledge should you bring?\nA degree in Computer Science/Software engineering from a well-regarded university OR a comparable experience from well renowned companies/military units\nAt least three years of hands-on experience with using object oriented methodologies with Python or Java/C#/C++ or Similar.\nFluency in Linux based operating system with focus on embedding open source tools within commercial products.\nAbility to quickly dive into new products and understand their inner working.\nSelf-driven individual who enjoys a startup culture.\nAdvantages:\nExperience with Dockers, Helm & Kubernetes.\nFamiliarity with AWS and other cloud platforms\nExperience with large scale management systems and performance.\n#LI-AR1','2020-07-14',78),(273,'Product Analyst','You figure out how the user navigates our web applications, find the pain points and help wrinkle them out. Google Analytics and A/B testing tools like Optimizely are some of the toolings you are using to get the data. You know that data does not just fall from the sky (or from a tracking script) so you are tech savvy enough to identify, track, and use the data you need to optimize the user experience. Sounds like you? Find out more!\nYour job:\nTogether with your teammates of the Frontend team in Tel Aviv, you are responsible for the best possible customer journey on our website. You will be part of a cross-functional team consisting of Developers, Quality Assurance Testers, UX/UI designers, a Product Owner and Scrum Master. Using the agile framework, we add new features, improve conversion and innovate our website iteratively. Your contribution to the team is to provide performance insights for newly added features, the overall usability of the website and monitor our KPI\'s with a direct line to the Product Owner.\n\nAt the same time, you are part of the global Web Analytics tribe which is responsible for the alignment and guidelines of our data infrastructure among all Takeaway platforms.\n\nYour tasks consist of:\nDesign measurable metrics and KPIs according to the business of stakeholders, and develop reports using Business Intelligence tools and languages such as Tableau, Amazon Redshift SQL and Python, so that stakeholders can regularly keep track of their achievement and know where they are right now\nYou are able to interpret the questions behind the question and have experience in communicating clearly and in a concise manner with stakeholders\nProactively propose business actions and opportunities which is taken out from data to stakeholders, so that they can take an innovative approach to efficiently and effectively improve their business\nTrain fellow team members on the usage of the various data & analytics tools available\nYou know exactly how data is gathered and processed by the different analyzing tools\nYou are the first point of contact and thought leader for behavioural analysis and website optimization strategies by using Google Analytics, Optimizely X, and similar toolings\nIt would be a plus if you know how to find improvement points and troubleshoot tracking implementations on customer-facing applications.\nYour profile:\nAdvanced knowledge of SQL and Business Intelligence tools especially Tableau, Google Analytics and at least good knowledge of another data analytics tool like R, Python etc\nBeing able to do in-depth analyses, for example, performance analysis about the different steps in the funnel\nYou have at least 5 years working experiences as Web Analyst, Business Analyst, Conversion Optimization Specialist, Product Analyst or similar areas\nYou have been working together with product and different IT departments\nYou know how to assist them with insights from the digital analytics platform and help them optimize their products for web applications\nYou relish working in a team and enjoy collaborating and sharing knowledge with your peers.\nHere\'s our offer:\nThe freedom to go where no one in our company has gone before\nPossibilities to strengthen your skills and grow in the role\nWork in a fast-growing company\nBeing part of a new, young, professional and international team\nAn office location within the heart of Tel Aviv\nInternal as well as external schoolings and conferences\nHackathons and prototyping of new solutions\nAwesome team events!','2020-07-27',99),(274,'Personal Assistant','As a personal assistant you will act as the right-hand person of the founders of monday.com. You will provide strategic administrative and project management support, calendar management , travel planning and be a full partner with projects, initiatives and events. The chosen candidate can build this role independently, and with the correct passion, the sky is the limit.\n\nThe Role\n\nOversee meeting coordination from sending invites, scheduling catering, securing meeting spaces, and follow-up correspondence\nFull calendar management for meetings, travel and personal issues when needed\nManage travel coordination such as booking flights, hotels and local transportation\nAssist with personal items as requested i.e. errands, scheduling, coordinating and meeting with investors\nResponsibility on different kind of projects that relevant to the founders work\nדרישות תפקיד\nOperational/ Administrative experience\nSelf-starter with strong organization and time management skills\nAbility to multi-task while remaining detail oriented\nProactive, resourceful and self-driven – anticipates needs before we know there is a need\nWillingness to accept and embrace change in a fast-paced environment\nFluent English and Hebrew\nBA – Advantage\n\nworkהגשת מועמדות','2020-07-14',367),(275,'Performance Analyst','Wix’s Acquisition team. We’re responsible for a big part of the online marketing that tells the world about our awesome products. With over 190 million current users and 2 million new users a month, we’re growing fast and looking for a passionate Online Performance Analyst to use analytics to influence and drive our team’s online advertising strategy.\n\nYou are:\n\n\nAn analytical expert with a head for numbers that you’re not afraid to use. You’re goal-oriented and independent, with an excellent grasp of data analytics. You’re passionate about the power of analytics and believe that data should drive the decision-making process. You’re also great at identifying and following up on new business opportunities.\n\nBonus points if you have a strong knowledge of Excel.\n\nAs a Performance Analyst, you will:\nManage PPC advertising campaigns on Google AdWords, Facebook, and other platforms, translating the outcomes into easy-to-understand results.\nAnalyze results and optimize performance according to various KPIs.\nCultivate fresh ideas and discover new opportunities based on big data analysis.\nStay up-to-date with the latest Google AdWords/Facebook Advertising features and integrate applicable ones into the team’s strategy.\nDraw on the data to spearhead relevant initiatives that support business objectives.\n\nResponsibilities\nResponsibilities\nRequirements / Minimum requirements\nRequirements','2020-07-19',91),(276,'Product Specialist','An essential part of the Product Development group, the Product Specialist works closely with global and regional business teams (Customer Success, Sales, Marketing, Support) and customers to drive product development, adoption and growth for AppsFlyer\'s products.\n\nThe OneLink squad offers a variety of B2B2C tools for marketers to use in order to increase user acquisition and retargeting campaigns.\nThe squad is in charge of the initial part of the attribution process (collecting engagements) and all Deep Linking related work.\n\nWhat you\'ll do\nAct as the primary and expert focal point with in-depth knowledge of your product area, both internally within the company and externally towards customers\nAssist in outreach, education, upselling and onboarding of your product area; facilitate education, training, and onboarding as it relates to your product area\nDrive global product adoption for your product area by working with regional business and customer-facing teams\nGather customer feedback from customer-facing teams related to your product area, filter and relay back to the product development team to influence design and delivery\nConnect the product development team with relevant prospects for product discovery and user testing purposes\nBe the main point of contact for the \"outside the team world\"\nWhat you have\nHands-on experience driving customer onboarding for a SaaS product\nAt least 3 years experience as a senior/strategic customer success manager\nTech-savvy approach with a proven track record in working closely with RnD and product teams\nStrong ability to mobilize offshore, regional business teams\nAdvanced proficiency in written and spoken English\nProficiency in SQL and querying real-time data sets\nBonus Points\nTechnical Degree or equivalent professional experience\nExperience in mobile marketing / digital advertising\nFamiliarity with programming concepts and modeling\nExperience as a team lead\nBeing introduced by an AppsFlyer member\nAs a global company operating in 16 countries across 5 continents, we reflect the human mosaic of the diverse and multicultural world in which we live. We ensure equal opportunities for all of our employees and promote the recruitment of diverse talents to our global teams without consideration of race, gender, culture, or sexual orientation. We value and encourage curiosity, diversity, and innovation from all our employees, customers, and partners.\n\n\"As a Customer Obsessed company, we must first be Employee Obsessed. We need to make sure that we provide the team with the tools and resources they need to go All-In.\" Oren Kaniel, CEO','2020-07-20',158),(277,'Customer Experience Specialist','IL-Haifa\nAE.718\n\nDescription\n\nWe are looking for Customer Experience Specialist that will handle the following:\nMonitor and control the activities of customer service representatives and also service KPI’s (in company, country and teams level) to ensure compliance with the standards defined.\nMonitor the “service chain” and analyze service failures.\nManage and control the implementation of the measurement process.\nConduct different researches (CS surveys including online surveys, customer interviews etc.) to identify company strengths and weakness points in the different interfaces with customers\nWork in cooperation with the countries and also with organization’s functions (marketing, sales and operational) in order to analyze customer feedback and develop programs effective for improved customer experience.\nIdentify bottlenecksand non-optimal processes and promote process improvements. It should be analyzed in company and country level.\nIdentify challenging interfaces & customer dissatisfactionand implement & promote process of changing the customer perception.\nRecognize Knowledge Gaps and training needs\n\nRequirements\n\nFirst degree in Statistics/ Economics / Industry and Management\nAt least 5 years of experience in the field of customer service\nExperience working in service analysis\nExperience working in a global company- Advantage\nFluent English – both writing and talking','2020-07-27',378),(278,'Performance Analyst','StreamElements, the fastest growing platform for live video content creators, is looking for a full-time analyst with specific expertise in performance marketing to join our brand partnerships team.\nThe person we hire for this role will be responsible for enhancing campaign success by optimizing curation, measurement, ,and tracking, while also ensuring peak performance of ROI-driven campaigns and brand sponsorships.\nWe are looking for a Performance Analyst with a passion for gaming and content creators with several years of experience in deploying millions of dollars through performance marketing channels. They should also embrace the agile, success-driven culture we nurture as a company. Individuals who are excellent communicators and independent operators thrive with us. If you are such a person, we would love to talk soon.\nJob responsibilities\nLeverage data to understand creators and their communities in-depth, identify areas of opportunity, and curate creators for performance campaigns\nProvide cross-campaign performance overview, including proactively monitoring company deployments and trends, and being able to raise flags when there is a substantial change worth focusing on\nEvaluating and measuring influencer marketing campaign results and trends among our clients\nBeing accountable for campaign reporting and visual deliverables, such as performance reports, Excels, and presentations\nHaving the ability to work across multiple data sources in order to research and capture full activity and to set requirements for our BI development team when identifying technical gaps\nBe an analytical focal point for anything related to curation, performance KPIs, tests and performance monitoring\n\n\nRequirements:\n3+ years of analytical work experience, preferably for a web or mobile company/e-commerce/online gaming industry\nDeep understanding of online metrics (Attribution funnels, user acquisition KPIs)\nBA/B.Sc. in Statistics / Math / Engineering / Economics or other quantitative field\nStrong SQL with experience in querying large, complex data sets\nProven strong Excel skills\nProven experience in creating performance dashboards and other analytical visualizations\nExperience with influencer marketing on YouTube/Instagram - advantage\nAbility to collaborate with colleagues across different disciplines, geographies and time-zones to achieve success\nHigh level of analytical and problem-solving skills with strong attention to details\nEffective communication skills - Excellent level of verbal and written English a must','2020-07-28',379),(279,'Privacy Counsel','Manager : Gally Perry\n\nTalent Acquisition: Racheli Even-Chen\nWho are we?\nEvery day, billions of transactions, calls and messages that hold the world’s communications fabric together run on systems that Amdocs has helped to create.\n\nBecause we work with some of the largest and most innovative companies on the planet, our work makes an impact. Over the past four decades, we have continually reinvented ourselves, and as we keep moving into exciting new areas such as media, gaming, IoT, 5G, cloud services and more, there are always opportunities for us to grow and develop. We will nurture your entrepreneurial instincts with open doors and promote your ability to seize the day. Our company is built of amazing people, a supportive atmosphere and a culture built on mutual support, respect and a “feel-good factor” that can only happen in a workplace built by the kind of people that Amdocs employs.\n\nMake your career journey with us.\nIn one sentence\nWe are seeking a talented Privacy Counsel to assist in a range of privacy-related programs and initiatives. The role involves advising all Amdocs units on various legal risks, obligations, and additional issues related to privacy. We are looking for someone who is diligent, proactive, practical, and has demonstrated excellent legal and business judgment. Candidates should work well in teams and demonstrate the ability to work independently.\nWhat will your job look like?\nAdvise on all aspects of global privacy law and regulations, including data protection, retention, security and data breach rules\nAssist in the continued development and improvement of all aspects of Amdocs’ privacy compliance program (data transfers, processing, privacy policies, staff training, etc.)\nReview, draft and negotiate privacy agreements and contractual obligations of vendors and customers\nAssist in building the general Amdocs privacy strategy\nAll you need is...\nLaw degree (JD or LLM)\nBar membership\nCIPP/E, CIPM or other officially recognized privacy certification – advantage\nSignificant in-depth, related experience, including prior in-house experience with global technology companies and/or at a top tier law firm (with at least 2-3 years in privacy law)\nDirect experience applying global privacy laws, regulations, and industry guidelines, with in-depth familiarity with GDPR and CCPA\nDirect experience evaluating and negotiating privacy impacts relating to new technology products, acquisitions, partnerships and commercial deals, and updates to internal and external policies and compliance programs\nPassion for and familiarity with new legislative, regulatory, and industry proposals in the privacy field\nFluency in written and spoken English is a must\nWhy you will love this job:\nYou will love this job because it will enable you to take theory and turn it into actuality in a global fast-paced environment in which numerous, complicated and intricate privacy questions are part of the day-to-day. You will enjoy being both independent in your work and also working as part of a privacy team that assures privacy compliance within the organization. You will be energized and challenged by the need to think creatively in confronting new issues and pursuing novel approaches to old problems.','2020-07-28',79),(281,'Enterprise Account Executive','The database market is massive (the IDC estimates it to be $89B+ by 2024!) and MongoDB is at the head of its disruption. The MongoDB community is transforming industries and empowering developers to build amazing apps that people use every day. We are the leading modern data platform and the first database provider to IPO in over 20 years. Join our team and be at the forefront of innovation and creativity.\n\nWe\'re looking for a hardworking, driven individual with superb energy, passion and initiative for new business acquisition. The Enterprise Account Executive role focuses exclusively on formulating and executing a sales strategy within an assigned territory, resulting in revenue growth and new customer acquisition.\n\nMongoDB is always changing and innovating — not only in our technology, but also in our sales go-to-market strategy. Our sales leadership is committed to building the best salesforce in technology. This means, inspiring and enabling success for everyone on the team. We not only equip you to be successful and close deals, but we want your feedback and input on how we can continue to \"Think Big and Go Far.\" As a crucial part of the Sales team at MongoDB, you will have access to a lucrative market and learn how to sell from some of the most successful sales leaders in the software industry.\n\nTo learn more about what it\'s like to be an Enterprise Account Executive, watch this interview with Jennifer Clark.\n\nResponsibilities\nProactively prospect, identify, qualify and develop a sales pipeline\nClose business to meet and exceed monthly, quarterly and annual bookings objectives\nBuild strong and effective relationships, resulting in growth opportunities\nParticipate in our sales enablement trainings, including our comprehensive Sales Bootcamp, sophisticated sales training, and leadership and development programs\nWork closely with the Professional Services team to achieve customer satisfaction\nRequirements\nBA/BS required\n5+ years field experience of quota-carrying experience in a fast-paced and competitive market with a focus on new business\nDemonstrated ability to articulate the business value of complex enterprise technology\nA track record of overachievement and hitting sales targets.\nSkilled in building business champions and running a complex sales process\nPrevious Sales Methodology training (e.g. MEDDIC, SPIN, Challenger Sales)\nFamiliarity with databases, develops and open source technology a plus\nDriven and competitive: Possess a strong desire to be successful\nSkilled in managing time and resources; sound approach to qualifying opportunities\nPossess aptitude to learn quickly and establish credibility. High EQ and self-aware.\nFluent in Hebrew\nMust live in territory (Tel Aviv area)\nPassionate about growing your career in the largest market in software (database) and developing and maintaining an in-depth understanding of MongoDB products.\nTo drive the personal growth and business impact of our employees, we\'re committed to developing a supportive and enriching culture for everyone. From employee affinity groups, to fertility assistance and a generous parental leave policy, we value our employees\' wellbeing and want to support them along every step of their professional and personal journeys. Learn more about what it\'s like to work at MongoDB, and help us make an impact on the world!\n\nMongoDB is an equal opportunities employer.','2020-07-24',382),(282,'Administration','Requirements:\nExperienced in office management.\n“Can-do” attitude. Plans in advance.\nGood organizational skills\nAn executer, “Gets things done”.\nComputer skills: Office, Word, Excel, Outlook\nFluent in Hebrew and English\nEloquent writing abilities\n\nJob description:\nBecome the first point-of-contact of the founders, and external entities:\nAnswering e-mails\nCoordination meetings\nHandling & managing financials\nCreating financial statements (income, expenses). Knowledge in finance - an advantage\n\nHuman Resources:\nDealing with salaries, vacation days, pension etc\nHelp screening CVs and candidates interviews\n\nAdministration:\nMarketing & Marcom materials preparation of for conferences\nManagement of petty cash box\n\nHandling External suppliers:\n10 Bis\nOffices\nAccountant and bookkeeping\nVAT refunds\nOffice cleaner\nBanks\nMore\n\nHandling Employees business trips:\nManaging invoices\nBooking flights, hotels, cars\n\nOngoing management of the firm:\nOffice shopping\n\nToonimo’s Clients:\nBilling (Stripe / Bluesnap) – Payment terms, invoices, updating Salesforce\nFilling out suppliers forms and helping with procurement processes\nTo apply kindly send you CV to jobs@toonimo.com - See you there :)','2020-07-11',383),(283,'חוקר/ת תלונות וחריגים במחלקת הבטחת איכות','אודות החברה\nטבע היא אחת מחברות הפרמצבטיקה המובילות, ויצרנית התרופות הגנריות הגדולה בעולם. היא מחויבת לשיפור בריאותם של לקוחותיה, כמו גם להגברת הנגישות לפתרונות בריאות איכותיים בכל רחבי העולם. העובדים שלנו, הפרוסים במעל 80 מדינות, נמצאים בלב הצלחת הארגון, ויחדיו מספקים את \"ארון התרופות\" הגדול בעולם, המשרת למעלה מ-200 מיליון אנשים מדי יום.\nאנחנו מציעים תמהיל ייחודי ורחב של מוצרים ופתרונות ללקוחותינו, ויצרנו סל מבטיח של מוצרים בפיתוח, כולם ממוקדים בתחומי העניין התרפויטיים שלנו. אנחנו ממשיכים לפתח פתרונות ממוקדי-לקוח ולהרחיב את עסקי התרופות הגנריות והייחודיות שלנו באמצעות השקעה במחקר ופיתוח, בשיווק, בחדשנות ובפיתוח עסקי. בדרך זו אנחנו משפרים את הבריאות של לקוחותינו ומאפשרים להם ימים טובים יותר וחיים בריאים יותר.\nהצטרפו אלינו במסע הצמיחה הזה!\nלאתר טבע כפר סבא דרוש/ה עובד/ת הבטחת איכות למחלקת חריגים ותלונות במפעל הסטרילי לתפקיד הכולל:\nכתיבה, בדיקה ואישור תחקירים עבור תלונות מלקוחות.\nביצוע הערכות סיכונים לאיכות אצוות וקבלת החלטות\nכתיבת דו\"ח מפורט על התלונה והכנסתו למערכת.\nבדיקה ואישור CAPAs.\nכתיבת ד