y business impact, Systems changes and Group KPI\'s improvements.\nMatrix management of Data Analyst - Responsible for Customer creation setup process in our ERP systems according to data policy management and governance. Resolve conflicts in the day to day customer creation process and assist with outstanding issues.\nPerforming data analysis to identify process improvements and interpreting data, analyzing results using statistical techniques and utilize that data to improve data quality and optimize data flow.\nDefine policies to support the new business requirements and data migration following acquisitions and internal system migrations.\nPartner with downstream stakeholder groups to facilitate end to end master data updates including Sales Operations, Business Operations, Finance and IT.\nDevelop training material and implement training for master data creation and governance polices.\nSupport quarter end and year end close processes for customer master maintenance.\nMinimum Qualifications and Education:\nBachelor\'s degree in Industrial Engineering/Economics/Business Administration, IT or equivalent work experience\nUp to 5 years\' experience in Project/Process management with Data management orientation.\nUp to 5 years\' working as a data analyst or Business analyst.\nPreferred Qualifications:\nStrong understanding of master data within an ERP and its distribution to connected systems for downstream process consumption.\nGood knowledge of Sales CRM/ERP systems (Salesforce.com, Oracle) and associated workflows\nGood knowledge of governance and process for financial data.\nData-oriented personality\nStrong Microsoft Excel, Access and Relational Database Experience required\nExperience with BI / data visualization tools (e.g Tableau, Oracle BI, etc.)\nCapability to interact with individuals from various disciplines: Finance, MIS, Sales/Marketing, Operations, Services, etc.\nStrong decision making and problem-solving skills, as well as strong verbal and written 