ze for data accuracy and attribution.\n\nDescription Of Duties\nExecute reporting / analysis against the analytics needs of internal marketing teams to enable data-driven marketing and drive efficiencies through developing automated reporting/dashboards, maintaining related systems, developing new processes, and implementing testing\nUse analytical and database skills to develop reports and analyses to assist in decision making processes\nDelivers recommendations and consultation to business teams regarding the efficiency of a variety of marketing tactics\nTake input from team leadership and business owners to understand the goals of the business and define meaningful metrics to track those goals\nDevelop executive level materials on marketing insights and learnings\nMaintain existing suite of automated reports.\nPerform ad-hoc analyses to answer business questions or generate data sets.\n\n\nRequirements:\nWho You Are & What You\'ve Done\nAt least 3 years of professional experience in a data-driven position\nGood understanding of Online Marketing Channels (Display, SEM, etc) and KPIs (CPO, ROI, CVR, etc)\nUnderstanding of attribution and the basic assumption behind various attribution models\nExperience with various data tools (Google Analytics, Adjust, Atlas, Google Adwords and Facebook Reporting) a strong advantage\nExcellent knowledge of Excel and Google Sheets including Google Sheet Scripts and VBA\nKnowledge of programming language like Python and SQL a plus\nAbility to generate insights from large amounts of data, evaluate validity and present insight concisely to relevant stakeholders\nAbility to manage complex projects across departments (including technical and non-technical colleagues)\nHands on and pragmatic approach to new challenges (ability to Google)\nData Driven Background\nFluency in English\n\n\nCountry:\nIsrael','2020-07-12',400),(295,'Junior FP&A analyst','Junior FP&A analyst\n\nSummary\n\nVaronis Systems is the leader in unstructured and semi-s