eep dive to set in motion actions and drive them for both short term resolution and long term remediation over different domains and stages of the product life cycle (e.g. IC design, screening, board design, FW, etc.).\nWork with peers across AWS (e.g. EC2, EBS, HWEng, NETEng, etc) and at Annapurna on health improvements, metrics definition, issue resolutions and other aspects of fleet operation.\nDrive resolutions, high standards of operational excellence, and improve on execution.\n\n\nDuties include:\n· Continuously enhance and improve the operational health of Annapurna products, either directly or by raising the bar of monitoring, debugging and reporting of product issues in the fleet\n· Integrate knowledge and data from customers and data sources for fast resolution of issues\n· Co-work with Annapurna Labs monitoring team and root cause team to improve quality and reliability of products operation in the fleet\n· Drive cross-functional tasks and follow-up on their execution to closure\n· Define and drive methodologies, flows and infrastructure for product operational excellence in the fleet\n· Drive and maintain trainings, quality documentation and collateral in order to improve in-fleet operations\n·\n\n\nBasic Qualifications\n\n· 10+ years experience in a technical position working on complex products\n· 7+ years technical managing of programs\n· Proven ability to deliver results in a matrix organization\n· Independent and biased for action\n· Multi-tasking and methodical\n\nPreferred Qualifications\n\n· Experience with Datacenter products, Networking, Servers, HW/SW integration, OS/Drivers integration\n· Experience in operations and process of large scale infrastructure\n· Good verbal and written communication in English','2020-07-10',115),(320,'Application Engineering Leader - Cisco Silicon One™','What You\'ll Do\n\nYou will be working as part of the Silicon One™ team, leading and shaping the team responsible for our Customer Product Support. interacting with our customers and Cisco products groups, both on software and hardware aspects, support developing, based on next generation silicon architectures, the tomorrow\'s leading network infrastructure solutions.\n\nManage and lead this new domain of implementation and integration, support activities with various of the most exiting next generation products systems, developed around Silicon One™ unique solution. The team you will be leading, and yourself, will provide integration and product support, troubleshoot, debug and resolve the issues, and provide actionable data to our internal team, SW and HW.\n\nAs part of this role, you will be working closely and be facing both with internal engineering, SW and HW, and with the customer products SW team, to guide them throughout their system development.\n\nLead the strong product specialist and customer facing team, and responsible for the entire support activities.\nAnalyze and debug next generation Network Infrastructure systems products with their technical issues and inquiries.\nProvide and be the centric guidance and support for Silicon One™ engineering teams.\nHands-on diagnose and troubleshooting, working on networking protocols for switch/router and infrastructure products.\nWork closely with Cisco and other customers System product development teams, understanding the applications the data path required and help them by bridging the knowledge on the various aspects related\nEstablish a new domain of Silicon One™ customer interface processes\nMange and build up with our customers, hands-on debug skills and methodologies\nTransform specialized knowledge of our development methodology and state of the art architectures to our System Product engineering teams.\n\nWho We Are\n\nLeaba semiconductor was acquired by Cisco a few years ago. and now Silicon One™ is the center of Cisco’s SW and ASIC design.\n\nYou\'ll be part of our Group driving our game changing next generation network devices - Cisco Silicon One™. Our unique team works in a startup atmosphere inside a stable and leading corporate.\n\nOur R&D center and development principals are very unique, hosting all silicon HW and SW development disciplines inside under our group.\n\nWe are transforming the industry and building a new internet for the 5G era, providing a unified, programmable silicon architecture that is the foundation of all Cisco\'s and other Network future routing products.\n\nOur devices are designed to be universally adaptable across service providers and web-scale markets, designed for fixed and modular platforms. Our devices deliver high speed without sacrificing programmability, buffering, power efficiency, scale or feature flexibility.\n\nCisco Silicon One™ is a revolutionary, ground-breaking technology for our customers and end users for decades to come! The Internet now has a new faster, better, safer engine!\n\nLearn more about us right here:\nhttps://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/solutions/service-provider/innovation/silicon-one.html\n\nhttps://fortune.com/2019/12/11/cisco-ceo-chuck-robbins-chips/?_lrsc=ce750ac5-11c8-4995-bfd3-936de1c06009&dtid=osolin001080\n\nhttps://www.calcalist.co.il/internet/articles/0,7340,L-3775619,00.html\n\nhttps://www.youtube.com/watch?v=iy8259BGg6U\n\nWho You Are\n\nExperienced Application Engineer for software and hardware development and integration.\nExperience in leading and manage local and multi-geographic team\nFamiliar and have some background level in networking, topologies and forwarding protocols (bridge and routers)\nReady to learn and expand your knowledge in the top line domain next generation Network infrastructure products\nA real team player with positive attitude and strong communication skills\nStrong orientation for system wise testing and debugging, a problem solver\nGood Knowledge on latest programming languages (Python,Perl).\nBackground in Software/Electrical Engineering\n\nWhy Cisco\n\nWe connect everything: people, processes, data, and things. We innovate everywhere, taking bold risks to shape the technologies that give us smart cities, connected cars, and handheld hospitals. And we do it in style with unique personalities who aren’t afraid to change the way the world works, lives, plays and learns.\n\nWe are thought leaders, tech geeks, pop culture aficionados, and we even have a few purple haired rock stars. We celebrate the creativity and diversity that fuels our innovation. We are dreamers and we are doers.\n\n#We Are Cisco\n\n#LI-MZ1','2020-07-23',229),(321,'Project Analyst Student','Job ID: JR0129206\n\nJob Category: Intern/Student\n\nPrimary Location: Haifa, IL\n\nOther Locations:\nJob Type: Intern\n\nProject Analyst Student\n\nJob Description\n\nWho are we?\nConnectivity Product Line – supporting the connectivity development teams of WiFi/BT technologies.\nOrganization is set in Israel and around the world.\n\nWhat will you do when you come to work?\nAs Project Analyst Student you will be part of the project development team in the connectivity department.\nYou will take responsibility for deploying and maintaining planning, scheduling, risk management processes, systems, and tools for the project as well as developing metrics to track and analyze project performance.\nAs part of the job, you should gather data, build schedules and track progress using different scheduling tools and provide indicators and status to management.\n\nQualifications\n\nwhat are we looking for/ Qualifications:\n\n* Student towards B.Sc/ M.Sc. In Industrial Engineering, Management, Business management with at least 4 semesters until graduation.\n\n* Availability of at least 25 hours a week (2.5-3 days a week). 4 days availability is preferred.\n\n* Projects management orientation or experience.\n\n* Excellent interpersonal and communications skills, organized, good analytical skills.\n\n* Knowledge in MS-Excel and MS-project is an advantage.\n\n* Good English level - written and spoke\n\n* Location - Petach-Tikva or Haifa\n\n* This is not an Information Systems oriented position, but will touch a little this world by developing tools which support the planning work.\n\nInside this Business Group\n\nThe Client Computing Group is responsible for all aspects of the client computing business across Phone, Phablet, Tablet and PC platforms, leading Intel\'s efforts to transform client computing through technologies, new form factors, and driving Intel\'s corporate-wide user experience initiatives. This spans all client device brands including hardware, software and connectivity ingredients for phones, tablets, Ultrabook™, All-in-Ones, 2 in 1 computing devices, and home gateways.\nILInternJR0129206Haifa','2020-07-28',422),(322,'System Engineer (with electro-optical background)','*CURRENT EMPLOYEES :\nPlease click here to be redirected to the internal career site.\nJob Description\n\n\nFlex is a leading Sketch to Scale company where customer needs meet supplier flexibility. In our Hiafa Design Center, in Israel, we develop for the medical market. For our expanding team, we are looking for a\n\nSystem Engineer (with electro-optical background)\n\n\nThe System Engineer will perform functions to define, develop, model, design, assemble, test, document, and support optical multi-disciplinary systems and medical products and use your extraordinary skills to bring to life new and exciting Medical devices.\n\nHere is a glimpse of what you’ll do:\nSystem engineer for electro-optical systems and other multidisciplinary medical systems\nSupporting projects for the complete life cycle: Requirements definitions, development, testing, transfer to production\nGood system engineering and a good understanding of multidisciplinary systems, combining optics, hardware, software, mechanics\nFormulating requirements documents\nGenerating test plans, participating in lab tests and analysis\nLeading small teams and subcontractors\nGood engineering capabilities to engage technical challenges\nHere is some of what you’ll need:\nBSE in electronics or physics\n10-15 years of experience with multidisciplinary systems that combine electro-optics\nExperienced in generating requirement documents, design documents and test reports\nPrevious experience in: Sensors such as CMOS, photodiodes, illumination sources, analysis\nWe consider the following experience as a plus:\nPrevious experience with optical measurements tools\nBackground in image processing\nPrevious experience with medical devices design\nWe are looking for someone who demonstrates:\nIntense collaboration\nPassionate customer focus\nThoughtful, fast, disciplined execution\nTenacious commitment to continuous improvement\nRelentless drive to win\nRV22\n\n#LI-RV1\n\nJob Category\nDesign, Process & Technology Engineering\n\nFlex does not accept unsolicited resumes from headhunters, recruitment agencies or fee based recruitment services. Flex is an Equal Opportunity Employer and employment selection decisions are based on merit, qualifications, and abilities. Flex does not discriminate in employment opportunities or practices based on: age, race, religion, color, sex, national origin, marital status, sexual orientation, gender identity, veteran status, disability, pregnancy status or any other status protected by law. Flex provides reasonable accommodation so that qualified applicants with a disability may participate in the selection process. Please advise us of any accommodations you request to express interest in a position by e-mailing: accesibility@flextronics.com. Please state your request for assistance in your message. Only reasonable accommodation requests related to applying for a specific position within Flex will be reviewed at the e-mail address. Flex will contact you if it is determined that your background is a match to the required skills required for this position. Thank you for considering a career with Flex.\n\nThe information we collect:\n\nWe may collect personal information that you choose to submit to us through the Website or otherwise provide to us. This may include your contact details; information provided in online questionnaires, feedback forms, or applications for employment; and information you provide such as CV/Resume. Your details will be provided to the entity you are applying for a job with. We will use your information for legitimate business purposes such as responding to comments or queries or answering questions; progressing applications for employment; allowing you to choose to share web content with others or; where you represent one of our customers or suppliers, administering the business relationship with that customer or supplier. We will process your data in accordance with our Recruitment Privacy Notice.\n\nIf you have any queries about the processing of your data, please contact:\n\nGlobal Data Privacy Officer:\n\nEmail Address: chiefprivacyofficer@flex.com','2020-07-28',433),(323,'Maintenance Department Manager','IL-Haifa\n56.711\n\nDescription\n\nWe are looking for a Maintenance Department Manager that will handle the following:\nOngoing maintenance of the buildings , equipment & computer systems (cooling, air conditioning, lighting, lifts, plumbing, etc)\nReceiving offers from contractors and presenting them for approval to administration division manager\nApproving invoices for maintenance work, monitoring expenses and preparing the annual budget\nOrganizing all relevant documents and passing the yearly review\nAnnual (8 days) safety training in order to be qualified\nPreparing the annual safety plans\nSending & Coordinating the safety trustees and training to safety refresh course\nCoordinating all relevant administration workers\nMonitoring the cleaning team on the cleanliness of the bathrooms\n\nRequirements\n\nMaster Electrician- a must\nPractical engineer- An advantage\nAt least 5 years’ experience in management in the electric & maintenance field\nSafety officer qualification from the Ministry of Labor- great advantage!\nGood technical English\nAbility to read and understand technical plans & designs','2020-07-23',378),(324,'Emulation and Prototyping Intern','Job Description\n\nA candidate for a temporary position who has not yet graduated and is working towards a relevant Bachelor\'s, Specialist\'s, Technical, Master\'s or PhD degree from a relevant academic institute. A Student employee can do specific work in the area of their future degree or work as a Generalist in a specific department. The Studentship is limited in time with the intent to hire into an College Graduate/Technical Graduate position as appropriate.\n\nQualifications\n\nAt least 2 years left before completing studies in Electrical engineering.\nIndependent worker and capable of studying new material alone.\nSystem engineering view is a benefit.\n\nMust:\n\nGood English. Capable of learning new material from documentation and overcoming obstacles. Good grasp of working with new environments and EDA tools. Capable of driving debug across HW and SW environments.\n\nNice to have:\n\nExperience in RTL Verilog, Linux environment, VLSI or FPGA model building. Experience in debug of SW and of HW. Lab equipment know-how: LeCroy, Pattern Analyzer\n\nInside this Business Group\n\nThe Data Center Group (DCG) is at the heart of Intels transformation from a PC company to a company that runs the cloud and billions of smart, connected computing devices. The data center is the underpinning for every data-driven service, from artificial intelligence to 5G to high-performance computing, and DCG delivers the products and technologiesspanning software, processors, storage, I/O, and networking solutionsthat fuel cloud, communications, enterprise, and government data centers around the world.','2020-07-08',398),(325,'Part time or full time student position (Computer Science, Bioinformatics, Statistics)','Please send a letter of application with CV in English to:\nLeonid Brodsky, Director, University of Haifa.\nEmail: lbrodsky@research.haifa.ac.il\n$5,000 – $20,000 from the Donation and grant','2020-07-28',436),(326,'Test and Product Engineer','Challenging job in an innovative environment. Covering test development of SoC devices from the test concept & methodology phase through the ramp-up of the test solution, both hardware and software, all the way to volume production. Creating test programs and special tests for debug , characterization, and optimization towards mass production. Lead characterization efforts , production optimization and follow up . Cooperate with design, hardware and software teams\n\n\nBasic Qualifications\n\n· Work effectively in a start-up culture\n· A team player, with the ability to work in a rapidly evolving environment\n· Experience with state-of the art Automated Test Equipment (ATE), preferably on Teradyne UltraFlex and Advantest 93k\n· Bachelor\'s/Master\'s degree in Electrical Engineering\n· At least 5 years or more of experience in the field of IC development, including test programs development, test hardware design, product characterization and product manufacturing\n· One or more of the below:\n- Familiar with chip design processes\n- Familiar with debug techniques\n- Familiar with data mining and analyses techniques\n- Knowledge of SoC testing during both the development and volume production stages, including product ramp-up\n\nPreferred Qualifications\n\n· Wide knowledge and experience in silicon debug techniques and flows.\n· Experience with C or C++ programing\n· Deep understanding of DFT and DFM methods','2020-07-27',115),(327,'Order Desk Operational Admin Student','Job Title\nOrder Desk Operational Admin Student\nJob Description\nIn this role, you have the opportunity to\n\nServe Philips customers in the best way possible by meeting the committed delivery schedule, delivering quality full orders and providing accurate and timely service according to customer\'s needs and order desk KPI\'s.\n\nYou are responsible for\nManage and process backlog and orders changes in a ti