ayer, with the ability to work in a rapidly evolving environment\nScripting skills\nChallenging job in an innovative environment. A group that will ramp you to the highest standards, with career path and skills that are always desired in the industry. Covering test development of SoC devices from the test concept & methodology phase through the ramp-up of the test solution, both hardware and software, all the way to volume production. Creating test programs and special tests for debug , characterization, and optimization towards mass production. Identifying bugs and design marginalities, leading characterization & debug efforts , production optimization and follow up . Close cooperation with design (e.g. DFT) , hardware and software teams\nKnowledge of SoC testing during both the development and volume production stages, including product ramp-up\nExperience with Automated Test Equipment (ATE), preferably on Teradyne UltraFlex and Advantest 93k\nExperience with C or C++ programing\nUnderstanding of DFT and DFM methods\nFamiliar with chip design processes\nFamiliar with debug techniques\nFamiliar with data mining and analyses techniques','2020-07-24',463),(349,'Hardware Engineer Student','Job ID: JR0137930\n\nJob Category: Intern/Student\n\nPrimary Location: Haifa, IL\n\nOther Locations:\nJob Type: Intern\n\nHardware Engineer Student\n\nJob Description\n\nAre you a hardware savvy? Would you like to be a part of a team to solve hardware design challenges related to the newest interfaces? Would you like to learn how to design hardware systems to enable Intel products validation and PRQ? Are you familiar with the excitement and rush of first power-on of a system that was never tried before?\nMVS HW Group is looking for a board design student.\n\nYou\'ll be joining a team that develops validation hardware solutions for Intel products and newest Intel\'s IPs targeted at next gen CPUs, participate enabling state of the art technologies in the areas of PCB manufacturing, debug and probing solutions. A winning team with a clear vision of delivering cutting edge products and that cares about who and what you are.\n\nYou will:\nTake part in board design projects at various levels of complexity and purposes\nLearn to resolve challenges in the areas of high speed board design, power and analog\nBring the designs to live in lab and support hardware aspects of our users activities\nDynamically interact with Intel\'s design teams and the various validation teams\n\nQualifications\n\nYou should have:\nA Bsc\\Msc Student in Electronics/Electrical Engineering or Computer Engineering\nPractical Engineer Diploma\nAt least 2 years of remaining studies\nPrior experience in the industry, will be considered as advantage\nA precise attention to details\nPeople skills and team spirit\n\nAbility to work at least 3 days a week is an advantage\n\nInside this Business Group\n\nThe Silicon Engineering Group is a worldwide organization focused on the development and integration of SOCs, Cores, and critical IPs that power Intel’s leadership products. This business group leverages an incomparable mix of experts with different backgrounds, cultures, perspectives, and experiences to unleash the most innovative, amazing, and exciting computing experiences.\nILInternJR0137930Haifa','2020-07-24',422),(350,'Software Development Student','Job Description\n\nWho Are We?\nOur vision at Intel\'s Real Sense Group is to enrich people\'s lives through devices and machines that perceive the world in 3D. We work on a portfolio of computing devices including VR/AR devices, Smartphones, Drones, Robots and Peripherals.\nOur mission is to enable our partners to build high volume products powered by best-in-class RealSense 3D technologies.\nThe Real Sense product portfolio includes 3D Cameras, Tracking Modules, Computer Vision libraries and ASICs for depth processing and sensing and understanding with world class algorithms.\n\nWhat Will You Do?\nYou will contribute to a large cross-platform open-source project on GitHub. (github.com/IntelRealSense/librealsense) You will have access to a variety of cutting-edge hardware running Linux, Windows, Mac OS, and Android. and a wide range of technologies including C++, Python, C# and more. As an engineer on the team, you will be responsible for a variety of activities including design, implementation, and testing of new features.\nThis is what we do - https://realsense.intel.com/sdk/\nWant to see what we really do? Here is our open source: https://github.com/IntelRealSense/librealsense\nBe a part of Intel RealSense SDK team!\n\nQualifications\n\nWhat Are We Looking For?\nYou are a student of computer science or related technical field\nYou are willing to learn new topics, improve skills, influence processes to increase team efficiency.\nYou are passionate about programming and technology\nYou are able to communicate in English at intermediate level\nYou are a perfect match, if additionally:\nYou have previous experience (industry or hobbyist) with C++, git and/or computer graphics\n\nInside this Business Group\n\nEmerging Growth Incubation (EGI) Group is responsible for creating an environment within Intel to generate new billion-dollar businesses leveraging Intel\'s competitive advantages. We focus on new business opportunities and identify, incubate and scale the next \"big thing\" for Intel.','2020-07-06',398),(351,'Applications Engineer DDR','Business Title\nApplications Engineer DDR\n\n24-Jun-2020\n\nRequisition Number\n25801BR\n\nJob Description and Requirements\nAt Synopsys, we’re at the heart of the innovations that change the way we work and play. Self-driving cars. Artificial Intelligence. The cloud. 5G. The Internet of Things. These breakthroughs are ushering in the Era of Smart Everything. And we’re powering it all with the world’s most advanced technologies for chip design and software security. If you share our passion for innovation, we want to meet you.\n\nOur Silicon IP business is 