ing team that is:\nFamiliar and have some background level in networking, topologies and forwarding protocols (bridge and routers)\nIs a team player with positive attitude\nEnjoy learning, self learning which can quickly ramp into new domains\nbackground in software/electrical engineer\nHave a B.Sc or higher, cum laude, from the top University’s, or are highly praised/recommended by a Cisco employee.\nWhy Cisco?\n\nAs Cisco, we connect everything: people, processes, data, and things. We innovate everywhere, taking bold risks to shape the technologies that give us smart cities, connected cars, and handheld hospitals. And we do it in style with unique personalities who aren’t afraid to change the way the world works, lives, plays and learns.\n\nWe are thought leaders, tech geeks, pop culture aficionados, and we even have a few purple haired rock stars. We celebrate the creativity and diversity that fuels our innovation. We are dreamers and we are doers.\n\nBe You With Us! #We Are Cisco.\n\n#LI-MZ1','2020-07-23',229),(378,'Senior Software Engineer','Job Title\nSenior Software Engineer\nJob Description\nYou are a part of\n\nPhilips Oncology Informatics is an innovative group within the Philips Healthcare IT division. Our objective is to define and implement the next generation Oncology Informatics end-to-end solutions to enable clinical decision support for all the different clinical disciplines within the oncology treatment pathway.\nIn this role, you have the opportunity to\nbe involved in developing challenging software modules within complex and advanced environment.\n\nYou are responsible for\nResponsible for the design, implementation, integration and testing - implement full-stack application and technologies to assist power Oncology Informatics user experiences\nComply and align with software development professionalism standards within the team (processes and methodologies, quality of requirements, design, coding and testing).\nWrite clean, high quality, solid,