re routing products.\n\nOur devices are designed to be universally adaptable across service providers and web-scale markets, designed for fixed and modular platforms. Our devices deliver high speed without sacrificing programmability, buffering, power efficiency, scale or feature flexibility.\n\nCisco Silicon One™ is a revolutionary, ground-breaking technology for our customers and end users for decades to come! The Internet now has a new faster, better, safer engine!\n\nLearn more about us right here:\nhttps://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/solutions/service-provider/innovation/silicon-one.html\n\nhttps://fortune.com/2019/12/11/cisco-ceo-chuck-robbins-chips/?_lrsc=ce750ac5-11c8-4995-bfd3-936de1c06009&dtid=osolin001080\n\nhttps://www.calcalist.co.il/internet/articles/0,7340,L-3775619,00.html\n\nhttps://www.youtube.com/watch?v=iy8259BGg6U\n\nhttps://www.youtube.com/watch?v=BNkiprGWw4Y\nWho You Are\n\nB.Sc/M.Sc in EE from a top university with GPA above 85\nExperience in SI/PI analysis, lab test/characterization and board/package design is not a must. You should be eager to learn and succeed!\nWe are looking for exceptional individuals to join our team\nElectrical engineer with up to 5 years’ experience - advantage.\n\nWhy Cisco\n\nWe connect everything: people, processes, data, and things. We innovate everywhere, taking bold risks to shape the technologies that give us smart cities, connected cars, and handheld hospitals. And we do it in style with unique personalities who aren’t afraid to change the way the world works, lives, plays and learns.\n\nWe are thought leaders, tech geeks, pop culture aficionados, and we even have a few purple haired rock stars. We celebrate the creativity and diversity that fuels our innovation. We are dreamers and we are doers.\n\n#WeAreCisco\n\n#LI-MZ1','2020-07-28',229),(386,'Site Programs Manager, Caesarea','Careers that Change\nLives\n\nMazor\nRobotics Ltd, a Medtronic company since December 2018, is a\nglobal pioneer in the field of spine robotics. We have a multi-disciplinary\nteam developed on products that combine innovative 3D surgical planning and\nanalytics with cutting edge robotic solutions/products. Join us in working at a local and friendly\nsite with global impact and reach.\n\nA Day in the Life\n\nAs a highly qualified Site\nPrograms Manager we offer you a position where you will work closely with our site\nleadership team. From day one, you will have an immediate impact on our\nproductivity, streamlining strategic initiatives, overseeing cross site programs,\nmanaging key site functions and communicating between departments. Be a\nkey partner in our success.\n\nAs part of your day to\nday you will:\nJob Responsibilities\nOrganize and coordinate site staff\nfunctions and activities\nCoordinate strategic site\ninitiatives and guide to completion\nSupervise daily operations\nand help oversee projects of high importance\nAct as a main consultant to\nthe site leadership for site wide topics\nManage site calendar and\nensure proper planning and deadlines are being met\nWork with and/or lead\ncross-functional teams to simplify and escalate\nBe a liaison for staff,\ndepartment leaders, country initiatives and external partners\nAssist site leader with\ninternal communication and attending to staff needs, ensuring any problems are\nresolved\nKeep leadership abreast on\ncurrent company climate (employee wellbeing, project statuses, new proposals,\netc.)\nManage key administrative and\nfunctional areas (purchasing, admin, travel, metrics)\nBuild strong relationships\nwith employees and oversee their progress, noting any issues or successes\nHelp coordinate business-wide\nprocedures and work to improve existing processes for maximum clarity,\nefficiency, and success\nResearches and recommends new\nand revised policies and strategies\nCreates and maintains systems\nand processes to streamlineoperations\n\nMust Have\n\n• Bachelor’s degree in Business Management or related field\nMinimum of 7 years of relevant programs\nmanagement and operational experience\n• 5 years’ experience in a leadership/management role\nExcellent written and verbal\nabilities in Hebrew and English\nHighly experienced with\nproject coordinating and management\nExcellent oral and written\ncommunication skills\nStrong interpersonal skills\nand a knack for productive collaboration across varying departments\nDetail-oriented and\ndata-driven\nAble to successfully\norganize, lead and direct teams of people\nPossess an encouraging,\ncan-do attitude\nEffective manager\nImpeccable time management\nand multi-tasking skills\nBusiness-minded and a\nstrategic planner\nProven problem solver who can\nmake clear-headed decisions while under pressure\nAbility to analyze and\ncompile large sets of data and present effective reports\nSelf-motivated and\nself-sufficient\nProven creative thinker with\nstrong business acuity\nNice to Have\nMBA preferred\nExperience in global multi-national\norganizations\nYour\nAnswer\n\nIs this the position you were waiting for? Then\nplease apply directly via the apply button!\n\nAbout Medtronic\n\nMazor Robotics, Ltd., a\nMedtronic company .\nTogether, we can change healthcare worldwide. At Medtronic, we push the limits\nof what technology, therapies and\nservices can do to help alleviate pain, restore health and extend life.\n\nWe challenge ourselves\nand each other to make tomorrow better than yesterday. It is what makes this an\nexciting and rewarding place to be.\n\nWe want to accelerate\nand advance our ability to create meaningful innovations - but we will only\nsucceed with the right people on our team.\n\nLet’s work together to\naddress universal healthcare needs and improve patients’ lives.Help us shape\nthe\nfuture.\n\nWhatever your specialty or ambitions, you\ncan make a difference at Medtronic - both in the lives of others and your\ncareer. Join us in our commitment to take healthcare Further, Together.','2020-07-21',509),(387,'System Product Quality & Reliability (Q&R) Practical Engineer','Annapurna Labs is a semiconductor company established by semiconductor industry veterans and is now part of Amazon Web Services. We are developing leading edge products, manufactured on leading edge technologies. We offer a dynamic, open, teamwork environment operating at high pace mode.\n\n\nPrimary responsibilities:\n· Executing product quality & reliability (Q&R) validation and ongoing Q&R monitoring activities and tasks\n· Executing dedicated Q&R experiments and tasks for product development, production test coverage analysis, failure reproduction and analysis, etc.\n· Performing various product testing and inspection tasks for RMAs, product manufacturing quality assessments, supplier and component quality assessments, etc.\n· Selection, purchasing and maintenance of lab equipment and tools\n· Additional responsibilities and challenges are always available based on candidate abilities\n\nBasic Qualifications\n\n· Practical Engineer degree in electrical engineering or computer science or related fields\n· Knowledge of computer architecture, computer networks and data processing\n· Three to five years of relevant work experience\n· Fluent technical writing in English\n\n\n\n\nPreferred Qualifications\n\n· Knowledge and experience in quality and reliability engineering and statistics fundamentals\n· Knowledge and experience in PCBA design, manufacturing, testing and failure analysis','2020-07-08',115),(388,'Product Analyst Student for Advanced Analytics','Job Description\n\nWho are we?\n\nAdvanced Analytics is a leading group at Intel that develops big data, machine learning, and artificial intelligence solutions.\nThe group provides end-to-end solutions internally to Intel worldwide, supporting various divisions e.g.: R&D, manufacturing, sales and marketing etc., as well as products delivered externally, to Intel customers.\nAs a product analyst student you will collaborate with our data scientists, product managers, UX experts and developers in the team, and support the project throughout its life-cycle.\nYou will conduct requirements analysis write requirements & user stories, plan, document and perform the product acceptance testing.\nThe product development is driven by agile software development practices including SCRUM, continuous deployment, and more.\n\nQualifications\n\nWhat are we looking for?\n\n* First or second year student currently pursuing a Bachelor of Science degree majoring in Industrial Engineering or Information System Engineering\nStudents in advanced degrees with experience in Data Mining, Text Mining, Predictive Analytics - an advantage\nCapacity to work 2 - 2.5 days a week in parallel to the studies\nExcellent analytical skills\nMature and independent Highly and self-motivated\nWilling to work on multiple number of tasks in parallel\nExcellent communication skills and a strong team player\nExcellent English communication skills\n\nInside this Business Group','2020-07-06',398),(420,'WebMethods DevOps Engineer (f/m/x)','International business requires an international corporate philosophy. Are you open to new ideas and do you value cultural diversity? At Raiffeisen Bank International, we are pleased to have more than 16 million customers in 13 CEE countries. And our journey continues – with exciting new issues for us to tackle such as digitalisation and changing customer needs. Join us on our journey.\nWebMethods DevOps Engineer (f/m/x)\nWe are searching for additional people for an existing Team for building and operating a webMethods Integration & Business Processes Platform as a Service on Amazon Web Services (AWS). You will be part of that team and help us create and operate the platform, develop shared services on the platform and document and share your knowledge.\n\nWhat you can expect:\nBuild, automate and operate webMethods PaaS on AWS\nOnboard and educate other engineers to design and implements webMethods services and processes (current version 10.5) on this platform\nContributes to the design of the platform\nProactively support onboarding activities\nBeing part of a multi-cultural team, bringing agile and DevOps thinking into life. You build it, you run it\nProvide excellent support to users or customers of the products\n\nWhat you bring to the table:\nTechnical education (Technical school or suitable University degree)\nWorking experience in ESB or real-time integration development, preferable in webMethods, at least 3 years\nGood Java knowledge is expected\nExperience with cloud concepts and providers, virtualization and containers (preferably in AWS)\nOpen and team-minded personality and communication skills\nWillingness to learn\nEnd-to-end thinking and taking responsibility for your code and your product\nGood command of English (mandatory), German is a plus\nAs a plus\nwebMethods ESB developer certification is an asset\nExperience in BPM implementation projects is an asset\n\nWhat we offer:\nYou’ll work in an international team at a leading bank\nYou’ll benefit from flexible working arrangements and determine your own work-life balance\nYou’ll benefit from the very latest in tailored professional development\nYou’ll earn an appropriate salary starting at EUR 38.000 gross p.a. excluding overtime\n\nRBI AG is committed to creating a diverse environment and is proud to be an equal opportunity employer. All qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to age, ethnicity, race or color, national origin, religion, political or other opinion, gender, sexual orientation or disability.\nWe are looking forward to receiving your online application!','2020-07-28',546),(423,'מנהל/ת תחום אבטחת מידע','עבודה עם גורמי רגולציה שונים, ובניית תוכנית עבודה מטריציוניות כדי לעמוד בדרישות החוק · ליווי פרויקטים ארגוניים ומתן הנחיות בהיבטי אבטחת מידע בכל שלבי מחזור הפרויקט · ניהול והערכת סיכונים למערכות ותהליכים עסקיים בחברה · ביצוע קונפיגורציות ושינויים במערכות אבטחת מידע השונות · שליטה ברמת hands on במוצרי 