ellent writing abilities is required.\nGerman or French at a high level both in written and oral level an advantage.\nHebrew at a good level\nFull control of office and Internet applications.\nExcellent interpersonal skills and ability to work independently.\nCreativity, persuasive ability and ability to withstand stress conditions.\nCollege degree. MA – an advantage.\nAdditional Remarks\nThe contract is personal.\nEmployees employed at the university will be able to apply if they have been employed at HU for 11 months or more.\nCandidates maybe required to take an English exam at the required level for the position.\nAs part of the university\'s policy to encourage the employment of workers with disabilities, it is clarified that in cases where the assessments given to the candidates by the members of the committee are the same, preference will be given to candidates with disabilities.\nScope: Full-time employment\nTo Apply: Please send CV and Cover Letter to [email protected]','2020-07-11',551),(426,'Communication Officer','Grade: NO-B\nContractual Arrangement: Fixed-term appointment\nContract Duration (Years, Months, Days): 1 year (subject to availability of funds, satisfactory performance and continuing need for the position)\n:\nJob Posting: Jul 9, 2020, 11:36:53 AM\nClosing Date: Jul 30, 2020, 4:59:00 PM\nPrimary Location: Israel-Jerusalem\nOrganization: EM_PSE WHO Representative\'s Office, Palestine\nSchedule: Full-time\n\nIMPORTANT NOTICE: Please note that the deadline for receipt of applications indicated above reflects your personal device\'s system settings.\n\nCommunications Officer - Position #419083\nOBJECTIVES OF THE PROGRAMME\nThe objectives of the WHO Country cooperation strategy for 2017-2020 is to contribute to the strengthening and building the resilience of the Palestinian National Health system and enhance MoH leadership to progress towards the universal health coverage. This includes strengthening capacities of Palestinian health institutions to prepare for and respond to public health emergencies.\n\nDESCRIPTION OF DUTIES\n\n1. Identify subjects of interest for communications messages and products to promote country work for public and professional groups (including media, donors) via web and social-media, other platforms/materials;\n\n2. Maintain and enhance WHO oPt\'s website and social media platforms in English and Arabic (and other platforms as needed) through development of regular postings and engagement on such accounts/platforms; with an emphasis on video and visual content;\n\n3. Participate in the production of WHO and WHE oPt\'s main regular communication products and tools, and maintain an up-to-date contact database with target audiences, and communication for visibility among the donor community.\n\n4. Support the development and implementation of selected health and advocacy campaigns (e.g. barriers to health, non-communicable diseases, universal health coverage,) including messages, written and multimedia materials, dissemination and follow-up;\n\n5. Maintain contact and good relationships with communication specialists/teams at WHO regional level, in addition to local UN and partner and donor groups (eg UNICEF, ECHO).\n\n6. Support the development of content for emergency-related advocacy tools, in line with established WHO guidelines and standards used throughout the Organization, to ensure consistency of approach.\n\n7. Carry out other tasks as required to support the internal and external communication of the organization.\n\nREQUIRED QUALIFICATIONS\nEducation\n\nEssential:\n> University degree in communication, journalism, political science, social sciences, international relations or related field.\nDesirable:\n> Studies or experience-based knowledge of communications techniques\n> Knowledge or understanding of WHO mandate and goals in the emergency incident management context.\nExperience\n\nEssential:\n> Studies or experience-based knowledge of communications techniques . -> Knowledge or understanding of WHO mandate and goals in the emergency incident management context.\nDesirable: -> Experience in planning and implementing media and communications projects tactics, including the development of audio and visual materials and tools.\n\n> Related experience in the United Nations or an international organization involved in communications projects and/or tactics related to humanitarian crises, emergency preparedness and response relief interventions and risk reduction in public health\nSkills\n\n> Ability to write well in English and Arabic and produce engaging communication materials in written and visual form (photo and video)\n> Excellent interpersonal skills complemented by the ability to conceptualize ideas and advocate consensus.\nProven skills in the development and implementation of communication/media products and tactics, including excellent storytelling and presentation skills and photo production abilities.\n\n> Knowledge of social media and website management;\n> Demonstrated ability to work under pressure to achieve multiple deadlines\n> Ability to \"think out of the box\" and to make innovative proposals to extend communication reach.\n> Demonstrated ability to work within an emergency context at the country level\n> Knowledge of public health sector and issues.\nWHO Competencies\n\nTeamwork\nRespecting and promoting individual and cultural differences\nCommunication\nProducing results\nKnowing and managing yourself\n\nWHO global Competencies model at http://www.who.int/employment/WHO_competencies_EN.pdf?ua=1\n\nUse of Language Skills\nEssential: Expert knowledge of English. Expert knowledge of arabic.\n\nDesirable:\nREMUNERATION\nRemuneration comprises an annual base salary starting at ILS 201,346 (subject to mandatory deductions for pension contributions and health insurance, as applicable) and 30 days of annual leave.\n\nADDITIONAL INFORMATION\nThis vacancy notice may be used to fill other similar positions at the same grade level\nOnly candidates under serious consideration will be contacted.\nA written test may be used as a form of screening.\nIn the event that your candidature is retained for an interview, you will be required to provide, in advance, a scanned copy of the degree(s)/diploma(s)/certificate(s) required for this position. WHO only considers higher educational qualifications obtained from an institution accredited/recognized in the World Higher Education Database (WHED), a list updated by the International Association of Universities (IAU)/United Nations Educational, Scientific and Cultural Organization (UNESCO). The list can be accessed through the link: http://www.whed.net/. Some professional certificates may not appear in the WHED and will require individual review.\nAny appointment/extension of appointment is subject to WHO Staff Regulations, Staff Rules and Manual.\nStaff members in other duty stations are encouraged to apply.\nFor information on WHO\'s operations please visit: http://www.who.int.\nWHO is committed to workforce diversity.\nWHO\'s workforce adheres to the WHO Values Charter and is committed to put the WHO Values into practice.\nWHO has a smoke-free environment and does not recruit smokers or users of any form of tobacco.\nThis is a National Professional Officer position. Therefore, only applications from nationals of the country where the duty station is located will be accepted. Applicants who are not nationals of this country will not be considered.\n\nInterested candidates are strongly encouraged to apply on-line. For assessment of your application, please ensure that your profile on Stellis is updated; all experience records are entered with elaboration on tasks performed at the time. Kindly note that CV/PHFs inserted via LinkedIn are not accessible.','2020-07-10',552),(428,'West Bank English Language Instructor','West Bank English Language Instructor\n\nLocation:\nWest Bank Job Type:\nPart-Time Posting Date:\n06/01/2020\n\nAMIDEAST is searching for certified experienced EFL teachers for our English language programs in Al-Bireh/Ramallah, Jerusalem, Nablus, and Hebron offices in the Palestine. Our EFL trainers are responsible for teaching adults and students English language courses. Our EFL teachers are also responsible for tailoring material to meet the needs and demands of our clientele.\n\nQualifications\nFluent English speaker;\nBA in TESOL, Language Education, English OR BA in a related field;\nCertification such as TESOL, TEFL, or CELTA, from an accredited university or institute;\nMinimum equivalent of 2 years teaching experience in an educational institute; Experience mentoring and observing is a plus.\nExcellent interpersonal, communication, customer service, and problem solving skills, including the ability to maintain composure under stress;\nHighly professional, organized and dependable;\nAble to interact with students of all ages and skill levels;\nExperience leading a classroom and creating interactive student-centered lesson plans;\nFlexibility as to the hours/schedule of teaching; and\nProficient computer and internet skills.\n\n\nTasks and responsibilities for this position include but are not limited to the following:\nArrive for classes on time, fully prepared with lesson plans in-hand to teach the full period;\nCreate interactive lessons with supplementary materials from course curriculum that engages learning in the classroom;\nFollow up on students’ performance and provide updates concerning the progress of each class and any occurrences that may need follow up from administration;\nProvide continuous feedback to students on their performance;\nAdapt designed syllabi to suit the needs of the clientele with approval from supervisor;\nCorrect and grade reports, assessments, and submit a final evaluation per individual, reports and requested data in appropriate formats;\nPrepare, review, evaluate and revise reports and other course materials, and participate in ongoing development and review of curriculum;\nParticipate in staff –development programs, including workshops, in-service training programs, visits by academic specialists, and other activities;\nFollow all standard procedures detailed in teacher handbooks or elsewhere.\nConsultant Contract Agreement Details\n\n\nConsultant Contract Agreement Details: All EFL teachers are hired as Consultants by AMIDEAST/West Bank and are reimbursed per teaching hour which is inclusive of preparation, grading, lesson planning, etc. Teachers are not paid for holidays or absent days. AMIDEAST does not offer accommodation and/or travel stipends for EFL teachers. Only short-listed applicants will be notified.','2020-07-30',554),(429,'ראש צוות ייצור','תיאור המשרה:\nלחברה פארמצבטית מובילה דרוש: ראש צוות ייצור.\n\nהעבודה כוללת את ניהול קו הייצור ואת ניהול עובדי הייצור.\n\nדרישות התפקיד:\nניסיון מחברת פארמה כאיש ייצור או כראש צוות ייצור.\n\nידע בכתיבת SOP','2020-07-24',140),(430,'Head of Programme','Background Information - Job-specific\n\nThe Head of Programme reports directly to the Operations Centre Director who pro...\n\nThe Head of Programme reports directly to the Operations Centre Director who provides direction\nand general supervision. The Head of Programme is responsible for programme development\nplanning and preparation and for managing all stages of programming to achieve results in the\narea/s of responsibility. The role contributes to the development and implementation of strategies\nto enhance the competencies and position of UNOPS in sustainable project management and\nservices to partners, stakeholders and UN system partners.\n\nFunctional Responsibilities\n\nSummary of key results:\n\nProgramme governance, implementation and monitoring...\n\nSummary of key results:\nProgramme governance, implementation and monitoring\nProgramme development and planning\nManage programme resources\nPartnership networking and advocacy\nKnowledge management and innovation\n1. Programme governance, implementation an