agement through guidance and assurance of security implementation and cyber defense across Mobileye enterprise and production IT systems, cloud environments and secure development.\nMonitor compliance with data protection laws and policies. Develop, assess, implement and maintain clear and effective organizational information privacy policies and procedures.\nDrive implementation of essential privacy elements, such as the principles of data processing, data subjects\' rights, data protection by design and by default, records of processing activities, the security of processing, and notification and communication of data breaches.\nWork with legal counsel and management to ensure the organization has and maintains appropriate records required to demonstrate data protection compliance - e.g. privacy and confidentiality consent, authorization forms, and information notices and materials reflecting current organization and legal practices and requirements.\nAct as a contact point and co-operate with the relevant Data Protection Authorities and to data subjects when exercising their individual data rights as well as supervise and advise on the response to such requests.\nPerform periodic information privacy risk assessments, conduct data protection impact assessments, and related ongoing compliance monitoring activities in coordination with Mobileye Legal, Compliance, and Operational assessment functions.\nLiaise with legal counsel to conduct compliance monitoring of all partner and business agreements, to ensure all privacy concerns, requirements, and responsibilities are addressed.\nDevelop, assess, and adapt clear and effective remediation and corrective action initiatives, protocols, and controls to ensure proper and timely improvements and compliance.\nSupport the data incident response and data breach notification procedures.\nManage a program of awareness-raising and training to deliver compliance and to foster a data privacy culture. Direct and deliver privacy training and orientation to all employees, contractors, and other appropriate third parties.\nDevelop annual privacy strategic plans and objectives, based upon regular risk assessments and ongoing, data- and metrics-driven analyses, proactively identifying and utilizing the most recent and relevant industry/regulatory trends.\nDevelop and deliver clear, effective and timely reports and updates for senior management regarding Privacy Program effectiveness, initiatives and issues.\nServe as a liaison to Intel privacy office and DPO.\n\nDesired Background\nExpert knowledge and in-depth understanding of data privacy legislation (including GDPR, IL Privacy regulation, CCPA and others). Knowledge applying legislative requirements within an operational context.\nProven experience (3+ years) with privacy and security requirements. This includes a thorough understanding of how privacy relates to business drivers, legal requirements, marketing functions, technical / security controls, and organizational operational risk tolerance.\nExperience performing surveys and inventories. Proven (3+ years) of experience building privacy requirements frameworks/matrices and performing audits of complex IT systems and applications for privacy requirements.\nGood understanding of data processing operations, as well as their information systems, and data security and data protection needs.\nKnowledge of Cyber-security risks and information security standards.\nKnowledge of Data discovery tools - an advantage.\n\nPreferred Qualifications\nAble to conduct the role independently.\nDemonstrated organization, facilitation, communication, and presentation skills.\nExcellent oral, listening, and written communication skills. Fluent in English written and spoken (mandatory).\nStrong project management skills and experience required, particularly as it relates to managing and leading across large, complex, and matrixed organizations.\nBachelor\'s degree in Computer Science, Engineering, Statistics, Finance or a related field required (Or related field or significant industry work experience).\nCIPP certification- an advantage.','2020-07-28',558),(449,'מנהל/ת פרויקטים','לארגון פיננסי גדול בתל אביב ניהול והובלת פרויקטים על כל שלביו בהיבטי לו\"ז, תקציב, תכולה, ניהול סיכונים וניהול שינויים. כתיבת מסמכי אפיונים טכניים ועסקיים, אפיון וניתוח תהליכים ומערכות, הגדרת דרישות. ניסיון בעבודה מול גורמים רבים ורוחביים בארגון. תקשורת בין אישית מצוינת, שירותיות, מקצועיות, יכולת הנעה, יכולת התמודדות עם התנגדויות.\n\nעבודה על מספר משימות במקביל, עצמאות, כושר סדר וארגון, יכולת עבודה תחת לחץ, יכולת עבודה בצוות וכושר למידה עצמית גבוה. שימוש במתודולוגיית ניהול פרויקטים וניסיון בעבודה בשיטת AGILE. תואר ראשון בהנדסת תעשייה וניהול או תואר רלוונטי אחר- חובה 3-5 שנות ניסיון בניהול פרויקטים בתוך עולם הטכנולוגיה ומערכות מידע- חובה. הכרת מתודולוגיות ניהול פרויקטים - חובה.\n\nניסיון מוכח בניהול פרויקטים בתחום הפיננסי והדיגיטלי (אתרים ואפליקציות) וניתוח מערכות. ידע והבנה טכנולוגית – חובה.','2020-07-30',575),(450,'Call center sales representative','Duties will include but not limited to the following: • Reach quotas for daily call volume and numbers of leads qualified. • Conduct a structured qualification survey and conversation with leads through outbound phone calls. • Assign leads to field sales team members and/or partners as directed by manager. • Record all interactions in CRM systems and issue periodic reports on activity to manager. • Learn and maintain full knowledge of OrCam products.\nMust be available to work in US working hours (16.00-1.00 IL TIME). • Must be fluent in English and Hebrew • Experience in sales, account management \\ customer success • Strong phone and verbal communication skills along with active listening • Familiarity with CRM systems and practices. • Customer focus and adaptability to different personality types • Ability to multi-task, set priorities and manage time effectively. • Strong verbal communication skills and attention to detail are essential for succes