,'2020-07-21',308),(459,'Retention / Conversion Agents -15K Basic','A very successful fintech company is hiring for conversion and retention agents in English, German, French, Spanish, Portuguese, Russian, Polish and Arabic High salary and amazing benefits for the relevant candidates Fluent English / German / Arabic / Portuguese / Russian / French / Spanish / Polish Previous experience in the fintech industry - an advantage','2020-07-05',585),(460,'Automation Development Student Part Time Position','Automation Development Student Part Time Position\nJob Description\nOur company is looking for students to work in Resource Management Department in Alma project. The job is to work directly with manual QA people, to take from them scenarios and according to it to implement automation tests in Java + WebDriver (on JUnit and TestNG frameworks). The student will report to automation team leader and will get an appropriate guidance.\n\nResponsibilities\nDirect work with manual QA team to obtain new scenarios\nWriting new WebDriver automation tests according to scenarios\nRunning the tests under continuous integration server (Jenkins)\nJenkins reports analysis, Jenkins new and old jobs configurations\nRelevant education\n\nComputer Science students – starting from second year\n\nKnowledge and Requirements\nExcellent knowledge of Java or C# basics (C++ can be the option as well)\nSome experience with Eclipse or similar workspace\nPreference will be given to students with high average\nQuick self-education, high work motivation\nStrong OOP and design skills\nExcellent team worker as well as independent performer\nThe position is 100 hours per month\nLanguages\n\nHigh level of English','2020-07-26',564),(461,'Product Manager','Location\n\nIsrael\n\nLightricks Uk\n\nWe want to continue our tradition of creating award-winning apps - in London! Our R&D-oriented office offers the agility and excitement of a startup while at the same time reaping the benefits of an established and successful company.\n\nLocation\nDESCRIPTION\n\nHaifa\n\n,\n\nIsrael\n\nLightricks Germany\n\nDo you want to work on beautifully crafted applications in a creative startup environment while enjoying the benefits of a mature and profitable company? Then read on. We are currently forming a new team in Munich and are looking for top-notch developers who share our vision of democratizing creativity with award-winning apps.\n\nJOB DESCRIPTION\nDESCRIPTION\n\nWe are looking for an experienced Product Manager to spearhead one of Lightricks new apps, within the Facetune division (take a look at Facetune2 and Seen on the App store to get a general idea of the division’s products). Our ideal candidate is someone who’s all about well executed and designed products, a technology lover (with high affinity for mobile apps), data oriented, who has business acumen, a strategist and an analyst that identifies needs, translates those needs into an executable roadmap and delivers it ahead of time. This person also considers themself and is considered by others to be a people person and a dedicated team leader. If this resonates with who you are - we encourage you to keep reading. We’re looking for a Product Manager to manage all the product life cycle aspects, from timetables to prioritizing tasks, budgets and scaling, hearing what users want and letting them have the things they really need. As a leader, you should be a “multiplier” for others while having a phenomenal sense of judgement. People will always pressure you to do lots of stuff, you’ll have to do only what’s right. You are very intelligent, curious, hungry, hold broad views and, again, are data oriented (this is important for our mutual success).\n\nWe are looking for an experienced Product Manager to spearhead one of Lightricks new apps, within the Facetune division (take a look at Facetune2 and Seen on the App store to get a general idea of the division’s products).\n\nOur ideal candidate is someone who’s all about well 