tions with regulators and policymakers.\nWork closely with the product and R&D teams on new developments and privacy by design principles\nConduct data privacy impact assessments.\nDraft, review and negotiate privacy related agreements and policies including, data protection addendums, privacy polices etc.\nAssist in preparing and delivering appropriate data protection trainings across company departments.\n\n\nWhat you have\nCertification as a Qualified Lawyer\nAt least 6 years of privacy and technology law experience, including work in a major law firm and/or in-house legal department environment\nExperience handling complex technology and privacy related matters\nStrong ability to understand requirements and translate them into practical advice\nKnowledge and experience in data privacy laws and related regulations including GDPR, CCPA\nBonus Points\nCIPP certification\nEnglish at mother tongue level\nExperience in SaaS and Big Data\nExperience in adtech and/or martech\nAs a global company operating in 16 countries across 5 continents, we reflect the human mosaic of the diverse and multicultural world in which we live. We ensure equal opportunities for all of our employees and promote the recruitment of diverse talents to our global teams without consideration of race, gender, culture, or sexual orientation. We value and encourage curiosity, diversity, and innovation from all our employees, customers, and partners.\n\n\"As a Customer Obsessed company, we must first be Employee Obsessed. We need to make sure that we provide the team with the tools and resources they need to go All-In.\" Oren Kaniel, CEO','2020-07-26',158),(565,'Product Marketing Manager','We are looking for:\n\nAn energetic professional Product Marketing Manager and a great team player, passionate about turning technology and innovation into stories and value to customers.\n\nWho you are:\n\nYou have five years\' experience in Marketing for technology companies. You are tech savvy, but your true love is for storytelling. You are a forward thinker and love solving challenges in new, creative ways. You have excellent presentation skills and your English is fluent and professional You are passionate about your customers, can easily relate to their point of view and are always looking to stay close to them. You have an academic degree. MBA is an advantage.\n\nWhat you will be doing:\n\nYou will be busy daily with creating great content and extraordinary experiences for our customers and prospects. To be more specific:\nCreate content of all sorts: from collaterals, through blogs to complex reports\nDefine and execute Marketing plans and new product introductions\nDefine our products\' value proposition\nPlan and execute lead gen and awareness marketing campaigns\nPromote our industry thought leadership\nSupport Sales professionals with content and training\nRole includes delivering webinars and presentations to customers, prospects and sales\nRole includes working with multiple internal and external interphases (vendors)\n\n\nWhy NICE MCR:\n\nThe Multi-Channel Recording Line of business is the largest within NICE. We have cutting-edge technology, a very exciting business environment, and some of the world’s biggest and most demanding customers. We work hard and enjoy every minute. And we are a great team. Our Marketing work is dynamic and diversified. We are at the forefront, leveraging our creativity to create a real impact every day for our customers and business','2020-07-09',62),(566,'Senior Content Marketing Writer','Eager to make a difference with your words, ideas, creativity and insight? This career-making opportunity in one of Israel\'s unicorns will present incredible opportunities for the right candidate. If you have a passion for content and technology, and are both highly creative and analytical, this one\'s for you!\n\nResponsibilities\nPlay a central role in the company\'s content creation through blog posts, data reports, white papers, videos, infographics, webinars, and educational guides (the position is not a copy-driven role)\nDevelop outlines, briefs and ideas into well-researched, SEO-optimized, effective, and articulated content pieces that make an impact\nWork closely with the marketing team\'s growth specialists, designers, and PR teams to create great-looking and top-performing content\nWork with key stakeholders across product, customer success, data analysis, and other business units to inform the most informative and actionable content pieces\nProvide insight to develop stories and effectively communicate to target audiences\nRequirements\nNative English\n5 years of experience creating high-quality content, of which at least 2 years spent as a writer for a B2B product company\nSuperior writing, storytelling and editing skills\nHighly creative, sharp and analytical\nAbility to communicate complex ideas in a simple, conversational manner\nKnowledge and interest in the worlds of tech, mobile or digital marketing\nFlexibility to handle multiple projects and changing priorities\nResourceful and independent go-getter!\nPreferred Requirements\nExperience working for a Marketing-oriented SaaS tech company\nIn-depth knowledge of the mobile ecosystem\nFamiliarity with SEO-oriented writing and KW research tools\nBeing introduced by an AppsFlyer team member','2020-07-28',158),(567,'Product Marketing Manager','Pepperi is the leading provider of B2B commerce solutions to consumer goods brands and wholesalers. We work with over 1,000 of the worlds leading brands, including SodaStream, Seiko, Hallmark, and Rip Curl, and we are continuously expanding our customer base.\nWe are looking for a product marketing manager to join the marketing team.\nIn your role you will be the expert on the market, the competitors, customers, why they buy and their buying criteria and will turn that knowledge in to marketing content and activities.\nYou will understand our solutions and combine this understanding with your story-telling ability to create compelling marketing content such as webinars, success stories, site content, partner and sales tools, thought leadership and more.\nAttention to detail and an eye for quality, strategic thinking, along with the ability to grasp and translate technical features into business benefits are crucial\n\n\nRequirements:\nAt least 4 years experience in product marketing\nExperience of launching new features, creating content and videos\nexperience with product positioning, messaging, and strategy\nCreative, Excellent written and verbal communication skills, with proven experience in writing, producing materials and presentations\nGood understanding of technical product features\nStrategic thinking with an analytical approach\nSelf-starter, motivated, independent\nExperience in a SaaS enterprise software company is an advantage\nExcellent command of relevant software and analytical tools\nExcellent English is a must\n\n\nResponsibilities:\nDevelop quality marketing content that drives demand\nCommunicate the value proposition of the products and develop sales tools\nMarket intelligence be the expert on the buyers, how they buy and their buying criteria; be the expert on the competition and how to crush them. Use this expertise to create content and sales tools.\nKnow our competitors and how to position our product to win deals\nPlan and implement strategy around the launch of new features and releases\ninfluence the road-map of the product','2020-07-26',699),(568,'Marketing and Business Development Manager / Director','Careers\nOpen Positions in Israel\nMarketing and Business Development Manager / Director\nMarketing and Business Development Manager / Director\n\nCrazyLabs is a leading developer and publisher of casual and hyper casual mobile games based in Tel Aviv.\n\nWe are looking for a Marketing and Business Development manager to lead branding, business strategy and marketing initiatives.\n\nWhat will you be working on?\nPlan, produce and execute gatherings and events, by way of pitching, seeking speaking opportunities, sponsorships, hosting etc.\nDevelop content strategies and ensure they are clear, compelling and adequately distributed across all outlets.\nDevelop strong collaborative relationships with key stakeholders across the company.\nPlan and manage day-to-day resources and dealings with vendors, suppliers, 3rd parties around marketing and business development initiatives (web site, social , events, etc.)\nDeeply understand our brand and know how to communicate it and build it from the ground up in new markets.\nExperience in a similar skills at tech companies operating in B2B/B2C arena\nBachelor’s degree in Business / Communications / Political Science / Law\nSuccessful track record in marketing / business development\nExcellent verbal and written communication skills in English\nProven ability to plan and manage resources\nStrong leadership skills and proven ability to organize, motivate and help improve the others around you\nYou go beyond tactical tasks and come up with strategies that work across all media\nYou are positive, collaborative and work well with others\nCapable of articulating and presenting your ideas\n\ninput.disabled {\nbackground: #5f5f5f !important;\ncursor: not-allowed !important;\n}\n.resume-form input[type=\"checkbox\"] {\nwidth: auto;\nmin-width: 0;\npadding: 0px !important;\nmargin-right: 10px;\n}\n#consent-message { width: 100%; line-height: 25px; }\n.lg-input input {\nms-transform: scale(1.5); /* IE */\nmoz-transform: scale(1.5); /* FF */\nwebkit-transform: scale(1.5); /* Safari and Chrome */\no-transform: scale(1.5); /* Opera */\npadding: 10px;\n}','2020-07-27',700),(569,'Marketing Entrepreneur','monday.com is looking for a soul of an entrepreneur and a passion for solving marketing challenges to join our rapidly growing Marketing team. In this position you will create strategic and actionable marketing plans for new marketing fields from scratch. This is an amazing opportunity to join one of Israel\'s fastest growing startups and make an immediate and real impact.\nYoull join our Marketing team based in our headquarters, Tel Aviv, Israel.\n\n\nRequirements:\nA soul of an entrepreneur and a passion for solving challenges\nAt least two years of experience in start-up and entrepreneurship\nExperience in different marketing fields\nUnderstanding the business world and identifying business opportunities\nGreat interpersonal and communication skills\n\n\nAbout The Role:\nDevelop new disciplines and verticals in the marketing field from A-Z by planning, strategizing, organizing and leading\nIdentify problems and opportunities, make decisions and analyze results\nWorking closely with Product, Design, taking full responsibility and ownership from conception execution in a fast-paced, collaborative environment\n\n\nSocial Title:\nMarketing Entrepreneur\n\n\nSocial Description:\nWe\'re looking for a soul of an entrepreneur and a passion for solving marketing challenges to join our rapidly growing Marketing team. In this position you will create strategic and actionable marketing plans for new marketing fields from scratch. This is an amazing opportunity to join one of Israel\'s fastest growing startups and make an immediate and real impact.\n\n\nOur Team:\nThe Marketing team is the growth engine of monday.com! With every kind of marketer using every possible offline and online channel, the sky\'s our limit. We are bold, unconventional and on a mission to reach as many potential customers that we can.','2020-07-05',367),(570,'Inbound Marketing Manager','2+ years experience required\nAre you a self-motivated marketing fanatic with a passion for data?\n\nStoremaven has already become a thought-leader in the ASO space through successful client relations and strategic content. You will lead inbound marketing initiatives that will maximize Storemaven’s reach and lead generation efforts.\n\nAm I eligible to apply?\nBelow are non-negotiable requirements for the position.\n\n2+ years writing and managing inbound marketing in tech/SaaS environment\n\nFluent English speaker\n\nWhat is the seniority level?\nMid-level position\nJunior\nMid\nSenior\nDirector\nVP\nC-LEVEL\nYOU ARE TWO DEGREES AWAY FROM THE MAIN DECISION MAKER\n\nA day in the life of an Inbound Marketing Manager\n9:00-9:30\n\nBegin your day with a catered breakfast and freshly brewed coffee\n\n9:30-9:45\n\nJoin us for a marketing team sync\n\n9:45-11:30\n\nDefine and lead the marketing projects you own. Plan and execute a webinar with one of our key clients and push through the promotion plan for it\n\n11:30-12:30\n\nMeet with the company’s leadership team to make sure your promotion plans are consistent with the company’s global messaging\n\n12:30-13:00\n\nEnjoy a delicious catered lunch with colleagues in Storemaven’s sunny and relaxing courtyard\n\n13:00-14:00\n\nDevelop a nurturing campaign for leads that converted on the website\n\nPlan an automated drip campaign that aims to get users to book a demo with our sales team\n\n14:00-18:00\n\nWork on an upcoming conference we’re sponsoring\n\nPlan a campaign to maximize the number of meetings we secure with qualified leads at the conference\n\nWork with the booth design company to ensure our presence at the conference reflects our brand\n\n18:00-18:30\n\nBrainstorm new and creative outbound marketing strategies','2020-07-30',702),(571,'Marketing Copywriter (English)','Marketing Copywriter (English)\nMarketingHerzliya\nCome join Plarium’s awesome marketing department. Plarium is dedicated to creating the best mobile and social experience for our ever-increasing 290 million hardcore and casual gamers worldwide. With over 20 games ranging from hardcore RPGs to casual adventures, and featuring acclaimed titles such as Raid: Shadow Legends, Vikings: War of Clans, and Lost Island: Blast Adventure, our diverse portfolio is forever growing, and we’re looking for hungry marketers.\n\nAre you looking for a culture that acts on data? A super-creative team that develops its own tools? A larger than life company with cutting-edge gaming technology in a gamut of game genres? Are you ready to work with an impressive marketing budget to massively drive our games to global markets? If so, you’ll love working with our talented, data-driven teams. Join us and together we’ll leave our mark on the game industry!\nOther vacancies\nASO Manager\nMarketing - Herzliya, Israel\nSenior Mobile UA - Google\nMarketing - Herzliya, Israel\nSenior SEO\nMarketing - Herzliya, Israel\n3D Character Artist\nStrategy Games - Kharkiv, Ukraine\nGoogle & Search Team Lead\nMarketing - Herzliya, Israel\nResponsibilities:\nYou’ll be responsible for the ideation, scriptwriting, and co-production of impactful, broadly-appealing content in support of Plarium’s marketing and communication goals. This includes all marketing needs - from co-developing big campaign scripts for user acquisition and TV, integration concepts for influencer channels, to writing Google, Facebook and Taboola titles for testing.\nCollaborate with design, animators, sound, and analysis teams in order to create and develop new creatives and concepts.\nWork in a performance-oriented environment.\nEvaluating creative content based on performance KPIs of each platform and with our game brands’ distinctive style and voice.\nStaying up on trends and consumer culture relevant to our target audiences.\nRead and understand game briefs and product bibles to ensure game accuracy, brand integrity, and key messaging\nAssist with the planning and direction of voice recording sessions\nWorking with influencer marketing - Drafting briefs, ideas, and script-writing for any standard or out-of-the-box integrations with influencers.\nRequirements:\n\n\nEnglish - native speaker level, proficient in recent American slang & customs - required\nStrong portfolio or showreel - required\n2-4 years of experience in creative writing in advertising or marketing\nExcellent communication, interpersonal, and organizational skills\nHighly creative and imaginative, with a great understanding of current content trends\nStrong creative writing skills, excellent grammar, and spelling mandatory\nGood PC skills (Excel, Google Suite)\nAbility to multitask in a multicultural, fast-paced, deadline-driven environment.\nAble to demonstrate comprehensive historical and current knowledge of the video game industry for the console, social, and mobile markets - an advantage.\nInterest in gaming and the video game industry necessary - an advantage.\nStrong background in gaming, fantasy, sci-fi, comic book, and other game-relevant creative material - an advantage.','2020-07-08',703),(572,'Product Marketing Manager','Papaya Global is reinventing global payroll and workforce management. Our automated platform helps companies hire, onboard, manage, and pay employees in more than 100 countries.\n\nWe are looking for a qualified and experienced Product Marketing Manager to join our team. You will be responsible for developing effective marketing strategies and plans to communicate the features and benefits of our products to prospects and customers.\n\nOur ideal candidate is an experienced professional with demonstrable creative writing skills. As our Product Marketing manager, you should perform well under deadlines and be detail-oriented. If you are expert in product marketing for SaaS-based products and brand consistency, we would like to meet you.\n\nYou will\nBuild on product messaging that sets new products apart from others in the market to give them a unique selling point\nEnsure brand consistency in all our content\nWrite, edit, proofread and publish creative content, turning words into inspiration\nCreate content such as case studies, videos, website copy and blog posts\nStay up-to-date with developments and generate new ideas to draw audience\'s attention\nHandle market research on current trending products\nPlan and participate in the launch of new services and products which involve several different departments\nObtain insights into customers\' usage of current products, buyer personas, through interviews, surveys, and sales data\nRequirements:\n3 or more years or proven work experience as a Product Marketing manager in a technological company\nExciting writing skills in English (native speakers only!)\nAttention to detail\nHands on experience with MS Office and WordPress\nKnowledge of SEO and web traffic metrics\nFamiliarity with social media\nGood organizational and time-management skills\nBSc Degree in Computer Science, Marketing or related field.','2020-07-13',704),(573,'Enterprise Solution Marketing Manager','monday.com is looking for an Enterprise Product Marketing who will develop a deep understanding of our competitive landscape, and bring this knowledge to our sales, marketing and product teams to help shape our go-to-market and sales execution. This is an amazing opportunity to join one of Israel\'s fastest growing startups and make a significant business impact. Youll join our Consulting Team based in our headquarters in Tel Aviv, Israel.\n\n\nRequirements:\n2+ years of B2B product/solution marketing experience in enterprise software companies\nProven outstanding abilities to translate customer needs and market demand into sharp and compelling messaging, content, sales tools, and campaigns to help us meet our business goals\nTrack record of identifying and seizing growth opportunities through integrated marketing campaigns\nPassionate about driving impact through measurable results throughout the sales cycle.\nEnglish - mother tongue\nVery strong communication skills verbal and writing\nPassionate, self-starter with a can-do attitude\nTeam player who can build strong relationships with peers and stakeholders across sales, marketing, product, CS, and more\nBachelors degree in marketing, business, or technology\n\n\nAbout The Role:\nPlay a key role in defining and executing monday.com GTM strategy to enterprise clients.\nConduct customer, market and competitive research to shape messaging, lead generation campaigns, and sales activities; as well as identify opportunities for growth.\nCreate sales kits for different buyers and verticals - to enable and accelerate the enterprise sales cycle to new and existing accounts: solution sales decks, solution overview, success stories, competitive positioning, and objection handling tactics, demo.\nWork with Content writers to deliver high-quality sales enablement content\nInitiate lead gen and other marketing programs and projects to support monday.com objectives\nProvide input from the market and customer base back to the product team.\n\n\nOur Team:\nThe consulting team is goal-oriented, customer-centric and comfortable dealing with big numbers. With our end-to-end consultative approach, we gain a deep understanding of our customers\' pains and processes to create a tailored solution to derive maximum value from monday.com. We are quick thinkers, initiative-takers, not afraid to go the extra mile.','2020-07-26',367),(574,'Digital Marketing Manager','For a startup developing technologies for the automotive industry, with offices in the center דרישות: Former experience working in a dynamic start-up company * At least 3 years experience in a creating content for technical B2B companies * Former experience in writing articles, blogs, case studies, whitepapers, polls, eBooks, social media posts/tweets, videos, etc * Former experience creating online campaigns- SEO , retargeting/remarketing campaigns etc. * Structured and well organized * creative able to think \"out of the box\" * English as a Mother tough','2020-07-26',24),(575,'Digital Marketing Consultant','SimilarWeb is the pioneer of market intelligence and the standard for understanding the digital world. SimilarWeb provides granular insights about any website or app across all industries in every region enabling the world\'s biggest brands like Airbnb, Walmart, HSBC, eBay and adidas to create the strategies necessary to win market share. The company has raised over $112M and has nearly 400 employees across eight global offices. SimilarWeb has been named one of Inc.com 15 Israeli Startups to Watch in 2017 and one of Business Insider\'s Top 50 Enterprise Startups to Bet Your Career On.\n\nBut if we want to continue helping the world\'s biggest brands reimagine what is possible online, we need talented and driven individuals who are looking for the chance to make a real and tangible impact. Does this sound like you?\n\nAs a Digital Marketing Consultant at SimilarWeb you will:\nYou\'ll have the opportunity to directly advise the biggest companies around the world on their digital strategy.\nYou\'ll collaborate with multiple departments at SimilarWeb to help turn SimilarWeb\'s data into actionable insights for our key customers.\nKey responsibilities include:\nOwning the value-based cycle of the sales process.\nSpeaking to customers to understand pain-points and qualify need\nAnalyzing data and turning into presentations\nPresenting deck as well as live product demos\nSupporting the Account Executive in the sales process by generating insights and helping with the value-side of the proposal\nContributing to global strategy\nRunning initiatives (like trials, outreach programs etc) in your market\nUpon success, can be rolled out across Solution Engineering globally\nSupporting salesenablement by sharing learnings on key industries/use-cases with Account Executives\nWhat will I bring to the team?\n2+ digital marketing experience (client or agency) – turning marketing data into insights\nAnalytical mindset with the ability to quickly digest a problem and identify a solution\nStrong communication skills\nWhy choose SimilarWeb?\n\nWe believe that building a great product and a great company starts with finding amazing people and helping them grow and develop professionally and personally. At SimilarWeb, you\'ll be surrounded by the most talented professionals and you\'ll work across departments gaining skills and driving impact.\n\nWhy choose SimilarWeb?\nData Driven: We believe data driven decisions are the key to success and we are evangelists for the power of digital insights\nPassionate: We care deeply about what we do, are accountable for our actions and are committed to helping each other\nExcellence: It\'s in our nature; and we work hard to make a difference\nWinning Together: We know what it takes to build a great company and a great product and it begins with valuing each and every member of our team','2020-07-23',707),(576,'Digital marketing manager','ironSource Marketing are looking for a superstar to build the foundation for a strong growth team serving a massive 800 person company with multiple businesses and products. If you\'ve worked in digital marketing for 3-4 years and are hungry for a massive challenge with a lot of room for growth, this role is for you.\nYou will have the opportunity to play a leading role in building ironSources digital marketing and media buying strategy from the ground up, focused on acquiring and converting leads and engaging existing customers across the globe.\nDay to day, you will be working with the business, marketing and design teams to ensure that ironSources PPC, media buying & ad campaigns are aligned around a clear vision and strategy, and delivering on KPIs and goals.\nIf you have hands on experience of creating, implementing and managing digital marketing campaigns that promote products and services in creative ways and drive business impact - we want to hear from you.\n\n\nRequirements:\n3-4 years experience in B2B digital marketing\nExperience running and optimizing campaigns across different marketing channels, including social, search, display, video, and content recommendation\nStrong proficiency in data analysis and familiarity with diverse analytics and marketing software platforms (Google Analytics, Mixpanel, Mailchimp, Salesforce)\nKeen attention to detail, and critical thinking skills\nStrong organizational and multitasking abilities\nBA/BSC in marketing or advertising a plus\nPrevious experience working in the mobile game or app industry a huge plus\n\n\nRole:\nWork with leadership to craft a cross-platform media strategy to support business goals across divisions and internal stakeholders\nCollaborate with the marketing, design and product teams to create compelling ads, landing pages, and user flows\nSet up, manage and optimize multiple campaigns, including customer acquisition, lead generation, content marketing, brand awareness\nReport on campaign performance regularly to company stakeholders\nAchieve positive ROI, prove impact, and scale digital marketing activities in the company\n\n\nBusiness Unit:\nMarketing\n\nSkills:\nPPC,Google Analytics,optimizing campaigns','2020-07-15',17),(577,'Growth Marketing Manager','This position is under local marketing, working independently in your local location with directions from the Global Marketing Operation Team.\nApplicant needs to have the proven track record of successful local experience.\n\nIn very little time, Binance has become the no. 1 global crypto-currency exchange in the world.\nAre you looking to be a part of one of the most influential companies in the blockchain industry and contribute to the crypto-currency revolution that is changing the world?\n\nAs a Growth Marketing Manager, you’ll drive the way we connect with potential users to grow Binance’s active user base. Leveraging your growth marketing skills (including paid advertising and experimentation), you’ll create programs and find repeatable channels that reach and activate new users.\n\nAs the right person for the job, you’ll care deeply about how to leverage media to reach new audiences and build an enduring brand, be creative about the deployment of marketing messages, and be rigorous about learning from the data you collect and the experiential campaigns you run.\n