eeves to get things done (even the unglamorous things)\nCuriosity: Desire to know everything about our members journeys\nFlexibility: Problem-solve in a fast-paced, self-driven environment\n\n#HiringNow , #GetHired , #Hiring , #startupjobs\n#roundforest , #shoppingmadeeasy , #lifeatroundforest , #startupnation','2020-07-26',723),(586,'Technical Marketing Content Manager','THE TEAM\nAquas global team of analytical and creative product marketers are on a mission to drive our products forward. They are a unique group of storytellers, writers and designers who arm our teams with compelling market data, messaging and images. Evident through our many product awards, Aquas high performing Product Marketing team excels at connecting our products to our customers. They are the champion voice of Aqua. Are you ready to be heard?\n\nTHE Opportunity\nThe ideal technical marketing content manager is a native English speaker with experience in blogging, community marketing, and producing technical marketing content such as whitepapers, solution briefs and infographics, and a passion for thought leadership and marketing engagement through storytelling.\nWere offering a unique opportunity to join a hyper-growth startup in a hot space, that both educates the market and evangelizes best practices and technology leadership.\nThis position is not intended for marketing copywriters that lack technical experience in enterprise software.\nResponsibilities\nWork closely with the product marketing and online marketing teams to create meaningful content, that tells the story of the our leading technology.\nManage the content calendar and align assets with company product releases, thought leadership themes, and marketing campaigns.\nPlay a central role in the companys content creation with a focus on writing insightful blog posts, customer stories, white papers, and web contents.\nDevelop outlines, briefs and ideas into effective, well-researched and articulate content pieces, aligned with th