gether:We know what it takes to build a great company and a great product and it begins with valuing each and every member of our team and working together to reach new heights.','2020-07-13',707),(591,'Head of Product Marketing','Spot\'s Head of Product Marketing is an experienced marketer with a strong grasp of messaging, positioning and storytelling as well as a proven manager capable of guiding and developing a growing team.\nIn this role you will have the opportunity to make a highly visible impact on the success of Spot, being a key player in shaping Spots message to the market and how that message is delivered in a way that helps Spot to stand out and capture business. The Head of Product Marketing is responsible for guiding product, solution, technical and competitive marketing activities at Spot, will interact with and be highly visible to key executives across the company.\nMain responsibilities:\nIdentifying and assigning projects that will help their part of the marketing team support the goals and priorities of the marketing team and company\nPrioritizing competing projects and demands for their part of the marketing team\nAssisting and providing feedback to their team to create compelling messaging, positioning and content\nMentoring and developing a strong product, solution, technical and competitive marketing team\nIdentify and address key bottlenecks and obstacles within their team and in their teams work with other parts of the marketing team and company\nHelping to coordinate content plans, announcements and launches with key stakeholders across the company\nEnsure smooth communication and cooperation within the marketing team\n\n\nRequirements:\nBasic Qualifications:\n5+ years of relevant marketing experience, ideally in product, solution or technical marketing\nStrong understanding of messaging, positioning and storytelling in the context of technology-driven products\nProven success in managing a team of individual contributors\nHighly organized with an ability to manage resources, budgets, and personnel\nStrong communication skills, written and oral\nHighly organized and skilled at balancing and prioritizing multiple projects simultaneously\nBachelors degree in marketing or a relevant technical discipline (e.g. computer science, engineering, etc.)\n\nPreferred Qualifications:\nExperience marketing cloud and software-as-a-service (SaaS) products to enterprise companies\nProven success in a technology startup\nUnderstanding of content marketing best practices','2020-07-07',729),(592,'Marketing Operations & Automation Specialist','Cato Networks is the provider of the worlds first SASE platform. If you dont know what SASE (Secure Access Service Edge) is, Google it now. What we envisioned already 5 years ago is now being formally endorsed by Gartner as the future of network and security.\n\nWe are looking for a Marketing Operations & Automation Specialist to join our growing Marketing team!\nThe Marketing Operations & Automation Specialist will own the management and optimization of Catos marketing technology stack to enable the marketing organisation to meet demand generation goals.\n\nThis is your opportunity to get on the rocket ship, and join a company that is building a cutting-edge enterprise network and security cloud platform, and is on a fast track to become the worldwide market leader dont miss it!\n\nKey Responsibilities:\nSelect, test, and deploy new marketing technologies\nIntegrate the marketing technologies with critical sales and finance platforms\nEnsure the marketing platform is optimized to support corporate and channel marketing initiatives.\nIdentify areas of improvement, opportunities to achieve better scale and cost-efficiency.\nProduce reports/dashboards to monitor and support ongoing processes\n\n\nRequirements:\n4+ years working in a marketing organization with ownership of Marketing Automation/Technology stack\nDeep expertise in Marketo or HubSpot and its integration with Salesforce\nExperience in integrating external data feeds into marketing workflows and processes\nClear understanding of Marketing funnels and sales lifecycle\nExperience in a SAAS company\nCreative and strong initiative. Can bring new ideas and to systems and processes\nExcellent verbal and written communications in English\nTeam player, fast learner\nUnrelenting attention to details while seeing the big picture','2020-07-05',730),(593,'Web Marketing Manager','The Opportunity\n\nWere looking for a seasoned Web Marketing Manager to own the operations for Imperva web properties. In this position, you will work closely with designers, developers, and product teams to create immersive online experiences and ensure that the Imperva websites are best-in-class.\n\nAs our Web Project Manager, you will play a key role in the creative and operational aspects of large strategic web initiatives, as well as being able to own the day-to-day management of imperva.com content and architecture. You will drive forward cross-functional initiatives, and work with key stakeholders to manage and own projects from inception to completion.\n\nIn this position, you will work as part of Imperva Digital Marketing team, located in Rehovot, Israel, and reporting to Director of Digital Marketing.\n\nResponsibilities\n\n· Manage day to day operations across all Imperva web properties\n\n· Craft engaging user experience for effective and unobstructed user journeys through the web\n\n· Gather requirements, scope, timeline, manage, document and lead web projects\n\n· Prioritize and assign tickets for web development using JIRA\n\n· Work with IT and web developer to translate business requirements to technical requirements\n\n· Support the localization process for global websites and landing pages\n\n· Coordinate with designers, developers and project stakeholders for the implementation of bug fixes, improvements and new features for our website\n\n· Work with program management to define cross-functional requirements, to develop and maintain efficient processes\n\n· Manage project lifecycle from project intake and prioritization process to requirements definition, resource planning, project timelines, and implementation\n\n· Be a liaison between business and web development teams; perform user acceptance testing and drive approval processes\n\n· Manage reporting for the website and present to marketing teams\n\n· Hands-on inputting of assets into the CMS, in addition to being instrumental in influencing CMS enhancements and the overall CMS functionality roadmap\n\nQualifications\n\n· 3+ years of web operations experience, preferably in the B2B software industry\n\n· Track record of managing content and functionality projects on large-scale websites\n\n· Excellent organizational skills and great attention to detail\n\n· Self-starter with excellent project management skills; ability to manage multiple projects\n\n· Marketing background with basic knowledge of SEO\n\n· Strong communicational skills - strong English skills are a must\n\n· Experience with analytics tools like Google Analytics is a plus\n\n· Experience in tracking projects in an agile development environment - JIRA is a plus\n\n· Experience with content management - HTML/CSS/JS is a plus\n\n· Technical/CyberSec background is a plus\n\n· Familiarity with Marketo and Salesforce is a plus\n\nAbout Imperva\n\nImperva is an analyst-recognized, cybersecurity leaderchampioning the fight to secure data and applications wherever they reside. Once deployed, our solutions proactively identify, evaluate, and eliminate current and emerging threats, so you never have to choose between innovating for your customers and protecting what matters most. ImpervaProtect the pulse of your business.\n\n#LI-HW1','2020-07-22',731),(594,'Growth Marketing Manager','About this position\nResponsible for both scaling current channels and generating new opportunities. Balance efforts of analytical, creative and optimization skills to execute, analyze impactful campaigns and develop new avenues for acquiring customers effectively. This role requires a mix of campaign management skills and operational excellence.\nDuties & Responsibilities\nHands-on management of paid customer acquisition efforts, including (but not limited to) SEM, Social, email, paid content syndication and paid media partnerships\nIdentify opportunities for innovation and experimentation; test creative strategies while rigorously supporting assumptions with data\nMeasure and analyze campaign effectiveness and present ongoing reporting. Apply insights to improve results as aligned to business objectives\nExecuting an SEO strategy, improving relevant KPIs such as domain authority and average position\nPresenting weekly reports analyzing performance, optimization and action items\nRequirements\n1-3 years of performance-driven digital marketing experience, with proven direct-to-consumer success\nVery strong analytical skills allowing measuring results and applying insights from data\nBachelor\'s degree in economics, sciences, marketing communications or related\nEntrepreneurial approach; self-motivated and innovative, with a high degree of personal ownership\nGood learning abilities and desire to learn and own new responsibilities as required in a growing startup\nGoogle Ads/Facebook Ads Manager – at least one is a must\nHigh level of proficiency in Excel - a must\nSEO knowledge - an advantage\nAffiliate marketing - an advantage\nEmail marketing - an advantage\nSQL knowledge - an advantage','2020-07-20',735),(595,'Marketing Manager','Market Group is an international group of companies with portfolios in the ad-tech as well as e-commerce spaces. We have offices in Cyprus, Athens, Tel Aviv and Berlin.\n\nWe are a global network of brands combining innovative eCommerce platforms with unique programmatic native ad exchange & mediation solution for publishers across the most relevant demand sources. We are always looking for great talents. And we would like to meet smart, open-minded, technically-advanced and team-oriented people.\n\nReady for your next adventure? Join us as Marketing Manager in our Tel Aviv office.\n\nIdeal candidates for the position have hands-on experience with web analytics tools and be able to turn creative ideas into effective advertising projects. They will also be excited about working in a fast-paced startup environment.\n\nJob Description:\nLooking for an ambitious and experienced marketing professional to proactively lead our engagement and retention marketing strategies.\nTaking an active hands-on role in the strategy and deployment of a wide scope of projects across the group’s various activity divisions & products.\nConducting market research, analyzing business reports and interpreting data into practical insights and client strategies.\nCollaboratively develop and execute effective marketing materials focused on attracting new strategic business collaborations or developing relationship with existing clients.\nJob Requirements:\n2+ years of digital marketing experience\nBachelor’s degree in Business, Marketing, or related field- an advantage\nKnowledge of market research practices and techniques- experience identifying content necessary to support effective digital marketing presence\nExperience in consumer segmentation and targeted, personalized marketing, leveraging digital technologies\nEstablished experience with commercial content writing or basic visual design- a big advantage\nKnowledgeable on principles, practices and techniques of marketing strategies & social media platforms\nCreative individual with strong interpersonal and communication skills, able to influence across organizations, and build strong internal and external partnerships\nExcellent project management and problem-solving skills\nFluent English, verbal & written (Mandatory)+ any additional languages other than Hebrew -an advantage\nStrong operational and time-management skills- ability to break 