ytical tools.\nYou’ve done this before. This is NOT a junior position. 2+ years of Product Management/User Acquisition experience.\nPast experience go-to-market strategy, analyse users behaviour and funnels.\n“Can-do” and hands-on mentality and a drive for continuous improvement.\nExceptional marketing and analytical knowledge and skills.\nExperience with B2B- an advantage.\nExcellent communication skills.','2020-07-26',737),(597,'Marketing Automation Specialist','eToro, the worlds leading social online trading platform, is a revolutionary Fintech company that has been at the forefront of online trading for more than a decade.\nWhat will you be doing?\nJoin the Marketing Automation Team as a Marketing Automation Specialist. We are looking for a team player to create, manage and optimize multi-channel marketing campaigns with an eye for attention to small details.\nThe role requires a combination of technical and analytical skills, and a creative mind. The candidate will be in charge of creating concepts for campaigns (both marketing and operational), technically executing, analysing, optimizing and reporting on them.\nAn Integral part of the campaign creation process will require handling HTML code and SQL queries, so we are looking for someone who is not afraid to mess around with code.\nOur mission is to deliver the optimal message to specific clients and do so by monitoring each message within the following steps: content, design, development, localization and delivery. The candidate will be in charge of the entire process and is required to perform daily work with requesters from the organization.\nWe are looking for a doer, someone who can handle multiple tasks at a time, has the ability to manage their time efficiently, someone who can make things happen.\nManage multi language campaigns high-level of English, knowledge of other languages can be an advantage.\nFind ideas and solutions for automating, optimizing and improving internal processes, by routine analysis and supplying actionable items.\n\n\n\nRequirements:\nB.A, B.S or B.S.c\nHighly proficient in spoken and written English\nTechnical approach - A must\nExperienced with a Marketing Automation Platform, such as SalesForce Marketing Cloud / Eloqua / Pardot / Marketo / Hubspot - A must\nExceptional team player - the role requires cooperation with your team members and other departments and roles in eToro on a daily basis\nCreative marketing orientation\nAttention to details\nBasic knowledge in Excel. - A must\nBasic knowledge in SQL - A must\nBasic knowledge in HTML - A must\nAnalytical skills\nFinancial background - An advantage\nOur working days are Monday - Friday, alongside the international financial markets','2020-07-28',339),(598,'Cyber Product Marketing Manager','We are looking for an experienced Product Marketing Manager to join our team.\nThe ideal candidate is an experienced professional with demonstrable creative writing skills and market intelligence. Must be a native English speaker all the content is generated in English. Experience in cyber security or IAM is a must.\n\n\nRequirements:\n5+ years of product marketing experience with at least 2 years of experience in a cyber security company\nMust be a solid writer, have strong public speaker, comfortable in front of large, senior groups.\nExcellent people and management skills to interact with staff, colleagues, cross-functional teams and third parties. A true team player!\nFamiliar with marketing and CRM tools such as Hubspot, Google Analytics and Salesforce.\nPower user of networking tools such as LinkedIn, Twitter and Facebook.\nNative English level both spoken and written, a must\nBachelors degree in business or marketing; MBA preferred.\n\n\nResponsibilities:\nPlan and produce content on solution capabilities, including blogs, briefs, whitepapers, videos, etc.\nMarket intelligencebe the expert on our buyers, who are they, how they buy and their key buying criteria.\nUnderstand the competitive landscapebe an expert on our competition and how they are positioned.\nCollaborate with product management to develop product positioning and messaging that resonate with our target buyer personas.\nDevelop a marketing plan, including key activities and budgets to support the retention of existing customers and the acquisition of new customers.\nAssess the effectiveness of the marketing programs on an ongoing basis\nAct as the primary thought leader, including speaking engagements and written content.\nUnderstand and support our sales channels; train them on the problems we solve for our buyers and users; develop internal tools and external collateral and teach them how and when to use it.','2020-07-13',741),(599,'Product Manager - Visual Marketing','As a Product Manager leading our Visual Marketing product line, you will be responsible for successfully leading the product strategy, roadmap and execution - shipping products to market that create superior value to our customers. You will be working extensively with our customers, Client Success Managers, Product Marketing, R&D, Design & Sales.\n\nOur visual platform owns all of Yotpo\'s video & image assets. The product focuses on enabling our marketers to curate, manage and display visual content, aimed at increasing brand authenticity, engagement and conversions. This product line is also responsible for Yotpo Ads, a tool which allows original, verified customer reviews, images and videos, to immediately be made into optimised Facebook Ads. Marketers can target specific audiences in just one click, based on Yotpo\'s use of existing Facebook data.\n\nOur ideal candidate is a true leader, that is able to define what success looks like, get all stakeholders excited & aligned, and ship products that are consistent with our customers\' needs. We are looking for someone with passion for technology, innovation and e-commerce.\n\nResponsibilities:\nSetting & communicating the vision and true north of the VMS product-line\nEnsuring your products fits in with the overall company and product strategy\nWorking closely with multiple stakeholders and executives in the company, being the focal point for all decisions around your product\nBeing a major force in helping defining & driving the VMS product-line revenues, win rates & customer retention\nDeveloping a strong understanding of the market, competition, customers and the business\nLeading cross-departmental initiatives related to your product line\nCollaborating closely with R&D and Design during scoping and product development\nCreating and managing KPIs, roadmaps, project plans and product specifications\nBuilding product prototypes and mock-ups, prioritizing and creating detailed product specifications, business rules, flows, use cases, and user stories\nWorking closely with BI, monitoring and turning \"numbers\" into actions\nLeading customer interviews, usability tests and Betas\nRequirements:\nAt least 3-4 years of product management experience\nExperience working in B2B2C / SaaS / ecommerce marketing - an advantage\nStrong command of all aspects of the product development lifecycle\nStrong UX/UI abilities with proven experience in shipping UX oriented products\nPassion for combining technology and design to create excellent user experience\nHighly analytical background and proven attention to detail\nExceptional communication skills and proficiency in English\nAbility to travel to our NY offices at least once a quarter','2020-07-23',742),(600,'Inbound Marketing Manager','Marketing Envy is looking for a new Inbound Marketing Manager\n\nOk, what we’re really looking for is someone with the writing style of Hemingway combined with the social media acumen of a Kardashian. But I’ve been told that’s “not realistic” and I should “stop wasting time”.\n\nSo let’s try again.\n\nWe’re looking for Inbound marketers who can not only write well, but can answer questions like:\n\nWhat kind of content should my company be producing?\n\nWhy isn’t