ator, you will also demonstrate excellent interpersonal and analytical skills.\n\nResponsibilities:\nDesign and manage all aspects of our digital marketing including our marketing database, email, and display advertising campaigns.\nPlan, setup, run and monitor paid campaigns (PPC)\nPlan and manage our paid social media programmes.\nPrepare accurate reports on our marketing campaign’s overall performance.\nCoordinate with advertising and media experts to improve marketing results.\nEvaluate important metrics that affect our website traffic and target audiences.\nWork with the broader marketing team to brainstorm new and innovative growth strategies.\nOwn and manage all digital projects.\n\nRequirements:\nBachelor’s degree in Marketing or relevant field.\nA minimum of 5 years’ experience in a digital marketing or advertising position.\nProven hands-on experience with marketing automation platforms (Marketo preferably)\nGood knowledge of content management systems (Drupal preferably)\nIn-depth knowledge of various social media platforms, best practices, and website analytics.\nSolid knowledge of HTML, CSS, and JavaScript is required.\nHighly creative with excellent analytical abilities and high attention to detail.\nOutstanding communication and interpersonal skills.\nUp-to-date on the latest trends and technologies in digital marketing.\nProficiency in English (spoken and written) is a must.','2020-07-08',747),(603,'Performance Marketing Lead','In the past 4 years, we have built a world-class marketing practice that\nis at the forefront of data-informed strategy, creative quality, and optimization and scale across a broad variety of channels here in PLAYSTUDIOS Israel.\nWe are looking for Marketing Lead to own App Level User Acquisition & Re-Engagement efforts.\nThis is a strategic role for the business and the potential leader will play a critical role in our future growth of the company and our marketing organization. As a top 30 mobile game developers worldwide, our UA operation is scaled both in talent, technology, and marketing spend and we\'re looking for best in class leaders to join our business.\n\nWe need someone with sharp business instincts, a great creative mind, who loves data and has a passion for running an operation at scale. If you got all of the above and you are a team player, fun to work with and amazing in general. Dont be shy and apply!\nWHAT WILL YOU BE DOING?\nDesign and lead implementation of growth strategy by using paid and owned media channels to grow new user acquisition, activation, engagement, and retention in a scalable and efficient way.\nBuild and allocate the app marketing budget across different channels based on performance and the app business goals.\nLead rapid experimentation of new channels, campaigns, creative, incentives, and approaches for the purpose of building scalable solutions to push the app DAU & revenue up!\nManaging key projects focused on optimising marketing campaigns with technical stakeholders, such as Data Scientist, to design and implement automated workflows that will improve work efficiency and effectiveness.\nBuilding and maintaining strategic relationships with key acquisition partners (getting them to do whats right for us!).\nManage and lead relationships with external partners such as ASO agency, including setting goals and objectives, approving a/b tests, and supervising ongoing activities.\nHold team members accountable for recouping goal achievements, KPIs, and engagement in all marketing activities.\n\n\n\nRequirements:\n\n1+ years as a marketing lead or head of marketing of a product/service or application with a significant budget ($500K+ monthly).\n5+ years in mobile user acquisition and ad buying analysis experience at scale.\nStrong marketing instincts and proven track record of shaping and executing on user growth strategies.\nHands-on experience in campaign management on self-served platforms (such as FB, Google, DSP & Ad Networks).\nObsessed with optimization - you live and breathe campaign performance data and know exactly what levers to pull when optimizing a campaign against specific KPIs.\nStrength in communicating, visualizing, and reporting results/analysis so they are clear and unambiguous to various stakeholders, including game partners and senior leadership. This will include building reports and presenting the results of your/ your teams efforts using tools such as PowerPoint and Tableau.\nDeep understanding of mobile attribution models and platforms.\nStrong proficiency in Excel, with a desire to develop additional technical skills (SQL, Tableau).\nAbility to lead complex operational and strategic change initiatives managing a wide set of stakeholders including data & creatives teams.\nAbility to lead and inspire a highly skilled team across multiple locations\nAbility to negotiate and effectively influence internal and external parties\nPassion for games and a strong understanding of the industry.\nStrong business logic thinker who quickly identifies new opportunities to challenge the status quo.\nFluent in English.\nYOU GET BONUS POINTS FOR ;)\nExperience working with SQL\nBA/BSc, preferably in a quantitative field.','2020-07-27',749),(604,'Marketing Lead','�� Super creative marketers - this is a great opportunity to build a growing company\'s marketing capabilities ��\n\nJoin The Builders - a unique innovation platform. Partnering with huge multinationals brands like Coca-Cola, WarnerMedia, Mercedes-Benz & Walmart, The Builders operate several proprietary programs that increase the “conversion rate” of innovations into adopted corporate practice.\n\nWe are currently extending our local core team, and looking for a Marketing Lead to staff a brand new role that they will be able to build from scratch. We are looking for a passionate jack of all trades that will be able to work across many different channels and skill areas, from advertising and events to email marketing and analytics, from strategy 