neer. You will be required to design and build a scalable analytical system, collect and process high volumes of data, implement ETL and automation processes, deliver end-to-end solution to make information accessible, reliable and actionable. Main Responsibilities: · Deliver end-to-end solutions · Define data requirements and System architecture · Design data models · Build smart ETL and automation processes · Implement business logic into the data processes · Performance tuning Position Requirements: · Experience in design and implementation of data warehouse and BI solutions using high standard methodologies · Hands on experience working with Analytical DBs (Redshift, Vertica, Snowflake) · Experience with BIG DATA technologies such as Hadoop, Amazon EMR, Presto, Spark · Expertise with at least one programming language - Python, Java or Scala · Expert in SQL · Autodidact, with strong technical skills · Business understanding · Great team player with excellent communication skills · High level of English proficiency Come join the BI elite forces!','2020-07-28',816),(666,'Data Architect','As a global, multi-national company, we would like to ask that you please submit your resume in English.\n\nHave we got a job for you?!\n\nData Architect , Petach Tikva\n\nBuild Your Career | Have Fun | Make a Difference\n\nPayoneer systems are composed of multiple WEB applications, relying on a strong backbone of payment processing and fraud, risk and cyber prevention – all operated in high-complexity and high scale. Payoneer\'s technology division (R&D, IT, Data, Architecture) is composed of over 20 teams. Development starts with .NET WEB environment (C#, SQL-Server, IIS, TFS), and incorporates technologies as React for UI, NoSQL (Hadoop on Cloudera stacks) and both Azure and AWS cloud toolsets. Each development team is operating in SCRUM methodology. Data and AI teams work with the latest BigData toolsets (mostly in JAVA/SCALA and python).\n\nPayoneer is expanding its R&D and is