th Python.\nExperience with data modeling.\nBSc in Computer Science (or equivalent) – preferred higher educational background\nNot a must but a great advantage\nExperience in ETL and Data Lakes\nExperience with Micro-services\nExperience with CI/CD , testing-automation\nExperience in Scala / R / Tabular cubes.\nExperience with Client frameworks (React is preferred) and client development toolset (CSS/JQuery/JavaScript and AJAX)\nExperience with real time analytics.\nCheck us out!\nEver wondered whether that perfect combination really exists? You know, the job we always dream where we develop professionally and enjoy a fun workplace surrounded by passionate people, at a company that is really changing the world?Payoneer empowers entrepreneurs and businesses anywhere in the world – from Cairo to California, Buenos Aires to Bangalore and Tel Aviv to Tokyo – to expand beyond their borders and grow successful, sustainable businesses. With millions of customers in over 200 countries worldwide, Payoneer connects anyone, regardless of their location or socio-economic background, with opportunities to trade globally. Our Values','2020-07-13',321),(667,'Cloud & Data Engineer','Arpeely is an Ad-tech startup building and operating Machine Learning algorithms for autonomous media acquisition. Our business and tech meet at the intersection of the exciting fields of Digital Marketing, Fraud Detection and ML\\AI.\nConnected to the world\'s largest Real-Time-Bidding Ad-exchange - Google AdX, we use data, ML, engineering, and hacker-like thinking to short-circuit and out-preform the market.\n\nBootstrapped in 2017 with a small team of ex-IDF elites, Arpeely has reached MM$ revenues in its first year of operation and is now in its next period of growth.\n\nWe are looking for a passionate Cloud & Data Engineer to join our small all-star team. As part of your role, you will design, implement and deploy products and infrastructures which will directly amplify our core business and enable