ecisions by understanding why things happen across the digital ecosystem. Learn more at WWW.SIMILARWEB.COM.\n\nThe company has raised over $112M and has over 500 employees across ten global offices.\n\nSimilarWeb has been named one of CALCALIST\'S TOP 50 STARTUPS 2019 and one of the 10 MOST DESIRABLE ISRAELI COMPANIES TO WORK FOR. Similarweb is also ranked 8th in DUN\'S BEST HIGH TECH COMPANIES TO WORK FOR IN ISRAEL in 2018, taking over companies such as Amazon, Mobileye, PayPal, eBay and more.\n\nWe Want You!\n\nWe are looking for a talented and dedicated analyst with research/business mindsets to join our Data Solutions team as an Analyst. As part of this role you will help us scale and stabilize our new rocketing Digital Insights (DI) reporting products at SimilarWeb.\n\nAs a Data Analyst at SimilarWeb you will:\nResearch: Using SimilarWeb\'s data and tools, explore companies and websites to identify site structures and user journeys to allow scalable reporting on user behavior and engagement.\nAnalyze: Understand how to leverage SimilarWeb data in order to answer the client\'s business custom questions.\nConsult: Be a direct conduit between the Data Solutions team, GTM teams and enterprise customers , serving as the technical expert of everything our team does externally.\nAutomate & Maintain: Reporting automation and infrastructure python scripting and maintaining team documentation to minimize report code rewrites.\nWhat will I bring to the team?\nAt least 2-3 years experience with SQL/HiveQL data analysis - Must\nAt least 1-2 year experience in Python scripting - Must\nExcellent verbal and communication skills (in English) - Must\nHadoop/Spark/AWS/EMR s3 Infrastructure experience - Big Advantage\nProficiency in Online Marketing/Online Services- Advantage\nAt least 1 year work experience in Online/Tech Company - Advantage\nTeam player, autodidact, fast learner with excellent analytical/research/business skills.\nWhy choose SimilarWeb?\n\nWe believe that buildi