rity, cost, performance, reliability and operational efficiency to accelerate key projects for our customers.\nInside AWS, you are an ambassador of our customers. You will articulate customer needs by synthesizing your observations from customer engagements and market trends around Analytics workloads to inform the roadmap of AWS features.\nIn this role, your creativity will link technology to tangible solutions, with the opportunity to define and implement cloud-native reference architectures for a variety of use cases.\nSpecialist Solutions Architects are thought leaders in AWS technology and industry trends in the Analytics space who create and share best practices through white papers, code samples, workshops, user groups and blog posts.\nIf you are enthusiastic about enabling AWS customers on the art of the possible, while challenging the impossible, come and build the future with us.\n\n\nBasic Qualifications\n\n· Background in any of the following: Data Warehousing, Big Data, Hadoop ecosystems, Business Intelligence, Streaming applications, Data Lakes, Data Migration or or large scale operational Analytics\n· Experience designing, building, refactoring or operating Analytics - either on premises or in the cloud\n· Knowledge of some relevant languages, tools and frameworks (e.g python, Java, R, scala, spark, Kafka, Hadoop ecosystem, presto, Hive,Teradata, Elasticsearch and SAS Analytics amongst others)\n· Experience engaging successfully with internal or external stakeholders delivering solutions to help businesses succeed\n· Fluent in Hebrew and English\n\nPreferred Qualifications\n\n· One or more of the following qualifications are desired but not required:\n· In-depth working knowledge in a technology domain such as distributed internet-scale web applications, DevOps, Serverless, Machine Learning, high-performance databases (SQL and/or NoSQL), Master Data Management (MDM), Data Governance, Change Data Capture (CDC), highly secured workloads etc.\n· Experience working in a customer-facing role, creating technical content or delivering enablement sessions\n· Experience with cloud technologies including relevant industry certifications (e.g. AWS Solutions Architect Associate or Professional)\n· Experience with migrating workloads between data centres or from on-prem to cloud\n· Technical degree (Maths, Science, Engineering, Computer Science, Information Technology or similar)','2020-07-13',115),(681,'Data Engineer','monday.com is looking for Data Engineer who lives for data and who can design, implement & scale Data/BI solutions E2E and design data models. Youll join our R&D Team based in our headquarters, Tel Aviv, Israel.\n\n\nRequirements:\n2+ years of experience as a former Data Engineer, including all the aspects of the profession.\n2+ years of programming experience. Python - advantage.\nFamiliar with data science concepts and solutions.\nExperience in operating data processing systems.\nExperience in designing and operating data pipeline solutions for a high volume data flow.\nYou speak SQL fluently and can optimize queries for performance.\nCollaborated with data analysts to design and adapt data models with alignment to business needs.\n\n\nAbout The Role:\nBe part of a growing team at the core of the companys operations affecting every department and helping monday.com outdo its best.\nResponsible for the BigBrain data infrastructure - Data Lake, Data Warehouse, Pipeline, BI and Visualization tools and Data Science infrastructure.\nOur Stack - React.JS, Redux, Node.js, Ruby on Rails, AWS, Elastic Search, Redis, MySQL.\n\n\nSocial Title:\nData Engineer\n\n\nSocial Description:\nmonday.com is looking for Data Engineer who lives for data and who can design, implement & scale Data/BI solutions E2E and design data models. Youll join our R&D Team based in our headquarters, Tel Aviv, Israel.\n\n\nOur Team:\nThe R&D Team is passionate about building innovative and lovable products, while tackling complex engineering problems at a great scale. Were accountable for bringing the companys vision to life by navigating our progress into flawless execution and encouraging full ownership and independence in all projects. The BigBrain Core team is at the base of the entire BigBrain operation, leading and driving the companys culture, responsible for BigBrains infrastructure, data infrastructure and exciting cross-company opportunities.','2020-07-22',367),(684,'Data Analyst','FGG is a startup entertainment company and games studio. We are looking for a Data Analyst to join our ambitious multinational team in making a gyaru-gemu card-collection game for the Japanese mobile market!\n\nAs a Data Analyst you will be working from within the Game Design team, making sure that our players get the best experience possible. If you have a passion for video games, manga/anime and you want to work in a friendly and international environment, please don’t hesitate – apply below now.\n\n【Responsibilities】\n\nAnalyze analytics data and interpret product and player data to determine observations and player trends.\nJoin the Game Design team to identify strategic business questions, key metrics and actionable insights.\nDefine requirements for data collection and data modeling for the Game Development team.\nEnsure that the implementation of metrics corresponds to the observed values.\nCollaborate with a Games Economist to balance and monitor our game economy.\nLead the Analytics in a fast growing startup company!\n\n【Requirements】\n\n2+ years of directly relevant experience, working with data of a digital product\nExperience using SQL for analysis and visualizing and validating results\nVery strong experience with Microsoft Excel\nStrong data analysis with proven capacity to run the right tests and iterate effectively\nAnalytical thinker who constantly questions states and values\nStrong communication skills, to clearly and concisely convey testing design, results and recommendations\nComfortable working 