sponsibilities:\nResearch different data assets, understand their value, distribution and quality (structures, semi structured and unstructured).\nOwn data quality - from detecting issues to fixing those which can be fixed automatically using scripts and other tools\nDevelop the internal logical data model, and co-write the code which populates the data model from raw data.\nBuild the training data sets on which our algorithm will train, based on a thorough understanding of the medical phenomenons in questions, as well as how algorithms learn from examples\nAnalyze the effectiveness of our algorithms, visualize their results, detect blind spots using statistical/heuristics.','2020-07-12',836),(687,'Data Tagging Specialist','Are looking for an opportunity to jumpstart your career in hightech? Do you see yourself as an energetic, curious and driven professional who wants to join a fast-growing, award-winning visual AI startup, Syte is looking for you. Syte is the leading AI-driven visual search and recommendation technology for retail.\n\nSyte is looking for a self-motivated, organized and detail orientated Tagging Specialist\n\nWhat you\'ll do:\nYou will be working on labelling, tagging and building data into large data systems to train the algorithm, responsible for the visual search tool.\nConstantly building new data into the system\nReview, classify and tag hundreds of wonderful images (fashion, accessories etc)\nExecute tasks in a timely manner and to a high degree of quality\n\nThis position is technical and requires close attention to detail.\n\nRequired skills:\nGood technical skills\nA methodical approach to tasks with attention to detail\nPatience and an eye for small details\nHigh level of English (reading, speaking and writing)\nPosses the ability and patience to stay focused on repetitive tasks for long periods of time without compromising on quality\nGood communication and interpersonal skills and the ability to work as part of a team\nStrong time management and load balancing skills\nAble to work with a sense of urgency and under pressure\nProblem-solving skills with the ability to think “out-of-the box”\n\nAbility to work independently.','2020-07-27',838),(688,'Data Researcher','Responsibilities:\n\nPayPals Global Data Sciences team is responsible for developing and enhancing machine learning and data mining capabilities, which are key in PayPals top-of-the-line data-driven decisions, especially in the risk and counter-fraud domains. Our researchers overcome challenges presented by big data, evolving fraud techniques and new payment technologies by leveraging domain expertise and creating sophisticated data-driven products which enable us to make the best possible decisions to protect Paypals customers.\n\nWe are looking for somebody with good understanding of data problems, great analytical skills and the capability to drive deliveries from an idea to production. The researcher will:\nLead the teams portfolio of data solutions, which are at the core of PayPals risk decisioning\nPerform the relevant analytical research, data mining and extracting information in PayPals Big Data environment to identify gaps and possible improvements in those solutions\nManage the product-related aspect of the portfolio - define, drive forward and coordinate the analytical and technical execution of new and existing data solutions\nCollaborate with all relevant stakeholders (software engineers, analytical customers, data scientists) to deliver state-of-the-art data products\nJob Requirements:\n\nWe know the confidence gap and imposter syndrome can get in the way of meeting spectacular candidates. Please don\'t hesitate to apply.\nStrong analytical skills\nExcellent proficiency in SQL\nCode writing capability in any programming language (Python, R, Scala, etc.)\nExcellent spoken and written English\nBachelors Degree in Mathematics, Physics, Computer Science, Statistics, Engineering or similar. Average 85 and above from top universities.\n1-2 years related work experience (data analyst, technical product manager, or similar) an advantage\nHadoop experience (MapReduce, PIG, Hive, Spark) an advantage\nGraph DB experience an advantage\nExperience in Machine-Learning, Data Mining or Statistics an advantage\nQuick-thinker, fast learner, wide general knowledge, problem solver\nTeam worker, responsible , delivery-oriented\nWhat we offer?\nA supportive and diverse environment that allows our employees to thrive and learn.\nFuture career opportunities with international exposure via PayPals network of global locations.\nAttractive compensation and benefits.','2020-07-07',113),(689,'Data Engineer','Explorium is a cutting-edge data science company that has recently closed a Series B round bringing their total funding to $50 million.\nExplorium offers a first of its kind data science platform powered by augmented data discovery and feature engineering. By automatically connecting to thousands of external data sources and leveraging machine learning to distill the most impactful signals, the Explorium platform empowers data scientists and business leaders to drive decision-making by eliminating the barrier to acquire the right data and enabling superior predictive power.\nJob Description\nWe are looking for a talented Data Engineer with a passion for data and complex problems.\nAs a Data Engineer, you will join a diversified engineering group consisting of Data Engineers, Machine Learning Engineers, and Algorithms Engineers. You will work on data pipelines varying from high resolution geospatial data to the stock market and implement both infrastructure and serving. You will have a key role in Exploriums Data Organization, responsible for collecting, integrating and serving high quality features for machine learning models.\nAt Explorium we believe strongly in personal and professional development, constantly researching new technologies and methodologies.\nResponsibilities:\nWork closely with business and research teams to deliver high quality results to customers and partners.\nDesign and Implement complex end-to-end data pipelines including data extraction, feature engineering, data quality and data serving.\nWork with Data Scientists to deliver high scale, high quality features for machine learning models.\nTake ownership of the project from POC to production.\nContribute to a wide variety of projects using a range of technologies and tools.\nIf you are someone that thrives in a fast-paced environment where being self-directed, creative and determined are a requirement, we would love for you to join us.\n\n\nRequirements:\nRequirements:\nBsc in CS/Mathematics/Statistics/Physics/EE or equivalent experience.\n2+ years of industry experience working with large data sets with Spark\n3+ years of hands-on experience programming in Scala and Python\nExperience with working with complex data sets.\nExperience with Databases, SQL and NoSql, and Data modeling.\nExperience with data visualization and analytics.\nExperience working with cloud compute and storage services on AWS/GCP.\nHacker mindset - deliver results fast using creative solutions.\nA team player with excellent collaboration skills.\nKafka, Airflow and K8S - advantage.\nExperience with building Machine Learning models - advantage.\nExperience with designing datalakes - advantage.\nDeep knowledge in internal Spark tuning - advantage.','2020-07-06',141),(694,'Data Science עבור חברת סטארטאפ בעולם ה- E-commerce','מיקום: ת\"א והמרכז\n\nתיאור המשרה:\nאנחנו סטארטאפ ממומן היטב ואנחנו מפתחים אלגוריתמים שמסייעים לאנשים לרכוש בצורה חכמה יותר.\nאנחנו עובדים עם רשתות ומותגים ברחבי העולם. יש לנו לקוחות משלמים ואנחנו שמחים להרחיב את הצוות ולצרף Data Science עם התמחות ב- NLP\nממוקמים בתל אביב.\n\nדרישות המשרה:\nתואר ראשון במדעי המחשב/ סטטיסטיקה/ מתמטיקה\nניסיון עם Machine Learning\nNLP\nמס\' משרה: 117309','2020-07-09',76),(695,'Cross Asset Market Data Analyst','Job Purpose\n\nThe ICE Data Services group offers a multitude of opportunities and responsibilities around the monitoring and analysis of real-time market data. We are looking for a dynamic, driven and determined candidate to help monitor, analyze and assist our Global Market Data team, in financial derivatives sectors as diverse as Foreign Exchange, Interest Rates, Commodities and Energy, Equities, Credit and Fixed Income. As a Market Data Analyst, you would be working with us at the forefront of cutting edge, market moving information and technologies.\n\nResponsibilities\nMonitoring raw and derived data using in-house analytical tools\nAnalysis of cross asset market data\nMonitoring market data alerting systems\nTroubleshooting data inconsistences\nMonitoring global financial news\nCommunication with internal support and operational teams\n\nKnowledge and Experience\nBachelor’s degree in Economics / Math / Finance or other quantitative major - MUST\nFluent English (mainly written) - MUST\nAbility to work day/night shifts, Mon - Fri\nGood knowledge of Excel\nOrganized and detail oriented\nBasic knowledge of SQL/VB – an advantage\nExperience/interest in global derivatives markets','2020-07-28',218),(698,'Big Data Engineer','Have we got a job for you?!\n\nData Engineer, Petach Tikva\n\nBuild Your Career | Have Fun | Make a Difference\n\nIf you\'re the kind of person that loves to get stuff done, collaborate with colleagues all over the world and is interested in joining a fast growth global company that is trusted by the world\'s top digital brands and truly cares for its customers, join us at Payoneer!\nCheck out our values\n\nWe\'re looking for an experienced Data Engineer to join our amazing Data department and to help us taking our data platform to the next level.\n\nIs this you?\n\nWhat\'s the job?\nEnd to end development of data models, from gathering the data sources, develop ETL processes and develop front end data model solutions for users, helping our clients to make smarter decisions.\nBuilding automated validation processes to ensure data integrity.\nOptimizing processes run-time and solving problems in a scalable manner.\nTaking full ownership of designing, building and deployment of data products.\nHave you done this kind of stuff?\nAt least 3 years of experience with Python.\nAt least 3 years of experience with data streaming technologies (Kafka, RabbitMQ, Spark etc.).\nAt least 3 years of experience with extracting data from unstructured data sources.\nExperience creating and optimizing big data processes, pipelines and architectures.\nExperience with big data solutions like Redshift, BigQuery, Hive, Presto, Neo4J, etc.\nExperience with BI solutions development (DWH, ETL).\nExperience with data modeling.\nAbility to work independently and multi-task to meet deadlines.\nAbility to learn new technologies fast.\nAbility to work in a dynamic environment while providing solutions for complex business requirements.\nTake part in all research & development stages: design, build, deploy, monitor, troubleshoot and maintain our backend services.\nNot a must but a great advantage\nExperience in SQL and ETL tools like SSIS\\ Informatica.\nExperience with real time analytics.\nExperience in Scala \\ R.\nExperience in Tabular cubes.\nExperience with building automated validation processes to ensure data quality.\nRelevant Bachelor degree –preferably Industrial Engineering/ Information Systems/ Computer\nA few words about us\n\nPayoneer is a leading payment platform and one of the world\'s fastest growing fintech companies, ranking high on Inc. 5000, Deloitte Fast 500, and the CNBC Disruptor List. We empower entrepreneurs and businesses anywhere in the world – from Cairo to California, Buenos Aires to Bangalore and Tel Aviv to Tokyo – to go beyond and grow successful, sustainable businesses. With millions of customers in over 200 countries worldwide and trusted by clients like Amazon, Airbnb and Google, Payoneer truly connects anyone, anywhere, with opportunities to trade globally.','2020-07-10',321),(699,'Data Analyst','Placense is seeking a strong Data Analyst for joining a team of highly talented R&D professionals, who help businesses understand the connection between people’s behavior and physical locations by turning data from mobile apps into aggregated & anonymous insights. We provide metrics such as customer visits, visit duration, visit frequencies, customer journey paths, customer distribution to gender, age, income levels, modes of transport, and other related demographic characteristics. As a Data Analyst, you will take part in the company\'s research and analytics activities, over one of its most valuable assets - its data.\n\nResponsibilities\n\nMaster the different data sets in the company, and the value they can provide to customers.\nCommunicate with various stake holders across the company, gather and translate business requirements to data analysis activities and processes.\nPerform data analysis activities for researching and validating current/future data sets; and for generating information and insights for prospects and customers.\nRequirements\n\nFirst degree in Computer Science/Statistics/Mathematics or related field from known university.\n3+ years of experience in data analysis in high data volume environments.\nExcellent knowledge and proved experience in SQL and BI platforms.\nStrong analytical abilities, technical orientation and exceptional problem-solving skills.\nExcellent English communication skills – spoken and written.\nSelf-starter, fast learner, team player and can-do attitude.\nAdvantages\n\nExperience with Python.\nExperience with statistical analysis.\nFamiliarity with geo-spatial data and methodologies.','2020-07-14',850),(700,'Data Science לחברת סטארטאפ בתחום הרובוטיקה','מיקום: ת\"א והמרכז\n\nתיאור המשרה:\nחברת סטארטאפ שקיימת עשר שנים ופועלת בתחום הרובוטיקה מגייסתData Science.\nהרובוטים שלנו עתידים לייעל את שוק העבודה. אנחנו ממומנים היטב. על ידי קרנות מובילות - 50 מיליון דולר\nממוקמים בתל אביב\nנשמח לפגוש Data Science שרוצה להיות חלק מהעבודה שלנו\nתפקיד עם אורינטציה מחקרית חזקה\n\nדרישות המשרה:\nשנתיים ניסיון בעבודת Data Science\nDeep Learning ניסיון של שנה\nC# Python\nמס\' משרה: 117310','2020-07-09',76),(702,'Data Analyst','מיקום: ת\"א והמרכז\n\nתיאור המשרה:\nהזדמנות מעולה!\nאנחנו מפתחים מוצר מבוסס בינה מלאכותית ומסייעים לעסקים קטנים לנהל את תחום המרקטינג שלהם בצורה קלה נוחה. האלגוריתם שלנו הופך עיצוב לבר השגה, קל ונוח.\nגייסנו 25 מיליון דולר מקרנות מובילות\nיש לנו Work life balance אמיתי אנחנו גם Dog friendly\nהצוות שלנו מתרחב ואנחנו מחפשים אנליסטים/יות שיצטרפו למשימה שלנו- להנגיש מיתוג לעסקים קטנים!\nמונים 45 עובדים ורובם בפיתוח\n\nדרישות המשרה:\n3 שנות ניסיון כ- Data Analyst\nSQL הכרחי\nPython\nמס\' משרה: 116676','2020-07-14',76),(703,'Product Support Expert (Data Specialist)','What is #LifeatAF? How can we crystalize its DNA into one eye-catching sentence for you? Our culture is defined by our people! Everyone is an approachable professional, tenacious and versatile, a challenging team member, and a respected and valued mentor.\n\nThe Data Specialist will have to work closely with our Product and Engineering teams, learning our data products and communicating the affects of our data platforms to our customers and customer-facing teams. S/he will provide a deep technical understanding of the product, alongside strong data analytics and research methods.\n\nThe right candidate will work in close collaboration with AppsFlyer\'s Engineering, Customer Success, Customer Support and Product Teams. He/She will actively engage in cross-departmental projects and strongly represent Client Services in the product\'s evolution by providing viable feedback to advance the future of our product.\n\nWhat you\'ll do\nPlay a pivotal role in the product lifecycle and its roadmap, providing insights on the role of data systems in the product\nCollaborate with the CSM, Support and Engineering teams internally\nTake end-to-end ownership of new features from the support perspective, including training, creating/updating knowledge base articles, and other internal communication\nServe as a knowledge hub on features and ensure support issues are resolved meticulously\nWork with AppsFlyer\'s Engineering and product teams on escalations and product enhancement requests\nCreate and lead support improvement processes in our data systems across the company\nManage various internal projects, such as: training, ensuring support readiness for new feature releases, etc.\nWhat you have\nExperience in customer-facing roles\nExperience with technical support / QA / development/ technical account management\nDeep understanding of data flows and data infrastructure\nAbility to mobilize cross-functional teams and resources\nExperience in SQL querying and data analysis\nAdvanced proficiency in written and spoken English\nAbility to learn new technologies quickly\nBachelor\'s degree in a technical field such as Computer Science or Engineering or equivalent practical experience\nBonus Points\nExpertise in creating tech documentation writing, managing knowledge databases\nBeing introduced by an AppsFlyer team member\nAs a global company operating in 16 countries across 5 continents, we reflect the human mosaic of the diverse and multicultural world in which we live. We ensure equal opportunities for all of our employees and promote the recruitment of diverse talents to our global teams without consideration of race, gender, culture, or sexual orientation. We value and encourage curiosity, diversity, and innovation from all our employees, customers, and partners.\n\n\"As a Customer Obsessed company, we must first be Employee Obsessed. We need to make sure that we provide the team with the tools and resources they need to go All-In.\" Oren Kaniel, CEO','2020-07-09',158);
INSERT INTO `job` VALUES (704,'Data Engineer','Hundreds of millions of people around the world choose Viber as their top messaging and calling app every day. Our mission is to connect people freely and securely, no matter who they are or where they are from. We look for exceptional team members that want to make an impact – keeping and growing Viber as an easy, secure, and meaningful communication platform.\n\nThis is a unique opportunity to join a new team and work closely with data scientists to develop and deploy scalable, high throughput production services, machine learning models, tackle challenges in the worlds of spam, computer vision and more.\n\nResponsibilities\nImplement solutions in a Big Data environment from top to bottom, by gathering requirements, specifying data schemes and developing machine learning processes\nDesign and apply cutting edge technology stacks in a high throughput environment\nDesign and implement advanced algorithms in the machine and deep learning frameworks\nRequirements\nAt least 3 years experience with Python\nExperience with Big Data – Spark/PySpark\nExperience working in cloud environment, preferably AWS\nBSc. in Computer Science or equivalent\nGood Analytical & Problem Solving Skills','2020-07-15',855),(706,'Big Data Engineer','The Big Data Engineer will join the data team alongside other data experts (Engineers & Analysts).\nIn this role you will influence every decision making process in the company and thus this is a crucial role for the company. The role allows the different departments to gain the much needed visibility to different data sources that shed light about every aspect of our product, from user behavior, new feature adoption, operational , financial and marketing KPIs and more.\nYou will work closely with different departments to understand their needs and gain in-depth understanding of the business as this is key for any data engineer to fulfil this role properly.\n\n\nRequirements:\nBSc in computer science / software engineering or other equivalent / related academic degree - Nice To Have\nHold a relevant certification in the area of big data architecture in one or more of the public clouds (AWS Solution Architect / Big Data | GCP Data Engineer) - Nice to Have\nAt Least 4 years of industry experience in a similar role - A Must\nFamiliar with different tools for using off-the-shelf ETL tools (like Matillion, Stitch, Fivetran) and orchestration frameworks (like Airflow, AWS Appflow, AWS Step Functions & Data pipelines, AWS Glue, GCP Cloud Composer & Dataflow) - A Must\nExtensive experience in big data architectures at scale in the cloud (AWS | GCP) - A Must\nDeep understanding and experience with data lakes & data warehouses in the cloud (S3, Redshift, Cloud storage, BigQuery) - A Must\nDeep understanding and experience with RDS and NoSql DBs (MySql, Elastic, MongoDB, Redis) - A Must\nYou speak fluent python but can understand other languages as well - A Must\nFamiliar with bash scripting and linux OS - A Must\nExperience with near real time data streaming solutions (mainly different types of queueing and streaming, pub/sub paradigms, Kafka, AWS sns / sqs, Kinesis firehose & streames, GCP Cloud Pub/Sub & Dataflow) - Nice to Have\nYou are accustomed to talking to internal stakeholders, understand their needs and build the absolute best-in-class data architecture to solve their problems while looking at the company needs for short and medium term\n\n\nWork environment:\nElementor is the leading website builder for professionals on WordPress, powering 5M+ active sites. Elementor is the ultimate WordPress page builder that lets you create beautiful WordPress websites in the easiest and quickest way possible.\nThe key difference is that you can reach a high level of design, while designing live, and on the frontend of your site. It includes dozens of useful widgets & features like drag & drop and live editing, achieve a pixel perfect design with ease, a stunningly designed template library, a unique mobile editing toolset and a visual revision history feature.\nJust recently we launched the Elementor Experts Arena that allows everyone to find an Elementor Expert that will build the best website for them, and there are even more products to come to extend the Elementor ecosystem and create the complete package for web creators to build their business on top of Elementor.\n\nMore awesome facts about Elementor\nSimply put, Elementor is the best website builder in the world. Its not that we are arrogant, there was actually a contest and we won. Twice !!. Elementor has won the best Wordpress plugin contest for two years in a row.\nWe just recently celebrated more than 5M websites built on top of Elementor, and Elementor is only 4 years old.\nIn 2019 there were more than 100+ meetups worldwide, driven by our huge community.\nThere are Udemy courses that teach web professionals how to use Elementor to produce great stunning websites.\nWe didn\'t actually count, but there are probably hundreds of tutorials, guidelines, webinars and youtube videos out there that educates our awesome community on how to utilize the Elementor page builder to its full potential.\n\n\nResponsibilities:\nDesign, architect and build Elementor data architecture from the ground up\nImplement best in class solutions for different use cases\nUtilize a combination of cloud based and open source tools and frameworks to solve our most complex data problems\nDevelop tailormade solutions as part of the data pipelines\nImplement data pipelines and data architecture that are scalable, fault tolerant, support high throughout, low latency while considering security aspects at all times\nConsider cost optimization (finops) at all stages of the implementation\nYou will be expected to provide solutions that are best-in-class in terms of industry standards and best practices','2020-07-21',90),(707,'Data Engineer','Data Engineer\nData EngineeringHerzliya\nThe Data Engineering department is responsible for full-stack design and development of the company\'s central data & ML services and business platforms.\n\nThe department is responsible for the overall projects, design, architecture and development of huge scale and very challenging cloud-based Big Data, machine learning and business applicative platforms for ensuring excellence in the performance of business aspects including games & product design, marketing, retention, monetization, etc.\n\nDepartment solutions support the optimization of the company\'s overall business performance.\nOther vacancies\nData Integration QA Engineer\nData Engineering - Herzliya, Israel\nMachine Learning Engineer\nData Engineering - Herzliya, Israel\n3D Character Artist\nStrategy Games - Kharkiv, Ukraine\nGoogle & Search Team Lead\nMarketing - Herzliya, Israel\nSenior SEO\nMarketing - Herzliya, Israel\nJob responsibilities:\nLead the data solution, technical design and development for Plarium data platform\nWork closely with the product and infrastructure R&D teams to deliver the best data solution and insights over billions of daily events\nDesign, Develop and Operate the data pipelines required for optimal extraction, transformation, and loading (ETL) of data from a wide variety of data sources using distributed processing engines such as Apache Spark and Apache Beam\nWork closely with the data science and ML engineers to develop and implement the ML framework and data features\nExplore and deploy new data technologies to support Plarium data platform\nRequirements:\n\n\n2+ years of hands-on experience writing complex ETL pipelines using parallel processing engine (Spark/MapReduce/Beam etc) - Must\n4+ years of hands-on experience in Scala/Java/Python - Must\nExpert in writing efficient sql queries and optimize performance (Impala/SparkSQL/BigQuery etc) - Must\nExcellent understanding of development methodologies, paradigms (OOP, FP) and test driven environment - Must\nYou can write Technical Designs and turn business requirements to technical solutions\nTeam player with a can-do attitude - Must!\nBachelor’s degree in Computer Science or related - Must\nAdvantages:\n\n\nExperience working on cloud solutions (GCP a big advantage) - a plus\nKnowledge in Qlik Sense/Looker/Tableau or other visualization solutions - a plus\nExperience working with notebook solutions (Jupyter, Zeppelin) - a plus\nExperience with building Machine Learning solutions - a plus\nExperience working in Agile Scrum methodologies - a plus','2020-07-16',703),(708,'Data Engineer','מיקום: ת\"א והמרכז\n\nתיאור המשרה:\nסטארטאפ בחזית הטכנולוגית בעולם הבינה המלאכותית מגייס Data Engineer. מדובר בחברה עם מוצר טכנולוגי שפונה לחברות Enterprise. הזדמנות להיות חלק מכתיבה מחדש של כל המערכת.\nממומנים היטב עם תנאים נלווים מעולים\n\nדרישות המשרה:\n3 שנות ניסיון כ- Data Engineer\nהכרות עם: kafka/Hadoop/spark.\nCloud/ AWS\nניסיון בעבודה עם חברות web\nמס\' משרה: 116215','2020-07-21',76),(710,'Big Data Architect','· At Amazon Web Services (AWS), were hiring highly technical cloud computing architects to collaborate with our customers and partners on key engagements. Our consultants will develop and deliver proof-of-concept projects, technical workshops, and support implementation projects. These professional services engagements will focus on customer solutions such as HPC, batch data processing, Big Data and Business intelligence. This role will specifically focus on Data processing capabilities and helping our customers and partners to remove the constraints that prevent our customers from leveraging their data to develop business insights.\nProfessional Services engage in a wide variety of projects for customers and partners, providing collective experience from across the AWS customer base and are obsessed about strong success for the Customer. Our team collaborates across the entire AWS organization to bring access to product and service teams, to get the right solution delivered and drive feature innovation based upon customer needs.\nResponsibilities include:\n· Expertise - Collaborate with AWS field sales, pre-sales, training and support teams to help partners and customers learn and use AWS services such as Amazon Elastic Compute Cloud (EC2), Amazon Data Pipeline, S3, DynamoDB NoSQL, Relational Database Service (RDS), Elastic Map Reduce (EMR) and Amazon Redshift.\n· Solutions - Deliver on-site technical engagements with partners and customers. This includes participating in pre-sales on-site visits, understanding customer requirements, creating consulting proposals and creating packaged Big Data service offerings.\n· Delivery - Engagements include short on-site projects proving the use of AWS services to support new distributed computing solutions that often span private cloud and public cloud services. Engagements will include migration of existing applications and development of new applications using AWS cloud services.\n\nBasic Qualifications\n\n· 5+ years experience of IT platform implementation in a highly technical and analytical role. · Demonstrated industry leadership in the fields of database, data warehousing or data sciences.\n· Deep understanding an implementation experience of database and analytical technologies in the industry including MPP databases, noSQL storage, Data Warehouse design, BI reporting and Dashboard development\n· Travel to customer locations is required to sell and deliver professional services as needed.\n· Fluent in Hebrew and English\n\n\nPreferred Qualifications\n\n· AWS Experience\n· Strong verbal and written communication skills, with the ability to work effectively across internal and external organizations.\n· Hands on experience leading large-scale global data warehousing and analytics projects. · Customer facing skills to represent AWS well within the customers environment and drive discussions with senior personnel regarding trade-offs, best practices, project management and risk mitigation\n· Demonstrated ability to think strategically about business, product, and technical challenges in an global environment.\n· Implementation and tuning experience for Apache Hadoop + tools such as Pig and Hive.\n· Implementation and tuning experience specifically using Amazon Elastic Map Reduce + tools such as Pig and Hive.\n· Track record of implementing AWS services in a variety of distributed computing, enterprise environments.\n· BA/BS degree or equivalent experience; Computer Science or Math background preferred\n\naws-proserv-ea\n\n** AWS_PROFESSIONAL_SERVICES **\n\nAmazon aims to be the most customer centric company on earth. Amazon Web Services (AWS) provides a highly reliable, scalable, low-cost infrastructure platform in the cloud that powers critical applications for hundreds of thousands of businesses in 190 countries around the world.','2020-07-09',115),(712,'Data Analyst- Data Department','Have we got a job for you?!\n\nData Analyst, Petach Tikva\n\nBuild Your Career | Have Fun | Make a Difference\n\nIf you\'re the kind of person that loves to get stuff done, collaborate with colleagues all over the world and is interested in joining a fast growth global company that is trusted by the world\'s top digital brands and truly cares for its customers, join us at Payoneer!\nCheck out our values\n\nWe\'re looking for a data business-oriented individual who can turn data into insights, collaborate with executive and technical stakeholders.\n\nIs it you?\n\nWhat\'s the job?\n\nAs a data analyst, you will be the link between the data and the main business stakeholders and analysts in the company. You will enable data and share your insights to influence and support the decision-making process.\nIf you enjoy working in a high paced environment, leading data solutions, conducting challenging analysis and would like to make an impact on the company\'s growth, then this is the right place for you.\nCollaborate with various roles in the organization: working with technical teams on design and implementation, along aside with management to prioritize business and information needs.\nBring an economical edge to your analytical outcomes.\nUse statistical methods, analytical skills, complex data and business judgment to address strategic and operational business questions.\nWork with key metrics and implements control tools to validate them.\nCreate and deliver accurate, detailed, timely and user-friendly reports and dashboards with interpretation and insights.\nProactively look at the data and provide useful insights that will drive improvements in users acquisition, engagement and retention.\nDeal with lateral ad hoc analysis and requests.\nHave you done this kind of stuff?\n3 + years\' experience of analyzing Data.\nExpert in SQL: extract and analyze data - a must !\nExcellent Excel skills – a must !\nExperience working with BI tools\nExcellent verbal and written communication skills in English. The ability to communicate complex ideas in clear and succinct terms to both analytical and non-analytical audiences.\nStrong analytical skills with the ability to collect, organize and analyze significant information with attention to detail and accuracy.\nNot a must but a great advantage:\nExperience with financial models (Revenue and Cost)\nFamiliarized with Python and\\or R environments\nExperience with statistical and prediction models\nWorking with Google Analytics\nExperience with Data Warehouse \\Solution Design and Dimensional Modeling\nKnowledge in ETL, data streams & pipelines.','2020-07-23',321),(714,'Data Engineer','Investing.com was founded in 2007 and now has over 300 employees across offices in Tel Aviv, Madrid, Tokyo, Shenzhen, and Seoul. With 40 million monthly users, over 400 million sessions, and over 300,000 financial instruments covered, Investing.com is one of the top three global financial websites, Ranked at the top 200 websites by Alexa.\n\nInvesting.com offers unlimited access to cutting-edge financial market tools such as real-time quotes and charts, customized portfolios, personal live alerts, calendars, calculators, and financial insights, completely free of charge. In addition to the global stock markets, Investing.com also covers world indices, ETFs, commodities, bonds & interest rates, cryptocurrencies, futures, and options“. Investing.com strives to be a one-stop-shop for traders and investors with apps available.\n\nWe are seeking a data engineer with a passion for data wrangling.\n\nWhat we offer:\nInfluence over 40M high profile traders and investors around the world, creating over 400M sessions and 3B monthly page-views on our websites and apps.\n\nBe a part of one of the top, online company\'s in Israel, in one of the most competitive markets in the world.\n\nEnjoy excellent benefits and a high-energy working environment.\n\nWhat will you do:\nAs a data engineer, you will build, maintain, and optimize data solutions. You will develop data warehouse models and reporting solutions that will support the analysts, data scientists, and business units.\n\nWe’re looking for someone who can take ownership of the full insights delivery pipeline.\n\nFrom integrating into sources, model the data, manipulate it and deliver it in an insight ready form.\n\nWe expect the best candidate to have both technical skills and business and communication skills.\n\nRequirements:\nWhat we are looking for:\nBA/B.Sc. graduate in industrial/information systems engineering, computer science, statistics or equivalent\n2+ years of experience as a data engineer doing data integration and modeling.\nHands-on actual work experience with a programming language (python, java, scala, ruby, etc)\nHigh SQL skills\nSome experience with dashboarding tools like Tableau, Sisense, Looker, etc\nExperience with MPP columnar databases like Snowflake, Redshift, Bigquery, etc - Advantage\n\nAs with all investing.com positions - we\'re looking for someone who is self-motivated and meticulous, with a creative and resourceful mind, bright, proactive, works well independently and as part of a team.\n\nCheck out openings on our brand new career website: https://www.investing-careers.com/\n\nOur Privacy Policy: Your resume and information will be kept confidential\n\nEmployment Type:\nEmployee','2020-07-21',865),(715,'Data Engineer','תמיד חלמת לעבוד בחברה שמביאה בשורה חדשנית לעולם? חברת Ness מגייסת Data Engineer מנוסה להשתלב במיזם חדשני של חברה ישראלית בינלאומית. במסגרת התפקיד אחריות מלאה על כל תחום ה- Data בחברה, החל מתחקור ותכנון הארכיטקטורה בסביבת עבודה טכנולוגית ומתקדמת. מיקום המשרה, בתל אביב.\n\nדרישות: הכרות מעמיקה עם עולם ה- Data וניסיון עם טכנולוגיות Big Data - חובה. ניסיון כמפתח/ת Java - חובה. ניסיון בפיתוח ב- Python - חובה. ניסיון בעבודה עם SQL, ברמה גבוהה - חובה.\n\nאנגלית ברמה גבוהה - חובה. הכרות עם AWS Data Services - יתרון.','2020-07-10',24),(716,'Data Engineer - Business Intelligence','Are you looking for an opportunity to challenge yourself?\n\nAt ZoomInfo our employees work hard to \'define new possibles\', and they are driven by winning. ZoomInfo is a company that got to where it\'s at today on the backs of heroic efforts, over the years, by our employees and we are looking for more people to contribute to those efforts.\n\nAt our company you\'ll see that collaboration is second nature, and you\'ll be greeted by a team of incredibly smart, talented, and motivated individuals who will help you define your new best.\n\nYou\'ll be presented with opportunities to both personally and professionally develop as you build your career. We believe that our employees love to work and love to work here, and that you will like coming to work because of the sense of accomplishment you get from being a part of what we\'re building.\n\nYou are a fit for our team if you refuse to lose, you seek challenges, and you love to win. We welcome you to join our team of difference makers who are people working with a passion to win together.\n\nIf you\'re the kind of person that loves to get stuff done, collaborate with colleagues all over the world and is interested in joining a fast growth global company , join us at ZoomInfo! You will work regularly with our development and analyst teams, while coming up with your own creative BI solutions.\n\nWhat will you actually be doing?\nOwn the transformation process from turning raw data into analytical insights\nDesign, implement and maintain ETLs to enhance business analysis capabilities\nProactively identify gaps in data consumption and define processes to complete them\nTranslate business needs into technical requirements\nResponsibilities\nDevelop and maintain ZoomInfo analytical data model.\nAnalyse, design, document, develop, test and deploy a BI solution (end to end)\nOwn and provide data development tools for internal use.\nCreate new ETL processes and optimize existing.\nProvide analysts and other internal customers with technical support related to data activity.\nWork closely with tech teams on the design and implementation of data solutions.\nRequirements\nAt least 4 years of relevant experience as BI developer / Data engineer\nBA/B.Sc. in industrial/information systems engineering, computer science, statistics or equivalent.\nVery high level of SQL and data warehouse modeling - a must.\nExperience with big data solutions like BigQuery/Snowflake/RedShift - a must.\nHands-on programming skills in Python or other scripting languages - a must.\nExperience with cloud platforms (GCP/AWS/Azure) - big advantage.\nExperience with workflows and data processing pipelines like AirFlow - big advantage.\n1-year experience in reporting platforms like Tableau/Looker - advantage.\nIn-depth understanding of database management systems and ETL (Extract, transform, load) framework\nExperience in the online industry.\nQuick learner, a team player, independent and motivated individual\nAble to multitask, prfioritize, and manage time efficiently!\nAbout us:\n\nBuilt over 20 years ago, ZoomInfo Powered by DiscoverOrg has helped companies achieve their most important objective: profitable growth. Backed by the world\'s most comprehensive B2B database, our platform puts sales, marketing and recruiting professionals in a position to identify, connect, and engage with qualified prospects. ZoomInfo offers unrivaled data and accuracy with contacts, companies, direct dials and professional movement. For more information on our intelligence solution, visit us at zoominfo.com','2020-07-19',867),(717,'Data Architect','Playtika is looking for an experienced Data Architect to join our talented team.\nPlaytika is a Game-Entertainment company that provides audiences around the world with a wide variety of games based on quality, original content that is constantly changing and tailored to each player specifically.\nPlaytika uses massive amounts of data to reshape the gaming landscape by tailoring user experience based on in-game actions.\nWith 30 million daily active users (DAU), billions of daily events and over terabytes of daily processed data, Playtika is able to provide its data scientist and business analyst the data they need to create a continuously changing game environment for its users based on their in-game behavior.\nResponsibilities:\nEnd-to-end ownership of the group technical design of new products and features of our Data Lake and Data Warehouse products\nDesign and build highly scalable, reliable and well-designed software solutions, enhancing our core data infrastructure\nDeveloping Proof of Concepts (PoC) in order to demonstrate feasibility and value of new technologies and product features.\nWork with the Data Product Managers to understand product road-map and play an active role in defining features and changes in product requirements that influence the future usage of the product within the company\nProvide technical guidance and coaching to engineers through brainstorming sessions, and design reviews.\nWork on complex problems and performance issues of our ingestion and ETL pipelines.\nCollaborate with other departments in order to fully cover business needs\nWriting well-documented technical documentation/specification\nSupporting team in implementation and integrations\nCoach and supervise technical team members on data architecture best practices\nParticipate routinely in design and code reviews\n\n\nRequirements:\nBachelors degree in Computer Science/Engineering\nAt least 10 years of practical experience in development\nAt least 2 years of experience as an architect or technical lead\nExpert knowledge of writing code in Python, Java and Scala; other languages is an advantage\nExperience with custom ETL, schema design, and dimensional data modeling\nExtensive hands-on experience in building Data Lake (DL) and Data Warehouse (DWH) space\nProven knowledge and hands-on experience in large scale batch (Hadoop, Spark, Hive etc.) and stream processing (Spark, Kafka ,Flink, Akka etc.)\nExperience with relational (MySQL, Postgres), NoSQL databases (Couchbase, Aerospike, Cassandra), search engines (elasticsearch), caching solutions; Queue solutions and data pipelines\nGood knowledge of architecture, design patterns and styles\nExperience in mentoring engineers to develop new skills and grow professionally\nExcellent analytical and problem-solving skills\nExperience with database performance tuning and optimization (an advantage)\n\n\nBusiness Unit:\nTechnologies\n\nSub Department:\nTechnologies\n\nWebsite Group:\nR&D','2020-07-28',871),(718,'Data Engineer \\ ETL Developer לחברה בתחום ה Ad-Tech','מיקום: ת\"א והמרכז\n\nתיאור המשרה:\nדרוש/ה Data Engineer לחברת Ad-Tech מצוינת באזור המרכז!\nהחברה מפתחת דרכים לנתח ביג דאטה של אנליטיקות שיווק. המוצר שלהם מסייע ללקוחותיה להבין אילו לקוחות הם הטובים ביותר, וכיצד הם משפיעים על לקוחות פוטנציאליים נוספים להפוך ללקוחות משלמים של החברה. עושים שימוש באנליטיקות של Big Data ואלגוריתמים!\n\nדרישות המשרה:\nניסיון של שנתיים ומעלה בפיתוח ETL\nניסיון ב SSIS\nניסיון ב PYTHON\nמס\' משרה: 119663','2020-07-24',76),(719,'Data Engineer','Perion is a global technology company that provides digital advertising technology solutions to the biggest brands and publishers around the globe.\nWith our unique data-driven AI/ML based technologies, we deliver and optimize hundreds of terabytes of data and billions of events per day from dozens of sources to provide a superior user experience across screens and platforms, including mobile, video, social and native.\n\nWe are looking for a highly skilled Data Engineer to join our Data Platforms Group to the journey of leveraging Big Data to revolutionize our offering, business operations and decision making across the companys ecosystem.\nAs a Data Engineer you will build data driven solution using cutting edge data tools and large-scale data on Undertones AWS winning data infrastructure..\n\nJob Responsibilities:\nWork closely with product, architects and the R&D teams to deliver the best solution to the business.\nDesign the solution by understanding the needs, modeling the data, choosing the right tools and defining the interfaces / reports.\nImplement a variety of data solutions while following engineering best practices.\nMake sure the solution is stable, scalable and provides accurate data at all time.\nManage the interfaces with the data partners and other R&D teams to deliver the solution on time.\nDevelop expertise in the business topics that the solutions you own covers.\nRun research and POCs for new technologies and tools as part of our continuous improvement life-cycle.\nProfile and Experience:\n+3 years of proven experience in building complex BI solutions end to end, using ETL processing, data visualization tools and reporting systems\nExperience with Amazon Redshift, Pentaho, Tableau significant advantage\nExperience/training in Spark - significant advantage\nStrong analytical and problem-solving skills with attention to details\nBy pressing “Apply Now”, you agree and accept to our privacy policy as well as the transfer of your personal information to countries outside the country in which you reside and which have a different data protection regime than in the country in which you reside. Nevertheless, the Company takes appropriate technical, organizational, and legal steps to secure personal information collected about you.\n\nPowered by JazzHR','2020-07-27',873),(720,'דרוש/ה אנליסט/ית אבטחת מידע - BIG DATA','ביצוע משימות ניתוח לטובת טיוב מענה לאירועי סייבר ואבטחת מידע, הטמעה וטיוב של כלי ההגנה וליווי תהליכים עסקיים בהיבטי הסייבר ע\"מ לחזק את עמידות הארגון למגוון תרחישי תקיפה בסייבר דרישות: ידע וניסיון בחקירת חולשות ובניתוח ותגובה לאירועי אבטחת מידע היכרות עם מערכות BIG DATA ו Threat hunting','2020-07-04',24),(721,'Data Product Manager','As a Data Product Manager at Playtika you will take part and manage projects in varies aspects of data oriented solutions.\nFrom streaming data consumers up to data infrastructure projects and data dashboards, serving teams around the world, games & management.\nYou will work with:\nPlaytikas professional teams built from data engineers, data scientists, BI engineers, Business analysts, IT, Security, Marketing and managements teams.\nYou will partner with Playtikas domain experts and top level business professionals in the gaming and online marketing industries.\nResponsibilities:\nGather, design and manage the product requirements\nUtilize data management capabilities to consolidate the different aspects of our data products\nInitiate new products and sell across the organization\nBe part of the data platforms management team, main data pipes in Playtika\nPromote best practices in data modeling and products execution\nIntegrate the business goals with the different professionals teams, spread globally (BI, DE, DS, Infra, IT etc. )\nChampion the overall strategy for data governance, security, and quality that ensure requirements are met.\nCollaborating with our architects to capture, transform and consume data for ML and R&D.\n\n\nRequirements:\nExperience of developing & managi