e, across all mediums and platforms; Desktop, Mobile, YouTube, Facebook, Twitter, etc. and provide our functionality in real time and in reports across a range of products; Fraud Protection, Brand Safety, Engagement, Geo Verification and more. DV has multiple R&D centers in Tel Aviv, New York, Finland, Belgium and San Diego, the center in Israel is focused on building the core products. We are a fast-paced bunch with a lot of things to build.\n\nWhat you\'ll do\n\nAs a Data Engineer, you will be designing, implementing, improving and maintaining large scale ETL processes that process billions of data records a day and make them available in our analytics platform. you will model new data sets to support new product initiatives. you will be the owner of the data and as such, you will learn how the data serve our goals, come up with ways to improve our data processes, perform data analysis, add automation and alerts to validate our data integrity, and by that, help our clients to make smarter decisions that continuously improve their ad-impression quality. You will work with a wide array of languages and technologies such as Python, SQL, Vertica, Kafka, PySpark, Docker, Kubernetes to achieve that. We don\'t have architects or QA, we believe in our people\'s abilities to take things end to end; working with product, designing solutions, continuously building and deploying, building monitoring dashboards - getting things done.\n\nWho you are\n5+ years of experience working with relational/analytical databases (MSSQL, Oracle, MySQL, Vertica, Redshift, etc.)\n5+ years of hands-on experience in ETL development (design optimization and implementation)\n2+ years of hands-on development experience in python\nData lover with outstanding SQL querying abilities and data modeling\nInterested in learning about the ad tech industry and a general willingness to learn new things\nThe mentality of a team player - great communication skills, with a sense of ownership and of urgency\nPa