ya is to provide consumers with the best possible experience in an increasingly digital world, with the utmost respect for user privacy and protecting personal data.\n\nResponsibilities Include\nDesign & develop Big Data pipeline platform.\nPlan and build creative solutions that operate at huge scale.\nMaintain the entire product lifecycle, from planning, execution, QA, and deploy to production.\nData operations on real customer data\nWorking from the Tel-Aviv office - Must\nIdeal Candidates Will Have\n5+ years experience programming in Java server side\nExperience with RDBMS or NoSQL database systems\nExperience with asynchronous and multithreaded programming\nPassionate about building backend infrastructure.\nExperience with Linux\nExtra Points For\nExperience with big data processing pipelines\nWorking with Big data technologies\nExperience with distributed systems at huge scale\nExperience with devOps tools\n#SAPcareersLasisrael\n\n#SOF2020\n\n#SAPGigyaCareers\n\nWHAT YOU GET FROM US\n\nSuccess is what you make it. At SAP, we help you make it your own. A career at SAP can open many doors for you. If you’re searching for a company that’s dedicated to your ideas and individual growth, recognizes you for your unique contributions, fills you with a strong sense of purpose, and provides a fun, flexible and inclusive work environment – apply now.\n\nSAP\'S DIVERSITY COMMITMENT\nTo harness the power of innovation, SAP invests in the development of its diverse employees. We aspire to leverage the qualities and appreciate the unique competencies that each person brings to the company.\n\nSAP is committed to the principles of Equal Employment Opportunity and to providing reasonable accommodations to applicants with physical and/or mental disabilities. If you are in need of accommodation or special assistance to navigate our website or to complete your application, please send an e-mail with your request to Recruiting Operations Team (Americas: Careers.NorthAmerica@sap.com