io and helps to deliver value to customers across a variety of Financial Crime and Compliance initiatives. This role will be responsible for defining Actimize’s growth as a provider of cloud/SaaS based Case Manager solutions within our platform. This product manager will work with all NICE Actimize lines of business to go from vision to delivery while maintaining a focus on a profitable solutions business model.\n\nResponsibilities\n\nDefine, validate and take to market cloud/SaaS based Case Manager solutions for financial institutions, leveraging Actimize’s footprint and advanced analytics\nStrategy and planning to support business growth and market leadership through understanding the market (market segmentation, growth opportunities, key industries and solution areas)\nProduct strategy, roadmap and requirements for building market leading products\nHelp define and execution on a partner strategy for enriching our financial crime solutions with 3rd party data solutions go-to-market strategy and execution including packaging, pricing, positioning, marketing campaigns and sales enablement\nEvangelize and provide thought leadership through constant engagement with the market and the client community\nStrong relationship and management skills in a highly-matrixed environment with customers, sales, regions, partners, services and product groups.\n\n\nQualifications\n5 + years experience in Software product management mandatory\nExcellent verbal, written, analytical, and interpersonal communication skills mandatory\nExperience in cloud/SaaS\nExperience in public speaking\nExperience in automation\nLearning agility\nExperience in financial services nice to have\nMust be willing to travel up to 25% to customer sites\nSome international travel may be required\n\n\nNICE Actimize offers a competitive base salary, bonus and a full benefits package. Benefits include: medical, dental, 401K, vision, life, disability, transit checks, and a Flexible Spending Account (FSA).','2020-07-23',212),(796,'Product Manager - SaaS','SolarEdge is a top global leader in smart energy technology. SolarEdge\'s broad range of products encompasses intelligent & efficient conversion systems, EV chargers, smart energy solutions, monitoring platform, 3D design tool, sophisticated applications and more.\nThe product department in SolarEdge is responsible for overseeing the development of all new products. The team is in charge of implementing strategy, roadmap, and feature definitions for all of SolarEdge\'s product lines, hardware and software.\nAs a product manager for SAAS solutions you will manage SolarEdge\'s data-intensive web-based & mobile-based solutions.\nYou will need to be at the edge of your technical, marketing and management skills to bring to the market the most useful and innovative offering.\nYour main interfaces will be system product managers, R&D developers and information system engineers.\nWhat will you be doing:\nGather market and field feedback and translating it to product requirements and detailed specifications for product features\nDrive inbound and outbound product management activities\nDefine user workflows and GUI including mockups, wire frames and visual prototypes and develop written materials such as manuals, presentations, training to communicate product advantages and benefits.\nWork close with software engineers and ensure R&D are considering all relevant factors in the architectural design of the solution\nCombine deep technical and technological understanding with business view\nRequirements:\n5+ years of product management experience in a web or SaaS company\nDemonstrated ability to drive product research, planning, development, and launch\nTechnical degree such as Electrical Engineering or Computer Science\nBackground in SW development of scalable Web and Big Data applications Advantage\nExcellent English - Highly articulate and clear in both speaking and writing\nAbility to drive and motivate\nHard worker, self-driven and success hungry','2020-07-19',647),(797,'Product Manager','Centrical offers performance and engagement solutions that help companies maximize the value of their employees. It leverages employee and customer data to blend real-time performance management with personalized microlearning and advanced gamification – providing employees with clear goals, the knowledge they need to achieve them and a motivation to excel. Centrical’s platform seamlessly integrates with all major enterprise systems and is deployed by some of the world’s leading organizations such as Microsoft, Novartis, SwissLife and Unilever. It delivers measurable and sustainable value for customers – such as shorter time to proficiency, improved employee productivity and reduced absenteeism and attrition.\n\nCentrical was named a 2019 Deloitte Technology Fast 500 EMEA Company, honored for its exceptional growth during the prior year. Also, Centrical was ranked 1st overall Culture Score vs. competitors by Comparably; recognized with the Comparably “Best Compensation” and “Best Benefits & Perks” Awards; Top 5% on Gender and Diversity Scores of similar sized companies, and, top 5% CEO Performance in our peer group, with a CEO rating from employees of 98/100! We are a hard-working, fast-moving, growing company that has an encouraging, inclusive culture that makes for an enjoyable place to work.\n\nResponsibilities:\nEnd to end management of product lifecycle – prioritize features based on business value, collect and analyze requirements, write clear and detailed specs, create wireframes and define A/B tests.\nAnalyze results of features after deployment, iterate based on data to improve performance.\nWork with sales, marketing and customer success teams, as well as strategic clients in order to launch new products and features to market and analyze needs in order to implement new tools and products accordingly\nDemonstrate strong business acumen to help identifying opportunities where machine learning can drive business growth and determine how to incorporate these innovations through experimentation, all in line with the global strategy\nRequirements:\n5+ years as product manager in Saas product / B2B and B2C products – must!\nStrong UX background – must!\nHands on experience as UX designer – Clear advantage\nHands on experience with making data-oriented business decisions using analytics and visual reporting tools\nAbility to interact with and understand technical subjects/emerging technologies and their relevance to the marketplace.\nExperience working in Agile development cycle\nHigh level of English speaking and writing\nPresentations skills\nAbility to meet deadlines in a fast-paced environment\nExperienced with startup dynamic environment.','2020-07-16',951),(798,'Product Manager','Product Manager\n\n\nLocation: Kfar Saba\n\nSeaLights is the first innovative cloud-based Continuous Testing Platform. We developed a groundbreaking product which is transforming the world of software development and testing. Today, dozens of global companies from different industries (as well as SeaLights itself) are increasing their release speed with SeaLights.\n\nRecently we closed a financing round with strategic investors, bringing our total investment to $19M million dollars and we are continuing to rapidly grow our team.\n\nSeaLights is seeking a talented, technical, and analytical senior product manager who is an exceptional team player, to drive the strategy and execution of the SeaLights product. The senior product manager will be responsible for defining a new market category which will change how software is developed, tested and delivered, and take an active roll in building a multi-billion dollar company!\n\nReady for the challenge of a lifetime?\n\nResponsibilities:\nPartner with the engineering team in planning, execution, and management of resources, roadmap, and releases\nManage project execution, define schedules and release plans based on a strategic market/business view\nDefine the product priorities through understanding customers’ needs and company vision\nDrive product development with the R&D team\nDefine user stories, lead sprint planning and backlog management in partnership with the engineering team to ensure quality on-time feature delivery\nResearch market & industry trends, demand drivers, customer needs and competitive landscape\nRequirements:\nA self-starter, reformed developer and a natural leader, who enjoys orchestrating the launch of features and at the same time rolling up his/her sleeves, getting into technical details and design, while doing whatever is necessary to deliver\nDirect product experience creating and working on enterprise SaaS software\nDeep knowledge of development processes and QA/testing processes\nAbility to garner respect from engineers, to quickly absorb technical concepts and effectively simplify and communicate them to a non-technical audience\nStrong R&D background, software development experience as a developer, team leader, Test Automation, QA management/DevOps at high-growth startups\nProduct management experience – a big advantage.\nClear communication skills and experience interfacing with multiple cross-functional teams and stakeholders.\nStrong organizational, analytical & problem-solving skills\nPlease send your CV to jobs@sealights.io','2020-07-07',952),(799,'Product Manager','Do you understand what users want?\n\nBizzabo is looking for a talented and experienced Product Manager with a strong SAAS B2B startup experience to join as a member of the Product team and work on defining the next generations of Bizzabos Events Cloud to revolutionizing the event space experiences. Bizzabo is the only Events Success Platform for in-person, virtual, and hybrid events.\n\nBizzabos all-in-one event software helps companies measure, manage, and scale events towards key business outcomesempowering every organizer, marketer, exhibitor, and attendee to unleash the power of professional events. Bizzabo powers events for brands like Forbes, HubSpot, Dow Jones, Gainsight, Uber, Bank of Ireland, and Electronic Arts. The company was founded by Boaz Katz, Alon Alroy, and Eran Ben-Shushan, and has more than hundred of Bizzaboers working in our NY and TLV offices\n\n\nRequirements:\nPRODUCT STRATEGY\nYou will play a pivotal role in shaping the product strategy and shipping the roadmap on our flagship product\nYou will develop new product ideas and experimentation plans via brainstorming, market research, customer interviews, discovery processes, and competitive analysis\nPRODUCT PLANNING\nYou will define and maintain product roadmap together with the Product team and in coordination with the company\'s executive team\nYou will prioritize product development effort\nPRODUCT EXECUTION\nYou will lead a squad of your own (Devs + Product Designer)\nYou will create detailed product requirements of new features, building and maintaining with your squad features for the flagship product\nWork closely with R&D, Data and Go-To-Market teams in order to bring product requirements into implementable design and definitions\nWork closely with the Product Designers to define style and design that aligns with the user experience\nTranslate concepts to wireframes, mockups, prototypes, and detailed design specifications\nWork closely with customers and partners\nWHAT YOU HAVE\n3+ years experience as a Product Manager responsible for a B2B SaaS product\nGreat understanding of all aspects of the product development lifecycle\nExcellent understanding of data and how to interpret it to improve products\nStrong user experience skills, along with technical understanding\nStrong execution of qualitative and quantitative analysis\nExperience in outbound product activities of directly engaging with customers\nYou are a team player with the ability to thrive in a fast-paced, startup environment\nHigh degree of creativity and drive\nBachelors Degree in relevant field','2020-07-27',789),(800,'Product Manager','Your role at Vim as a Product Manager:\n\nVim is building a platform to align and connect patients with the best providers for their needs. We empower providers to make the best decisions for their patients at the time of a referral.\n\nYou\'ll be joining our new delivery team and as a product manager you will help setting up and leading the team. Our team is responsible for taking our platform and turning it into complete solutions for our customers. We augment our platform\'s APIs and SDKs and deeply embed them into our customers\' workflows. We engage with our customers and listen to them, scope their changes, develop new custom products or features and are responsible for managing the projects end to end - we deliver!\n\nThis is a challenging role in a complex and dynamic environment, you\'ll need to be able to learn, fail, and learn from your mistakes. We\'re moving fast, which means not all of our work processes are fine-tuned, and we\'ll need your help to put them in place.\n\nWhat you will do:\nYou\'ll work closely with big enterprise customers, account team, and sales team to gather customer needs, and prioritize them.\nYou will collaborate and communicate effectively and very often with our teams in the United States\nUnderstand the market, and customer needs in-depth.\nAnalyse customer needs and requirements, create a viable solution to satisfy them while using the building blocks of the platform, and plan and manage the delivery teams\' development cycles.\nOwn the roadmap for custom products delivered by Vim to strategic enterprise customers.\nWork closely with our design team to plan user interactions and create screens and new features that will meet users\' needs.\nWhat we are looking for:\nAt least two years of professional experience as a Product Manager, working alongside R&D.\nExperience in outbound product activities of directly engaging with customers.\nExcellent written and verbal communication skills in English.\nStrong ability to communicate with key stakeholders across multiple levels of an organization who have varying degrees of technical aptitude.\nYou genuinely enjoy a dynamic and fast-paced startup environment where every day presents a new challenge.\nYou\'re a quick learner with an unwaveringly positive, action-oriented attitude\nFlexibility working in late hours between Monday - Thursday to work with the US.\nNice to have, but certainly not necessary:\nUser experience skills, along with technical understanding.\nHands-on experience in an Account Manager / Customer Success Manager role.\nAbout us: We are headquartered in San Francisco, with R&D in Tel Aviv, and are backed by Sequoia, GreatPoint Ventures, Optum Ventures, and large BCBS payers. Our customers include health plans and physician-led healthcare systems.\n\nBy inputting your information and clicking \"Submit Application\", you acknowledge that you have read and agree to Vim\'s Candidate Privacy Notice.','2020-07-23',105),(802,'Product Manager','As a Product manager @XM you will be leading the design and delivery of the next big features of our HaXM product, from end-to-end - from initial concept, understanding the customer experience through technical design aspects with the R&D.\nWork on both inbound and outbound aspects of the product.\nDevelop product backlogs, drive execution to results and manage outcomes in an agile \"ship it\" environment.\nWork with customers to help direct product roadmap and improve customer experience.\nWork with UX designers, engineers and security experts to design and deliver product features.\nAnalyzing the market trends, competitive landscape and new business opportunities of the security market.\n\n\nRequirements:\n3+ years of experience as a Product Manager - A MUST\nStrong security background - A MUST\nProven track record of delivering software products/services to market.\nKnowledge in architecture and design of scalable and high performance Cloud services.\nDeep customer empathy and ability to identify customer needs.\nExcellent communication, writing, and presentation skills in English.\nTeam player, confident, independent and enthusiastic!\nBA/BS degree in Computer Science or related technical equivalent. MBA is an advantage','2020-07-28',956),(803,'Product Manager','monday.com is looking for a Product Manager who will be responsible for leading a world-class team of engineers & designers and is passionate about building ground-breaking, lovable products. You will join our Product Team based in our headquarters in Tel Aviv, Israel.\n\n\nRequirements:\nYou have at least 3 years of experience as a product manager with a proven track record of delivering impactful products - must\nYou possess natural ownership abilities and entrepreneurial qualities - youre self-driven and you feel comfortable motivating, leading, and making decisions without consensus\nYou are passionate about building great user experiences, and you have a keen eye for details, UX, and design\nYou have strong communication skills and have the ability to thoroughly explain the rationale of product decisions\nYou are analytical and experienced in working both with qualitative insights and quantitative data to drive product decisions. You know your way around A/B tests, analytics tools and user interviews, surveys, and usability tests\nYou are a fast learner, adaptive, and thrive in a fast paced, ever-changing environment\nPrevious experience leading SaaS products/ consumer products Advantage\nPrevious entrepreneurial or consulting experience Advantage\n\n\nhttps://www.startupforstartup.com/back-to-the-roots-from-founding-a-startup-to-joining-one/\nhttps://www.startupforstartup.com/the-methodology-behind-monday-coms-growth-tactics/\nhttps://www.startupforstartup.com/on-partners-resellers-and-channels-8/\nhttps://www.startupforstartup.com/user-interviews-data-isnt-just-numbers/\nhttps://www.startupforstartup.com/defining-and-measuring-success/\n\n\nAbout The Role:\nEstablish a shared vision for your product across the company while working with talented cross-functional team members (across engineering, design, customer success, marketing, sales, etc.). Youll take full ownership and have a massive impact on the company\nDrive focus and speed within your team to ship products people need and love\nCollect and analyze a wide range of inputs to identify opportunities to make sure your team is always working on the most impactful things\nEvaluate the teams solutions through qualitative methods such as user interviews, usability tests & surveys along with data analysis and AB tests\nUnderstand the market, competition, and champion our users to craft product strategies that will lead to long term success\nMotivate a group of some of the smartest, most committed, and fun people youve ever worked with.\n\n\nSocial Title:\nProduct Manager\n\n\nOur Team:\nThe Product Team is a group of innovative individuals who are passionate about building impactful, state-of-the art products and thrive in a hyper-growth and problem-solving environment. Our work not only shapes our entire platform, it also influences the day-to-day of more than 100,00 businesses (and counting) which rely on monday.com.','2020-07-23',367),(804,'Product Manager, Trading','If you dare to change the world, keep reading!\nJoin our leading product team, passionate about creating the very best products eToro offers to its 10M users worldwide.\nAs a product manager, you will be involved in every aspect of the product development process, from brainstorming the next great product innovation to tweaking UI right before launch. .\nThe position calls for someone who can take initiative, work independently, enjoy working hard on a challenging environment and learn on the job quickly to make a difference.\nAs a product manager you will gather the business requirements from the company business owners and internal users, define roadmap, design and launch product features.\nThis role is focused on the Trading product domain.\nWhat will you be doing\nServe as the primary point of contact for all aspects of your products domain.\nDesign, manage and launch new features that are all about increasing user engagement and our competitive edge.\nDevelop a detailed product roadmap based on the companys existing strategic plan, and manage all product milestones through agile workflow.\nEnsure that the engineering team, the testers, customer support and all people across the company know exactly where the product is, and where it is going.\nWork closely with Trading and customer service departments to identify new product needs.\nWork closely with the Engineering team to build new features and make changes and improvements as needed.\nEnsure that the product adheres to the highest standards of usability and quality.\nCreate required deliverables for all project lifecycle phases, including project schedules, scope documents, mockups, wireframes and requirements.\nTrack and measure user engagement and analyze results. Leverage data to optimize critical flows and user paths in order to increase conversion rates and overall growth.\nProactively seek out, track and remove barriers to completing a project.\nDrive people and projects through pure leadership and passion to the products you own.\n\n\n\nRequirements:\nWant to join? If you:\nHave a track record launching things successfully, on time.\nTell us what you launched and how you made a difference.\nHave strong written, verbal communication and presentation skills, including the ability to communicate between technical and non-technical personnel.\nHave the ability to understand and take ownership of complex processes and business needs and translate them to simple, effective and scalable product solutions.\nGreat interpersonal relations and ability to collaborate with multiple functions.\nExperience in data analysis and reporting systems.\nHave knowledge or background in Finance and/or experience in Trading.\nHave a proven ability to manage and follow up on multiple concurrent tasks and requests on tight deadlines.\nHave knowledge and love for technology, design, mobile, social and online trends.\nFamiliar with project management procedures and methodology, especially requirements management, planning, scheduling and agile methodologies.\nIt will also be nice if you:\nHave a B.S./B.A. in Computer Science or a degree in a related field.\nHave knowledge or background in Blockchain and/or experience in Trading Crypto.\nHave Experience with designing and launching consumer web products.\nHave knowledge or experience with UX/UI design.\nBesides that you must possess the following qualities and skills:\nA self-starter with an initiative personality.\nAbility to work well with interfaces as well as work independently.\nExcellent organizational and project management skills.\nPassionate about user experience.\nAbility to think outside the box and come with great initiatives.\nPhenomenal learning abilities.\n\n\nThis position is a full time position','2020-07-16',339),(805,'Product Manager','Guardio is a Tel Aviv based Cyber Security startup, developing a browser and cloud protection tool for consumers (B2C).\n\nGuardio is seeking a seasoned Product Manager to join us.\n\nYou will\n\"Own\" the product\'s user experience and feature set and act as the product evangelist to build awareness within the company\nOptimize the customer experience and key KPIs through onboarding, retention and upselling.\nLead the product lifecycle from ideation to launch and success.\nDefine and analyze metrics that inform the success of products.\nEngage closely with the R&D, support, and marketing teams to gather requirements.\nConduct customer segmentation, define and understand the target customers persona, and collect and analyze customers\' needs.\nWho we are looking for\n2+ years of product management experience, preferably in B2SMB or B2C products.\nData-driven and comfortable writing SQL queries.\nAble to balance quantitative and qualitative analysis - comfortable building your own queries to analyze data as well as conducting research through various discussions with customers and teammates.\nAnalytical and strategic thinker with strong attention to detail and end-to-end ownership.\nExperience leading cross-functional teams to deliver products and projects on tight deadlines.\nMust be able to think creatively, deal with ambiguity, and manage changing priorities.\nContinuously looking to maximize impact. As part of your application, and to show you read this far, please describe an accomplishment of yours that you believe had a big impact.\nWork from our offices in Tel Aviv.','2020-07-28',959),(806,'Product Manager','Optimove is the Science-First Relationship Marketing Hub, used by over 350 customer-centric businesses to drive measurable growth by scaling customer engagement. Were obsessed with what drives customer behavior and strive to provide our clients the solution to foster long-lasting customer relationships. The Optimove family is 220 strong, spread over three locations: New York, London, and Tel Aviv.\nTwo-thirds of our managers were promoted from within. If youre looking to develop your career, get acknowledged for your efforts, and work with dedicated people who love what they do, youve come to the right place.\nOptimove is looking for a Product Manager to join our growing Product team in Israel. This is a key position, and the ideal candidate will have B2B Product Management experience, strong Product Discovery skills, and data and analytics orientation. The candidate will thrive in a fast-paced and innovative development environment, that requires strong problem-solving skills and independent self-direction, coupled with an aptitude for team collaboration and open communication.\nResponsibilities:\n• Identify and understand customers business challenges through direct and frequent interactions with customers, as well as close collaboration with sales, marketing, customer success, data science, operations, and professional services and come up with valuable, usable, feasible and viable solutions\n• Translate these solutions into clearly articulated product requirements in the form of User Stories for new features and for improvements to existing features. This is based on thorough understanding of the user needs and on feedback from customers and stakeholders.\n• Collaborate closely with UX designers and engineers, to provide context, clarity and motivation, communicate the needs, combine functional and technical requirements with great designs, groom user stories, verify correct implementation, prioritize and provide solutions to challenges and difficulties in real time.\n• Orchestrate product releases and feature launches across multiple departments to verify relevant training, documentation, enablement, and internal and external communications are done effectively and successfully.\n• Collect, analyze and present usage analytics to measure and improve the product\n• Contribute to product strategy definition, roadmapping and internal process improvements\n• Stay current with industry knowledge and best practices for product management and UX design\n\n\nRequirements:\n• At least 3 years of experience as a Product Manager for B2B SaaS web/mobile applications, with multiple paying customers\n• Experience working with large R&D organizations (20+ engineers), in Agile Scrum, with excellent understanding of the methodology and practices\n• Fluent English with excellent communication skills (written and verbal)\n• Strong technical understanding required for effective collaboration with R&D\n• Excellent people skills maintaining strong and effective working relationships with peers\n• Meticulous attention to detail\n• Independent, proactive, takes ownership and accountable\n• Smart, curious, self-learner and enthusiastic about product management and UX design\n• Comfortable with multi-tasking\n• Willing to occasionally travel abroad (usually up to 4 times a year, USA and/or EU)\n\nExperience and knowledge in any of the following will be of high value:\n• Managing MarTech products\n• Working with data scientists on AI/ML products\n• User research including identifying user personas, prototyping, usability testing\n• Ability to extract data independently from SQL DBs\n• Mobile applications and technology\n• Data warehousing products and technology\n• Managing products with rich APIs and SDKs, where the customer/user is IT or R&D\n\n\n\nSite:\nIsrael','2020-07-08',889),(808,'Product Manager','Serverless & microservices radically changing software development as we know it, allowing organizations unprecedented pace of innovation.\nThe Lumigo SaaS platform enables organizations to develop modern cloud applications while preserving visibility & control throughout the application lifecycle from dev-time to runtime.\nWe are seeking a senior product manager to execute on the product vision based on deep understanding of developers\' use cases.\nYou will work closely with some of the most innovative organizations spearheading the serverless transformation from the one side and some of the brightest R&D minds on the other.\n\nResponsibilities\nUnderstand and represent the challenges and requirements of the users (developers).\nTranslate requirements to specifications - collect requirements, develop user stories, collaborate with Product Design to drive and validate UX requirements, provide specifications to R&D.\nProduct backlog - Define and prioritize the product backlog based on market research and competitive analysis, supported by ongoing customers interaction.\nGuide all relevant parties as part of the feature development including beta users and validate the result.\nDrive projects across departments to full completion.\nMetrics - Lead data-driven product decisions by setting and analyzing product metrics.\n\n\nRequirements:\n2+ years experience building B2D SaaS products, writing user stories, overseeing the day-to-day product development.\nExcellent verbal, written, and interpersonal skills, with a demonstrated ability to create and deliver presentations and persuasive papers.\nTeam-player, self-managed and fast-learner.\nAbility and drive to work long hours when needed\nMost importantly, a person we\'ll have fun working with :)\nAdvantage:\nMonitoring / Serverless products experience\nDevelopment background','2020-07-14',962),(809,'Product Manager','Playtika, the largest gaming company in Israel and #1 worldwide in its genre, is seeking for a Product Guru.\nWe are looking for a brilliant, organized and creative person. Someone with talent, passion and experience.\nIn this position you will need lead, invent, get things done by taking an idea and turn it to reality.\nWe believe in a combination of collaboration and autonomous work, working effectively to achieve high-reaching results. A Product\nOwner in the deepest sense of the term.\n\nResponsibilities:\nOwn web/mobile product features roadmaps from end to end\nEnsure success and growth of the product by developing a product vision, strategy, roadmap and lifecycle management framework\nCollect and analyze requirements, write clear and detailed MRDs, PRDs, UI/XU & flow, wireframes, defining AB test and user stories, prioritize backlog and handle development/engineering\nAnalyze the success of the feature once its released to production, responsible for the usage data and patterns, and run tests to optimize & improve performance and business results\nWork with all relevant cross-functional teams (R&D,Designers, BI/BA, etc.) to guarantee smooth, efficient implementation\nFind opportunities for key initiatives to improve the customer experience\nManage ongoing maintenance and improvement of product features\n\n\nRequirements:\nAt least two years of experience as a Product Manager in the gaming field or B2C Industry\nGoal oriented, highly motivated, takes full ownership on projects.\nMover & shaker, who adapts well to a dynamic and rapidly changing environment\nStrong organizational and analytical skills, high attention to details\nGreat communicator who is able to clearly convey messages in written and oral form (in English)\nAbility to partner with cross-functional disciplines and to influence effectively\nA problem solver highly inventive thinker that will provide insightful, innovative solutions to any problem\nProject management abilities and passion for games\nIf you feel the above describes you perfectly apply now!\n\n\nBusiness Unit:\nBingo\n\nSub Department:\nProduct\n\nWebsite Group:\nProduct','2020-07-06',871),(810,'Product Manager','Intro\n\nPerimeter 81 is looking for a Product Manager to join our rapidly growing network security startup. The Product Manager will be responsible for defining, planning, and executing new features for our award-winning SaaS platform.\n\nIn this role, you will work closely with our R&D, Marketing, Sales, and Design teams to contribute to the development and evolution of a fast-growing network security startup. The Product Manager will be responsible to prioritize projects and make the impact our customers want the most.\n\nThis role is perfect for you if you have a strong technical, UX and analytical background that can think holistically about customer pain points. You will be involved in defining and developing new products & features that take us to the next level.\n\nThis is a full-time position from our offices in the heart of Tel Aviv. It is the perfect opportunity for someone to join a fast-paced startup that is growing quickly in an exciting space.\n\nAbout Perimeter 81\n\nPerimeter 81 is a Zero Trust Secure Network as a Service that is simplifying network security for the modern and distributed workforce. The team of security as a service experts comes together every day to deliver a truly innovative, world-class network security service. Perimeter 81\'s clients range from SMBs to Fortune 500 businesses and industry leaders across a wide range of sectors, and its partners are among the world\'s foremost integrators, managed service providers and channel resellers. In 2019, Gartner selected Perimeter 81 as a \"Cool Vendor in Network and Cyber-Physical Systems Security”. We recently completed a $10M funding round led by our new partners, SonicWall, an industry leader in network security.\n\nJob Description\nTake full responsibility and ownership of the Perimeter 81 features, from ideation to production and measurement\nCreate and manage feature plans, roadmaps, project plans and specifications\nCollaborate with marketing and R&D on product development during the discovery phase to assess value, usability, and feasibility of features\nManage and have a significant impact on the product\'s user experience and feature set and act as the product evangelist to build awareness within the company\nResearch, gather and define product’s business requirements from discussions with clients and other sources for current and future product releases\nWriting solution definitions for new features\nWork closely with customers and partners to get feedback and define new features\nRequirements\nAt least 3 years experience as a Product Manager (SaaS)\nBachelor’s Degree in computer science or engineering\nNative level of English (written and spoken) - a must\nStrong technical background with understanding or hands-on experience in software development\nExcellent communication and presentation skills with a high level of self-training and self-drive\nStrong understanding of all aspects of the product development lifecycle, including product strategy development, requirements definition, UX design, engineering, QA and launch\nCustomer-oriented and experienced in working with enterprise customers\nExperience working in cybersecurity or a SaaS product - an advantage','2020-07-28',964),(811,'Product Manager','Playworks, ironSource’s in-house mobile creative team, works with all the lea