nager','Job Description\nResponsible for development of IDE products in terms of product management in the areas of SWRO, Reuse, BWRO & Brine Management\nAnalysis and in-depth understanding of market needs, gathering clients\' and consultants\' technical, regulatory and commercial requirements and consultants in various markets, market needs.\nAdaptation of the Company offering to the needs of the different markets - processing customers\' needs into guidelines for R & D and engineering activities, as well as guidelines for marketing and sales activities.\nFamiliarity with the Best Practices and aligning these with the product\nActivities with potential customers, strategic partners, consultants and engineering companies to promote IDE products in the market.\nSupport pre- and post-sales activities by the members of the Company sales team with customers in the field.\nIdentify suppliers of technological components and partners with complementary technologies in the field – lead internal activities for evaluating technology/capabilities.\nInterfacing with department across the organization (sales and marketing, supply chain, engineering, pricing).\nJob Requirements\nEducation: B.Sc. in Engineering - mandatory.\nBachelor or master\'s degree in Business Administration - advantage.\n3-5 years\' experience in a commercially-oriented position (sales/product management, etc.)\nPrior experience in a position in engineering, environmental engineering or water treatment development must.\nPrior experience in a position in engineering, environmental engineering or water treatment development must.\nExcellent English – mandatory; other languages - advantage\nLocation: Israel','2020-07-06',966),(813,'Product Manager','Description\n\nThe Product Manager is reporting to Director Product Manager and responsible for product line planning and execution throughout the Product Life cycle process in the company. By applying smart fusion of market needs, competitive landscape, customer r