re in charge of the initial part of the attribution process (collecting engagements) and all Deep Linking related work.\nWhat you\'ll do\nManage the product\'s lifecycle end-to-end\nDefine the priorities of the product through understanding customers\' needs and company vision\nDeliver a great experience to our product\'s users\nHelp to create the product\'s vision and to build the plan to achieve it through concrete milestones and versions.\nCommunicate product status internally and externally\nResearch and understand key customers, market trends, upcoming opportunities, and challenges.\nWork with our clients directly first-hand feedback is important\nCollaborate with the Business, Marketing, CSMs and R&D teams internally\nWhat you have\nAt least 5 years of experience working as a product manager in a SaaS or mobile app company\nBasic technical knowledge of web and mobile development\nStrong leadership and project management skills with the ability to mobilize cross-functional teams\nAbility to turn requirements, ideas, and a vision into well processed and thought out documentation, presentations, and wireframes.\nAbility to analyze data and extract insights out of it.\nExperience working as part of a team including R&D, other product managers, and the design team (UX/UI).\nBonus Points\nPractical knowledge of digital marketing and advertising technologies\nExpertise in marketing cloud solutions, online campaign optimization and analytics and/or digital marketing solutions integration\nExperience in the design and development of mobile components\nBeing introduced by an AppsFlyer team member\nFamiliarity with AppsFlyer system as a previous customer/partner\nAs a global company operating in 16 countries across 5 continents, we reflect the human mosaic of the diverse and multicultural world in which we live. We ensure equal opportunities for all of our employees and promote the recruitment of diverse talents to our global teams without consideration of race, gender, culture, or sexual orientation. We value and encourage curiosity, diversity, and innovation from all our employees, customers, and partners.\n\n\"As a Customer Obsessed company, we must first be Employee Obsessed. We need to make sure that we provide the team with the tools and resources they need to go All-In.\" Oren Kaniel, CEO','2020-07-12',158),(816,'Product Manager','A leading fintech company located in Hertzlia Pituachis looking for a Product Manager As a Product manager, you will be responsible for: Product management of the online products, responsible for defining and implementing the relevant products Roadmap in, writing PRDs (product requirements documents) and User stories. Providing support throughout all the products development stages, up to its launch, while working jointly with the product developers. Conduct competitive intelligence research and identify market opportunities in the online trading domain. Defining the product interfaces and user experiences (UI, UX) of the front and back end users.\n\nConstant monitoring of new product developments, as well as developments in the world of online and online trading. At least 2 years of experience as a product manager. Knowledgeable in the world of online trading - an advantage. Product management abilities Able to work with numerous interfaces, matrix management, amicable assertiveness.\n\nBackground / experienced in Internet and mobile technologies. High analytical skills, business / marketing oriented. English at a very good level, including verbal expression abilities. Proactive, demonstrating autonomy and accountability.\n\nTeam Player with the ability to Lead by Example. You Might Also Have: Knowledgeable in the world of online trading - an advantage. Working with B2C and B2B - an advantage.','2020-07-28',970),(817,'Telco Product Manager','About the role:\nWe are looking for a product manager to join our product team. Product Managers in Anodot are a one-stop shop - inbound, outbound and all-around players.\nThe product manager we are looking for will lead our evolving portfolio of Autonomous Network products - Anomaly detection, Integrations, Dashboards, Correlation, Forecast and others.\nTogether with our elite team of engineers, data scientists, marketers and designers who build and maintain the most advanced analytics, operations, monitoring product to date. Processing tens of billions of data points each month to power an elegant user interface for thousands of users.\nWere looking for:\n5 years of experience working with software engineering teams with at least 3 years of hands-on product management or product design experience.\nThorough understanding of telco operations, network and data challenges (OSS, BSS) - a must.\nDemonstrated ability to gather user requirements from a number of sources, build a compelling product vision and translate it into actionable requirements for our development teams.\nExperience building web technologies and products.\nA strong track record of project delivery for large, cross-functional projects.\nExperience in development and documentation of on-prem products.\nSuper creative thinker, with a keen eye for design and details.\n\nWhy choose Anodot?\nWe are the future of business monitoring.\nLeading the market to the Autonomous Monitoring Era. Funded by world-class VC firms and proudly serving some of the worlds largest brands including: Tesla, Facebook, T-Mobile, Atlassian, AT&T and many others.\nOur ambitious, collaborative team makes it possible by finding creative solutions to new challenges with scaling, reliability, design,and customer service. Anodot has a team of 70+ in our offices in San Francisco, Raanana, London and Sydney.','2020-07-14',971),(818,'Product Owner','Spot is a dynamic, fast-growing startup with headquarters in Tel-Aviv and additional offices in San Francisco, New York, Washington D.C., and London. With innovative technology that is revolutionizing the cloud-computing industry and a team of highly motivated and creative employees, our vision is to optimize the way DevOps and R&D teams consume Cloud Computing.\n\nThe Product Owner will be a member of our growing product and technology team. We are looking for a hands-on, technology proficient, team player who can define and deliver innovative solutions for new and existing products. As a Product Owner at Spot, you will gain ownership over a product, deliver functional requirements and technical solutions by coordinating with R&D and Sales teams. This position involves the development of the company’s internal and client-facing applications, as well as the data that drives them.\n\nThe ideal candidate will:\nHave a proven track record of shipping user-facing SaaS products\nHave a strong technology and/or engineering foundation that drives innovation and vision\nPossess great UX and UI instincts\nHighly organized and capable of working on several projects\nSelf-learn new technologies and concepts\nObsess over the details, while also focusing on what comes next. A strong technical background, and are comfortable making impactful decisions\nWork under tight deadlines\nTake responsibility for deliverables\n\nResponsibilities\n\nDeliver PRDs with prioritized features and corresponding justification\nTrack product performance, specifically to analyze the successful completion of short and long-term goals\nManage both internal and external professional documentation\nWork with scrum masters on defining user story details\nPrioritize agile teamwork efforts in alignment with strategic goals and objectives\nAnswer questions from dev teams to clarify requirements\nEncourage innovation and ongoing process improvements\nCollaborate with cross-functional team members to plan software releases\nBrief and train the sales force and other customer-facing colleagues\n\nRequirements:\nBasic Qualifications:\nTwo years of previous experience as a product owner\nSolid technical background, with understanding or hands-on experience in Software development or DevOps Engineering etc.\nSolid understanding of the product life cycle\nSolid understanding of the Scaled Agile Framework\nExperience in cloud technologies\nExceptional communication and presentation skills, both in English and Hebrew\nStrong interpersonal skills, ability to influence others, and work effectively in a cross-functional team\nExcellent soft skills, interpersonal relationship abilities, and working in a fast-paced environment\n\nPreferred Qualifications:\nUnderstanding in Cloud Finops\nExperience in CI/CD platforms\nDegree in Computer Science, Information Systems, industrial engineering, or equivalent','2020-07-28',729),(819,'Product Manager – Security','A leading cybersecurity company is looking for a.Product Manager\nAct as product owner for features and projects.\nManage the product backlog. Write clear use cases and requirements, detail the functionality which will be executed by the engineering team.\nGather product requirements from customers, sales and the market. Define the product roadmap.\nWork closely with development teams to determine technical solutions, prioritize work, adapt to new information and ensure high quality deliverables.\nWork with security experts like security researchers, SOC analysts and incident response teams to understand customers’ requirements and difficulties.\n\nדרישות:\n3+ years of experience as a Product Manager building successful enterprise Big Data or security platforms\nDemonstrate conversational understanding of development technologies, being able to understand APIs and technical concepts\nExperience working closely with development teams\nHighly organized, detail oriented and deadline focused\nStrong analytical and decision making skills to prioritize activities, issues and customer needs in a highly dynamic environment\nStrong communication skills, both verbal and written.\nTeam player, positive attitude and collaborative.\nCybersecurity domain knowledge – an advantage\n\nאיזור: גוש דן\n\nתחום: מוצרפרויקטים','2020-07-19',155),(820,'Product Manager','Natural Intelligence is a global leader in the online comparison market. Our goal is to simplify decision-making and connect customers with valuable brands.\nOur technology helps millions of consumers around the world make smart, confident and informed buying decisions. We do so by creating trusted comparison websites that enable consumers to easily compare products and services online.\nWe are seeking an experienced product management leader to join our product team. This is a unique opportunity to work on one of our most strategic and growing businesses Financial Services, where we help millions of users decide which provider they will choose for their mortgage, personal loan, or even insurance for their beloved pet.\nWhat youll do:\nLead the definition and development of a new financial services comparison website.\nBuild a unified product vision and product scope across multiple stakeholders.\nIntegrate user research, market analysis, business and technical needs into product requirements.\nCollaborate with multiple stakeholders: SEO, Content Managers, Marketing Managers, Designers and Analysts to constantly enhance user experience and satisfaction.\nWork in great synergy with backend and frontend development teams to execute the product roadmap.\nAnalyze product and feature performance, evaluate the success or failure of features, determine next steps, and constantly use data to guide decision making.\nConduct A/B tests to measure performance and iterate through ongoing experiments.\n\n\nRequirements:\n4+ years of product management experience in an internet company.\nExperience in building consumer products that involve full stack features - user experience and backend.\nExperience in complex funnel definition and quantitative and qualitative analysis.\nUnderstanding of SEO and content management.\nExperience in building product plans, defining goals and success metrics, and tracking execution.\nExperience in conversion optimization - planning and performing A/B tests.\nKnowledge in the financial services space (e.g. personal lending and insurance) - advantage.','2020-07-27',160),(821,'Product Owner','Net-Bet is looking for a talented product owner to lead cross functional development teams and generate awesome products.\n\nAs a product owner you will be responsible for building product backlog which is aligned with the company milestones, missions and opportunities while focusing on VALUE.\n\nResponsibilities\n\nYou will lead one or more teams, defining “what” to build.\nYou will create prototypes and define minimal viable products backlog.\nYou will create user stories and acceptance criteria.\nWhen needed you will analyze the stories into development tasks focusing on the details.\nYou will be allocated with a long-term company mission, to lead and evolve.\nYou will measure, monitor, experiment, and constantly learn about the product in order to build valued features.\nYou will work closely and aligned with other product owners, development teams, and cross functions in the company.\nYou will make sure that your teams have sufficient work at all time.\nYou will play a significant role shaping our future and you will have the opportunity to learn and grow with the team and the company.\n\nRequirements\n\nSystem Analysis background\nYou have a technical background (some coding experience is a plus), and you gravitate towards solving problems with technology\nProduct Owner background in an agile process\nMVP & prototyping\nYou’re ambitious, independent and dedicated, and willing to get hands-on solving any problems needing help to move forward\nYou have excellent analytical skills and experience drawing insights from internal and external data\nYou’re extremely structured, organized and have an outstanding attention to details\nYou approach your work with a collaborative and team-oriented mindset\nExperience in web & mobile products – advantage\nEx