ased on business value, collect and analyze requirements, write clear and detailed specs, create wireframes and define A/B tests.\nAnalyze results of features after deployment, iterate based on data to improve performance.\nGuide and mentor assigned production teams.\nWork in close collaboration with production, BI, analytics, content, CRM and game economy departments to ensure smooth execution with minimum iterations.\nProactively seek opportunities to drive key initiatives to improve user experience and boost game KPIs.\n\n2+ years experience as a B2C product manager, preferably in the online gaming or gambling space.\nStrong problem solving skills and ability to come up with creative solutions to complex issues.\nData driven and analytical with exceptional attention to detail.\nStrong communication skills, ability to manage cross-functional interfaces and guide remote teams.\nFluent English - both written and verbal.\nExperience with JIRA - a plus','2020-07-28',979),(826,'Security Product Manager','מיקום: ת\"א והמרכז\n\nתיאור המשרה:\nחברת סטארט-אפ חלוצה בתחומה מגייסת Security Product Manager.\nהחברה מפתחת פלטפורמת SaaS אשר מעבירה תקשורת ואבטחת מידע על הענן. מדובר בפתרון תקשורת ארגונית מלא, שנותן מענה מקיף לצרכי הארגון באמצעות ארכיטקטורת ה-Cloud-Native Carrier.\nהתפקיד כולל עבודה בצוות, כאשר כל אחד עוסק בתחום אחר ומקבל את הבלעדיות עליו. מחפשים מנהל/ת מוצר לתחום הSecurity. תפקיד מאד רחב ואסטרטגי בכפיפות לדירקטור מוצר.\nגייסו 125M דולר, מונים כ180 עובדים, נמצאים בתל אביב על קו רכבת.\nשלח/י קו\"ח!\n\nדרישות המשרה:\n4 שנות נסיון בניהול מוצר מחברת Security\nנסיון בפיתוח\nמס\' משרה: 120376','2020-07-20',76),(828,'Product Manager','Rapyd is a financial technology company that allows businesses to accept and make payments anywhere, using any method. With Rapyd, businesses can quickly enter new markets and integrate financial tech into their apps and software.\nWere a global organization and diversity is in our DNA. We have offices in London, Tel Aviv, Singapore, and California, as well as employees in Mexico, Brazil and Africa. Rapyd helps businesses and their customers pay and be paid however they choose. Our fintech-as-a-service platform enables any payment type for in-country or cross-border commerce. Clients seamlessly integrate local payment methods like bank transfers, e-wallets, or cash into digital applications from a single API. Rapyd operates the worlds largest local payments network that connects to over 2B+ consumers transacting around the corner and across the globe.\nRapyd is looking for a dynamic, high impact Product Manager for its core payments product management team to help extend our network of networks lead integration with new partners, optimize performance, and define and develop new features, and services.\nThis Product Manager will be responsible for aggressively expanding our network footprint, deeply understanding the nuances of each payment experience we offer, define the integration and feature roadmap, prioritize the backlog, develop the product solution and design, and lead execution and launch end to end.\nThis is a global role, based in Mountain View, CA. working with engineering and other product managers globally, in addition to collaborating with engineering, operations, client and professional services, support, and our sales, business development, and network teams.\nIn addition, this role will be a member of our Americas team and will work closely with the team to ensure Rapyd goes to market effectively across the region and is able to deliver a hyperlocal payment platform that unlocks growth and creates opportunities in the largest and most dynamic payments market in the world.\n\nResponsibilities:\nLead all aspects of product management and development including design, planning, specification, product development, go-live, and rollout\nWork with other Product Managers globally and cross-functionally across Rapyd to drive excellence in our network\nProvide day-to-day product delivery and quality management\nEnsure awareness of product status and roadmap risks across Rapyd\nDrive post-launch look-backs and internal process improvements\n\n\n\nRequirements:\n\n3+ years of product management experience in payments, financial services, or technology company\nAt least 3 years in payments, and a clear knowledge of the payments lifecycle that drives your Spidey sense\nMust be able to talk knowledgeably with eCommerce players, banks, lenders, FinTechs, and clients who live and breathe payments every day\nExperienced as an Agile product owner\nWell developed product management skills\nDemonstrated experience developing advanced technical specifications\nExperience integrating third-party providers and clients\nExcellent verbal and written communication skills\nGood knowledge of international and online payments\nExcellent program and project management skills\nStrong personal leadership skills\nGreat analytical and problem-solving skills\nFluent or native English speaker\nBachelor\'s degree in Computer Science preferred','2020-07-28',982),(829,'Product Manager','About this position\nWe are looking for a Product Manager that will join our team in our Tel Aviv office to be responsible for planning, designing and delivering optimal consumer-facing services and products. The position requires proven experience in building digital consumer products, optimizing customer acquisition funnels, and a natural tendency to operate based on data.\nDuties & Responsibilities\nDevelop in-depth knowledge and understanding of Sproutt\'s customers, competitors, partners, and the overall landscape\nDevelop product strategies to drive the company\'s business objectives\nCollaborate with designers, engineers, marketers, data scientists, and content writers to transform the strategy into plans, requirements, wireframes, mocks, etc.\nLead the product lifecycle process including testing, optimization, and enhancements\nSupport the sales and customer success organization with product related knowledge\nRequirements\n3+ years experience working as a consumer-facing product manager - MUST\nStrong analytical, design, rapid prototyping skills\nExcellent communication and personal skills\nExperience with analyzing consumer behavior in a digital environment\nUp to date, and constantly learning, modern design, consumer products, and apps\nPerfect English - MUST\nExperience with agile development','2020-07-09',735),(830,'Product Manager','We are looking for a promising Product Manager to join as a key member of our team, and help us define the future of our product line. As a Product Manager, you have a deep understanding of the user experience and passion for challenges, people, and sports! You will work closely with our clients and represent their voice.\n\nWhat you’ll do:\nBe the client\'s voice. Write detailed product requirements of new features, API capabilities, integrations, and UI components. Create wireframes for new products and features.\nWork closely with external and internal R&D, Technical writing, UI design, Customer Success, Support, and Marketing teams.\nDefine and maintain product roadmap together with the product team and in coordination with the company\'s executive team.\nDefine and analyze metrics that inform the success of products and features.\nWhat you’ll need:\n3-5 years of product management experience in B2B SaaS High-Tech companies.\nStrong understanding of all aspects of the product development lifecycle, including product strategy building, requirements definition, UX/UI, engineering, QA, and release.\nExperience in writing detailed product specs.\nStrong management skills ability to drive inbound processes.\nAbility to work in a super challenging and dynamic startup environment.\nFluent in English, both written and verbal.\nLove for sports.\nTeam player, great communication skills with tech and non-tech people alike.\nDevelopment background and/or BSc in Computer Science- advantage.\nStrategic thinking skills, design skills, and user-experience orientation- advantage.','2020-07-09',984),(831,'Product Manager - Real-Time attribution Group','We\'re looking for a talent with a pioneering spirit to join the Real-time Attribution (RTA) Product team in our Herzliya office. The RTA team is responsible for the algorithms and our critical APIs to partners which allow us to build the best Mobile Marketing Analytics product. The ideal candidate will have a proven track record as a product manager of SaaS platform with deep technical knowledge of Big Data and SaaS real-time solutions.\n\nHe/she should also be a good listener who can distill product feedback and analyze market needs/trends to ensure that the AppsFlyer platform remains at the tops of its class. A good ability to handle product features with strategic partnerships with the top companies in the world (Such as Google, Facebook, Amazon).\nThe Product Team is committed to creating the product roadmap and making the vision a reality. The product team works closely with the business team to understand clients\' needs and with the R&D team to make it happen.\n\nMeasuring mobile advertising activities has never been more important for advertisers, and we\'re all about providing the most advanced tools for doing so.\nWhat you\'ll do\nManage the product lifecycle and its roadmap\nDefine and prioritize new feature releases\nDeliver a great experience to our product\'s users\nCommunicate product status internally and externally\nWork with our clients directly first-hand feedback is important\nCollaborate with the Business, Marketing and R&D teams internally\nCommunicate well with strategic partnerships\nWhat you have\nAt least 5 years of experience as a leading Product Manager\nExpertise in SaaS B2B Product Management\nLeader with the ability to get things done\nTeam player, ownership and sense of urgency\n\"Can-do approach\"\nDeep technical background\nBonus Points\nMobile marketing and advertising experience\nPrevious experience in design and development of business-side components\nBeing introduced by an AppsFlyer team member\nAs a global company operating in 16 countries across 5 continents, we reflect the human mosaic of the diverse and multicultural world in which we live. We ensure equal opportunities for all of our employees and promote the recruitment of diverse talents to our global teams without consideration of race, gender, culture, or sexual orientation. We value and encourage curiosity, diversity, and innovation from all our employees, customers, and partners.\n\n\"As a Customer Obsessed company, we must first be Employee Obsessed. We need to make sure that we provide the team with the tools and resources they need to go All-In.\" Oren Kaniel, CEO','2020-07-15',158),(832,'Product Manager','Kaltura’s mission is to power any video experience and deployed globally in thousands of companies and educational institutions and engages hundreds of millions of viewers at home, at work, and in school. Kaltura is a recognized leader in the Online Video Platform (Educational institutions and Enterprise companies such as Harvard, Yale, SAP, Oracle Etc.) and Cloud TV (Vodafone, Cellcom TV etc).\n\nOur core values are openness, flexibility, and collaboration, and we are the initiator and backer of the world\'s leading open-source video management project, which is home to more than 150,000 community members.\n\nWe like to think of ourselves as a cool, fun and talented group of professionals looking to create cutting-edge technology. Kaltura is a fast-paced environment where standards are high, and initiative is always encouraged.\n\nKaltura currently have approx. 500 employees across offices in New York, London, Sao Paolo, Singapore, and Tel Aviv. We are growing rapidly including positions all over the world.\n\nWe promote: a flexible work environment that encourages work-life-balance, internal mobility and relocation, community involvement, LGBTQ rights, refer-a-friend program and a newly launched paternity leave policy.\n\nRequirements:\nIf you are passionate about building products that change how people work, share, collaborate, and communicate, Kaltura\'s product team is the place for you. As a product manager on the team you will be responsible for imagining the roadmap and future of your products and executing on a plan to get there. This position requires technical savviness with a willingness to dive into protocols, alongside a passion for user experiences that delight our customers. It requires working with R&D on developing the product and prioritizing needs, as well as working alongside sales and marketing in presenting the products to customers and prospects. If you love a challenge and want to join a fast moving company to work on it, reach out!\n\nResponsibilities:\nPlan, develop and execute the product deliveries\nTranslate users’ needs into prioritized product requirements\nWrite product specifications, user stories and build wireframes. Work closely with UX/UI designers to deliver simple and engaging user experiences.\nLearn the market, competitors, future technologies\nWork with marketing on value prop and positioning and support marketing efforts in go-to-market plans.\nCollaborate with and support sales and sales engineering\nPresent products and roadmap to customers and prospects\nQualifications\n5+ years of experience in product management\nStrong UX/UI sense, hands on experience in creating wireframes\nTechnical background, preferably in video technologies\nExperience in working with R&D teams in an agile environment\nProven ability to drive research, planning, development and launch\nDetailed oriented and data driven, with strong analytical and problem solving skills\nTeam player with excellent communications skills and ability to influence cross-functional teams without formal authority\nExcellent English skills and ability to present in front of an audience – a must','2020-07-20',986),(833,'Product Manager','Job Description:\nWork with a team of Product Analysts and a dedicated agile development organization to drive execution of development projects\nWork with internal and external customers as well as business partners (mainly in North America) to understand the Cardiology market trends and the needs of the different stakeholders\nAnalyze data from internal and external resources and combine it to define innovative products and solutions\nCreate product documentation\nCollaboration with a variety of internal functions across the organization such as Development, Sales, Services, Support and Marketing and Business Development as the subject matter expert for the product suite\nAdditional Positions:\nProduct manager\n\nCategory:\nSoftware\n\nJob Qualifications:Required Qualifications:\nEngineering degree or computer science degree or relevant discipline\nTechnical and business orientation\nSelf-Driven individual\nWilling to travel abroad - 20% (Mainly to NA)\nExcellent English communication skills (both verbal and written)\nAt least 3 years work experience in a technology company\nCompany Occupation:\nBiotech/medical, High Tech, Internet related, Software application\n\nCompany Size:\nMedium (50 - 150)','2020-07-27',150),(834,'Product Manager','We are looking for a brilliant Product Manager to join our fast growing company and our amazing Product Team. Fiverrs product team is driving our rapid growth via product innovation and high pace product delivery. As a product manager at a consumer and e-commerce company you will make a huge impact by designing products that will be used by millions of people. You will join a flat organization, lead a multidisciplinary team, get the resources you need, work closely with the CEO and all the support you need to make your impact. This is the ultimate position for a leader, a product manager and a doer to influence!\n\n\nRequirements:\nAt least 3 years of relevant experience as a product manager.\nA Doer with proven track record of making an impact as an entrepreneur, leader or a product manager.\nStrong analytical skills, developing product hypotheses and understanding the results.\nStrong ability transforming opportunities and needs into products and features.\nGood understanding of UI/UX.\nSavvy learner, avid listener, articulated communicator and presenter.\nAbility to work in a fast paced internet startup environment.\nBA/MA/BSc/MSc in related fields.\n\n\nResponsibilities:\nMake an impact - grow the business by developing new products and features.\nLead a multidisciplinary team of developers, designers and analysts.\nPlan product roadmaps and execute on them.\nInnovate and prioritize products and features.\nInteract with other Fiverr teams maximizing the impact on Fiverrs growth and business.\n\n\nShort description:\nFiverr is looking for a talented and experienced Product Manager to join our TLV team!\n\n\nPerks:\nWhen you join our team, you\'re helping create opportunities for anyone in the world to build their business, brand, or dream. Is there a more meaningful benefit than that? To top it off we also have a tight-knit Fiverr employee culture, team gatherings, a pretty amazing office-space (even if you\'re working from home, we\'ll send the office to you), an opportunity to participate in Fiverr\'s stock option plan, daily virtual workout inspirations, ice cream delivered during hot summer months, and much more.\n\n\nvideo_url:\nhttps://www.youtube.com/embed/8rvtNcJPIlE\n\nEqual Opportunities:\nAt Fiverr, we prioritize diversity. We celebrate difference and embed it into every aspect of our workplace, from our community to our product. Fiverr is proud and committed to providing equal opportunity employment to all individuals regardless of race, color, religion, sex, sexual orientation, citizenship, national origin, disability, Veteran status, or any other characteristic protected by law. In addition, Fiverr will provide accommodation to individuals with disabilities or a special need.','2020-07-21',881),(835,'Product Manager','Aqua is looking for a product manager to join our Product Management team.\n\nWorking closely with engineering, sales, marketing and customers to ensure customer satisfaction goals are met.\n\nResponsibilities\n\nManage the product life cycle from planning to releasing\nCollect, specify and characterize product requirements by conducting market research and evaluating customers’ needs\nScope and prioritize activities based on business and customer impact\nWork closely with engineering on an ongoing basis to deliver with quick time-to-market and optimal resource\nServe as the knowledge focal point for the sales engineers and support on the product\nRepresent the company by visiting customers to solicit feedback on company products and services\nדרישות תפקיד\nBachelor’s Degree in computer science or engineering\nAt least 3+ years of experience as a product manager\nSolid technical background with understanding and/or hands-on experience in software development\nCustomer oriented and experienced in working with enterprise customers\nHigh level of self-training and self-drive\nDetail oriented, problem solver\nFluent English - writing and speaking\nExcellent communication & presentation skills\nExperience with cyber security domain – advantage\nExperience with cloud native / container-driven infrastructure – big advantage\n\nworkהגשת מועמדות','2020-07-21',724),(836,'Product Manager','Description\n\nWho Are We?\n\nMoovit (www.moovit.com), an Intel company, is a leading Mobility as a Service (MaaS) solutions company and the maker of the world’s #1 urban mobility app. Moovit was acquired by Intel in May 2020 to join forces with Mobileye and advance its MaaS strategy. Together, Moovit and Mobileye will accelerate the global adoption of autonomous transportation.\n\nMoovit’s iOS, Android, and Web apps guide people in getting around town effectively and conveniently, using any mode of transport. Introduced in 2012 it now serves over 800 million users in more than 3,200 cities across 103 countries.\n\nMoovit amasses up to six billion anonymous data points a day to add to the world’s largest repository of transit and urban mobility data. For governments, cities, transit agencies, and private companies, Moovit offers AI-powered MaaS solutions covering planning, operations, and optimization with proven value in reducing congestion, growing ridership, and increasing efficiency and asset utilization. Industry leaders such as Microsoft, Uber, and Cubic have partnered with Moovit to power their mobility offerings.\n\nThe Role\n\nWe are growing and looking for a talented Product Manager to join our Product team. Moovit’s Product team leads strategy & tactics of Moovit consumer B2C products in iOS, Android and Web, and the Moovit B2B2C & SaaS products, via high pace product delivery.\n\nAs a Product Manager, you’ll have the opportunity to make a huge impact by creating and optimizing products that will be used by hundreds of millions of people around the world who use Moovit apps and other leading mobility apps by the largest companies in the industry who are using Moovit B2B products.\n\nIf you’re passionate about creating true value for real needs, and eager to continuously optimize for the best UX based on data-driven decisions process, help mobility companies to be more efficient and successful, your place is with us!\n\nResponsibilities\nOwn the product development cycle from concept to production, through iterations and measurements.\nActively & constantly seek for new opportunities to impact product growth.\nPlan & prioritize new products creation and existing features optimization.\nLead a multidisciplinary team of Engineers, Product Designers and Product Analysts to drive rapid product releases.\nMaintain competitive product analysis\nDefine and analyze metrics that inform the success of products.\n\nRequirements\n\nLeader character who has a “Get things done” mentality.\nAt least 5 years in managing B2C or B2B2C consumer mobile apps with an international audience with 10s of releases and iterations.\nProven mobile-first product management experience in one of the following is a must, managing major features, from concepts to implementation with numerous interactions:\nNative app.\nMobile web.\nB2B2C SaaS mobile products.\nProven experience with user communication at scale via push notification / Email / SMS to segmented users.\nUnderstanding the mobile ecosystem:\nApp distribution methodologies\nUser acquisition methodologies\nRetention methodologies\nExperience in SEO (search engine optimization) and ASO (App Store Optimization) is an advantage.\nStrong analytical skills:\nDemonstrated ability in making data driven decisions.\nProven experience with A/B testing methodologies and implementations for native app or mobile web.\nBA / BSc in technical field. Computer Science, Industrial Engineering majoring in Information Systems - an advantage.\nStrong technological background. Be able to articulate accurate product logics and understand the implications of that with engineers.\nExcellent communications & presentation skills. Fluent and well articulated in English - writing and speaking.\nExperience with creating clear product specifications.\nExperience with planning and testing UX & Copy - Advantage.\nAbility to juggle multiple priorities and work in a fast-paced, dynamic environment','2020-07-02',403),(837,'Product Owner','Have we got a job for you?!\n\nProduct Owner, Petach Tikva,\n\nBuild Your Career | Have Fun | Make a Difference\n\nIf you\'re the kind of person that loves to get stuff done, collaborate with colleagues all over the world and is interested in joining a fast growth global company that is trusted by the world\'s top digital brands and truly cares for its customers, join us at Payoneer!\n\nCheck out our values\n\nWe\'re looking for an excellent and experienced Product Owner to join the product team and take part in developing the fintech industry\'s leading cross-border payment platform for marketplaces and other businesses. You will join a dynamic and fast-paced environment and work with cross-functional teams to design, build and roll-out products that deliver the company\'s vision and strategy. You will use data and customer feedback to define and drive new products and features.\nIs this you?\n\nWhat\'s the job?\nCollaborate with global cross-functional team to develop, market, and launch product globally\nOwnership of product requirements, driving the product life cycle in an agile methodology including user stories, personas, UX, UI, user stories and production of detailed specs (PRDs)\nWorking closely with the R&D teams to define requirements and ensure the end-to-end high quality product delivery\nUse A/B Testing, analytics, market research, usability studies, and competitive analysis to drive decision making\nMonitor product and business performance, and take action as needed to drive business success\nCommunicate the product roadmap to both internal and external key stakeholders\nHave you done this kind of stuff?\nAt least 3 years experience in PO roles. Preferably with experience in Fintech, Banking, Payment & credit-card industries\nStrong interpersonal skills leading and driving execution with cross-functional teams\nProven ability to execute complex projects in mid-size organizations\nExcellent written, verbal and presentation communication skills across technical and non-technical stakeholders\nExperienced in implementing products using Agile methodologies\nFamiliar with web methodologies for B2B and B2C including UX and UI definition\nBachelor degree in Computer Science or Engineering. MBA as a plus\nA few words about us\n\nPayoneer is a leading payment platform and one of the world\'s fastest growing fintech companies, ranking high on Inc. 5000, Deloitte Fast 500, and the CNBC Disruptor List. We empower entrepreneurs and businesses anywhere in the world – from Cairo to California, Buenos Aires to Bangalore and Tel Aviv to Tokyo – to go beyond and grow successful, sustainable businesses. With millions of customers in over 200 countries worldwide and trusted by clients like Amazon, Airbnb and Google, Payoneer truly connects anyone, anywhere, with opportunities to trade globally.','2020-07-06',321),(838,'Product Manager','PayU, a leading payment and Fintech company, in 18 high growth markets throughout Asia, Central and Eastern Europe, Latin America, the Middle East, and Africa, is redefining the way people buy and sell online for our 200.000+ merchants and millions of consumers. As a leading online payment service provider, we deploy more than 300 payment methods and PCI certified platforms to process approximately 1.2 million payments every single day.\n\n2 years ago we acquired ZOOZ, our one-stop shop for international payments operation markets who manage and optimize multiple payment providers through a single platform.\n\nWe are looking for a Product Manager to join our global team of payment evangelists developing the next generation product for PayU. If you are passionate, proactive and innovative and thrive in a dynamic, evolving, and global environment, this opportunity is for you!\n\nTo succeed in this role, you should love to build awesome products, thrive on analyzing and understanding the customer and the ecosystem, and shouldn\'t be afraid to get your hands dirty.\n\nWhat you\'ll do\n\nHelp grow our awesome PayU Hub - PayU\'s global offering\nWork with cross functional teams spread across different geographies, including operations, commercial, engineering, etc.\nOwn prioritise and manage the product roadmap of the team\nLead products lifecycle from ideation through technical development, and launch.\nResearch competitors\' services and products and explore new ways of improving your product\nTranslate merchant and internal stakeholders needs and different regulations into product goals and features\nCoordinate product releases with marketing, sales, operations and development teams.\n\nWhat you\'ll need to succeed\n\n2 years of product management experience in a global B2B company\nSuperb articulation, communications, and overall leadership capabilities\nThe ability to drive decisions, take action, and roll up your sleeves and dive into the work\nTeam player with the ability to contribute to the strong team culture of our co-located and diverse group\nPayments industry familiarity\nFluent in English – a must.','2020-07-14',992),(839,'Product Manager','A successful cybersecurity company, based in Hertzliya, is looking for a Product Manager to develop the core positioning and messaging for the product and act as a leader within the company.\n\nדרישות משרה\n4 years of experience as a Product Manager\nDemonstrated success defining and launching excellent products.\nמיומנויות ויתרונות\nProven ability to influence cross-functional teams without formal authority.\nStrong analytical skills.\nExcellent Integration skills.\nInnovative, open-minded, out-of-the-box thinking abilities.\nProven presentations and customer-facing skills.\nExcellent written and verbal communication skills.\nTechnical background, with experience in designing UX.\nExcellent teamwork skills.','2020-07-20',166),(840,'Technical Product Manager','As a Technical product manager in GDS you will be responsible for:\nDriving product vision and strategy, and creating capabilities that data science teams can leverage when building solutions for various PayPal business domains, such as: risk, marketing, sales, customer support, products and more.\nRepresenting the product to stakeholders and to peers across PayPal.\nEvangelizing product roadmap internally and externally in informal and formal settings.\nWorking cross-functionally and build strong relationships with key customers (data engineers, software engineers, product analytics and other business teams) that will allow understand gaps and build the right solutions.\nDefining and measuring key performance indicators to evaluate and understand product value.\nIdentifying new opportunities based on research, industry trends and best practices, driving innovation.\nDelivering Results\nSuccess In This Role Requires :\nPassion to product manager role with at least 4 years of experience as a product manager\nAn experience as a product manager of machine learning based solutions and/or big data platforms a plus\nA can do spirit combined with high energies and positive attitude\nGood problem solving skills\nExcellent and effective interpersonal and communication skills (written, verbal and listening).\nAbility to drive people\nSelf Starter which doesnt hesitate to proactively approach in order to learn fast\nSkilled at working with cross functional groups and matrix organizations in multiple geographies to manage multiple projects simultaneously.\nTech savvy which loves to stay on top of industry trends','2020-07-20',113),(841,'Sr. Product Manager - Technical Sizmek By Amazon','Sizmek by Amazon is seeking a talented Product Manager to join the Application team working on a variety of application related products.\nThe position requires strong understanding of the digital advertising ecosystem, with a balance of strategic judgment and technical acumen.\nThe ideal candidate is highly collaborative, able to build consensus across multiple teams, and ultimately building products that meet the goals of our business as well as our customers.\n\n\nYou will be in charge of the Sizmek by Amazon core application foundation (user management, billing, advertiser management, admin areas, etc.) and all associated customer-facing interfaces. In a nutshell, your team owns the foundation that every other team interacts with in order to deliver new features on Sizmek by Amazon. In addition, you will also take full ownership of our API product for both internal (within Amazon) as well as external customers. Responsibilities around our API product will include versioning, documentation, authentication,