 discipline (or equivalent work experience)\n· At least 3 years of experience as a product manager.\n· Track Record successfully driving large online products to market. Preferably from the online ad industry.\n· Familiarity with software development, and specific methodologies such as Agile.\n· Ability to work autonomously in a highly demanding and often ambiguous environment, with attention to detail and organizational skills\n· A results oriented approach with the ability to prioritize complex organizational objectives with aggressive deadlines.\n· Strong analytical and strategic thinking skills.\n· Excellent project management skills and attention to detail.\n· Passion for technical problem solving and driving towards solutions.\n· Great communication skills and ability to work effectively on projects with developers and software dev managers\n\n\nPreferred Qualifications\n\n· Familiarity with technical aspects of digital / display advertising\n· Passionate about generating big, creative ideas to differentiate in the market, growing the business and working with advertisers and agencies to build innovative products\n· Analytical and able to create sound business arguments backed up by data','2020-07-24',115),(842,'Product Manager','Localize.city is looking for an exceptional consumer product manager to join us in leading our B2C product in the US market. As the Product Manager at Localize you will drive product vision, feature design, prioritization and strategic planning. To be our ideal candidate, youll need to have extensive experience with online, consumer-facing products and a deep understanding of user experience and Agile methodologies. You are user-focused, use data to guide and drive your decisions and extremely detail-oriented.\nWhat you will be doing?\nTake full responsibility and ownership of features/funnels from ideation, through design, development, launch, growth and maintenance\nDrive a cross-functional team to realize maximum consumer and busin