 in data delivery.\nOwn and design data focused product features start to finish, including user stories, functional & non-functional requirements, feature specifications, quality control checks, and data dictionaries\nManage the prioritization and focus on data pipeline enhancements\nAuthor high-quality design specifications within an agile methodology based upon industry and customer requirements\nSupport release and sprint planning to ensure product enhancements support customers at the right time and the right sequence\nBe the voice of the customer to design product capabilities that meet customer/market needs\nCollaborate closely with Development, Data Scientists, Engineering, QA, and Product Management to ensure products are built and delivered with quality\nBe the product owner for communications between the Tel Aviv and NYC offices, including translating downstream business requirements into technical requirements, and communicating technical feasibility to end users\nWhat You\'ve Done\n6+ years hands-on Product Management experience, technical services, engineering, analytics or other related positions\nExperience working on data pipelines, such as designing ETL/ELT processes, schemas, and QC checks\nUnderstand data and data infrastructure, and experience designing transformations, mappings and working with reference tables\nUnderstanding of cloud based applications and designs\nProficient in SQL and Python\nUnderstanding of NoSql databases\nExperience investigating data issues and working with Data Scientists as needed for complex analysis\nExperience with data visualization tools, such as Tableau or Spotfire\nEnergized by working through complex problems and bringing innovation to products\nNice to have\nExperience in the Life Sciences industry, SaaS and/or enterprise products\nUnderstanding of healthcare data, including Rx Claims, Medical Claims and EHR\nFormer Data Engineer transitioned to Product Management\nMilitary experience in technical divisions\n