t\nFluent English speaking & writing is a must\nMarketing and Sales oriented','2020-07-15',1047),(891,'Strategic Partners Manager','We are looking for an all-star Strategic Partner Manager to join our Tel Aviv team . This person will be directly responsible for managing advertisers\' agencies and identifying up-sell /optimization opportunities at scale. The ideal candidate will be sales oriental, entrepreneurial, analytical, designer, creative and have strong relationship management skills.\n\nResponsibilities and skills:\nBuild a strong relationship with the media planners within each agency\nIdentify upsell opportunities at scale within each agency and their customers\nDrive the entire sales process, from introduction, demos / meetings to closing deals\nProvide feedback to customers on product offering and how to best service advertiser\'s needs\nHelp customers with campaign strategy & optimization and increase customer satisfaction\nTroubleshoot and resolve issues in a timely manner\nIdentify opportunities to improve products and the customer experience\nRequirements:\n2+ years’ of experience in ad agency with deep understanding of brand strategy and performance campaigns- a must!\nExperience in a lead generating / sales planning / strategic planning preferably at a digital media/agency company - a must!\nExperience in client-facing in the digital media /online publisher space - preferred\nProven communication, presentation, phone etiquette and general sales skills (mainly cold-calls).\nExperience in structuring and negotiating deals within the digital media space.\nA true passion for marketing, interactive & engaging content, native advertising and a strong sales drive.\nStrong analytical skills to collect business intelligence by conversing with clients and identifying trends.\nAbility to effectively prioritize and manage tasks within a fast-paced environment\nDemonstrated ability to work and collaborate within a high-performing team\nSelf-motivated, entrepreneurial, and comfortable dealing with ambiguity\nMail your CV to jobs@FORTVISION.com','2020-07-05',297),(900,'Ad Operator','appTV is looking for an ad operator that would assist us move faster more productively.\nIn this role, your main mission is to upload campaigns and banners to our unique platform according to different client’s & technical requirement.\nThis is a technical operational, back office position, in which you would be exposed to the online advertising industry and how it is working from Behind the Scenes.\n\nIf you are:\nA Responsible person\nWith high attention to details\nTechnical orientated\nAble to work with order and organization\nAnd with high level of English\nLet’s meet…\n\nThis role is perfect for parents and will require flexible hours on a part time position according to the company’s needs.','2020-07-11',1060),(902,'Junior Analyst','DESCRIPTION\n\nA part-time position in fast growing AI startup facing the US market. The position requires working closely with our Machine Learning team and pick-up on trends and inefficiencies in customer support conversations. The successful candidate is likely to demonstrate self-learning abilities, motivation, strong data analytics knowledge, exceptional problem-solving skills and attention to detail analyzing happy customers indication vs frustration - and help us develop the algorithms around it.\n\nFocus on customer monthly reports - find new trends once a week\n\nOverlook, validate and edit the weekly BI reports to some our biggest accounts\n\nWork closely with the algo team and have self-learning skills to talk on a technical level\n\nDesign, develop and deploy customer BI reports (as emails)\n\nClosely monitor and check the accuracy of our deployed models\n\nREQUIREMENTS\n\nExcellent communication skills, both written and oral. Motivated to stay in touch with the customer’s relevant POC\n\nComfortable with change, and working in an agile manner. We grow fast and move fast\n\nGood knowledge of MS Excel macro a plus\n\nHands-on SQL database experience (although we use NoSQL databases)\n\nGood knowledge in JavaScript/Java is a plus\n\nWe would love to find smart people who want to work at least 3 days a week','2020-07-16',1062),(905,'Publisher Content Reviewer','Taboola, the world\'s largest content recommendation platform, is hiring a Publisher Content Reviewer for a temporary role\n\nWhat is the biggest challenge of being a Publisher Content Reviewer?\nReview different sites and make a correct decision based on Taboola\'s policy\nCommunicate clearly with different stakeholders, while managing a large amount of constantly updating cases.\nWhat are some of the things you do on a day-to-day basis?\nReview different publishers and classify them quickly and correctly per policy\nUse various tools to identify non-compliance issues\nProvide suggestions to improve process and workflows\nWork closely and independently with other departments inside Taboola including business and legal\nTimely response to incoming requests for review, inquiries via email and ticketing system\nCommunicate urgent issues internally\nQuickly adapt to change (new publishers, changing policies, changing workflows)\nCommunicate issues comprehensively and coherently in a formal way (verbal and written)\nWrite detailed descriptions of workflows, create informative slideshows for internal use and maintain the department\'s written database.\nTrain and educate internal users regarding Pub CRT\'s work, policy and workflows.\nWhat are the skills a good Publisher Content Reviewer needs to have?\nNative level English - must\nAbility to work independently and within a team\nComfortable working with sensitive and unpleasant content\nAbility to understand contexts and see the bigger picture within the grey areas\nBe comfortable working with data and reporting\nAbility to make fact-based decisions quickly coupled with great attention to detail to ensure high-quality work products while being aware of constant policy changes.\nExcellent work pacing (time management) skills, able to work independently and prioritize\nFamiliar with MS office (mainly Excel) and Google Drive tools for updating progress and have good search and navigating skills\nHighly organized, multi-tasking, self-learning, motivated team player\nKnowledge in SQL - advantage\nThe will and ability to work in a fast-paced environment and learn, learn, learn!\nWhy should you be a Publisher Content Reviewer at Taboola?\nBecause your opinion matters and makes a difference, because you\'ll be working on different tasks that will keep the day to day interesting and because you\'ll be trusted with creating and leading projects that bring real added value to Taboola and its users.','2020-07-29',362),(909,'Backend Developer','Cloudinary is the leading provider of media management solutions, powering the trusted, award-winning visual experiences for many of your favorite brands. Cloudinary is the de facto media platform standard for developers and non-technical brand managers looking to upload, store, transform, manage, and deliver images and videos online. With more than 30 billion assets under our management and 6,500 customers worldwide, were always looking for exceptional people to help us reach for the cloud\nWe are looking for an energized, brilliant and creative senior backend developer to join us and work on unique challenges of scale and complex functionality while keeping the product fast and simple to use.\nIf you care about architecture and building scalable, extensible and robust software you belong with us!\nResponsibilities\nArchitect and build the next generation of Cloudinary\'s management console, upload and presentation widgets.\nWork closely with product managers in defining and implementing roadmap features.\nOptimise infrastructure for the best user experience in our Digital Asset Management solution.\nRequirements\n5+ years of experience in application design and development.\nExperience in building RoR based backend services from DB via Businesses Logic and APIs\nAbility to carry requirements from early phase to full implementation.\nGreat communication skills with tech and non-tech alike.\nFluent in English, both written and verbal.\nBonus\nWorking with high scale, distributed cloud-based architectures\nExperience with NodeJS\nExperience with Elasticsearch\n\n\n\ncustom_url:\nBackend_developer','2020-07-12',295),(910,'Publisher Contract Monitor','Publisher Contract Monitor\n\n\nThe Sales Operations team is looking for a Publisher Contract Monitor. The Publisher Contract Monitor will help ensure the inventory from our Publisher Partners is adhering to deal terms and will work closely with our global Publisher Account Manager and Legal teams to identify, communicate and execute the required implementation changes.\n\nIn this job you will:\nActively monitor the inventory of Taboola\'s publisher partnerships with the goal of ensuring deal terms are being fully adhered to\nWork with our global Publisher Account Management team to communicate the required changes with their clients\nFrequently update Salesforce to track the progress and status of violations\nWork closely with our legal team to define violation\nWork closely with the publisher contract manager on further developing additional processes and initiatives for more yield optimization\nImpact the revenue directly and contribute to its growth!\nAbout you:\nMinimum 2 years of experience in a business/ legal /professional services or operations role\nA highly analytical and critical thinker. Excellent attention to detail and the ability to remain organized.\nSensitivity to the day-to-day of a publisher account manager and the nature of addressing contract violations\nAn understanding of the core KPI\'s of the online advertising industry\nUnderstanding of Taboola\'s publisher product, jargon and Backstage\nExperience in analyzing and understanding contractual agreements - advantage\nExperience working 