tribute to documentation, best practices, and internal BI training','2020-07-12',1159),(995,'Internship Opportunities for Students: Data science/Researcher','Data Scientists and AI reserachers at Microsoft help to improve the quality of experiences on our devices and services. We are looking for highly motivated and passionate Data Scientists to design and apply rigorous scientific methodology and algorithms to data to improve Microsoft’s devices, operating systems, and services. As a Data Scientist, you will provide unique insight into business and customer scenarios that cut across organizational boundaries and lead the growth of a data-driven culture within Microsoft.\n\nAs an AI expert, you will help push the state-of-the-art in computer vision, speech recognition and speech enhancement, using Microsoft\'s extensive domain- specific knowledge, data, and compute resources.\n\nWe are looking for people who wish to work on a meaningful and impactful project and make a difference while using their creativity to solve scientific problems. Are you willing to learn from others and open to new ideas? Do you want to support others to succeed and operate in a highly collaborative and global environment? Do you like working with real data and solving real world problems? If this sounds like you, Microsoft would like to invite you to come join us as you are, where you can find more than just a job.\n\nResponsibilities\n\nAs a Data Scientist or an AI reseracher intern , you will help formulate approaches to solve problems using various algorithms and data sources. You will incorporate an understanding of product functionality and customer perspective to provide context for those problems. You will use data exploration techniques to discover new questions or opportunities within your problem area and propose applicability and limitations of the data. Successful Data Scientists will interpret the results of their analysis, validate their approach, and learn to monitor, analyze