perience in working under pressure\nExcellent attention to detail\nAbility to work as part of a team\n-- Hebrew description below -\nמיזם בינלאומי מחפש עובדי מעבדה קלינית לתפקיד מפתח במעבדה בעל חשיבות קריטית למדינת ישראל במלחמה בנגיף הקורונה.\n\nהמעבדה הוקמה בהזמנת משרד הבריאות ומשרד הביטחון.\n\nמדובר בהזדמנות ייחודית להוביל את המלחמה בנגיף ולהגדיל את כמות הבדיקות בישראל באופן משמעותי.\n\nהעבודה מתבצעת במעבדה בפתח תקוה.\n\nהמשרה אינה מתאימה למי שמועסק כיום באופן ישיר או בעקיפין במעבדה של משרד הבריאות וכל העוסק כיום בבדיקות קורונה או פעילות אחרת במסגרת המאבק בנגיף.\n\nמייהריטאג\' אינה מעוניינת לפגוע בכל דרך בעבודת משרד הבריאות או בפעילות מעבדות קיימות.\n\nאיך העבודה שלכם תיראה?\nתבצעו בדיקות דיאגנוסטיות בתחומי הוירולוגיה, שיכללו קבלת דגימות ורישומן, אינאקטיבציה, הפקת רנ\"א, ופענוח תוצאות.\nתטפלו במכשירים השונים במעבדה ותתחזקו אותם, בהתאם לדרישות הטיפול בהם ולנהלי העבודה במעבדה.\nתעבדו עם צוות מעולה ומגוון מישראל.\nהעבודה מתבצעת במעבדה בשלוש משמרות יומיות. אנו מחפשים עובדים למשרה מלאה, חמש משמרות בשבוע.\n\nדרישות:\nתואר ראשון אקדמי במדעי החיים והרפואה, עם לפחות קורס מעשי אחד בשיטות מעבדה בתחומים הבאים מיקרוביולוגיה / ביולוגיה מולקולרית / גנטיקה / אימונולוגיה - חובה\nרישיון עובד מעבדה רפואית – יתרון\nתעודת הכרה במעמד \"עובד מעבדה רפואי אקדמאי\" מטעם משרד הבריאות - יתרון\nניסיון קודם במעבדה רפואית - יתרון\nתואר מתקדם במדעי החיים - יתרון\nמה עוד:\nניסיון בעבודה תחת לחץ\nיכולת מעולה לירידה לפרטים\nעבודת צוות','2020-07-17',1117),(999,'Clinical Trial Assistant','Vectorious has developed the worlds first in-heart microcomputer and is on a mission to transform heart failure treatment. As part of our first in human clinical study, we have successfully implanted our sensory device in patients across Europe, while demonstrating a huge potential in helping millions of people living with heart failure to take control and manage their disease, keeping them stable, out of hospitals, and living longer, fuller lives.\n\nAbout this role:\nThe Clinical Trial Assistant will report the Clinical Trial Manager and will support the conduct of clinical trials, handling administrative aspects of clinical trial execution and tracking the progress of clinical trials.\n\n\nRequirements:\nResponsibilities:\nSupport clinical study documentation preparation, tracking and maintenance\nMaintain and perform periodic review of in-house study site records for completeness and accuracy\nPrepare and send study-related documents and materials to sites, CROs or development partners\nAssist in the preparation and maintenance of Clinical Study Agreements and Confidentiality Agreements\nDevelop and maintain effective tracking systems to ensure updates of regulatory documents\nInitiate request for investigator, site and vendor payments\nHelp facilitate shipment study supplies to study sites\nMaintain and organize reference materials related to the study\nMaintain systems to track study metrics and general study information\nCoordinate logistics and materials of formal meetings as needed (e.g. data review meetings and centralized investigator meetings)\nAttend study, project and departmental meetings\nSupport development of relevant tracking tools and other internal processes to increase departmental efficiency\nSupport other job-related duties as assigned by the CTM or designee\nQualifications and Requirements:\nBachelors degree in a related scientific discipline\nWorking knowledge of GCPs, Trial Master Files, ICH guidelines or experience working in a regulated environment\nProfessional demeanor and ability to work as a team member\nExperience with MS Office Suite (Word, PowerPoint, Excel, Project)\nAbility to coordinate and prioritize multiple tasks\nGood problem-solving skills\nDetail-oriented\nGood written and verbal skills in English','2020-07-19',1164),(1000,'Marketing Analyst','Use advance analytics, data mining and BI tools to execute top-notch marketing analyses to identify patterns, trends and opportunity from multiple large data sets Translate business questions and requirements to structured analyses and accordingly define suitable methods, techniques and solutions Deliver valuable outputs, recommendations, guidelines, conclusions and insights Proactively find gaps and opportunities in campaigns performance and budget management Work closely with the different marketing teams and stakeholders Plan, build and maintain BI reports for the different marketing teams and senior management BA in Industrial Engineering / Economics / Statistics or equivalent academic background 3+ years of practical analytic experience in big data environments, preferably in gaming, media/UA, internet or telecom industries Experience in media/UA industry- Major Advantage Experience in data mining, testing, analysis and problem-solving skills- Mandatory Excellent proficiency in Excel and SQL- Mandatory Experience working with a BI tool. Tableau- Major Advantage Passion for the gaming industry Self-learner, multi-tasking, strong analytical skills, able to work independently, initiative, strategic thinking, highly organized, pays attention to details, \"can-do\" approach','2020-07-07',190),(1001,'Information Technology Analyst','A leading healthcare company is looking for an Information Technology Analyst\nProvides technical user support and customer service on company-supported computer applications and platforms.\n\nResponsibilities:\nServe as the first point of contact for users seeking technical assistance (Help Desk Support)\nPerform troubleshooting through diagnostic techniques for both Hardware and Software issues\nRecord events and problems and their resolution in logs and direct unresolved issues to the next level of support\nProvide accurate information on IT products or services\nMaintain user access security, data integrity, and file system security\nResponsible to install, configure, maintain and troubleshoot all Operating Systems versions on all devices including end-users computers and production servers\nManage and maintain company Software assets like SharePoint, TFS, Active Directory, WSUS, and WDS.\nResponsible to Installs configure, maintain and troubleshoot workstations, servers & mobile devices in a heterogeneous environment\nFollow-up on any feedback or suggestions by users and Identify and suggest possible improvements on processes and procedures\nדרישות:\nBachelor’s degree in Computer Science or Computer Technology Certificate or MCSE\nMinimum 2 years of IT experience in a high tech company– Mandatory\nProven experience as a help desk technician or other customer support role – Mandatory\nAbility to diagnose and handle technical issues\nExcellent English communication skills (both verbal and written)\nHands-on experience with Microsoft OS, Active Directory, Linux – Mandatory\nHands-on experience with SharePoint, TFS, GPO, WSUS, WDS and VMware – Advantage\nExperience with PowerShell and Bash scripting\nאיזור: גוש דן\n\nתחום: מערכות מידע IT','2020-07-28',155),(1003,'ללא ניסיון','שלום חברים, הצוות שלי מתרחב ואני מחפש אנשים איכותיים שיצטרפו לקבוצת אנשים מדהימה. זאת עבודה עצמאית ומעצימה, כל אחד יכול לבחור איפה כמה שעות לעבוד ומה גובה הכנסה הרצוי. על מנת למנוע אי הבנות, אני לא מציע משכורת בסיס, אבל ניתן להרוויח מיד בהתחלה . ללא סיכון כלכלי , אין צורך בניסיון קודם.\n\nהעבודה בכל הארץ ובחו\"ל. אנשים רציניים בלבד להתקשר לפרטים: |** מס\' הטלפון במודעה **| נטלי','2020-07-26',24),(1004,'Personalized Internet Ads Assessor','Are you looking for an opportunity to work with one of America’s top 100 most trusted Companies while also increasing your income from the comfort of your home? Then why not join Lionbridge as a part-time Independent Contractor. We are currently recruiting for the opportunity of Personalized Internet Ads Assessor in Israel.\n\nWhat does the work involve?\n\nIn this opportunity you will be reviewing online advertisements in order to improve their content, quality and layout. You will be required to provide feedback and analysis on advertisements found in search engine results and provide ratings on their relevance to the search terms used. Another aspect of this opportunity will involve reviewing the language used in advertisements by examining grammar, tone and cultural relevance.\n\nThrough this work you will be making a valuable contribution to the quality of online advertisements in Israel.\n\nWho is suitable for this work?\n\nWe are looking for dynamic people who have strong communication skills and use the Internet daily. You should also be flexible, reliable and have the ability to interpret and follow established guidelines.\n\nYou will need to have the flexibility and freedom to work from your own home, working your own hours. Hours for this opportunity are up to 20 hours per week depending on task availability.\n\nWhat are the main requirements for the opportunity?\nYou must be living in Israel for the last 3 consecutive years\nYou must have familiarity with current and historical business, media, sport, news, social media and cultural affairs in Israel\nFluency in English and Hebrew\nAccess to and use of a broadband internet connection and associated computer and software to perform the work, all provided at your own expense\nExperience in use of web browsers to navigate and interact with a variety of content\nAccess to and use of an Android (version 4.1 or higher) or IOS Smartphone (version 8 or higher) to complete tasks\nA Barcode Scanner application must be installed on your smartphone to complete certain tasks\nActive daily user of Gmail and other forms of Social Media\nAPPLY NOW','2020-07-16',1169),(1005,'Talent Acquisition Specialist','Recruiting in AppsFlyer is very unique:\n\nOn one hand, the hiring pace is crazy (even these days) and we work very hard to meet our goals. But on the other hand, we are a big team of recruiters, sourcers and coordinators and we have each other\'s back. We are extremely data oriented yet creative in nature. Most of all, we believe that every person has their own strengths and passion and we allow each team member to focus on the areas they are most passionate about.\n\nIf you\'re not intimidated by difficult challenges yet seek to have the opportunity to apply your strengths and be part of a big recruiting team, this might be the place for you.\n\nWhat you\'ll do?\nHire end-to-end in Israel, Europe and LATAM. Mostly Sales, Marketing and Customer Success positions (some technical positions too)\nConduct HR interviews\nWork closely with country managers to align priorities and regional recruiting strategies\nTake part in our OKR framework and contribute to the ever evolving processes in our team\nWhat do you need to have?\n3 years experience recruiting in tech companies larger than 200 employees\nExperience hiring in other countries except Israel\nFluent English\nAs a global company operating in 16 countries across 5 continents, we reflect the human mosaic of the diverse and multicultural world in which we live. We ensure equal opportunities for all of our employees and promote the recruitment of diverse talents to our global teams without consideration of race, gender, culture, or sexual orientation. We value and encourage curiosity, diversity, and innovation from all our employees, customers, and partners.\n\n\"As a Customer Obsessed company, we must first be Employee Obsessed. We need to make sure that we provide the team with the tools and resources they need to go All-In.\" Oren Kaniel, CEO','2020-07-27',158),(1006,'מוקד מבצעים','סטטוס\nפעיל\n|\nתאריך אחרון להגשת מועמדות 01/08/2020\nמיקום\nכל הארץ\nישוב\nירושלים ראש העין קיסריה\nתאריך תחילת העסקה\n01/12/2020\nתאריך פרסום\n01/11/2020\nתיאור התפקיד\n\nעבודה בחדר המבצעים של משרד ראש הממשלה, אחריות אבטחתית מלאה על משרד רה\"מ ומתקנים מסווגים נוספים.\n\nהתפקיד כולל שליטה, ניטור ובקרה על אירועים חריגים בתחום האבטחה המבצעית והסייבר, תוך שימוש באמצעים טכנולוגיים מתקדמים והפעלת מערכות מידע ומחשוב.\n\nדרישות התפקיד\nשירות צבאי / לאומי מלא\nהשכלה תיכונית מלאה\nהתחייבות לשנתיים\nהמשרה בראש העין מחייבת רכב\nהיקף המש