ly with clients to understand priorities, review performance, and share product updates\n\nOversee technology integrations, with support from Technical Account Management and Product, to ensure smooth and successful launches\n\nQUALIFICATIONS\n\nNative Hebrew speaker, fluent and proficient in English (verbal and writing)\n\n1-3 years of digital/online marketing experience\n\nAt least 1 year of experience in a Content Arbitrage company – A MUST\n\nWillingness to work in flexible hours 1-2 days a week\n\nPrevious experience in Business / Systems Analysis\n\nProven ability and desire to interface with clients both remotely and face to face to provide timely, consistent and accurate support and account management\n\nAbility to proactively work with high profile clients independently and within a team environment\n\nExcellent quantitative skills and a proven ability to monitor, identify and present performance metrics\n\nExcellent written and verbal communication skills\n\nExcellent time-management and organizational skills\n\nStrong knowledge of Microsoft applications, especially Excel and PowerPoint\n\nAbility to execute efficiently and effectively in a fast-paced environment','2020-07-28',1175),(1008,'PPC Intern','Description:\nSeperia, a performance marketing company, is looking for a PPC Intern.\nAs a pioneer in digital marketing, Seperia offers a dynamic, empowering and fun work environment, while allowing fast professional and financial growth for top candidates.\nThe PPC work requires a combination of analytical and creative skills. The work is performed on advanced online technological systems such as Google Adwords and others.\n\nWhat Will You Do:\nAssisting a PPC optimizer, and gradually performing independently:\nCreating lists of keywords and categorizing them\nWriting an ad copy adapted to different keyword groups\nAnalyzing a multitude of key performance indicators over time and suggesting insights and action items\nKeywords Bidding\nCompiling performance 