3,'COLLECTION & AR TEAM LEAD','The Collection and AR Team Lead role in Gett is one that leads with the business in mind. Although this individual has an amazing ability to work with both clients and account management to achieve a very low DSO they are equally focused in helping the business to drive both the top and bottom line.\nResponsibilities\nLead the AR and collection team\nManaging and monitoring approximately 5000 clients.\nEnsure adequate and timely invoicing, reporting, collection and bank reconcilations\nReduce outstanding debt and control overdue clients\nNegotiating re-payment plans\nMaintaining contact with clients to ensure invoices are clear for payment\nResolving queries both internally and externally around outstanding invoices\nProviding accounts information, reporting and analysis to internal departments.\nEnsure there is an adequate provision for doubtful debt.\n\n\nRequirements:\n5+ years experience in collections and AR bookkeeping, at least 2 years of management experience\nAbility to establish and maintain good client relationships, both internally and externally at all levels\nAbility to reconcile complex accounts and have excellent attention to detail\nCompetence in Excel and accounting software programs (ideally SAP but not required)\nCalm, confident manner to handle potentially uncomfortable conversations','2020-07-27',393),(1014,'Business Analyst','Israel, Tel Aviv\nFinance\nJob description\n\nAtera is a SaaS B2B company in the IT space, located in the heart of Tel Aviv.\n\nProviding MSPs with an intuitive and powerful all-in-one platform to manage their customers end devices and networks, Atera is a top of the class solution for managing external and internal IT.\n\nWe are looking for a strong analyst to join our BI team. A Business analyst in Atera will be driving critical business decisions that influence our business performance and customer journey. We are looking for a superstar who is passionate about solving complex business questions, customers, product and most of all - data & numbers.\n\nWhat You\'ll Be Doing\n\nYou will be working closely with our Atera’s business units, providing strategic recommendations based on her or his data analysis. This includes setting the relevant KPIs and creating the tools to monitor our business performance and suggest, test, measure, and hypothesize on improvements.\n\nStrong analytical skills. BA/BSc/MSc in a quantitative field\n730+ Psychometric grade and/or a proven distinction record.\nExceptional attention to details\nExperience as a business analyst/product analyst/consultant in a well-known firm is an advantage\nExperience in working in a SaaS company or online world - Advantage\nExperience with data visualization platforms (e.g. Qlikview, Tableau, Power BI) - Advantage\nExperience with SQL/Python - Advantage','2020-07-08',1184),(1015,'PMO','Job Description:\nFor a software company developing products in the field of financial investment and social networking, with offices in the center\n\nAdditional Positions:\nProject manager\n\nCategory:\nSoftware\n\nJob Qualifications:\nMust have previous experience in project management from an Online companies.\nExcellent managerial skills\nMust have strong technical skills * R&D background an advantage\nVery strong interpersonal and communication skills\nExperience with R&D management in a large organization is an advantage\nSavvy with R&D projects life cycle and management issues\nExperience in development process of large products and experience with the process of delivering a product,\nExperience in working with the parties related to the project - marketing, development, operations, customers etc.\nKnowledge in defining requirements from the parties related to the project (administrative, development etc.) and synchronizing between them.\nB.A. / B.Sc. - from a well known university - a must\nExcellent English\nCompany Occupation:\nHigh Tech, Internet related, Financial Institutions\n\nCompany Size:\nSmall (0 - 50)','2020-07-21',150),(1017,'Growth Specialist','Are you a hardworking, energetic self-starter looking to change the face of an industry?\n\nAre you data-driven, with extensive experience in marketing and user acquisition? If this sounds like you, you\'ve come to the right place.\n\nWe\'re looking for a full stack growth specialist to join our talented Growth Development team, working with other members of Lemonade to reach our targets.\n\nIn your day-to-day, you\'ll research and explore new partnerships and user acquisition opportunities, creating and launching different growth initiatives from scratch. You\'ll frequently communicate with potential business partners and optimize the performance and relationships with existing partners.\n\nOur ideal candidate is a data-driven individual, adept at carefully monitoring and measuring performance, running A/B tests, gathering insights, and constantly optimizing channels to their fullest extent.\n\nRequirements\nMinimum of 5 years experience in digital marketing & user acquisition\nExtensive experience in media sales/buying\nProven track record in business development - a must\nExcel proficiency\nExperience in data analysis\nFluent English (additional languages are a plus)\nHard worker, multitasker\nProactive, independent, and reliable\nTeam player with zero ego and great social skills','2020-07-12',19),(1019,'Product Analyst','We create a safe space for communities to thrive.\n\n\nOpenWeb (formerly Spot.IM) is on a mission to increase the quality of conversations online. We build technologies that create thriving and engaged communities, reduce toxicity, and increase safety - improving the quality of civil discourse and supporting independent journalism. Today, OpenWeb works with more than 700 top-tier publishers (including News Corp, Verizon Media, CBS, Fox News, Hearst, Refinery 29 and more) and hosts 100 million monthly active users.\n\nFounded in 2012, OpenWeb has over 100 employees between New York City and Tel Aviv. We are backed by world-class investors including Insight Partners, Index Ventures, AltaIR Capital, ScaleUp, and Norma Investments. Together, we are empowering individuals to take action, and demand more from one another. We\'re crafting technology that naturally brings people together and fosters healthy discussionso they have more dinner-table talks and less shouting matches online. It starts with us. Let\'s take the web back from the trolls - together. Are you in?\n\nHow You\'ll Contribute as our Product Revenue Analyst:\nBuild our newest product - a monetization mechanism - hand-in-hand with the Product Manager\nDefine key product questions and resolutions, KPIs, provide business insights using your data-driven orientation\nAnalyze OpenWeb\'s terabytes of data to build insightful dashboards and complex reports with the goal of defining and improving product functionally and increasing revenue performance & opportunities\nSet the standard for best practices and suggest new processes/tools/initiatives to collect, analyze, and manage our massive amounts of data\nFor every event that happens - from feature consideration to product release - you will be a key player in the decision making process\nThe Skills and Experience You Bring:\n4+ years of relevant experience as a Data Analyst (or related position) - Must\nAdvantage for experience as a Product Analyst\nExperience working with Big Data - Must\nExperience working at an Adtech companies - Advantage\nWorking knowledge of the following tools is a MUST: Tableau, SQL\nPython, Redshift / BigQuery, Athena - Advantage\nAble to work in a dynamic environment and with tight deadlines\nDegree in Engineering/Mathematics/Statistics/Information Systems or equivalent\nBuild your skills with us as you build a better web for everyone. Join us!\n\nAlso, we care about your privacy! Please take a moment to review OpenWeb\'s Privacy Practices','2020-07-20',1189),(1100,'Senior System Engineer for AMI OEM','Job Title\nSenior System Engineer for AMI OEM\nJob Description\n\n\nIn this role, you have the opportunity to\n\nBe in charge of overall technical leadership and responsibility for realization of features and systems release and their life cycle management of AMI OEM Projects.\n\nYou are responsible for\nPlan, oversee and execute the system engineering activities including initiation, coordination, synchronization, review and integration of the technical work of OEM Projects.\nBe the R&D representative in discussions with the OEM.\nLead and technical escort the development effort as the key technical stakeholder of the project to meet the functionality, safety, serviceability, quality, cost and reliability targets.\nElicit stakeholders’ needs, translate into requirements specifications and lead/escort requirements’ materialization.\nPrepare and/or review the technical documentations to meet the high standard required for a medical device.\nLead cross-discipline feasibility, tradeoff studies and problem solving with the OEM provider, when applicable\nLead the Philips par system integration from planning to completion.\nDefine/Evaluate testing requirements & strategy and technically escort verification & validation teams.\nCollect Evidence and Verification/Validation reports from the supplier to finalize the design phase.\nYou are a part of\n\nA progressive and energetic team that contributes directly to the growth of the business. You have a direct reporting line to the Systems Engineering Sr.Manager, with Cross-Functional and Product Managers as your key stakeholders.\n\nTo succeed in this role, you should have the following skills and experience\nB.Sc. in Electrical/Mechanical/Software engineering/Physics/other relevant degree\nAt least 7 years of intensive experience as a System engineer in a regulated field (Medical, Aerospace, etc.)\nAt least 10 years of technical experience in product development prior to becoming a system engineer\nDemonstrated ability in leading development of complex features\nExcellent interpersonal skills and ability to influence without authority\nFluent English\nIn return, we offer you\n\nA path towards your most rewarding career. Philips is growing its technical capability enterprise wide. Succeeding in this systems engineering-based role in a complex environment will open many doors for your long term career, in other areas in Philips or otherwise.\n\nWhy should you join Philips?\n\nWorking at Philips is more than a job. It’s a calling to create a healthier society through meaningful work, focused on improving 3 billion lives a year by delivering innovative solutions across the health continuum. Our people experience a variety of unexpected moments when their lives and careers come together in meaningful ways. Learn more by watching this video.\n\nTo find out more about what it’s like working for Philips at a personal level, visit the Working at Philips page on our career website, where you can read stories from our employee blog. Once there,you can also learn about our recruitment process, or find answers to some of the frequently asked questions.\n\n#LI-EU\n\nContact\n\n\nIf you forgot your password, you can click the Forgot Password button on the Sign In screen to reset it.\n\nIf you have any other questions regarding the recruitment process please refer to our FAQs. In case of technical difficulties with the website, please send an email to careersite@philips.com.\n(Note: To ensure fairness and legal compliance in our recruitment processes, only technical issues will be monitored through the above inbox. Please do not submit resumes or applications to this email, as they will not be reviewed. Only applications received through the online application process will be considered.)','2020-07-08',417),(1101,'System QA Engineer','Join the Amazon family and take part in the development of next generation products that will define the future of the cloud domain.\n\nAnnapurnaLabs, an Amazon company, is looking for talented engineers to help us develop the semiconductor platform which is based on revolutionary architecture.\n\nTake part in the development of cutting edge products within disruptive system architecture. Youll have the opportunity to work on the technologies that power the worlds largest Cloud provider, within a dynamic, open, and fast-paced environment.\n\nAre you ready to join the future?\n\n\nBasic Qualifications\n\n· Experience: 2-5 years in QA, System-QA\n· Operating systems: Linux (high level), Windows (basic level)\n· Scripting: writing ability, required languages: Bash, Python\n· General: knowledge in STP/STD document writing, high analytics and debugging abilities\n\nPreferred Qualifications\n\n· Familiarity with x86 (Intel) server architecture/debug/environment\n· Familiarity with networking (switching/routing)\n· Testing tools: Ethernet packet generators, PCI analyzer\n· Familiarity with networking (TCP/IP, Ethernet Switching), embedded SoC system testing, storage (NVME), and virtualization','2020-07-08',115),(1102,'Software Engineer - Cisco Silicon One™','What You\'ll Do\n\nYou\'ll develop Core Software technologies at the heart of tomorrow\'s leading infrastructure solutions, tackling the entire range of challenges from user-facing API-s, through high-level algorithms, all the way down to firmware.\n\nThe Leaba core R&D group, now part of Cisco, develops breakthrough next-generation silicon products.\nIf you want to work with amazing people, developing the first iteration of world-class products, join us!\n\nIn this role, you will:\n• Design and develop software driving the world\'s most complex infrastructures\n• Gain intimate knowledge of world-class silicon and programming models\n• Work with architecture and design teams to define the next generation of ASIC products being developed\n\nWho You\'ll Work With\nLeaba semiconductor was acquired by Cisco a few years ago. It is now the center of Cisco’s SW and ASIC design.\n\nYou\'ll be part of our Group driving our game changing next generation network devices - Cisco Silicon One™. Our unique team works in a startup atmosphere inside a stable and leading corporate.\n\nOur R&D center is very unique - hosting all silicon HW and SW development disciplines inside one site.\n\nWe are transforming the industry and building a new internet for the 5G era, providing a unified, programmable silicon architecture that is the foundation of all Cisco\'s future routing products.\n\nOur devices are designed to be universally adaptable across service providers and web-scale markets, designed for fixed and modular platforms. Our devices deliver high speed without sacrificing programmability, buffering, power efficiency, scale or feature flexibility.\n\nCisco Silicon One™ is a revolutionary, ground-breaking technology for our customers and end users for decades to come! The Internet now has a new faster, better, safer engine!\n\nLearn more about us right here:\nhttps://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/solutions/service-provider/innovation/silicon-one.html\n\nhttps://fortune.com/2019/12/11/cisco-ceo-chuck-robbins-chips/?_lrsc=ce750ac5-11c8-4995-bfd3-936de1c06009&dtid=osolin001080\n\nhttps://www.calcalist.co.il/internet/articles/0,7340,L-3775619,00.html\n\nhttps://www.youtube.com/watch?v=iy8259BGg6U\n\nhttps://www.youtube.com/watch?v=BNkiprGWw4Y\n\nOur team develops the full software stack enabling the Leaba ASIC. Join a team of talented engineers with a proven track-record at delivering breakthrough products.\n\nYou have a unique opportunity to join this team at an early stage and work with us to design and deliver breakthrough technologies.\n\nWho You Are\n\n\"Choose a job you love, and you will never have to work a day in your life.\"\nWork is amazing when you work with amazing people.\nIf you:\n• Have a cheerful, positive attitude\n• Are a brilliant software/electrical engineer, regardless of previous experience\n• Can quickly ramp on multiple, interdisciplinary domains\n• Love tackling complex problems\n• Have a B.Sc or higher, Cum Laude, from the Technion, TAU, HUJI or BGU, or are highly recommended by a Cisco employee.\nNow\'s the time to contact us!\n\nWhy Cisco\n\nWe connect everything: people, processes, data, and things. We innovate everywhere, taking bold risks to shape the technologies that give us smart cities, connected cars, and handheld hospitals. And we do it in style with unique personalities who aren’t afraid to change the way the world works, lives, plays and learns.\n\nWe are thought leaders, tech geeks, pop culture aficionados, and we even have a few purple haired rock stars. We celebrate the creativity and diversity that fuels our innovation. We are dreamers and we are doers.\n\n#WeAreCisco #BeYouWithUs\n\n#LI-MZ1','2020-07-07',229),(1103,'Design Engineer for USB4 Project (Haifa, Israel)','Company:\nQualcomm Israel Ltd.\nJob Area:\nEngineering Group, Engineering Group > Hardware Engineering\nJob Overview:\n\n\nQualcomm is a company of inventors that unlocked 5G ushering in an age of rapid acceleration in connectivity and new possibilities that will transform industries, create jobs, and enrich lives. But this is just the beginning. It takes inventive minds with diverse skills, backgrounds, and cultures to transform 5Gs potential into world-changing technologies and products. This is the Invention Age - and this is where you come in.\n\nQualcomm is a company of inventors that unlocked 5G ushering in an age of rapid acceleration in connectivity and new possibilities that will transform industries, create jobs, and enrich lives. But this is just the beginning. It takes inventive minds with diverse skills, backgrounds, and cultures to transform 5Gs potential into world-changing technologies and products. This is the Invention Age and this is where you come in.\n\nWith this position you\'ll be joinin Qualcomm\'s USB4 group, working on innovative, market changing solutions in the field of laptops connectivity. Join the team designing the future\'s products.\n\nMinimum Qualifications\n2+ of design engineering significant experience.\nKnowledge in digital design techniques, preferably from the field of ASIC design front end activities.\n\nPreferred Qualifications\nDigital design tools for the following flows: simulation, verification, synthesis, timing analysis, formal verification and lint.\nAbility to work in a team.\nAbility to understand system wise aspects like interaction of HW with SW and FW.\nAbility to create digital micro architecture from specifications.\n\n*References to a particular number of years experience are for indicative purposes only. Applications from candidates with equivalent experience will be considered, provided that the candidate can demonstrate an ability to fulfill the principal duties of the role and possesses the required competencies.\nApplicants: If you are an individual with a disability and need an accommodation during the application/hiring process, please call Qualcomm’s toll-free number found here for assistance. Qualcomm will provide reasonable accommodations, upon request, to support individuals with disabilities to be able participate in the hiring process. Qualcomm is also committed to making our workplace accessible for individuals with disabilities. Qualcomm is an equal opportunity employer and supports workforce diversity.\n\nTo all Staffing and Recruiting Agencies: Our Careers Site is only for individuals seeking a job at Qualcomm. Staffing and recruiting agencies and individuals being represented by an agency are not authorized to use this site or to submit profiles, applications or resumes, and any such submissions will be considered unsolicited. Qualcomm does not accept unsolicited resumes or applications from agencies. Please do not forward resumes to our jobs alias, Qualcomm employees or any other company location. Qualcomm is not responsible for any fees related to unsolicited resumes/applications.','2020-07-14',1273),(1104,'Haifa Lab Technician Student','Job Description\n\nTest prototypes of products developed at Intel Haifa Design Center, while operating cutting edge test equipment and technology. The job requires implementing knowledge in various areas such as electronics, software and some mechanics. Measuring technologies and instruments are utilized to test CPUs for quality, reliability, and adherence to specs. Lab technicians perform electrical/mechanical or SW troubleshooting to determine problems in non-functioning electromechanical equipment or in the equipment\'s test program. May also perform set-up, calibration, and basic debug on testing equipment.\n\nQualifications\n\n- Studies for a technical degree in a relevant academic institute, in SW, Mechanical ENG or electronics fields\nLogical problem solving capabilities\nWillingness to work shifts of 9 or 12 hr., ~3-4 shifts per week, possibility to work weekends.\nProficiency in English communication skills (reading, writing and speaking).\nResponsibility and reliability\nDetail strictness\nInterpersonal communication skills & Team work\nSelf learning.\nIndependence\nLeading capabilities experience - advantage.\nRelevant experience - advantage\nPE degree in SW/Electronics - advantage\"\n\nInside this Business Group\n\nThe Infrastructure and Platform Solutions Group (IPSG) builds the silicon and platform infrastructure for Intel\'s silicon design teams. IPSG is comprised of a reusable pool of infrastructure IP blocks, design enabling services such as tools and automation, and a best-in-class post silicon ecosystem that ramps quickly to high volume manufacturing and validation. Our primary mission is to protect Intel\'s brand by providing the infrastructure necessary to enable all of Intel\'s products to hit the market on a dependable and predictable cadence.','2020-07-09',398),(1105,'Recruiting Coordinator - Amazon Go','The AmazonGo R&D Team in Haifa is seeking candidates for a Recruitment Coordinator (RC) Temporary Student Position (~20 hours a week) for 9 months.\n\nThe RC is an integral partner in managing recruiting activities and building candidate relationships; often providing candidates with their first impression of Amazon. This candidate will be an organizational guru, work effectively with internal and external clients and candidates, possess great communication skills, have the ability to shift gears at a moments notice and enjoy the challenges of helping to build a great organization of talented individuals. This is an amazing opportunity for someone looking to broaden their experience and work in a top recruiting organization.\n\nResponsibilities:\n· Scheduling interviews and phone screens working directly with candidates and hiring managers, in some cases arranging travel for visiting candidates\n· Updating candidate records and job postings in recruiting systems and confirming new hires\n· Providing follow-up correspondence to candidates on recruiting status via phone and email\n· Tracking recruiting activities and providing candidate status in a weekly report\n· Coordinating the post-interview debrief meetings and providing debrief materials\n· Identifying opportunities for improving candidate experience and scheduling efficiency\n· Assisting in the coordination of other recruiting activities as needed\n\n\nAmazon is an Equal Opportunity-Affirmative Action Employer Minority / Female / Disability / Veteran / Gender Identity / Sexual Orientation\n\n\nBasic Qualifications\n\nBasic Qualifications\n• Good level of English (reading/writing/speaking)\n• Experience with MS Word, Excel and Power Point\n\nPreferred Qualifications\n\nPreferred Qualifications\n• Superb customer focus, attention to detail and organization skills\n• Strong oral and written communication skills\n• Ability to work in a fast paced, quickly changing environment\n• Bachelors degree\n• 1+ years of recruiting coordinator or HR experience','2020-07-21',115),(1106,'Software Engineering - Engineer, SVE','Company:\nQualcomm Israel Ltd.\nJob Area:\nEngineering Group, Engineering Group > Software Engineering\nJob Overview:\n\n\nQualcomm is a company of inventors that unlocked 5G ushering in an age of rapid acceleration in connectivity and new possibilities that will transform industries, create jobs, and enrich lives. But this is just the beginning. It takes inventive minds with diverse skills, backgrounds, and cultures to transform 5Gs potential into world-changing technologies and products. This is the Invention Age - and this is where you come in.\n\nAs a member of the SVE team, you will be responsible for developing embedded software drivers, firmware and tests for Qualcomm Snapdragon chips. You will work closely with system architects, software teams, hardware designers and verification engineers on cutting edge mobile HW/SW as part of the pre and post silicon development and validation efforts\n\nMinimum Qualifications\n2-3 years of experience in developing embedded software\nStrong programming skills in C, C++, Assembly\nStrong software design skills backed with good analytical, debug and problem solving abilities\nExcellent understanding of operating systems and real time embedded systems\nExperience with real-time embedded software and device drivers (VxWorks, Linux, etc)\nKnowledge of SoC architectures, ARM microprocessor architecture and/or DSP architectures is an advantage\nFamiliarity and experience with USB, PCIe, UFS, Flash, SPI controllers is an advantage\nExperience with hardware debug equipment such as JTAG, scope, logic analyzer is an advantage\n\nPreferred Qualifications\nThis is a very challenging position that requires the candidate to learn and internalize various peripheral cores concepts quickly. The candidate will support a wide range of wired peripheral interfaces. Strong communication skills - able to understand and explain highly technical information in a clear and concise manner. Strong interpersonal skills, Self-starter, Strong initiative.\n\n*References to a particular number of years experience are for indicative purposes only. Applications from candidates with equivalent experience will be considered, provided that the candidate can demonstrate an ability to fulfill the principal duties of the role and possesses the required competencies.\nApplicants: If you are an individual with a disability and need an accommodation during the application/hiring process, please call Qualcomm’s toll-free number found here for assistance. Qualcomm will provide reasonable accommodations, upon request, to support individuals with disabilities to be able participate in the hiring process. Qualcomm is also committed to making our workplace accessible for individuals with disabilities. Qualcomm is an equal opportunity employer and supports workforce diversity.\n\nTo all Staffing and Recruiting Agencies: Our Careers Site is only for individuals seeking a job at Qualcomm. Staffing and recruiting agencies and individuals being represented by an agency are not authorized to use this site or to submit profiles, applications or resumes, and any such submissions will be considered unsolicited. Qualcomm does not accept unsolicited resumes or applications from agencies. Please do not forward resumes to our jobs alias, Qualcomm employees or any other company location. Qualcomm is not responsible for any fees related to unsolicited resumes/applications.','2020-07-14',1273),(1108,'Product Information Security Leader','התפקיד:\nחברה מצליחה בתחום הביוטק דרוש/ה Product Information Security Leader\nהובלה מקצועית של תחום אבטחת מידע למוצרי החברה. עבודה מול גופי R&D , ,QARA SERVICE ומנהלי פרויקטים\nבחינת טכנולוגיות SECURITY חדשות ומגמות שוק\nפתרון שאילתות המתקבלות מלקוחות החברה\nמעורבות ביצירת נהלי החברה בתחום ה SECURITY\nדרישות:\nתואר ראשון- יתרון. תעודות הסמכה רלוונטיות- חובה\nלפחות 3 שנות ניסיון בתחום ה SECURITY בארגונים גלובליים (אפשרות לניסיון בניהול צוות IT בארגוני הייטק\nגלובליים)\nניסיון עבודה מול ממשקי רגולציה, ניסיון בכתיבת נהלים בתחום\nניסיון בתפקידי פיתוח תוכנה / חומרה – יתרון\nאנגלית ברמה גבוהה מאוד\nאיזור: חיפה והקריות\n\nתחום: מערכות מידע IT','2020-07-08',155),(1109,'SW & Validation - High speed interface Engineer','Posted: Dec 12, 2019\nRole Number:\n200103002\nImagine what you could do here. At Apple, new ideas have a way of becoming extraordinary products, services, and customer experiences very quickly. Bring passion and dedication to your job and there\'s no telling what you could accomplish. Dynamic, smart people and inspiring, innovative technologies are the norm here. The people who work here have reinvented entire industries with all Apple products. The same real passion for innovation that goes into our products also applies to our practices strengthening our commitment to leave the world better than we found it.\nIn this highly visible role you will be responsible to design, develop and drivers, tests, and SW infrastructure for high-speed interfaces and HW accelerators.\n\nWork with architects and logic designers to understand the operation of the HW and system design. Investigate the use cases, system-level operation, and performance requirements.\n\nDevelop low-level software to validate functionality, conformance, and performance of the systems, as well as compliance with architectural models.\nKey Qualifications\n5+ years\' experience in HW-SW integration, directed test developments.\nGood understanding of high-speed interfaces: PCIe (GEN3/4), USB2/3.0/3.1/3.2, Ethernet, InfiniBand. Both SW and HW level flows,Good knowledge and experience embedded software development (RTOS, UNIX).\nStrong and shown debug skills, we are looking for a debug Guru.\nDescription\nThis position is for a seasoned engineer with strong background in either silicon validation or embedded software development to take on all aspects of SoC validation, from driver development, through SoC bring-up, Validation and debug.\n\nCore responsibilities: be a part of the silicon validation team, develop automated testing environment for SoC and execute all silicon validation related activities.\nEducation & Experience\nBachelor’s Degree or Master’s Degree in Electrical Engineering/ Computer Engineering with 5+ years experience.','2020-07-20',116),(1110,'System Validation Engineer','We are developing multiple Nitro cards, based on multiple generations of Silicon. Each product includes Hardware & Firmware integration, based on deliveries from several RnD teams. The integration of the components into a specific product release is going through product qualification before released to customers. The high quality releases and efficient qualification is what enabling us to meet aggressive schedule and bring our new technology to market on time.\n\nThe Nitro Products System Validation Engineer will work on the following tasks, and the Quality owner of release manages by Nitro development team:\n· Integration of cards HW with FW version\n· Integration of cards into platform level\n· Test new FW versions on cards\n· Test new Card Manufacturing packages (Test suite used by Cards Manufacturer to screen the products)\n· Test new Platform Manufacturing packages (Test suite used by Platform Manufacturer to screen its products)\n· Test new tools & tests integrated to Manufacturing packages\n· Develop tests based on Automation Infrastructure, to improve efficiency of above testing.\n· Develop dashboard to effectively manage the tests results.\n· Provide training and guidance to additional System Validation team members (students)\n\nBasic Qualifications\n\n· Education: Practical Engineer, B.Sc. in Electrical Engineering, Computer Science, or equivalent.\n· 2-3 years of System (HW+SW) Validation experience or SW QA\n· Script writing experience\n· Working with Bug Tracking tool/s\n\nPreferred Qualifications\n\n· Experience w Tests / Automation languages, such as Python\n· Experience in QA of adding cards','2020-07-14',115),(1111,'Senior Director R&D','Job Title\nSenior Director R&D\nJob Description\n\n\nDo you want to drive the development of the next generations of cutting edge CT systems and solutions? Are you excited about Philips vision to deliver on the quadruple aim of healthcare?\n\nIn this role, you have the opportunity to have end-to-end responsibility for the development of Philips high-end CT portfolio, from creating the product roadmap together with the cross-functional product team, to executing the product development and launch projects, to maintaining the product over the complete life-cycle.\n\nThe Senior Director Premium CT is leading an organization of multiple R&D groups in our Haifa, Israel development site and drives leadership and competence development, process improvement and achievement of product quality and development KPIs for the Premium CT segment. To achieve the development goals of the Premium segment, the Senior Director Premium CT collaborates with several platform organizations within the global CT/AMI business and other businesses in the Precision Diagnosis cluster.\n\nThe role requires to influence the practices of the CT/AMI organization across the whole product lifecycle. Starting from a clear north-star of how good development practices and team leadership look like, the Senior Director Premium CT will work with the other members of the global R&D Management Team to ensure that the work practices and competence in their teams supports his vision for Premium CT.\n\nWe are looking for a transformational leader that will lift the team performance to the next level and that builds strong leadership behaviors and competences in the team\n\nYou are responsible for\nBeing part of the global R&D Management Team of CT/AMI\nBeing R&D representative in the the cross-functional leadership team for Premium CT\nCreating a north-star vision and roadmap for Premium CT\nOperationalizing the vision into a development program for the Premium system organization and needs towards platform organizations and other businesses\nLeading a development organization in Haifa, Israel\nResponsible for the achieving the product quality and development KPIs for Premium CT\nWorking in close relation with Q&R to ensure compliance to FDA design controls, EU MDR and NMPA requirements\nUnderstanding external factors including: Regulatory, Customers, Competition, and Industry trends\nDriving functional excellence including: Professionalism in domain expertise, Building up a strong, innovative teams, World class productivity, Promote domain knowledge, system thinking, and customer understanding\nEnabling process management including: Support for all global initiatives, Prioritization of team goals, Enable adequate coverage for deliverables, Build and promote strong processes, Drives accountability across the team\nExemplifying global thinking including: Promoting openness to learning things and leverage others’ capabilities, Sharing capabilities across global locations, Building an environment of trust\nTo succeed in this role, you should have the following skills and experience\nMaster’s degree in Engineering or related discipline.\nDeep knowledge and experience in system engineering, HW and SW development, design controls and designing for quality and reliability.\n10+ years of experience working as an Engineer or in a similar field.\n6+ years of experience as a R&D group leader or equivalent.\nExperience with Lean, Agile, Six Sigma or DfSS practices\nExperience in a regulated / process-oriented environment such as medical device development\nExperience with change management\nExperience with imaging systems is a plus, but not a must\nExperience with working in a global organization across multiple locations\nStrong influencing and communication skills\nCan work with all levels people internally and externally\nBusiness proficiency in English\nWillingness to re-locate (if required) to Haifa, Israel\nWhy should you join Philips?\n\nWorking at Philips is more than a job. It’s a calling to create a healthier society through meaningful work, focused on improving 3 billion lives a year by delivering innovative solutions across the health continuum. Our people experience a variety of unexpected moments when their lives and careers come together in meaningful ways. Learn more by watching this video.\n\nTo find out more about what it’s like working for Philips at a personal level, visit the Working at Philips page on our career website, where you can read stories from our employee blog. Once there,you can also learn about our recruitment process, or find answers to some of the frequently asked questions.\n\n#LI-EU\n\nContact\n\n\nIf you forgot your password, you can click the Forgot Password button on the Sign In screen to reset it.\n\nIf you have any other questions regarding the recruitment process please refer to our FAQs. In case of technical difficulties with the website, please send an email to careersite@philips.com.\n(Note: To ensure fairness and legal compliance in our recruitment processes, only technical issues will be monitored through the above inbox. Please do not submit resumes or applications to this email, as they will not be reviewed. Only applications received through the online application process will be considered.)','2020-07-14',417),(1112,'QA Engineer (Mobile)','We are looking for a Quality Assurance (QA) engineer to write, execute and run test cases to test a mobile app on several operating systems, and verify product quality.\nThe QA engineer role plays an important role in our companys product development cycle. Our ideal candidate will be responsible for participating on a team that is writing test cases, executing test cycles, overseeing the development of a feature to ensure it meets both the companys standards as well as the clients need. Ultimately, the right candidate will be someone who will own the features they have worked on and can work to resolve system malfunctions and raise the quality of the companys system components.\n* This position is temporary for 6-7 months with an option to become a permanent position\n\nKey Responsibilities:\n· Review requirements, specification and technical design documents and provide meaningful feedback to improve its quality.\n· Create detailed, comprehensive and well-structured test cases\n· Estimate, prioritize and help plan testing activities\n· Participate in sprints, assisting the team and communicating status and blockers in a clear and concise manner\n· Identify, record and document bugs\n· Perform regression and sanity testing according to the definition of the sprint and product lifecycle.\n\n\nRequirements:\n· 1-3 years of experience in mobile app testing\n· Knowledge of QA methodologies, tools and processes\n· Experience in writing test cases and incident reporting\n· English communication skills\n· Willing to work in a temp. position for 6-7 months with an option to become a permanent position\n\nAdvantage\n· Bachelors degree in computer science\\ engineering\n· Knowledge of SQL\n· Experience in Agile\\Scrum\n· Previous experience / knowledge in the areas of IoT or financial\\banking platforms\n· Proven experience in code writing\nNayax Requirements\n· Ability to work both independently and as part of a team\n· Willing to share your knowledge with others\n· Passion, dedication, and desire to be the best\n· Strong interpersonal communication skills\n· Proven track-record of problem-solving\n\n\nGroup:\nMonyx\n\nWho we are:\nNayax is a global Fin-tech company and is the leading provider for cashless payment solutions for devices such as vending machines, self-check-out stations, EV chargers and more. Nayax develops both hardware and software products, telemetry, remote management, BI solutions, and mobile apps. Nayax devices can be found all over the world, with branches in 9 countries, and 40 distributing partners. Our devices serve consumers in 55 countries and accept 26 currencies.\nOur Haifa branch is located in WE WORK Haifa, right next to the train station. Join us in our growth!\n\nAbout Monyx:\nNayaxs Monyx Wallet, a consumer engagement platform & payment app for use with Nayax cashless devices has a rich array of features to help increase loyalty and revenue. Customers can receive free items with punch cards and with a gamification win cashback. Consumers can also rate machines, see purchase histories, save favorite locations and send feedback.\nMore about Monyx: https://www.nayax.com/cashless_payments/monyx/\nWatch Monyx on YouTube! https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=LuLG0y-0yE4','2020-07-15',1282),(1113,'RESEARCH ASSISTANT','Org. Setting and Reporting\n\nThis position is located in the Media Monitoring Unit in the Strategic Communications and Public Information Section, United Nations Interim Force in Lebanon (UNIFIL), Naqoura. The incumbent will report to the Head of Media Monitoring designate or his/her designate.\n\nResponsibilities\n\nResearches, extracts and compiles basic information and technical data on specific programmes/projects and related topics and issues.\nSorts, consolidates, extracts and processes data and enter into relevant database.\nAssists in monitoring developments/issues on subjects or areas assigned by collecting, selecting, analyzing and compiling materials from multiple sources, e.g., relevant databases, the library and the Internet.\nAssembles original statistical material, adjusts reported data from different sources and load data into computerized database system.\nAssists in the evaluation and examination of data sets for accuracy, clarity and validity.\nAssists in the maintenance of relevant computerized databases.\nPrepares a variety of reports, presentations, tables, lists, graphs, charts and/or diagrams for information and review by senior officers.\nTranslate press statement and press releases as necessary, maintains a cooperative relationship with local media;\nScreen news from a broad scope of information sources – printed and electronic – setting priorities in relation to UNIFIL’s mandate; analyze, translate and summarize the information in English for the preparation of draft reports and press summaries.\nAssists in Arabic/English Editing for UNIFIL’s bilingual magazine Al Janoub.\nPrepares abstracts/bibliographic descriptions for inclusion in documents, articles, books and publications.\nReviews, stores, classifies, and maintains relevant computerized databases.\nTakes notes and drafts executive summaries of meetings.\nCollects, organizes and disseminates relevant UN and media information.\nCo-ordinates and sets up press briefings, press statements, pamphlets or other public awareness campaigns to educate public on any specific issue.\nPerform other related duties that maybe assigned.\n\nCompetencies\n\nProfessionalism:\nGood computer skills, good knowledge of and internet research capabilities are required.\nShows pride in work and in achievements.\nDemonstrates professional competence and mastery of subject matter.\nIs conscientious and efficient in meeting commitments, observing deadlines and achieving results.\nIs motivated by professional rather than personal concerns.\nShows persistence when faced with difficult problems or challenges; remains calm in stressful situations.\nCommitment to implementing the goal of gender equality by ensuring the equal participation and full\ninvolvement of women and men in all aspects of work.\n\nCommunication:\nSpeaks and writes clearly and effectively\nListens to others, correctly interprets messages from others and responds appropriately\nAsks questions to clarify, and exhibits interest in having two-way communication\nTailors language, tone, style and format to match the audience\nDemonstrates openness in sharing information and keeping people informed\nTeamwork:\nWorks collaboratively with colleagues to achieve organizational goals\nSolicits input by genuinely valuing others’ ideas and expertise; is willing to learn from others\nPlaces team agenda before personal agenda\nSupports and acts in accordance with final group decision, even when such decisions may not entirely reflect\nOwn position.\nShares credit for team accomplishments and accepts joint responsibility for team shortcomings\n\nEducation\n\nHigh School diploma or equivalent is required.\n\nWork Experience\n\nA minimum of five years of progressively responsible experience in collecting and researching data across various areas of social and economic development or related areas is required.\nExperience in UN field mission is desirable.\nExperience in Arabic/English translation and editing document is desirable.\n\nLanguages\n\nEnglish and French are the working languages of the United Nations Secretariat. For the position advertised, fluency in English and Arabic (both oral and written) are required.\n\nAssessment\n\nEvaluation of qualified candidates may include an assessment exercise, which may be followed by competency-based interview.\n\nSpecial Notice\n\nRecruitment against this position is on a local basis; applicants in the General Service category shall meet the relevant employment requirements of the host country (Lebanon), including fulfilling visa or work permit stipulations. If you fulfill the visa and work permit stipulations for Lebanon, please specify in your cover letter and attach a copy of your visa and work permit under ‘attachments” of your application in Inspira.\n\nThe United Nations Secretariat is committed to achieving 50/50 gender balance in its staff. Female candidates are strongly encouraged to apply for this position.\n\nUnited Nations Considerations\n\nAccording to article 101, paragraph 3, of the Charter of the United Nations, the paramount consideration in the employment of the staff is the necessity of securing the highest standards of efficiency, competence, and integrity. Candidates will not be considered for employment with the United Nations if they have committed violations of international human rights law, violations of international humanitarian law, sexual exploitation, sexual abuse, or sexual harassment, or if there are reasonable grounds to believe that they have been involved in the commission of any of these acts. The term “sexual exploitation” means any actual or attempted abuse of a position of vulnerability, differential power, or trust, for sexual purposes, including, but not limited to, profiting monetarily, socially or politically from the sexual exploitation of another. The term “sexual abuse” means the actual or threatened physical intrusion of a sexual nature, whether by force or under unequal or coercive conditions. The term “sexual harassment” means any unwelcome conduct of a sexual nature that might reasonably be expected or be perceived to cause offence or humiliation, when such conduct interferes with work, is made a condition of employment or creates an intimidating, hostile or offensive work environment, and when the gravity of the conduct warrants the termination of the perpetrator’s working relationship. Candidates who have committed crimes other than minor traffic offences may not be considered for employment.\n\nDue regard will be paid to the importance of recruiting the staff on as wide a geographical basis as possible. The United Nations places no restrictions on the eligibility of men and women to participate in any capacity and under conditions of equality in its principal and subsidiary organs. The United Nations Secretariat is a non-smoking environment.\n\nApplicants are urged to follow carefully all instructions available in the online recruitment platform, inspira. For more detailed guidance, applicants may refer to the Manual for the Applicant, which can be accessed by clicking on “Manuals” hyper-link on the upper right side of the inspira account-holder homepage.\n\nThe evaluation of applicants will be conducted on the basis of the information submitted in the application according to the evaluation criteria of the job opening and the applicable internal legislations of the United Nations including the Charter of the United Nations, resolutions of the General Assembly, the Staff Regulations and Rules, administrative issuances and guidelines. Applicants must provide complete and accurate information pertaining to their personal profile and qualifications according to the instructions provided in inspira to be considered for the current job opening. No amendment, addition, deletion, revision or modification shall be made to applications that have been submitted. Candidates under serious consideration for selection will be subject to reference checks to verify the information provided in the application.\n\nJob openings advertised on the Careers Portal will be removed at 11:59 p.m. (New York time) on the deadline date.\n\nNo Fee\n\nTHE UNITED NATIONS DOES NOT CHARGE A FEE AT ANY STAGE OF THE RECRUITMENT PROCESS (APPLICATION, INTERVIEW MEETING, PROCESSING, OR TRAINING). THE UNITED NATIONS DOES NOT CONCERN ITSELF WITH INFORMATION ON APPLICANTS’ BANK ACCOUNTS.','2020-07-29',1283),(1114,'מהנדס/ת אוטומציה לחברה אמריקאית יציבה הממוקמת בחיפה','מיקום: חיפה והצפון\n\nתיאור המשרה:\nאנחנו ממשיכים בעשייה ענפה ונשמח לצרף להצלחה שלנו מהנדס/ת אוטומציה.\nאנחנו חברה אמריקאית ותיקה אשר מפתחת פלטפורמה לשמירת תמונות והדפסה על מוצרים. מרכז הפיתוח בארץ מתעסק בעולם הWeb והMobile. המוצר הינו מוצר פרסונליזציה טכנולוגי מאד שמאפשר בעצם חווית משתמש נוחה ויעילה.\nהפיתוח הינו עם Java, עבודה עם Selenium.\nהצטרף/י אלינו, שלח/י קורות חיים!\n\nדרישות המשרה:\nנסיון של שנתיים בפיתוח אוטומציה\nSelenium\nמס\' משרה: 119851','2020-07-22',76),(1115,'Software Development Engineer - Amazon Go','The Team: Amazon Go is a new kind of store with no lines and no checkout. You simply use the Amazon Go app to enter the store, take what you want from our selection of fresh, delicious meals and grocery essentials, and go. Our checkout-free shopping experience is made possible by our Just Walk Out Technology. It automatically detects when products are taken from or returned to the shelves and keeps track of them in a virtual cart. When youre done shopping, you just leave the store. Shortly after, well charge your Amazon account and send you a receipt. Check it out at amazon.com/go. Designed and custom-built by Amazonians, our technology uses computer vision, sensor fusion, and advanced machine learning. Innovation is part of our DNA. Were looking for people who want to join an ambitious team that continues to push the state of the art in computer vision, machine learning, distributed systems and hardware design.\n\nBasic Qualifications\n\n· We are seeking recent graduates to join our team. This is a unique opportunity to kick off your career in a growing team addressing unique challenges.\n· BSc in Computer Science or related technical field from a leading institution.\n\nPreferred Qualifications\n\n· High grades in courses on algorithms, data structures and systems.','2020-07-03',115),(1116,'SW & Validation: ISP Expert','Posted: Jul 7, 2020\nRole Number:\n200166808\nImagine what you could do here at Apple new ideas have a way of becoming extraordinary products, services, and customer experiences very quickly.\nBring passion and dedication to your job and there\'s no telling what you could accomplish.\nDynamic, smart people and inspiring, innovative technologies are the norm here.\nThe people who work here have reinvented entire industries with all Apple products. The same real passion for innovation that goes into our products also applies to our practices strengthening our commitment to leave the world better than we found it. Join us to help deliver the next groundbreaking Apple product.\nIn this highly visible role you will be responsible to design, develop and implement drivers, tests, and SW infrastructure for complex sensor Image processing pipes and HW accelerators. Work with architects and logic designers to understand the operation of the HW and system design.\nInvestigate the use cases, system-level operation, and performance requirements.\nDevelop low-level software to validate functionality, conformance, and performance of the systems, as well as compliance with architectural models.\nKey Qualifications\n5+ years’ experience in Image processing\nExperience and good understanding in one of more of:\nImage processing pipeline architecture\nImage processing algorithms: image enhancement, de-noising, de-mosaic, pyramid image processing, auto-focus, etc\nSerial camera interface Good knowledge and experience in Real-Time Embedded software development\nGood lab skills and familiarity with lab instruments and measurement techniques\nStrong and proven debug skills\nDescription\nThis position is for an ISP expert engineer with strong background in Embedded software development to take on all aspects of SoC validation, from driver development, through SoC bring-up, Validation and debug.\nCore responsibilities: be a part of the ISP validation team, develop drivers, FW and Automation setups for ISP validation and execute all ISP validation related activities\nEducation & Experience\nBachelor’s Degree or Master’s Degree in Electrical Engineering/ Computer Engineering/ Computer\nScience','2020-07-19',116),(1117,'SW Development Student','Job Title\nSW Development Student\nJob Description\n\n\nIn this role, you have the opportunity to take part in developing advanced CT related software development for a multidisciplinary product.\n\nThe Software Student has the responsibility to assist in creating or enhancing modules and features.\n\nYou are responsible for\nSW Testing on scanner and simulators\nTechnical documents writing\nWriting Unit tests\nStatic code analysis report review and analysis\nWrite an automation for SW team\nYou are a part of SW unit, which is responsible for developing all kind of CT/PET detection related software. The team focuses on developing state of the art software modules including HW controlling, physics algorithms and high performance applications.\n\nTo succeed in this role, you should have the following skills and experience\nB.Sc. in Biomedical Engineering or Computer science or student during his 3th-4th year\nGrade average - 80 and above\nGood English skills\nAvailability for at least 3 days a week (not including Friday)\nPython knowledge\nFull stack automation development in Python/C++ ~2-year experience\n.Net framework, C#, C++ – 2-year knowledge and experience\nGood Analysis and troubleshooting skills\nAdvantage: system integration\nAdvantage: Analysis and troubleshooting of data extracted from automation\nWriting technical documents in English\nWhy should you join Philips?\n\nWorking at Philips is more than a job. It’s a calling to create a healthier society through meaningful work, focused on improving 3 billion lives a year by delivering innovative solutions across the health continuum. Our people experience a variety of unexpected moments when their lives and careers come together in meaningful ways.\n\nTo find out more about what it’s like working for Philips at a personal level, visit the Working at Philips page on our career website, where you can read stories from our employee blog. Once there, you can also learn about our recruitment process, or find answers to some of the frequently asked questions.\n\nContact\n\n\nIf you forgot your password, you can click the Forgot Password button on the Sign In screen to reset it.\n\nIf you have any other questions regarding the recruitment process please refer to our FAQs. In case of technical difficulties with the website, please send an email to careersite@philips.com.\n(Note: To ensure fairness and legal compliance in our recruitment processes, only technical issues will be monitored through the above inbox. Please do not submit resumes or applications to this email, as they will not be reviewed. Only applications received through the online application process will be considered.)','2020-07-05',417),(1118,'Firmware Network Engineer - Cisco Silicon One™','What You\'ll Do?\n\nYou’ll live on the seam line between the SW and HW data path architectures of tomorrow\'s leading infrastructure solutions.\nLearn the functions, features and roadmap of various Cisco products enabled by Leaba Silicon, and program the device to enable those functions.\nContribute to data path architectures of roadmap devices to enable and improve support for new and existing product features.\n\nThis is a unique opportunity to understand products from the high level application down to the data path implementation, with diverse career path to SW or ASIC architecture & development\n\nIn this role, you will:\n\n• Design, develop and program data-path/packet processing flows to support Cisco infrastructure products\n• Interact with Cisco product teams, learn the applications the data path required to support\n• Drive the SW/HW integration\n• contribute to the next generation of leading infrastructure products\nWho You\'ll Work With:\n\nLeaba semiconductor was acquired by Cisco a few years ago. It is now the center of Cisco’s SW and ASIC design.\n\nYou\'ll be part of our Group driving our game changing next generation network devices - Cisco Silicon One™. Our unique team works in a startup atmosphere inside a stable and leading corporate.\n\nOur R&D center is very unique - hosting all silicon HW and SW development disciplines inside one site.\n\nWe are transforming the industry and building a new internet for the 5G era, providing a unified, programmable silicon architecture that is the foundation of all Cisco\'s future routing products.\n\nOur devices are designed to be universally adaptable across service providers and web-scale markets, designed for fixed and modular platforms. Our devices deliver high speed without sacrificing programmability, buffering, power efficiency, scale or feature flexibility.\n\nCisco Silicon One™ is a revolutionary, ground-breaking technology for our customers and end users for decades to come! The Internet now has a new faster, better, safer engine!\n\nLearn more about us right here:\nhttps://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/solutions/service-provider/innovation/silicon-one.html\n\nhttps://fortune.com/2019/12/11/cisco-ceo-chuck-robbins-chips/?_lrsc=ce750ac5-11c8-4995-bfd3-936de1c06009&dtid=osolin001080\n\nhttps://www.calcalist.co.il/internet/articles/0,7340,L-3775619,00.html\n\nhttps://www.youtube.com/watch?v=iy8259BGg6U\nhttps://www.youtube.com/watch?v=BNkiprGWw4Y\n\nWho You Are?\nWe are looking for someone to join a small, and yet influencing team that is:\n\n• Familiar and have some background level in networking, topologies and forwarding protocols (bridge and routers)\n• Is a team player with positive attitude\n• Enjoy learning, self learning which can quickly ramp into new domains\n• background in software/electrical engineer\n• Have a B.Sc or higher, cum laude, from the Technion, TAU, HUJI or BGU, or are highly praised/recommended by a Cisco employee.\n\nWhy Cisco?\n\nThe Leaba team is unique, motivated highly appreciated within Cisco.\n\nAs Cisco, we connect everything: people, processes, data, and things. We innovate everywhere, taking bold risks to shape the technologies that give us smart cities, connected cars, and handheld hospitals. And we do it in style with unique personalities who aren’t afraid to change the way the world works, lives, plays and learns.\n\nWe are thought leaders, tech geeks, pop culture aficionados, and we even have a few purple haired rock stars. We celebrate the creativity and diversity that fuels our innovation. We are dreamers and we are doers.\n\n#We Are Cisco\n\n#LI-MZ1','2020-07-08',229),(1119,'Sr. Marketing Operations Manager','The Sr. Marketing Operations Manager will have a strong technical background and heavy experience supporting Marketing organizations. This role will require people management and mentorship skills. Serve as an SME on data management, process, system integration and marketing cloud capabilities questions. The ideal candidate will spearhead process improvements via automation as well as exploring internal & external solutions to streamline process and tackle business tasks at scale. This role will require collaboration with pricing and promotion, Analytics and Insights, creative team as well as outside vendors to deliver best in class email and direct mail programs. Based on a broad and deep skillset developed by pulling data directly from databases, the ideal candidate will also have intermediate to expert mastery of one or more CRM Multichannel Campaign Development tools and how they are integrated to form cohesive data flow from site to inbox. Audience segmentation, targeting and campaign deployment should come naturally to this user as well as the best practices in identifying the desired recipients of a campaign. Out of the box thinker who can manipulate with data using SQL/Programing to derive desired output to meet business requirements. These concepts should be understood both at the individual campaign level as well as extended longitudinal marketing efforts.\n\nThe individual will be expected to work directly with Marketing Strategy to understand their target audience, project timelines, process and business value. He or she will need to be entrepreneurial as they pro-actively seek an understanding of the underlying data model and existing campaign logic. Keep asking questions, questions, and more questions but ideally with progressive complexity! A friendly and outgoing demeanor is also crucial to success.\n\nRequired\n6+ years of experience working in marketing / tech sector.\nLeading smaller size high impact tech cross-functional teams.\nServed as key participant in database, CRM/marketing cloud migration leading and delegating key tasks among stakeholders and brands/business units.\nExpert proficiency in Teradata or Redshift\n4+ years of Salesforce experience.\nExperience with automation studio, journey builder, audience builder, AMPscripting, creation of landing pages within Salesforce / Exact Target.\nHands on experience with SQL queries executing via various clients.\nShould have worked in medium-large Marketing Operations / CRM teams\nAbility to quickly interpret business requirements into technical language to execute on new/updated strategy and back non-technical terms to explain what has been build or already exists.\nHave created campaigns in Unica IBM, Salesforce or other segmentation software; the more complex the better including: large, multi-wave, multi-segment, multi-channel marketing campaigns.\nDesired\nExperience and knowledge in other digital marketing tools like Responsys, WSA (Watson Campaign Automation) etc.\nSome experience in system integration\nUnderstand and have experience in planning, segmentation, targeting, execution and analysis of marketing campaigns\nSome experience with enterprise marketing solutions like Tableau.\nUnderstanding the concepts of A/B testing, holdouts and control groups\nSome experience and knowledge of back end Unix Systems\nBachelor’s degree or equivalent experience in a technical field','2020-07-17',95),(1120,'Test and Product Lead Engineer','Lead one of Annapurna Labs product family test Engineering team .\nLead the team to cover all test and product engineering aspects of the semiconductor products from early product definition stage to design for test definition to high volume.\nDefine, lead and own all activities related to test development, characterization and product engineering from the test concept definition phase all the way to high volume production.\nDevelop tests, lead optimization of test at various stages to ensure highest quality at the lowest cost.\nWork with design, software and system teams to deliver optimized test and characterization solution to enable highest performance of the product.\n\n\nBasic Qualifications\n\n· Work effectively in a start-up culture\n· Strong technical skills (self and coaching others)\n· A team player, with the ability to work in a rapidly evolving environment\n· Experience in managing a small post Si team. Preferred in test/ product\n· Familiar with chip design processes\n· Hands on experience in productization of Si products\n· Bachelor\'s/Master\'s degree in Electrical Engineering, Computer Science or related field\n· 7 years or more of experience in the field of IC development, including test programs development, test hardware design, product characterization, product qualification, product manufacturing\n· Excellent communication skills. Should be able to well communicate and establish relations with internal customers and vendors\n\nPreferred Qualifications\n\n· Wide knowledge and experience in silicon debug techniques and flows\n· Knowledge of SoC testing during both the development and volume production stages, including product ramp-up\n· Deep understanding of DFT and DFM methods','2020-07-14',115),(1121,'Senior Embedded Engineer for the Silicon validation team','Posted: Jun 11, 2020\nWeekly Hours: 42\nRole Number:\n200000153\nImagine what do you could do here.\nAt Apple, new ideas have a way of becoming extraordinary products, services, and customer experiences very quickly. Bring passion and dedication to your job and there\'s no telling what you could accomplish.\nDynamic, smart people and inspiring, innovative technologies are the norm here.\nThe people who work here have reinvented entire industries with all Apple products.\nThe same real passion for innovation that goes into our products also applies to our practices strengthening our commitment to leave the world better than we found it. Join us to help deliver the next groundbreaking Apple product.\nWork with logic designers to understand the operation of the block and system levels.\nInvestigate the use cases, system-level operation, and performance requirements .\nDevelop low-level software to validate functionality, conformance, and performance of the systems.\nKey Qualifications\nStrong knowledge in C\nExperience in HW-SW integrations.\nAt least 3y experience programming in RT/Embedde