d\ncome join us invent the future and change the world.\n\n\n\n\n\nBasic Qualifications\n\n· MS or PhD required in computer vision, machine learning, or related discipline, 5-7+ years of professional experience\n·\n· 3-5 years of experience leading research teams working with state-of-the-art computer vision and machine learning technologies\n·\n· Strong record of patents and innovation or publications in top-tier peer-reviewed conferences or journals\n·\n· Proven track record of leading innovation efforts in creating novel algorithms and advancing the state of the art\n·\n· Strong business writing, verbal communication, and cross discipline collaboration skills\n\n\n\nPreferred Qualifications\n\n· Experience optimizing for short term execution while planning for long term technical capabilities. Ability and willingness to multi-task and learn new technologies quickly.\n·\n· Experience with designing and building large-scale systems in a multi-tiered, distributed environment (Service Oriented Architecture).\n·\n· Project planning/execution skills including estimating and scheduling.','2020-07-16',115),(1131,'Emulation Engineer','Posted: Jul 2, 2020\nRole Number:\n200165035\nImagine what you could do here. At Apple, new insights have a way of becoming extraordinary products, services, and customer experiences very quickly. Bring passion and dedication to your job and there\'s no telling what you could accomplish. Dynamic, smart people and inspiring, innovative technologies are the norm here. The people who work here have reinvented entire industries with all Apple Hardware products.\nThe same passion for innovation that goes into our products also applies to our practices strengthening our dedication to leave the world better than we found it. Join us to help deliver the next groundbreaking Apple product.\n\nAre you passionate about changing the world? We are looking for a you to join our emulation team focusing on the creation, deployment, and support of sophisticat