edge\nin CAPA, NCMR, RMA, Labeling, Rework and Batch release processes.\nAbility to\nwork effectively in a team environment with a diverse group of people.\nAbility to effectively solve problems.\nStrong technical understanding.\nFluent in English and Hebrew.\nNice to Have\nISO 13485:2016 Certified lead auditor\nCertified Quality Engineer (CQE) or other similar Quality/Reilibility certifications\nLean Six Sigma green/black belt\nExperience\nin utilization of statistical techniques such design of experiments,\nhypothesis testing, SPC, etc. as part of Quality Engineering discipline.\nSupplier\nQuality Engineering experience.\nWorking knowledge of process improvement skills.','2020-07-29',509),(1133,'Student for Physical Design (Layout)','Job ID: JR0130842\n\nJob Category: Intern/Student\n\nPrimary Location: Haifa, IL\n\nOther Locations:\nJob Type: Intern\n\nStudent for Physical Design (Layout)\n\nJob Description\n\nIn a world completely released from the bonds that tied him to place, the WCS group stands at the forefront of progress and technology. The group develops and implements wireless technologies, using Multi-Comm Wireless solutions in integrated products that enable smart and easy use of Intel products wide range of applications. We are working on delivering world-class wireless connectivity technologies such as Wi-Fi and Bluetooth.\n\nOur students have an important role now and in the future for our team. In this capacity you will be part of a design team that is responsible for design of sophisticated wireless SOC\'s with demanding requirements in power, performance, cost & area. The team is responsible for all stages of VLSI development including Layout circuit design, RF and analog design. In this capacity you will be responsible for the physical design (layout) of complex analog and mixed signal circuits.\n\nThese circuits are a critical element of Intel\'s solutions for wireless connectivity such as WiFi, Bluetooth etc.\n\nQualifications\n\nQualification