erformance analysis\nExpertise in various protocols: PCIe, DRAM, network, serdes etc','2020-07-16',115),(1135,'Manager Software Engineering - Medical Device','JOB DESCRIPTION:\n\n\nAbbott in Israel is looking for an\n\nManager Software Engineering - Medical Device\n\n\nto be based in the Haifa R&D Center.\n\nThe Software Engineering Manager will be responsible for leading the software engineering team for design, implementation and verification of our cardiac mapping and ablation systems. This is a highly visible role where you will join the project leadership team having an opportunity to directly interact with key stakeholders including KOLs and world-class researchers. You act as both Team Manager and Technical Lead.\n\nWe are seeking a highly-motivated, execution-focused leader with the ability to define roles and activities necessary for a successful product commercialization.\n\nResponsibilities\nBuild and manage a high-performance software engineering team by developing, mentoring and coaching each engineer as appropriate. Inspire and motivate the team members to achieve individual and project goals for on-time product delivery with exceptional quality\nDesign and deliver cardiac mapping systems with best in class data visualization and usability\nDrive development of software architecture and functionality - with an emphasis on modularity and portability to allow reuse. Manage and enhance software architecture and technology stack to meet future needs and scalability\nManage GUI, hardware control and database design for optimal performance and integration with system\nManage the research and prototyping of new and innovative solutions; manage feasibility studies of the design to determine if capable of functioning as intended\nLead software development efforts with various external partners and subcontractors. Work with them to ensure that the work is getting done when it needs to be and with the quality and consistency we strive to deliver to our patients. 