nce working with C/C++ or any other modern programming language\nFamiliarity with DICOM and PACS is a plus\nStrong leadership skills, including the ability to set goals and provide positive and constructive feedback respectfully to build positive relationships and improve business results.\nExcellent oral and written communication skills with the ability to communicate clearly to upper management and other stakeholders in different functions at various levels\nStrong organizational, planning, and follow-up skills and ability to hold others accountable\nAbility to work effectively a fast-paced changing environment.\nAbility to travel approximately 15%.\nWe are looking forward to your applications\nJOB FAMILY:\nIT Services & Solutions Delivery\nDIVISION:\nEPHF Electrophysiology & Heart Failure\nLOCATION:\nIsrael : MATAM - Advanced Technology Center Bld. 23, Floor 3\nADDITIONAL LOCATIONS:\nWORK SHIFT:\nStandard\nTRAVEL:\nYes, 15 % of the Time\nMEDICAL SURVEILLANCE:\nNot Applicable\nSIGNIFICANT WORK ACTIVITIES:\nNot Applicable','2020-07-29',492),(1136,'Israel CS Marketing Communications Student','Job ID: JR0140265\n\nJob Category: Intern/Student\n\nPrimary Location: Haifa, IL\n\nOther Locations:\nJob Type: Intern\n\nIsrael CS Marketing Communications Student\n\nJob Description\nJoin Intel-and build a better tomorrow! Intel is in the midst of an exciting transformation, with a vision to create and extend computing technology to connect and enrich the lives of every person on Earth. So join us-and help us create the next generation of technologies that will shape the future for decades to come.\n\nCorporate Services (CS) touches the lives of every Intel employee every day. CS creates an environment where employees can prosper while creating the innovative technologies that make amazing possible. Our scope is vast and includes operating and maintaining all Intel sites, offices, labs and factories globally as well as onsite services and onsite services and experiences that 