ts. Technical background or training is a plus.\nExperience with market research, competitive analysis, and usability testing. Leverage insights and data gathered to drive business decisions and inform product roadmap.\nPassion for bringing innovative new products to market and creating great user experiences.\nHolistic understanding of the mobile user experience (e.g. technology, user behavior, market).\nStrong analytic and strategic thinking skills.','2020-07-17',95),(1140,'Formal Verification Engineer','Posted: Dec 31, 2019\nRole Number:\n200023003\nWe’re looking for talented university recently graduates or with HW related experience, with real passion for Logic design and/or Mathematics, to join our unique formal verification team.\nWe’re offering formal verification course for learning the theory and practice from our leading industry experts.\nFormal verification (FV), means proving that a property holds for a model of a design. Proving is done exhaustively for all possible case.\nFV can be applied to verify SW or HW, our focus is on verifying HW (RTL) using Model checking techniques\nKey Qualifications\nExcellent graduates from leading universities\nanalytical thinking\nHighly motivated.\nDescription\nIn this role you will be responsible for applying model checking techniques, to find bugs in RTL and architecture specifications\nEducation & Experience\nB.Sc. in Electrical/Computer Engineering/ Mathematics and Computer Science.','2020-07-03',116),(1141,'Experienced Power and Performance Validation Engineer','Job ID: JR0139781\n\nJob Category: Engineering\n\nPrimary Location: Haifa, IL\n\nOther Locations:\nJob Type: Experienced Hire\n\nExperienced Power and Performance Validation Engineer\n\nJob Description\n\nWe have an opening for a talented power and performance validation and optimization engineer for Intel client products; as a PnP Engineer, you will be responsible for the product (SOC) characterization, power and performance optimization in addition to t