nd customer experiences very quickly.\nEvery single day, people do amazing things at Apple.\nDo you want to impact billions of users by developing extraordinary products with a prime focus on accuracy and performance of the product?\nYou will become part of a hands-on development team that furthers engineering excellence, creativity and innovation. Dynamic, inspiring people and innovative technologies are the norm here.\nWe want you to join our team if you are an innovative engineer with the dream to research and develop solutions that do not yet exist. As a member of our PD CAD team, you will take part in developing and supporting the Physical Design flow (netlist->layout) in advanced technologies and will be working closely with Physical Design teams and EDA vendors.\nThis position involves in-depth understanding of the physical design flow from Netlist to GDS2. You will possess detailed understanding of design partitioning, floor planning, place and route, and clock tree synthesis required for establishing flows and methodologies.\nKey Qualifications\nYou have experience 3+ years of experience with complete backend (RTL2GDSII) design flow: synthesis, formal (equivalence checks), floor planning, power grid planning, CTS, placement, route, post route optimization, extraction, static timing, physical verification, EM-IR and ECO flows.\nExperience in using EDA tools like Synopsys (Primetime, ICC, ICC2), Mentor (Calibre), and Cadence (First Encounter/Innovus, ETS/Tempus, Virtuoso, Conformal)\nAdditional experience with synthesis, static timing analysis, formal verification and custom layout tools (Virtuoso, VXL) is highly preferred.\nLayout design background and experience a plus.\nYou have good understanding of timing analysis (including noise and signal integrity), power analysis, physical verification, formal verification.\nYou have good knowledge of timing analysis, power analysis, physical verification, formal verification.\nYou have good Understanding of VLSI Flow from Specification to Silicon Programming Skills: Knowledge of Signal Integrity\nYou have good Scripting skills to debug flow related issues and make enhancements as appropriate\nLayout design background and experience a plus\nMust be proficient in PERL, Tcl/Tk, and shell scripting languages.\nExpert knowledge of programming and scripting language is a plus.\nYou have excellent communication and problem solving skills\nDescription\nAs a Physical Design CAD engineer, you will take part in flow development and in close day to day work with the physical design engineers, to make our physical design work better and projects execution successful.\nYou will Interface with the physical design teams/Vendor teams for flow bring up and validation as well as support issues related to the flow and tools You will be Working closely with the implementation team during the entire chip design cycle to drive sign-off closure for tape-out.\nEducation & Experience\nBSc/ MSc in Electrical Engineering or Computer Science.','2020-07-28',116),(1146,'DSP Algorithms Engineer','Job ID: JR0140295\n\nJob Category: Engineering\n\nPrimary Location: Haifa, IL\n\nOther Locations: Israel, Petah-Tikva\n\nJob Type: Experienced Hire\n\nDSP Algorithms Engineer\n\nJob Description\n\nIntel EGI develops next-generation high-performance long-range LIDAR systems for autonomously driving vehicles. The project involves cutting edge electro-optic modules for FMCW LIDAR, HW, VLSI, mechanics, SW FW and Algorithms.\n\nWe are looking for an experienced Algo DSP Engineer at the LIDAR system engineering group.\nAs a part of your work you will be a part of a team of experienced algorithms engineers and researchers that:\nDevelop ASIC (HW) based algorithms for sampling, pre-processing and processing of multi-channel RF signals for LIDAR applications, as well as range and velocity estimators and image processing of the 4D (range/directions/velocity) representation of the LiDAR output.\nDeliver fixed point ASIC algo specifications to VLSI team, and DSP algo specifications to SW team.\nDevelop comprehensive E2E simulation infrastructure for verification of algorithm pipes at the system level, and release algorithms to ASIC VLSI design and to FW and SW.\nAnalyze field recorded data and confirm system performance through emulations.\nWork closely with the physics team to develop novel concepts for algorithms developments.\nQualifications\nBA/MA in computer science, mathematics and/or B.Sc. in Engineering, Science\nAt least 5 years of relevant work experience\nExperience in DSP for RF signals (communication, RADAR, sensors)\nExperience in releasing algorithms to SW, FW and ASIC implementation.\nGood Understanding of multidisciplinary system modules - optics, mechanics, algorithms, and of the system level application.\nClose work interfaces with system architects, VLSI and SW teams.\nFlexible and adaptable to work in a fast-paced work environment while supporting field tests and other team tasks.\nPreferred - experience in algo/system engineering development of electro-optic multi-disciplinary systems and/or of imaging system of other modalities\nPreferred - experience with image analysis / imaging sensors development.\nInside this Business Group\n\nEmerging Growth Incubation (EGI) Group is responsible for creating an environment within Intel to generate new billion-dollar businesses leveraging Intel\'s competitive advantages. We focus on new business opportunities and identify, incubate and scale the next \"big thing\" for Intel.\n\nOther Locations\n\nIsrael, Petah-Tikva\nILExperienced HireJR0140295Haifa','2020-07-29',422),(1147,'Director, Marketing Technology Engineering','Shutterfly is looking for a talented and high-energy marketing analytics leader who will lead digital marketing analytics and data science function. In this role, you will have a deep understanding of the impact various demand gen programs and strategy have on each stage of the journey to help accelerate the buying decision and support the entire customer lifecycle. The role is perfect for someone with the player-coach approach –who can roll up their sleeves as well as provide mentorship to others.\n\nJob Responsibilities\nPartner with leadership across Marketing and IT to understand our funnel, measure, uncover opportunities, and influence strategy and roadmaps to improve progress towards business objectives.\nDevelop a team of exceptional analytics professionals\nDeliver presentations to clearly and effectively communicate findings to stakeholders and executive leadership\nTranslate data into actions and recommendations – appropriately interpreting and building on findings, and fully exploiting insights - the work does not stop at “pulling the data.”\nUnlock insights and guide the business – everything from tactical site optimizations to broad level strategic direction that is grounded in data evidence and substantial analytical rigor. The job requires a multidisciplinary blend of analytical experience, strong technical capability, and business strategy. All applied in tandem to discover key insights that lie hidden in web and transactional data.\nGood understanding of machine learning and artificial intelligence methodology.\nDrive the development of quantitative analysis, ad hoc reports, and models to support marketing decision making, particularly around lifetime value, retention, targeting, multi-touch attribution, and media mix optimization\nManage the design, execution, and analysis of A/B or multivariate testing programs; driving rigor, building a testing culture and enhancing measurement capabilities throughout the organization\nDetermine, analyze, maintain, and report on core marketing metrics to identify causal relationships between marketing actions and outcomes.\nLead by example by contributing first-hand in key business decisions, certifying assumptions, and assessing logic chains.\nDrive collaboration with internal and external technology partners (e.g., engineering, marketing/sales technology, data analytics, data science, and vendors) to firm up requirements and prioritize deliverables to enable data for decision-making.\nRequired Experience And Skills\n10+ years of total experience with 5+ years of experience building and leading analytics and data science teams with a strong understanding of ecommerce business. Ideally leading across a portfolio of business/products\nProven experience in driving projects from start to finish, while driving impact influencing roadmaps\nExpert command of analytics, statistical modeling, state-of-the-art tools, and marketing best practices. e.g., causal inference, significance testing, regression analysis.\nExperience with SQL, particular with big data\nSome coding ability in R or Python is a plus\nImpeccable attention to detail and a strong ability to convert complex data into insights and action plans.\nStrategic thinker, flexible problem solver, great listener, and team orientation.\nCommunication and presentation experience with a proven track record of using insights to influence executives and colleagues\n• MBA, or a BS, MS, or Ph.D. in an appropriate field (Computer Science, Engineering, Statistics, Applied Math, Econometrics, Operations Research','2020-07-17',95),(1148,'Software Engineer - Caesarea','Careers that Change Lives\n\nA Day in the Life\n\nResponsibilities may include the following and other duties may be assigned.\nDesigns, develops, tests, debugs and implements operating systems components, software tools and utilities.\nDetermines systems software design requirements.\nEnsures that system improvements are successfully implemented and monitored to increase efficiency.\nGenerates systems software engineering policies, standards and procedures.\n\nMust Have: Minimum Requirements\nBachelors degree required\nMinimum of 2 years of relevant experience, or advanced degree with 0 years of experience\nNice to Have\n\nAbout Medtronic\n\nTogether, we can change healthcare worldwide. At Medtronic, we push the limits of what technology, therapies and services can do to help alleviate pain, restore health and extend life. We challenge ourselves and each other to make tomorrow better than yesterday. It is what makes this an exciting and rewarding place to be.\n\nWe want to accelerate and advance our ability to create meaningful innovations - but we will only succeed with the right people on our team. Let’s work together to address universal healthcare needs and improve patients’ lives. Help us shape the future.\n\nPhysical Job Requirements\n\nThe physical demands described within the Responsibilities section of this job description are representative of those that must be met by an employee to successfully perform the essential functions of this job. Reasonable accommodations may be made to enable individuals with disabilities to perform the essential functions. For Office Roles: While performing the duties of this job, the employee is regularly required to be independently mobile. The employee is also required to interact with a computer, and communicate with peers and co-workers. Contact your manager or local HR to understand the Work Conditions and Physical requirements that may be specific to each role. (ADA-United States of America)','2020-07-28',509),(1149,'Frontend עבור חברת סטארטאפ בתחום ה- Agri-tech','מיקום: חיפה והצפון\n\nתיאור המשרה:\nחברת סטארטאפ גלובלית שמפתחת מערכת שמסייעת לחקלאים לנטר את היבולים שלהם מגייסת מפתח/ת Frontend. מדובר בפלטפורמה מבוססת IOT ובינה מלאכותית שמאפשרת לחקלאים להעניק לשדות טיפול מדויק יותר. לחברה לקוחות משלמים בכל העולם\nמונים 60 אנשים\n\nדרישות המשרה:\nשנתיים ניסיון בפיתוח Frontend\nAngular\nמס\' משרה: 116752','2020-07-25',76),(1150,'HW Engineering Student','Posted: Feb 17, 2020\nRole Number:\n200000200\nWill you help us design future generations of revolutionary Apple products? Be inspired every single day. We’re visionaries. Inventors. Forever tinkering with products and processes, always on the lookout for better. A job at Apple is one that requires a lot of you, but it’s also one that rewards bright, creative thinking and hard work. None of us here at Apple would have it any other way. At Apple, we work every single day to craft products that enrich people’s lives. Do you love working on challenges that no one has solved yet? Do you like changing the game? We have an opportunity for forward-thinking and uncommonly hardworking students to join our teams. As a member of our dynamic group, you will have the rare and rewarding opportunity to craft upcoming products that will delight and inspire millions of Apple’s customers every single day.\nKey Qualifications\nExperience with Python/ Linux/ C/C++ or other scripting languages is an advantage\nDescription\nTEAMS: In this student role you will work within a segment of Apple’s Engineering team responsible for various fields, focusing on hardware. Apple recruiting will work together with you and lines of business in order to find the best possible match for both sides!\n\nANALOG LAYOUT (HERZELIYA AND HAIFA): MsC students will have an advantage for this role. In this role you will take part in development of analog IP. Your job will be to assure, along with our analog engineers, the IP is meeting Apple’s high quality standards and can integrate into the industry’s leading mobile devices. This role involves working closely with different multi-functional teams within Apple. Your responsibility will likely include:\nDefining and specifying requirements for analog IP, IP design, characterization and debug - Writing specifications, test plans and characterization reports - Supporting Apple system teams with product integration, bring up and debug.\nWorking with our chip design teams, system HW and SW design teams, etc.\nPRODUCT TEST(HAIFA ONLY): As part of our VLSI Product and Test group, you’ll support the development of VLSI products. In the position you will have responsibility for developing programs for characterization, production test, test hardware, and maintaining cross product libraries and tools. You will work with both the manufacturing team and the design team to develop the product. Together, you and your team will enable our customers to do all the things they love with their devices. You will go beyond the industry norm and demonstrate creativity in problem solving, ability to think dynamically and outside of standard convention, and adapt quickly to new technical areas. We promote innovation and new technology. The people who work here have reinvented and defined entire industries with the Mac, iPhone, iPad, Apple TV, Apple Watch, AirPods, HomePod and a multitude of groundbreaking Accessories. We have done the same with services, including iTunes, the App Store, Apple Music, and Apple Pay. The same passion for innovation that goes into our products also applies to our practices — strengthening our commitment to leave the world better than we found it. You should join us to help deliver the next amazing Apple product.\n\nVALIDATION (HERZELIYA): This isn\'t an ordinary automation and validation engineering position. You will engage in a reciprocal and rapidly changing environment to discover and solve challenging problems that arise from integrating new technologies into Apple’s products. You will join a hands-on development team that champions engineering excellence, creativity and innovation. Put your creativity, hardware background, programming, and problem solving skills to the test. Adapt quickly to new technical areas, and deeply engage multi-functional teams to solve problems. In this role you will be responsible for all aspects of a large-scale lab designed for testing new Hardware and Firmware. Your responsibility will likely include:\nOperation of a large-scale automation lab testing multiple products simultaneously - Testing of HW and FW, including management of automated tests, integration and debug of lab failures - Integration of multiple deliverables from various R&D teams at Apple in order to ensure timely delivery of a quality product\nFAILURE & DATA ANALYSIS (HERZELIYA): Join a world-class team of Research & Development engineers in advancing mass storage solutions. In this role, you will be exposed to all aspect of the technology and will have a direct impact on Apple\'s next generation of storage products. You will be required to understand the full system’s behaviour in order to characterise and resolve system-level issues, typically by using multi-disciplinary approach. Your responsibility will likely include:\nIdentification and structuring of complicated, system-wide issues.\nAnalysis of flash memory characteristics.\nOversight of severe failures in conjunction with other teams around the globe.\nMine and interpret large data using statistical techniques.\nSW tool development for big data analysis and automated failure analysis.\nEducation & Experience\nPursuing a B.Sc.M.Sc. in Electrical Engineering, Computer Engineering, Communication System Engineering, SW Engineering or Computer Science from a leading university.\nStudents who have completed at least 3 semesters.\n\nPlease add your Grades sheet when applying.\nApple is an Equal Opportunity Employer committed to inclusion and diversity. We take affirmative action to offer employment and advancement opportunities to all applicants, including minorities, women, and individuals with disabilities.','2020-07-28',116),(1151,'Linux Kernel Developer','Job ID: JR0139837\n\nJob Category: Engineering\n\nPrimary Location: Haifa, IL\n\nOther Locations:\nJob Type: Experienced Hire\n\nLinux Kernel Developer\n\nJob Description\nMobileye Autonomous Driving software group in Haifa is looking for a Linux kernel developer who will be responsible for developing embedded SW products.\n\nThis is an exciting opportunity to work with highly talented engineers and be a part of product innovation on cutting edge technologies.\n\nWhat you will do?\nResearching, designing, imple