ment code in industry-standard tools and languages\n\nJob Responsibilities:\nYou will study the definition and functional requirements of hardware components and RTL designs,\nby reading specifications and reviewing with architects, designers, and verification teams.\nYou will define and develop Formal Verification environments, and run the proofs until fully verified.\nDuring the development of the proof you will identify design bugs and help to clean them out from the design.\n\n#HW\n\nQualifications\n\nMust Have :\nStudying for B.Sc. or MSc in Computer Science / Electrical Engineering\nCompleted at least 4 semesters and with at least 4 semesters till graduation.\nCompleted the following courses (or similar): Introduction to programming, Logic systems\nNeed to be available for 20 work hours a week (excluding semester exam periods)\n\nNice to have:\nCompleted course of introduction to networking, computer architecture\nExperience with working in Unix/Linux shell environment\nExperience with Perl/Python\n\nInside this Business Group\n\nThe Data Center Group (DCG) is at the heart of Intels transformation from a PC company to a company that runs the cloud and billions of smart, connected computing devices. The data center is the underpinning for every data-driven service, from artificial intelligence to 5G to high-performance computing, and DCG delivers the products and technologiesspanning software, processors, storage, I/O, and networking solutionsthat fuel cloud, communications, enterprise, and government data centers around the world.','2020-07-28',398),(1168,'System Architecture Verification Engineer','Job Description:\nFor a hi-tech firm developing products in the field of communication, with offices in the Haifa area\n\nAdditional Positions:\nVerification, Verification Engineer, Verification Manager\n\nCategory:\nHardware\n\nJob Qualifications:\nB.Sc. in Computer Science / Computer Engineering / Electrical Engineering from The Technion / Tel Aviv University / B