eedback of our Digital Marketing director. The program lasts for at least 7 weeks, during which interns work 5 days a week.\nIn exchange for your hard work you get:\nFree accommodation in a mixed-gender dorm room, occupied only by hostel volunteers (the room includes a shower and toilet, WiFi and air conditioning)\nFree access to all hostel facilities - guest kitchen, TV room, lounge, rooftop terrace and laundry\nFree breakfast\n50% off at the bar\nMost tours for free, based on availability\nFree stays at our other hostels (Jerusalem and Nazareth)\nFree or discounted stays at other hostels in Israel that are members of the ILH (Israeli Hostels)\nTo apply you must:\nBe between 21-35 years old\nCommit to a minimum of 7 weeks\nHave a good command of English\nHave experience traveling and staying at hostels\nBe able to bring your own photography equipment as well as a laptop\nBe flexible and have a high work ethic\nBe a non-Israeli foreigner\nPlease note - The program is for non-Israeli foreigners ONLY!','2020-07-30',606),(1253,'Java Engineer','We are looking for bright software Java Developer- to join our Rnd analytics Team\nJava Developer for Cyber Company in Petach Tikvah\n\nThis is focusing on expanding our solutions; learning different firewalls and network devices and implementing configuration analysis and management.\nThis is a great opportunity for a Java developer with passion for network security!\nThis is a huge challenge and an opportunity to get in at a very interesting phase of the product, and make a significant impact - while working as part of a highly talented team in an environment which fosters innovation, independence, responsibility and keeps the customer in mind at all times.\nRequirements:\nBSc. in Computer Sciences/Engineering from a known university.\nAt least 5 years of experience in software development ( C/C++ experience – an advantage)\nAt least 3 years of experience in Java\nExperience in Spring, Hibernate\nExperience in concurrency and data structures\nExperience in Linux/UNIX environments ( bash and scripting- an advantage)\nExperience in Unit tests and continues development\nExperience in SQL/PostgreSQL\nExperience in networking, routing protocols, firewalls, public clouds - an advantage\nMulti-service or multi component application development - an advantage\nTeam player, pleasant person to work with, high level of integrity\nVery bright, fast learner, independent and organized','2020-07-30',76),(1279,'Internship Program','The Cortica Internship Program offers students and recent graduates opportunities in a variety of the fastest growing technology arenas with one of the \"coolest companies in Israel\" (Business Insider, 2017).\n\nAn internship at Cortica gives you the opportunity to dive directly into high impact technology to work with teams on the forefront of the artificial intelligence revolution. Internship rotations are available across all divisions of Cortica including artificial intelligence (AI), autonomous vehicles, image understanding, and more.\n\nWithin these divisions, interns have the opportunity to work closely with our most important departmental teams including:\n\nAlgorithms\nWorking with the research and development team to devise new ways to understand concepts, objects, and more from within photos and videos\n\nSoftware\nOur SW team works very closely with algorithm developers on the next generation of autonomous platforms such as autonomous vehicles, autonomous drones and smart camera.\n\nBusiness Development\nInterfacing with Fortune 1000 companies and other potential partners to devise new strategic business initiatives, prospect new clients, and create pitch materials.\n\nProduct\nstructuring and planning the productization of Cortica\'s artificial intelligence computer vision technology across a multitude of verticals.\n\nMarketing\nCreating awareness of Cortica and our products through traditional marketing tactics, social media, and much more\n\nResponsibilities:\