adership and will curate opportunities for op-eds and events in relevant communities. As part of your role, you will help promote Jolt’s thought leadership within the technical community and create meaningful content about technical leadership that will help founders, CTOs and R&D leaders in Israel to excel at their positions.\n\nYou are\n\nThe perfect combination of a get-things-done persona and a curious individual; An independent, efficient, task-oriented and tech-savvy person, with a high level of creativity, who is passionate about researching, learning new things and creating content.\n\nYour day to day work will include:\nResearch potential topics for the podcast episodes about technical leadership\nEdit the content for the podcast and blog\nCreate a text version of the podcast episodes to publish them on the blog\nOutreach speakers\nCoordinate interviews and podcast recordings\nHelp promote the podcast and blog on social media\nFind opportunities to publish technical op-eds and to participate in relevant community events and webinars (in Israel and in the UK)\nRequirements\nExperienced in coordinating, production and rapid-scheduling\nExperienced in content editing\nProven record of research skills\nFast working\nTechnology orientation and familiarity with different high-tech fields\nFamiliarity with audio production or podcasting\nSuperb communications skills\nExcellent English\nAvailability to work 80 hours per month\nBenefits\n\nOther than working alongside passionate, mission-driven Individuals, you\'ll get full access to all of Jolt’s content, delivered by the world\'s top professionals.\n\nJolt is an equal opportunity employer. We do not discriminate against any employee or job applicant on the bases of race, color, gender, national origin, age, religion, creed, disability or sex.','2020-07-16',1464),(1295,'Brand Strategist','Brand Strategist - Tel Aviv\nTel AvivMarketing - Marketing planningExperienced\nResponsibilities\n• Support the sales team to co