ears experience in writing SQL statements.\nAbility to analyze data to identify deliverables, gaps, and inconsistencies.\nCommunication skills including the ability to identify and communicate data-driven insights.\nAbility in managing and communicating data warehouse plans to internal clients.\nPreferred Qualifications:','2020-07-27',127),(1570,'UX/UI Designer (Part time / Contractor)','We are looking for a passionate, creative and highly motivated Product Designer (UI/UX) to join our product team for on a part-time (or freelance) position in Tel Aviv.\nAs a product designer, you will be involved in all development process aspects of Mobilize\' wide range of products and features, from initial brainstorming, research, wireframe, high-end mockups and prototyping to launch and beyond.\nEnvision the entire end-to-end user experience and create strong visual, modern, and user-centric designs across our various product lines.\nCollaborate with the product managers and software developers to define, design, and deliver cutting edge products for both web and mobile.\nBuild wireframes and turn them into clean web interfaces that aim at wowing our customers and achieving business goals; develop the user interface so information is easy to read, understand and act on.\nTranslate business goals, product requirements, research and testing insights into designs that improve our products.\nRequirements\nA well-rounded designer with UX/UI experience who is competent in all of facets of the design process and who connects the dots between business needs, innovation and good design.\nA sense for extraordinary, pixel-perfect design solutions.\nA passion for solving design problems while wearing multiple hats and owning all facets of design (strategy, art direction, and interaction design)\nA portfolio that demonstrates excellence in visual design and a capacity to solve user experience challenges with simple, empathetic solutions.\nAt least 3 years of experience working in a profess