analyzing large datasets – an advantage','2020-07-27',964),(1581,'Full Stack Web Developer','Inlight Labs is a small and successful company, with products used by tens of thousands of business owners worldwide. We’re looking for an ambitious and experienced Fullstack developer who will be taking a major part in developing our products. We’re looking for someone with React and Angular experience and extensive backend knowledge. If you’re passionate about creating modern UI/UX and are able to execute sophisticated logic flows to perfection, contact us!\nRequirements\n3+ years of experience in web development\n2+ years of frontend or fullstack development\nBSc Computer Science / Software Engineering\nExperience working with node.js, Angular, React or similar frameworks and technologies - a must\nPython and dev-ops knowledge - a plus\nExperience working on products with high emphasis on design (working with designers, building design systems, etc) - a plus\nTechnical leadership and personal management skills\nTeam player with excellent interpersonal skills\nAttention to detail and ability to take direction and criticism\n\nBenefits\nTake a key part in a small team, with tons of responsibility and room to innovate and grow\nWork in a pleasant, respectful and success-oriented environment\nCompetitive salary\nAwesome office (dog friendly!), central TLV, 10bis, HH and bday celebrations','2020-07-22',1755),(1583,'מנהל/ת פרויקטים','אנו מגייסים מנהל/ת פרויקטים לארגון גדול, מפנק ויציב! אם מעניין אתכם/ן להיכנס ולנהל פרויקטים גדולים ומורכבים מאפס בתקצוב של מיליוני שקלים - מקומכם איתנו! ישיבה בפתח תקווה, נשמע לכם/ן? העבירו קו\"ח ** המשרה פונה לנשים וגברים כאחד 3-4 שנות ניסיון בניהול פרויקטים - חובה!\n\nהיכרות עם העולם האפליקטיבי, תשתיות ובסיסי נתונים- חובה! ניסיון בתכניות עבודה וניהול MS PROJECT - יתרון!','2020-07-31',1757),(1585,'Backend Team Leader (core)','Ever ordered something online and had to wait days or even weeks for it? Were here to put an end to thatwith robots! In a sea of ad-tech, cyber, and more of the same, were not just another boring SaaS platform. Yes, Fabric is a software and robotics company, but thats not the coolest thing about us; were here to solve real-world problems that you care about as a consumer and will find fascinating as a developer.\n\nWere on a mission to enable fast and profitable e-commerce fulfillment through a revolutionary concept called micro-fulfillment. Our engineers are solving complex problems in the areas of control, robot movement, stock management and prediction, image processing and much more. All that to make our micro-fulfillment centers (MFCs) fast, small, efficient, and optimized. Were already serving the likes of \"Rami Levy\" and \"Super-Pharm\" here in Israel, and we just received a mega funding round of $110M, making us the best funded player in the space.\nNow is the perfect time to join us, tackle the hard stuff and help scale our solution.\n\nWere looking for a brilliant Senior Back end Team Leader to join our growing R&D team. This is an amazing opportunity to join one of Israel\'s most promising startups [link] and make an immediate and real impact on the future of our product (and the world).\n\nOur Stack: Python, PostgreSQL, mongoDB, React.JS, Redux, node.js, Elastic Search, Docker, AWS, Mac/Linux\n\nIn this role, you will:\nLead a team of highly talented and independent developers in a rapidly changing environment where code is deployed every day.\nDevelop and improve features to optimize our sites performance and operation end-to-end - from ideation, design, implementation, testing, deployment, to post-deployment analysis.\nSolve highly complex problems in the fields of multi-agent motion, resource planning and optimization.\nCentralize team\'s activities, including new feature development, automation, testing, bug management, and planning your team\'s iterations in an Agile environment.\n\n\nRequirements:\nStrong algorithmic background.\nExperience in managing a team and leading projects hands-on from start to finish.\nPassion for both client-side and server-side development.\nTeam player, strong communication skills, empathy, someone who thrives working in a fast-paced environment.\nDegree in Computer Science (not a must; we\'re always looking for super talented people).\nAt least 5 years of experience.\n\nAbout us:\nFabric makes profitable on-demand e-commerce a reality. Its flexible micro-fulfillment solution was specifically designed to enable fast fulfillment from small spaces. By leveraging robotic automation, Fabric allows retailers to reduce costs and cut fulfillment times.\nUnlike any other micro-fulfillment solution, Fabrics software-led robotics and modular approach gives retailers the flexibility to build the fulfillment center that fits their requirements, allowing them to fulfill online orders at maximum speed while ensuring profitability. Retailers can choose a platform model to run and operate independently on their real estate or a service model in which fulfillment is offered as a service, with minimal capex investment.\nFounded in 2015, Fabric has raised $138 million to date and is backed by Aleph, Corner Ventures, Canada Pension Plan Investment Board (CPPIB), Innovation Endeavors, La Maison, Playground Ventures, and Temasek. With offices in New York City and Tel Aviv, Fabric is rapidly expanding its U.S. operations with over 170+ team members globally and 15 sites under development/contract, including two live micro-fulfillment centers.\n\nIn the news:\nTechcrunch\nForbes\nVenturebeat\nhttps://youtu.be/FBVUjvrs2yc\nhttps://youtu.be/LlNPHAj6ElA','2020-07-29',1159),(1589,'Junior Account Manager','As the Junior Account Manager, you will maintain, manage, and develop the company\'s relationships with global international key clients as well as partners, from the online video industry.\n\nYou will be responsible for:\nManaging and developing our most strategic global clients\' portfolios.\nMonitoring, determining best practice for tagging & reporting campaign performance per client priorities, strategies and KPIs, in order to initiate optimization, accordingly.\nBuilding and delivering daily reports to clients, to enhance performance.\nPerforming technical integrations with new and existing partners, through the on-boarding process.\nDeveloping and building in-depth partnerships, maintaining strong relationships with partners by delivering excellent client service.\nManage relationships with publishers, media vendors, and third-party vendors to maximize the performance of existing buys and stay current, with new products/features.\nContinually test and evaluate new strategies, tactics, and partnerships as part of an effort, to evolve and improve our products offering.\nOptimize deal performance by recommending and enacting adjustments to inventory and campaign delivery components.\n\nRequirements:\nHigh proficiency in English- a must\nExcellent writing & communication skills\nStrong analytical and technical skills- MUST be driven by numbers!\nAbility to connect the dots and execute changes by driving people to get out of their comfort zones! Inbound and outbound\nOrganized\nSharp\nAutodidactic\nSelf-motivated\nTo apply for this position please send your CV to jobs@vidazoo.com','2020-07-11',1763),(1590,'Internship Opportunities for Students: Security Software Engineer','With our world being more connected than ever and the rise in cyber threats, Microsoft has placed itself as one of the top security providers in the world. Realizing the opportunities talents in Israel can offer, a great portion of Microsoft’s security business is being run from the Israeli Development Center (or ILDC) with offices in Herzliya, Haifa, Tel-Aviv and Nazareth.\n\nThe teams in Israel are building products to protect cloud environments and on-premise networks, connected devices (IoT) and endpoints. Security administrators can control and manage their data and networks, quickly detect threats and respond using powerful tools for investigation and analytics.\n\nAre you an excellent teammate, looking to work in a live, dynamic environment, where you can contribute, learn and influence? Are you passionate about developing state-of-the-art engineering systems? Then your place is with us!\n**Our team will review applications as of March 1st. Last chance to apply is on May 1st***\nResponsibilities\n\nAs the field of cyber security is constantly evolving, we\'re looking for engineers to develop new features and components to help make our products more powerful and up-to-speed with the latest challenges.\n\nYou\'ll be taking part in deploying your code to production and making sure it works up to scale, to support the rising number of customers, onboarding every day.\n\nThis is an opportunity to reach tens of thousands of customers, and develop your logic based on real-life user data, and actual hack attempts.\n\nTo build the best Security tools, we try to think like an attacker on the one hand, and the responding Security Officer on the other.\n\nQualifications\nDue to nature of the Intern Program we are currently prioritizing applications from students with final graduation date of winter 2022 and beyond\nCurrently pursuing bachelor\'s, master\'s, or PhD degree in engineering, computer science or related field with at least 3 semesters remaining to graduation\nA year or two of experience programming in C++, Java or other computer programming languages preferred.\nAbility to demonstrate understanding of algorithms, data structures and other systems architecture factors that affect code quality, performance and customer experience\nSome experience building software outside of the classroom environment like an internship, hackathon, research project or related experience preferred\nDemonstrated skill in time management and completing software projects in a cooperative team environment\n\nMicrosoft is an equal opportunity employer. All qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to age, ancestry, color, family or medical care leave, gender identity or expression, genetic information, marital status, medical condition, national origin, physical or mental disability, political affiliation, protected veteran status, race, religion, sex (including pregnancy), sexual orientation, or any other characteristic protected by applicable laws, regulations and ordinances.\n\nBenefits/perks listed below may vary depending on the nature of your employment with Microsoft and the country where you work.','2020-07-06',129),(1591,'Manager, Software Engineering, Data Discovery','Facebook\'s mission is to give people the power to build community and bring the world closer together. Through our family of apps and services, we\'re building a different kind of company that connects billions of people around the world, gives them ways to share what matters most to them, and helps bring people closer together. Whether we\'re creating new products or helping a small business expand its reach, people at Facebook are builders at heart. Our global teams are constantly iterating, solving problems, and working together to empower people around the world to build community and connect in meaningful ways. Together, we can help people build stronger communities - we\'re just getting started.Helping more than 2 billion people connect on Facebook every month calls for extremely complicated systems built to operate at global scale. Facebook\'s Software Infrastructure org is what allows all of this to happen. At Data.AI, were focusing on solving some of the hardest infrastructure problems at Facebook using machine learning. We are a team of infrastructure experts, machine learning engineers, UI/UX enthusiasts and data scientists, all working together on building platforms, tools and systems that we could not build without leveraging strong algorithms and ML capabilities.\n\nWere looking for an experienced manager to lead our data discovery initiative. As a data-driven company, we are committed to enable engineers, scientists and analysts to discover the data they need for their daily work, explore how it is organized and understand how to use it to make better decisions. We aim to achieve this goal by utilising machine learning and the huge amounts of data we have, to create innovative solutions such as customized data search engines, data recommendation systems, automatic question answering services and curation tools. The ideal candidate will have industry experience working on a range of different Machine Learning disciplines such as search & ranking models, NLU, recommender systems and clustering. They will have experience working with large data sets and data-driven decision making systems.\n\nIn this role, you will interact and collaborate with all parts of the company to solve data related problems using ML, understand their needs and build the best products to enable users to do more with the data they have. Come help us Unlock the potential of data, so everyone at Facebook can have more impact.\n\nResponsibilities:\n\nBe a product-oriented leader, an effective people manager and provide valuable technical guidance\nMentor and support engineers\' growth and success, help them to find and focus on their strengths\nChampion engineering and operational excellence, establishing metrics and process for regular assessment and improvement.\nCommunicate across functions like data science, design and product management, and drive engineering initiatives\nFacilitate technical design discussions, help guide resolutions\nDefine and influence product strategy for your team and contribute to that of the org\nMaximize efficiency in a constantly evolving environment where process is fluid and creative solutions are the norm\nMininum Qualifications:\n\nMS degree in Computer Science or related quantitative field or Ph.D. degree in Computer Science or related quantitative field\n5+ years of experience architecting, developing, and shipping software products and/or services\n5+ years of proven engineering team management experience\nExceptional organizational and analytical skills\nExperience of delivering real world impact through full-stack software product engineering\nCuriosity to learn about different company cultures and help shape them\nComfortable supporting a team working across multiple technologies\nBe willing to travel and collaborate with teams and partners in the US\nProven track record of forming effective partnerships with product designers, product managers and data scientists.\nPreferred Qualifications:\n\nExperience in one or more of the following domains: predictive models, search and recommendation systems, pattern recognition, data mining and NLP.\nHave built products in the areas of product analytics, data management and data search.','2020-07-27',127),(1592,'Senior Data Infrastructure Engineer','Armis Data Infrastructure team is responsible for shaping and improving Armis data ingestion, storage, processing and access infrastructure on a daily basis.\nIt is also responsible for making the work of a data scientist easier by providing reliable infrastructure on which training and predictions can be tested and delivered into production.\nWe work closely with other R&D teams to enable them to become agile and efficient with data.\n\nAs a fast growing company, we face new challenges everyday with regards to the scale of our data, and the ability to process it faster, and to be able to query it.\nWe are processing Billions of events every day, and Petabytes of raw data every day, and this is just the beginning..\n\nArmis R&D strives to hire highly independent, innovative and responsible engineers who share our passion for technology, quality and speed.\n\nResponsibilities\nWork with teams to build and evolve data infrastructure tooling and data engineering to enable data driven decision-making\nDesign and implement all aspects of data infrastructure tooling: ingestion, storage, orchestration, processing and access. You will acquire in depth experience and knowledge in technologies such as Kafka, Spark, Airflow, Parquet, Presto and many others.\nWork on tools and flows, and improve the way Armis is delivering data science products back into the system.\n\n\n\nRequirements:\nExperience of at least 5+ years with data streaming application, performance optimization and scaling out data across the world.\nCoding experience in high throughput real time data processing as well as analytic systems.\nExperienced with POCing different Big Data technologies and rolling out new solutions to production environment.\nExperienced with Data Science related infrastructure.\nAt least 3 years of developing and maintaining a large production system\nPassion to create the best working software, learn cutting edge technologies and a constant craving for becoming a better engineer\nThe mentality of a team player, sense of ownership and of urgency','2020-07-19',794),(1593,'Talent Acquisition Partner','More about the role\n\nJoin a team that is transforming smiles, changing lives.\n\nAtAlign Technology, we believe a great smile can truly transform a person’s life, so we create technology that gives people the confidence to take on whatever’s next. We revolutionized the orthodontic industry with the introduction of the Invisalign system, and we have never lost sight of that spirit of innovation. Our teams are constantly pushing the boundaries of what’s possible.\n\nReady to join us?\n\nAbout this opportunity\n\nIn this position you will be a member of our Talent Acquisition EMEA team which is part of the Global Talent Acquisition organization. You will be a true contributor to the growth of the company and help us to provide the talent that makes this company successful. A very rewarding opportunity!\n\nIn this role, you will…\nAs Talent Acquisition Partner you are responsible to search and deliver highly qualified candidates and manage hiring process. Hiring strong candidates into a variety of positions like R&D, IT Development, Engineering, Clinical, etc. You will partner with managers to anticipate and meet the evolving needs of their departments and to deliver best talent in the organization.\nResponsibilities:\nAttract, search and hire talent from around the globe\n\nin a multi-site organization.\n\nDirect sourcing experience with a demonstrated ability to build a pipeline of qualified candidates for a variety of positions at different levels of the organization\n\nDevelop, implement and execute effective local and regional employer branding, search and hiring strategies.\n\nManage and contribute to local and regional Talent Acquisition projects.\nManage full cycle hiring process to meet the various hiring goals across all levels within multiple departments.\nWork with hiring managers to ensure job requirements and expectations are clearly understood and candidates are assessed against appropriate criteria.\nDevelop strong relationships with key stakeholders and relationships with third party firms.\nTrack and report key metrics designed to measure and predict Talent Acquisition activities.\nRegular follow up with hiring managers and candidates to ensure timeliness of the hiring process.\nIn this role, you’ll need…\n\nSkills and Qualifications:\n5-7 years of recruiting experience in-house from a Hi-Tech company\nHebrew and fluent in English (additional languages are considered a plus).\nExcellent stakeholder management and project management skills.\nStrong understanding and ability to attract, search and hire in all levels of the organization from entry level to managerial roles.\nClear understanding of full cycle hiring processes (first contact-first working day).\nMust have experience on mapping and sourcing resumes from all sources.\nVendor manager skills related to talent acquisition activities such as search firms and job boards.\nSound like a good fit?\n\nGreat! Click the Apply button to let us know you are interested.\n\nNot the right fit? You can join our Talent Community to receive notifications of new job postings in your desired career area or can click on the \"Share Job\" social media buttons to share this opportunity with others in your network.\n\nAbout Align\n\nAlign Technology is a publicly traded medical device company that is changing lives through better smiles. Our global team of talented employees develop innovative technology, tools and treatment options to help dental professionals worldwide achieve the clinical results they expect. Our digital ecosystem combines the power of technology to create beautiful smiles through the integration of AI and machine learning, digital imaging and visualization, biomechanics and material science to develop the Invisalign system, the most advanced clear aligner system in the world; iTero Intraoral Scanners and OrthoCAD digital services. Did you know? Align is the world’s largest manufacturer of custom 3D-printed materials.\n\nBy joining Align, you will be part of a global, fast-growing company in one of the most dynamic industries. Great people, innovative technologies, and meaningful work – these are just some of the things employees say make Align Technology a great place to work.\n\nAlign Technology is an equal opportunity employer. All applicants will be considered for employment without attention to race, color, religion, sex, sexual orientation, gender identity, national origin, veteran or disability status. We also respect your privacy. Please review our Applicant Privacy Policies for additional information.','2020-07-22',1767),(1594,'Revenue Manager','Overview\n\nAvePoint\'s Finance department is seeking a full time Revenue Manager to work remotely from Tel Aviv or Be\'er Sheva. This is an excellent opportunity to join a highly productive team and offers the opportunity to support the business.\n\nThe Revenue Manager will have responsibilities for revenue advisory, compliance and overseeing the accuracy of revenue, and will support month end close tasks. This highly visible role will work closely with senior management in the Finance team as well as cross-functional leaders throughout the company.\n\nWhat will you be doing?\n\nAs the Revenue Manager on the finance team, you\'ll be challenged to grow professionally and personally through assignments entrusted to you.\n\nYour responsibilities will include:\nApplying technical ASC606 knowledge to accurately schedule subscription, maintenance, services revenue in NetSuite; applying the five steps of the ASC606 guidance to identify required adjustments to revenue and deferred revenue (including treatment of discount, termination clauses, warranties);\nReviewing of Standard Selling Price (SSP) set up. Analyzing deal pricing trend, categorizing outliers to established SSP ranges;\nReviewing service projects status tracking, revenue recognition and forecast and service projects profit/loss analysis;\nMaintaining and updating revenue recognition policies and procedures;\nEnsuring timely and accurately completion of month end closing, including review journal entries, revenue accruals and account reconciliation. Reviewing and providing commentary on revenue flux;\nPartnering with Deal Desk, Legal and Sales to review new or complex deals, analyze, allocate and calculate revenue for multi-element sales contracts. Preparing executive briefing for complex/large deals;\nPartnering with FP&A Director to forecast revenue; analyzing revenue forecast vs. actual variance on a monthly basis;\nSupporting annual audit, including US financial audit as well as statutory audit for our international subsidiaries;\nOther ad hoc revenue related tasks\nOK, I\'m interested… is this the job for me?\n\nWe look for people who value agility, passion and teamwork; those who can bring fresh ideas to the table and want the opportunity to learn, grow, and expand their careers. Bring your aptitude and build upon what you do best for our customers, partners, team, and you.\n\nOther qualities you\'ll need to be a fit for this role include:\nCPA;\nBachelor or above degree in Accounting;\nMinimum of 5 years work experience in managing revenue recognition and/or service project accounting within the Tech industry, public accounting in big-4 is a plus;\nAdvanced knowledge of ASC606 revenue recognition and ASC340 deferred cost (ideally participated in ASC606 adoption project in the past);\nAbility to work independently with different time zone, proactive and self-motivated;\nExcellent interpersonal skills, generate deliverables and meet deadlines, able to frequently adjust priorities and to work with team with diversified background;\nExcellent written and verbal communication skills;\nHigh attention to details;\nStrong Microsoft Office skills with emphasis on Excel;\nNetSuite/ERP experience is a plus;\nAbout AvePoint\n\nWe are an equal opportunity employer and value diversity at our company. We do not discriminate on the basis of race, religion, color, national origin, gender, sexual orientation, age, marital status, veteran status, or disability status.','2020-07-22',1768),(1595,'Fullstack Software Engineer','Contentsquare is a fast-growing startup founded in 2012 with the mission to improve digital experiences across the board. To do this, we developed an innovative SaaS solution that helps businesses understand how people are behaving on their digital platforms and how they can optimize the customer journey.\n\nWe love having a close relationship with our customers such as Walmart, Tiffany & Co, l’Occitane, Kering, L’Oréal, and more.\n\nSince 2012 we have had 150% YOY growth and raised $190M in May 2020 to accelerate our international expansion with one goal: to become the leading Digital Experience Insights platform thanks to the infinite possibilities of AI.\n\nWith offices in Paris, London, New York, Munich, Tel Aviv and expanding throughout North America and Asia, we have a great international team with tons of career opportunities, a unique environment with strong values, a fun atmosphere, a very exciting vision and culture!\n\nWe are precisely looking for a Fullstack Software Engineer!\n\nYou will responsible for enriching our SaaS application, a Single Page Application using Angular and Node.js APIs. We highly value user experience, the quality of the interfaces that we deploy, and the quality of the code.\n\nYour daily work will consist of:\n- Working alongside other developers and UI and UX designers, collaborating on the various layers of our application\'s UI and infrastructure.\n- Developing new user-facing features\n- Optimizing application for maximum speed and scalability\n- Integrating user-facing elements developed by front-end developers with server-side logic\n- Writing reusable, testable, and efficient code\n\nGeneral Requirements:\n- At least 3 years of experience as either Front End or Back End developer.\n- Strong proficiency with JavaScript and JavaScript frameworks (TypeScript is a plus)\n- Good understanding of code versioning tools such as Git and methodology (git flow, pull requests, merges)\n- Experience in implementing automated testing platforms or unit tests in frameworks such as Jest and Karma\n\nFront End:\n- Proficient understanding of web markup, including HTML5, CSS3\n- Experience in translation of designer mock-ups and wireframes into front-end code\n- Experience with ReactJS/Angular/Vue.js\n\nBack End:\n- Experience with Node.js and frameworks such as Koa/Express\n- Familiarity with API Creation and RESTful services\n- Experience working with databases that represent and support business processes (non-SQL databases such as MongoDB, Redis and rational DB such as MySQL)\n- Experience in integration of multiple data sources and databases into one system\n- Understanding fundamental design principles behind a scalable application\n- Understanding the nature of asynchronous programming and its quirks and workarounds\n- Knowledge and familiarity with microservices architecture is a plus\n\nIf the above sounds like a great fit for you, then join us at ContentSquare and be a part of this awesome adventure! With tech teams that are as passionate as you are, cultivate knowledge sharing and strive for team cohesion. We are committed to innovating towards tomorrow’s user experience.\nJoin our adventure where together we go beyond ourselves and conquer the next big challenge!','2020-07-25',1666),(1599,'QA Tester','We are looking for a talented QA Tester to assess software quality through manual testing. You will be responsible for finding and reporting bugs and analyze the results.\n\nThe job responsibility includes installing, operating and debugging video management systems, situational awareness systems and video analytics systems under one rooftop.\n\nA unique, versatile and exciting opportunity to work on various products tightly with cross-functional teams to ensure quality throughout the software development lifecycle.\n\nYou should have a keen eye for detail and excellent communication skills. If you are also competent in executing test cases and are passionate about quality, we’d like to meet you.\n\nUltimately, you will ensure that our products, applications and systems work as expected.\n\nRequirements:\nAt least 4-5 years experience in QA testing on multidisciplinary systems\nAcademic degree, preferably in technological field\nWillingness to integrate into long-term QA positions\nExcellent technical ability and deep technological system understanding\nFlexible, motivated, with ability to work in demanding environment and invest time and effort\nAbility to work independently and take full responsibility for tasks /Attention to detail\nExcellent communication skills/Team player\nVery good English language skills\n\nDepartment for Career Page:\nR&D\n\nHiring Manager:\nAngela Milis','2020-07-29',665),(1600,'Online Creative Acquisition Manager','Wix’s Creative Acquisition team. We’re masters in