y and easily scaled up\nCollaborate with our tech teams in offices across Europe\nHave a comprehensive vision of big & complex systems, to help improve our architecture\nSolve challenges, such as completing the gaps if you receive only a high-level documentation\nHave the opportunity to work with e-square, the leaders for Angular in Israel and across the world. There\'s also the chance to learn from world-wide experts as part of our meet-ups\n\nCan you deliver\nReady to bring us POS perfection? Here\'s what we\'re looking for from you:\n5+ years\' experience as a Frontend Developer\nIn-depth knowledge of Angular (preferably Angular 9) and Typescript\nExperience with RxJS\nYou enjoy working in an Agile environment and collaborating with team members\nYou\'re a strategic thinker who can proactively find ways to improve our POS offering\nYou understand how to work with Single Page Apps\nExcellent English and Hebrew (written & spoken)\nHere is our offer\n\nLike the best food pairings, we think your dev skills and these great rewards belong together:\nThe opportunity to make a huge impact on our set of products\nThe chance to work with state-of-the-art technologies\nA dynamic workplace where you\'ll work with some of the top talents in the industry\nGreat company events, such as our annual snow event on the slopes in Europe!\nFantastic location: we\'re next to Azrieli train station and offer spectacular views from our 32nd-floor office\nCompetitive salary\nAllowance for ordering lunches with 10bis\nIf you\'re ready to join the team in Tel Aviv, click Apply Now and send us your CV!','2020-07-27',99),(2451,'VIP Account Manager','LivePerson is a transformational force in how Brands and Consumers communicate. With over 18,000 customers including Citi, HSBC, Disney, Verizon, and Home Depot, we are on a mission to make life easier for people and brands everywhere through trusted conversational AI. We believe in a future where conversations are the norm for getting your intentions fulfilled - whatever they are.\n\nWe are an innovative, intent-driven company that believes in building the future and we are looking for growth minded, unconventional thinkers to join the team.\n\nYou will thrive here if:\nYou can operate in a fast paced, dynamic environment\n\nYou nerd out about AI, how it can be applied, or how you can learn more about it (don\'t worry we\'ll help)\n\nYou believe data-led decision making is the norm\n\nYou see feedback or failure as motivation to learn and to grow\n\nYou relate to our core principles and want to work with experts in their respective fields\n\nLivePerson Consumer group is growing its world class service group and is looking for a VIP Account Manager . The VIP Account Manager will be responsible for developing new VIP customers, increasing VIP client\'s life time value, satisfaction and revenue contribution for assigned VIP customers.\n\nOur B2C unit operates world\'s largest Online Experts Service marketplace! Under the brands PrestoExpert.com and Kasamba.com consumers from around the world can easily find the right expert to supply them with professional advice and assistance from a pool of over 200,000 + experts in 600+ categories.\n\nBe part of a strong team and enjoy the work environment of a start-up, with a robust product and the benefits of belonging to an excellent company.\n\nIn this role you will:\nIncrease Retention, Loyalty and Lifetime Value\nAnalyze reports to identify patterns in VIP behavior and upgrade opportunities\nHandle VIP\'s day to day written or vocal queries and complaints, including out of hours when necessary, in order to provide the VIP with personal service\nBeing responsible for revenue and engagement metrics for VIP clients\nEvaluate and monitor VIP activity to ensure maximum life time value\nWork to achieve revenue goals\nOwn special projects, Product, Marcom or service related from A to Z\nDevelop deep relationships with clients and be their POC for anything\n\nYour qualifications are:\n2+ years\' experience in customer service or account management\nNative English both in written and verbal communication skills - Must\nInter-departmental communication skills\nGoal oriented person with ability to work under pressure\nAbility to generate revenue on own initiative based on personal account relationships\nExceptional interpersonal skills using different channels such as phone, email and chat messaging\nAnalytical and operational skills\nFlexibility of working hours\n\nWhy you\'ll love working here:\nLivePerson was named to FastCompany\'s World\'s most innovative companies of 2020 list for the Artificial Intelligence category. We offer amazing colleagues along with opportunities to push your own limits to grow. We embrace invention and experimentation. You\'ll have great benefits plus flexible time off and free lunch on fridays. Most importantly, you\'ll have an ability to make an impact at work and at brands across the globe as we build the future with trusted Conversational AI together.\n\nAt LivePerson, people from diverse backgrounds come together to do their best work and be their authentic selves. We are proud to be an equal opportunity employer.\n\nAll qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to age, ancestry, color, family or medical care leave, gender identity or expression, genetic information, marital status, medical condition, national origin, physical or mental disability, protected veteran status, race, religion, sex (including pregnancy), sexual orientation, or any other characteristic protected by applicable laws, regulations and ordinances. We also consider qualified applicants regardless of criminal histories, consistent with legal requirements.','2020-07-15',2627),(2454,'Business Development Manager','Our growing company is hiring a Business Development Manager who will be responsible for developing and managing business development and sales activities for customers. Your job as a Business Development Manager will be to identify sales leads, pitch goods or services to new clients and maintain a good working relationship with new contacts.\nOUR PERFECT CANDIDATE\nBA or BS degree;\nThree years proven track record in business sales or related market;\nExcellent organizational skills, with emphasis on priorities and goal setting;\nStrong proficiency in MS Office, CRM and statistical analysis software;\nSuperior presentation and communication skills, both written and verbal;\nTechnical skills required to understand and propose products or solutions by focusing on client requirements;\nAbility to communicate information, whether technical or non-technical to staff members and customers, in a clear and concise manner.\nKEY QUALIFICATIONS / RESPONSIBILITIES\nContacting potential clients to establish rapport and arrange meetings;\nPlanning and overseeing new marketing initiatives;\nResearching organizations and individuals to find new opportunities;\nIncreasing the value of current customers while attracting new ones;\nFinding and developing new markets and improving sales;\nAttending conferences, meetings, and industry events;\nDeveloping quotes and proposals for clients;\nDeveloping goals for the development team and business growth and ensuring they are met;\nTraining personnel and helping team members develop their skills.\nEMPLOYMENT CONDITIONS FOR THIS ROLE\nCaptivating work with a friendly, young team;\nFlexible working schedule;\nSpacious comfortable office with cozy lounge zones;\nEmployment contract with company (full employment including social security);\nHigh salary: determined individually, but definitely above industry average;\nTaxes paid by the company.\nTell us about your dream job or if you have any additional questions, please contact us via e-mail: hr@computools.com','2020-07-14',2631),(2455,'Human Resources Manager','Tracking Code\n\n1879-167\n\nJob Description\n\nMaxLinear is seeking a dynamic, sharp and intelligent Human Resources Manager to lead HR initiatives for our Israel design center team, which was part of a large global acquisition. In this position, you will manage all aspects of Human Resources for the site, leveraging corporate initiatives but implementing them based on local best practices that fit the team. As a trusted, strategic advisor, you will partner closely with leaders and employees to drive culture and to help build the organizational and employee capability to help drive business results. This role reports to a manager based outside of Israel and here are some of the key areas you’ll focus on:\nConduct on-site interviews in coordination with the Recruiting and hiring teams, developing creative ways of finding the best people\nOrganize and attend university recruitment events so graduate students are aware of the company and interested in joining for intern or full-time roles\nManage new-hire orientation and onboarding\nManage site specific / local programs\nDrive employee performance management, including training employees on annual performance review process and coach managers on developing and delivering reviews\nPartner with managers to drive employee engagement, ensuring retention of strong performers\nPartner with management on employee issues and facilitate conflict resolution among employees\nCoordinate training and development programs\nMaintain open door policy\nCoordinate leave of absences\nFacilitate the exit and offboarding of terminating employees\nComply with all data requirements of the HR Data Administrative function at Corporate and based on local requirements\nTimely communication of updates to employee policies\nRequired Skills\n\nKnowledge and experience working within local Labor laws and practices\nStrong team player who can work across multiple functions and at all levels within an organization\nExperience supporting various HR projects and drafting or amending policies based on business need\nComfortable dealing with ambiguity, capable of interpreting non-verbal communication and understanding cultural nuances\nAble to proactively listen to the company or employee needs and take appropriate action\nA history of partnering well with leadership to develop a culture of innovation, excellence and openness\nAbility to work independently, reporting to a manager in a different country\nAbility to work effectively in a fast-paced and changing environment\nExcellent verbal and written communication skills\nStrong skills in Microsoft Office, especially Excel\nHRIS experience a plus\nHigh-tech industry experience preferred\nBS + 7 years of experience, or MS + 5 years of experience\nCompany Overview\n\n\nMaxLinear is a global, New York Stock Exchange-traded company (NYSE: MXL) where the entrepreneurial spirit is alive and well. We are a fabless system-on-chip product company, designing highly integrated, radio-frequency, and mixed-signal Communications ICs for broadband and infrastructure applications.\n\nWe hire the best people in the world and engage them in some of the most exciting opportunities in our broadband and infrastructure markets. Our growth has come from innovative, bold approaches to solving some of the world’s most challenging communication technology problems.\n\nMaxLinear began by developing the World’s first high-performance TV tuner chip using standard CMOS process technology. Others said we couldn’t achieve the extremely high performance requirements using CMOS, but we proved them wrong and achieved enduring global market leadership with our designs. Since then, we’ve developed a full line of products for satellite communications, cable modems, and terrestrial TV; diversified into high speed products addressing Datacom applications such as 400 Gbps fiber-optic interconnect chips for high-speed networks; and MoCA technology for home networking.\n\nOur headquarters is in Carlsbad, near San Diego, California. We also have major design centers in Irvine and San Jose, CA; in Vancouver, Canada; in Valencia, Spain; and in Bangalore, India.\n\nWe have approximately 800 employees, a substantial majority of whom have engineering degrees, and include masters and Ph.D. graduates from many of the premiere universities around the world. Our engineers thrive on innovation, outstanding execution, outside-the-box thinking, nimbleness, and collaboration. Together, we form a high-energy business team that is focused on building great products.\n\nJob Location\n\nHerzliya, Tel Aviv, Israel\n\nPosition Type\n\nFull-Time/Regular','2020-07-17',2632),(2456,'SMB Account Manager','As an AWS Acquisition SMB Manager, you will increase adoption and shape the future of cloud technologies across your regional territory by identifying and developing new business opportunities and collaborating with partners to scale and accelerate customer success.\n\nIn this role, you will use your background in sales and technology to increase engagement at the CXO level, as well as with Software Developers, IT architects and partners. Your team will manage the entire lifecycle of new business opportunities from prospecting to closure and adoption, whilst delivering against a territory scaling plan to achieve quarterly revenue targets.\n\nAre you a motivated self-starter with an analytical mind? Do you want to work on the forefront of the latest innovations and technologies? Do you seek the opportunity to work with a diverse set of customers, opportunities and markets as part of a team focused on increasing adoption of Amazon Web Services within the Israel SMB market?\n\nCome build the future with us.\n\nBasic Qualifications\n\n· Experience in technology related sales, business development or new business experience in the tech industry\n· Experience working with complex IT solutions\n· Self-starter with highly developed interpersonal skills; you are motivated and result oriented\n· Experience using CRM systems and or other sales prospecting tools\n· Experience working with partners to drive scaling campa